' /></p> <p> for all coprime <img src='http://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7Bq%2Cr+%5Cin+%7B%5Cmathcal+S%7D_I%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0' alt='{q,r &#92;in {&#92;mathcal S}_I}' title='{q,r &#92;in {&#92;mathcal S}_I}' class='latex' />, since one can identify <img src='http://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7Ba%5C+%28P_I%29%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0' alt='{a&#92; (P_I)}' title='{a&#92; (P_I)}' class='latex' /> with the tuple <img src='http://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7B%28a%5C+%28q%29%29_%7Bq+%5Cin+%7B%5Cmathcal+S%7D_I%7D%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0' alt='{(a&#92; (q))_{q &#92;in {&#92;mathcal S}_I}}' title='{(a&#92; (q))_{q &#92;in {&#92;mathcal S}_I}}' class='latex' /> for each <img src='http://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7Ba+%5Cin+%28%7B%5Cbf+Z%7D%2FP_I%7B%5Cbf+Z%7D%29%5E%5Ctimes%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0' alt='{a &#92;in ({&#92;bf Z}/P_I{&#92;bf Z})^&#92;times}' title='{a &#92;in ({&#92;bf Z}/P_I{&#92;bf Z})^&#92;times}' class='latex' />.</p> <p> If <img src='http://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7By+%3E+1%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0' alt='{y &gt; 1}' title='{y &gt; 1}' class='latex' /> and <img src='http://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7Bn%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0' alt='{n}' title='{n}' class='latex' /> is a natural number, we say that <img src='http://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7Bn%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0' alt='{n}' title='{n}' class='latex' /> is <em><img src='http://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7By%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0' alt='{y}' title='{y}' class='latex' />-densely divisible</em> if, for every <img src='http://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7B1+%5Cleq+R+%5Cleq+n%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0' alt='{1 &#92;leq R &#92;leq n}' title='{1 &#92;leq R &#92;leq n}' class='latex' />, one can find a factor of <img src='http://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7Bn%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0' alt='{n}' title='{n}' class='latex' /> in the interval <img src='http://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7B%5By%5E%7B-1%7D+R%2C+R%5D%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0' alt='{[y^{-1} R, R]}' title='{[y^{-1} R, R]}' class='latex' />. We say that <img src='http://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7Bn%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0' alt='{n}' title='{n}' class='latex' /> is <em>doubly <img src='http://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7By%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0' alt='{y}' title='{y}' class='latex' />-densely divisible</em> if, for every <img src='http://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7B1+%5Cleq+R+%5Cleq+n%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0' alt='{1 &#92;leq R &#92;leq n}' title='{1 &#92;leq R &#92;leq n}' class='latex' />, one can find a factor <img src='http://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7Bm%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0' alt='{m}' title='{m}' class='latex' /> of <img src='http://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7Bn%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0' alt='{n}' title='{n}' class='latex' /> in the interval <img src='http://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7B%5By%5E%7B-1%7D+R%2C+R%5D%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0' alt='{[y^{-1} R, R]}' title='{[y^{-1} R, R]}' class='latex' /> such that <img src='http://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7Bm%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0' alt='{m}' title='{m}' class='latex' /> is itself <img src='http://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7By%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0' alt='{y}' title='{y}' class='latex' />-densely divisible. We let <img src='http://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7B%7B%5Cmathcal+D%7D_y%5E2%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0' alt='{{&#92;mathcal D}_y^2}' title='{{&#92;mathcal D}_y^2}' class='latex' /> denote the set of doubly <img src='http://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7By%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0' alt='{y}' title='{y}' class='latex' />-densely divisible natural numbers, and <img src='http://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7B%7B%5Cmathcal+D%7D_y%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0' alt='{{&#92;mathcal D}_y}' title='{{&#92;mathcal D}_y}' class='latex' /> the set of <img src='http://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7By%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0' alt='{y}' title='{y}' class='latex' />-densely divisible numbers. </p> <p> Given any finitely supported sequence <img src='http://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7B%5Calpha%3A+%7B%5Cbf+N%7D+%5Crightarrow+%7B%5Cbf+C%7D%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0' alt='{&#92;alpha: {&#92;bf N} &#92;rightarrow {&#92;bf C}}' title='{&#92;alpha: {&#92;bf N} &#92;rightarrow {&#92;bf C}}' class='latex' /> and any primitive residue class <img src='http://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7Ba%5C+%28q%29%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0' alt='{a&#92; (q)}' title='{a&#92; (q)}' class='latex' />, we define the discrepancy </p> <p align="center"><img src='http://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%5Cdisplaystyle+%5CDelta%28%5Calpha%3B+a+%5C+%28q%29%29+%3A%3D+%5Csum_%7Bn%3A+n+%3D+a%5C+%28q%29%7D+%5Calpha%28n%29+-+%5Cfrac%7B1%7D%7B%5Cphi%28q%29%7D+%5Csum_%7Bn%3A+%28n%2Cq%29%3D1%7D+%5Calpha%28n%29.&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0' alt='&#92;displaystyle &#92;Delta(&#92;alpha; a &#92; (q)) := &#92;sum_{n: n = a&#92; (q)} &#92;alpha(n) - &#92;frac{1}{&#92;phi(q)} &#92;sum_{n: (n,q)=1} &#92;alpha(n).' title='&#92;displaystyle &#92;Delta(&#92;alpha; a &#92; (q)) := &#92;sum_{n: n = a&#92; (q)} &#92;alpha(n) - &#92;frac{1}{&#92;phi(q)} &#92;sum_{n: (n,q)=1} &#92;alpha(n).' class='latex' /></p> <p> For any fixed <img src='http://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7B%5Cvarpi%2C+%5Cdelta+%3E+0%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0' alt='{&#92;varpi, &#92;delta &gt; 0}' title='{&#92;varpi, &#92;delta &gt; 0}' class='latex' />, we let <img src='http://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7BMPZ%27%27%5B%5Cvarpi%2C%5Cdelta%5D%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0' alt='{MPZ&#039;&#039;[&#92;varpi,&#92;delta]}' title='{MPZ&#039;&#039;[&#92;varpi,&#92;delta]}' class='latex' /> denote the assertion that <a name="elx"> <p align="center"><img src='http://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%5Cdisplaystyle++%5Csum_%7Bq+%5Cin+%7B%5Cmathcal+S%7D_I+%5Ccap+%7B%5Cmathcal+D%7D_%7Bx%5E%5Cdelta%7D%5E2%3A+q+%5Cleq+x%5E%7B1%2F2%2B2%5Cvarpi%7D%7D+%7C%5CDelta%28%5CLambda+1_%7B%5Bx%2C2x%5D%7D%3B+a%5C+%28q%29%29%7C+%5Cll+x+%5Clog%5E%7B-A%7D+x+%5C+%5C+%5C+%5C+%5C+%281%29&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0' alt='&#92;displaystyle &#92;sum_{q &#92;in {&#92;mathcal S}_I &#92;cap {&#92;mathcal D}_{x^&#92;delta}^2: q &#92;leq x^{1/2+2&#92;varpi}} |&#92;Delta(&#92;Lambda 1_{[x,2x]}; a&#92; (q))| &#92;ll x &#92;log^{-A} x &#92; &#92; &#92; &#92; &#92; (1)' title='&#92;displaystyle &#92;sum_{q &#92;in {&#92;mathcal S}_I &#92;cap {&#92;mathcal D}_{x^&#92;delta}^2: q &#92;leq x^{1/2+2&#92;varpi}} |&#92;Delta(&#92;Lambda 1_{[x,2x]}; a&#92; (q))| &#92;ll x &#92;log^{-A} x &#92; &#92; &#92; &#92; &#92; (1)' class='latex' /></p> <p></a> for any fixed <img src='http://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7BA+%3E+0%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0' alt='{A &gt; 0}' title='{A &gt; 0}' class='latex' />, any bounded <img src='http://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7BI%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0' alt='{I}' title='{I}' class='latex' />, and any primitive <img src='http://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7Ba%5C+%28P_I%29%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0' alt='{a&#92; (P_I)}' title='{a&#92; (P_I)}' class='latex' />, where <img src='http://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7B%5CLambda%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0' alt='{&#92;Lambda}' title='{&#92;Lambda}' class='latex' /> is the <a href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Von_Mangoldt_function">von Mangoldt function</a>. Importantly, we do <em>not</em> require <img src='http://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7BI%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0' alt='{I}' title='{I}' class='latex' /> or <img src='http://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7Ba%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0' alt='{a}' title='{a}' class='latex' /> to be fixed, in particular <img src='http://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7BI%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0' alt='{I}' title='{I}' class='latex' /> could grow polynomially in <img src='http://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7Bx%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0' alt='{x}' title='{x}' class='latex' />, and <img src='http://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7Ba%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0' alt='{a}' title='{a}' class='latex' /> could grow exponentially in <img src='http://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7Bx%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0' alt='{x}' title='{x}' class='latex' />, but the implied constant in <a href="#elx">(1)</a> would still need to be fixed (so it has to be uniform in <img src='http://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7BI%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0' alt='{I}' title='{I}' class='latex' /> and <img src='http://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7Ba%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0' alt='{a}' title='{a}' class='latex' />). (In previous formulations of these estimates, the system of congruence <img src='http://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7Ba%5C+%28q%29%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0' alt='{a&#92; (q)}' title='{a&#92; (q)}' class='latex' /> was also required to obey a controlled multiplicity hypothesis, but we no longer need this hypothesis in our arguments.) In this post we will record the proof of the following result, which is currently the best distribution result produced by the ongoing polymath8 project to optimise Zhang&#8217;s theorem on bounded gaps between primes: </p> <blockquote><p><b>Theorem 1</b> <a name="main"></a> We have <img src='http://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7BMPZ%27%27%5B%5Cvarpi%2C%5Cdelta%5D%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0' alt='{MPZ&#039;&#039;[&#92;varpi,&#92;delta]}' title='{MPZ&#039;&#039;[&#92;varpi,&#92;delta]}' class='latex' /> whenever <img src='http://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7B%5Cfrac%7B280%7D%7B3%7D+%5Cvarpi+%2B+%5Cfrac%7B80%7D%7B3%7D+%5Cdelta+%3C+1%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0' alt='{&#92;frac{280}{3} &#92;varpi + &#92;frac{80}{3} &#92;delta &lt; 1}' title='{&#92;frac{280}{3} &#92;varpi + &#92;frac{80}{3} &#92;delta &lt; 1}' class='latex' />. </p></blockquote> </p> <p> This improves upon the previous constraint of <img src='http://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7B148+%5Cvarpi+%2B+33+%5Cdelta+%3C+1%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0' alt='{148 &#92;varpi + 33 &#92;delta &lt; 1}' title='{148 &#92;varpi + 33 &#92;delta &lt; 1}' class='latex' /> (see <a href="http://terrytao.wordpress.com/2013/06/23/the-distribution-of-primes-in-densely-divisible-moduli/">this previous post</a>), although that latter statement was stronger in that it only required single dense divisibility rather than double dense divisibility. However, thanks to the efficiency of the sieving step of our argument, the upgrade of the single dense divisibility hypothesis to double dense divisibility costs almost nothing with respect to the <img src='http://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7Bk_0%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0' alt='{k_0}' title='{k_0}' class='latex' /> parameter (which, using this constraint, gives a value of <img src='http://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7Bk_0%3D720%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0' alt='{k_0=720}' title='{k_0=720}' class='latex' /> as verified in <a href="http://terrytao.wordpress.com/2013/06/30/bounded-gaps-between-primes-polymath8-a-progress-report/#comment-237306">these</a> <a href="http://terrytao.wordpress.com/2013/06/30/bounded-gaps-between-primes-polymath8-a-progress-report/#comment-237324">comments</a>, which then implies a value of <img src='http://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7BH+%3D+5%2C414%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0' alt='{H = 5,414}' title='{H = 5,414}' class='latex' />). </p> <p> This estimate is deduced from three sub-estimates, which require a bit more notation to state. We need a fixed quantity <img src='http://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7BA_0%3E0%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0' alt='{A_0&gt;0}' title='{A_0&gt;0}' class='latex' />. </p> <blockquote><p><b>Definition 2</b> A <em>coefficient sequence</em> is a finitely supported sequence <img src='http://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7B%5Calpha%3A+%7B%5Cbf+N%7D+%5Crightarrow+%7B%5Cbf+R%7D%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0' alt='{&#92;alpha: {&#92;bf N} &#92;rightarrow {&#92;bf R}}' title='{&#92;alpha: {&#92;bf N} &#92;rightarrow {&#92;bf R}}' class='latex' /> that obeys the bounds <a name="alpha-bound"> <p align="center"><img src='http://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%5Cdisplaystyle++%7C%5Calpha%28n%29%7C+%5Cll+%5Ctau%5E%7BO%281%29%7D%28n%29+%5Clog%5E%7BO%281%29%7D%28x%29+%5C+%5C+%5C+%5C+%5C+%282%29&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0' alt='&#92;displaystyle |&#92;alpha(n)| &#92;ll &#92;tau^{O(1)}(n) &#92;log^{O(1)}(x) &#92; &#92; &#92; &#92; &#92; (2)' title='&#92;displaystyle |&#92;alpha(n)| &#92;ll &#92;tau^{O(1)}(n) &#92;log^{O(1)}(x) &#92; &#92; &#92; &#92; &#92; (2)' class='latex' /></p> <p></a> for all <img src='http://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7Bn%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0' alt='{n}' title='{n}' class='latex' />, where <img src='http://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7B%5Ctau%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0' alt='{&#92;tau}' title='{&#92;tau}' class='latex' /> is the <a href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Divisor_function">divisor function</a>. </p> <ul> <li>(i) A coefficient sequence <img src='http://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7B%5Calpha%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0' alt='{&#92;alpha}' title='{&#92;alpha}' class='latex' /> is said to be <em>at scale <img src='http://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7BN%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0' alt='{N}' title='{N}' class='latex' /></em> for some <img src='http://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7BN+%5Cgeq+1%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0' alt='{N &#92;geq 1}' title='{N &#92;geq 1}' class='latex' /> if it is supported on an interval of the form <img src='http://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7B%5B%281-O%28%5Clog%5E%7B-A_0%7D+x%29%29+N%2C+%281%2BO%28%5Clog%5E%7B-A_0%7D+x%29%29+N%5D%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0' alt='{[(1-O(&#92;log^{-A_0} x)) N, (1+O(&#92;log^{-A_0} x)) N]}' title='{[(1-O(&#92;log^{-A_0} x)) N, (1+O(&#92;log^{-A_0} x)) N]}' class='latex' />. </li> <li>(ii) A coefficient sequence <img src='http://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7B%5Calpha%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0' alt='{&#92;alpha}' title='{&#92;alpha}' class='latex' /> at scale <img src='http://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7BN%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0' alt='{N}' title='{N}' class='latex' /> is said to <em>obey the Siegel-Walfisz theorem</em> if one has <a name="sig"> <p align="center"><img src='http://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%5Cdisplaystyle++%7C+%5CDelta%28%5Calpha+1_%7B%28%5Ccdot%2Cq%29%3D1%7D%3B+a%5C+%28r%29%29+%7C+%5Cll+%5Ctau%28qr%29%5E%7BO%281%29%7D+N+%5Clog%5E%7B-A%7D+x+%5C+%5C+%5C+%5C+%5C+%283%29&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0' alt='&#92;displaystyle | &#92;Delta(&#92;alpha 1_{(&#92;cdot,q)=1}; a&#92; (r)) | &#92;ll &#92;tau(qr)^{O(1)} N &#92;log^{-A} x &#92; &#92; &#92; &#92; &#92; (3)' title='&#92;displaystyle | &#92;Delta(&#92;alpha 1_{(&#92;cdot,q)=1}; a&#92; (r)) | &#92;ll &#92;tau(qr)^{O(1)} N &#92;log^{-A} x &#92; &#92; &#92; &#92; &#92; (3)' class='latex' /></p> <p></a> for any <img src='http://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7Bq%2Cr+%5Cgeq+1%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0' alt='{q,r &#92;geq 1}' title='{q,r &#92;geq 1}' class='latex' />, any fixed <img src='http://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7BA%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0' alt='{A}' title='{A}' class='latex' />, and any primitive residue class <img src='http://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7Ba%5C+%28r%29%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0' alt='{a&#92; (r)}' title='{a&#92; (r)}' class='latex' />. </li> <li>(iii) A coefficient sequence <img src='http://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7B%5Calpha%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0' alt='{&#92;alpha}' title='{&#92;alpha}' class='latex' /> at scale <img src='http://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7BN%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0' alt='{N}' title='{N}' class='latex' /> (relative to this choice of <img src='http://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7BA_0%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0' alt='{A_0}' title='{A_0}' class='latex' />) is said to be <em>smooth</em> if it takes the form <img src='http://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7B%5Calpha%28n%29+%3D+%5Cpsi%28n%2FN%29%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0' alt='{&#92;alpha(n) = &#92;psi(n/N)}' title='{&#92;alpha(n) = &#92;psi(n/N)}' class='latex' /> for some smooth function <img src='http://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7B%5Cpsi%3A+%7B%5Cbf+R%7D+%5Crightarrow+%7B%5Cbf+C%7D%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0' alt='{&#92;psi: {&#92;bf R} &#92;rightarrow {&#92;bf C}}' title='{&#92;psi: {&#92;bf R} &#92;rightarrow {&#92;bf C}}' class='latex' /> supported on <img src='http://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7B%5B1-O%28%5Clog%5E%7B-A_0%7D+x%29%2C+1%2BO%28%5Clog%5E%7B-A_0%7D+x%29%5D%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0' alt='{[1-O(&#92;log^{-A_0} x), 1+O(&#92;log^{-A_0} x)]}' title='{[1-O(&#92;log^{-A_0} x), 1+O(&#92;log^{-A_0} x)]}' class='latex' /> obeying the derivative bounds <a name="soso"> <p align="center"><img src='http://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%5Cdisplaystyle++%5Cpsi%5E%7B%28j%29%7D%28t%29+%3D+O%28+%5Clog%5E%7Bj+A_0%7D+x+%29+%5C+%5C+%5C+%5C+%5C+%284%29&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0' alt='&#92;displaystyle &#92;psi^{(j)}(t) = O( &#92;log^{j A_0} x ) &#92; &#92; &#92; &#92; &#92; (4)' title='&#92;displaystyle &#92;psi^{(j)}(t) = O( &#92;log^{j A_0} x ) &#92; &#92; &#92; &#92; &#92; (4)' class='latex' /></p> <p></a> for all fixed <img src='http://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7Bj+%5Cgeq+0%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0' alt='{j &#92;geq 0}' title='{j &#92;geq 0}' class='latex' /> (note that the implied constant in the <img src='http://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7BO%28%29%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0' alt='{O()}' title='{O()}' class='latex' /> notation may depend on <img src='http://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7Bj%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0' alt='{j}' title='{j}' class='latex' />). </li> </ul> </blockquote> </p> <blockquote><p><b>Definition 3 (Type I, Type II, Type III estimates)</b> Let <img src='http://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7B0+%3C+%5Cvarpi+%3C+1%2F4%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0' alt='{0 &lt; &#92;varpi &lt; 1/4}' title='{0 &lt; &#92;varpi &lt; 1/4}' class='latex' />, <img src='http://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7B0+%3C+%5Cdelta+%3C+1%2F4%2B%5Cvarpi%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0' alt='{0 &lt; &#92;delta &lt; 1/4+&#92;varpi}' title='{0 &lt; &#92;delta &lt; 1/4+&#92;varpi}' class='latex' />, and <img src='http://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7B0+%3C+%5Csigma+%3C+1%2F2%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0' alt='{0 &lt; &#92;sigma &lt; 1/2}' title='{0 &lt; &#92;sigma &lt; 1/2}' class='latex' /> be fixed quantities. We let <img src='http://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7BI%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0' alt='{I}' title='{I}' class='latex' /> be an arbitrary bounded subset of <img src='http://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7B%7B%5Cbf+R%7D%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0' alt='{{&#92;bf R}}' title='{{&#92;bf R}}' class='latex' />, and <img src='http://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7Ba%5C+%28P_I%29%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0' alt='{a&#92; (P_I)}' title='{a&#92; (P_I)}' class='latex' /> a primitive congruence class. </p> <ul> <li>(i) We say that <img src='http://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7BType%27%27_I%5B%5Cvarpi%2C%5Cdelta%2C%5Csigma%5D%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0' alt='{Type&#039;&#039;_I[&#92;varpi,&#92;delta,&#92;sigma]}' title='{Type&#039;&#039;_I[&#92;varpi,&#92;delta,&#92;sigma]}' class='latex' /> holds if, whenever <img src='http://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7BM%2C+N+%5Cgg+1%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0' alt='{M, N &#92;gg 1}' title='{M, N &#92;gg 1}' class='latex' /> are quantities with <a name="lin"> <p align="center"><img src='http://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%5Cdisplaystyle++M+N+%5Csim+x+%5C+%5C+%5C+%5C+%5C+%285%29&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0' alt='&#92;displaystyle M N &#92;sim x &#92; &#92; &#92; &#92; &#92; (5)' title='&#92;displaystyle M N &#92;sim x &#92; &#92; &#92; &#92; &#92; (5)' class='latex' /></p> <p></a> and <a name="xss"> <p align="center"><img src='http://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%5Cdisplaystyle++x%5E%7B1%2F2-%5Csigma%7D+%5Clessapprox+N+%5Clessapprox+x%5E%7B1%2F2-2%5Cvarpi-c%7D+%5C+%5C+%5C+%5C+%5C+%286%29&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0' alt='&#92;displaystyle x^{1/2-&#92;sigma} &#92;lessapprox N &#92;lessapprox x^{1/2-2&#92;varpi-c} &#92; &#92; &#92; &#92; &#92; (6)' title='&#92;displaystyle x^{1/2-&#92;sigma} &#92;lessapprox N &#92;lessapprox x^{1/2-2&#92;varpi-c} &#92; &#92; &#92; &#92; &#92; (6)' class='latex' /></p> <p></a> for some fixed <img src='http://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7Bc%3E0%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0' alt='{c&gt;0}' title='{c&gt;0}' class='latex' />, and <img src='http://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7B%5Calpha%2C%5Cbeta%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0' alt='{&#92;alpha,&#92;beta}' title='{&#92;alpha,&#92;beta}' class='latex' /> are coefficient sequences at scales <img src='http://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7BM%2CN%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0' alt='{M,N}' title='{M,N}' class='latex' /> respectively, with <img src='http://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7B%5Cbeta%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0' alt='{&#92;beta}' title='{&#92;beta}' class='latex' /> obeying a Siegel-Walfisz theorem, we have <a name="alpha-beta"> <p align="center"><img src='http://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%5Cdisplaystyle++%5Csum_%7Bq+%5Cin+%7B%5Cmathcal+S%7D_I+%5Ccap+%7B%5Cmathcal+D%7D_%7Bx%5E%5Cdelta%7D%5E2%3A+q+%5Cleq+x%5E%7B1%2F2%2B2%5Cvarpi%7D%7D+%7C%5CDelta%28%5Calpha+%2A+%5Cbeta%3B+a%5C+%28q%29%29%7C+%5Cll+x+%5Clog%5E%7B-A%7D+x.+%5C+%5C+%5C+%5C+%5C+%287%29&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0' alt='&#92;displaystyle &#92;sum_{q &#92;in {&#92;mathcal S}_I &#92;cap {&#92;mathcal D}_{x^&#92;delta}^2: q &#92;leq x^{1/2+2&#92;varpi}} |&#92;Delta(&#92;alpha * &#92;beta; a&#92; (q))| &#92;ll x &#92;log^{-A} x. &#92; &#92; &#92; &#92; &#92; (7)' title='&#92;displaystyle &#92;sum_{q &#92;in {&#92;mathcal S}_I &#92;cap {&#92;mathcal D}_{x^&#92;delta}^2: q &#92;leq x^{1/2+2&#92;varpi}} |&#92;Delta(&#92;alpha * &#92;beta; a&#92; (q))| &#92;ll x &#92;log^{-A} x. &#92; &#92; &#92; &#92; &#92; (7)' class='latex' /></p> <p></a> </li> <li>(ii) We say that <img src='http://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7BType%27%27_%7BII%7D%5B%5Cvarpi%2C%5Cdelta%5D%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0' alt='{Type&#039;&#039;_{II}[&#92;varpi,&#92;delta]}' title='{Type&#039;&#039;_{II}[&#92;varpi,&#92;delta]}' class='latex' /> holds if the conclusion <a href="#alpha-beta">(7)</a> of <img src='http://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7BType%27%27_I%5B%5Cvarpi%2C%5Cdelta%2C%5Csigma%5D%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0' alt='{Type&#039;&#039;_I[&#92;varpi,&#92;delta,&#92;sigma]}' title='{Type&#039;&#039;_I[&#92;varpi,&#92;delta,&#92;sigma]}' class='latex' /> holds under the same hypotheses as before, except that <a href="#xss">(6)</a> is replaced with <a name="xss-2"> <p align="center"><img src='http://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%5Cdisplaystyle++x%5E%7B1%2F2-2%5Cvarpi-c%7D+%5Clessapprox+N+%5Clessapprox+x%5E%7B1%2F2%7D+%5C+%5C+%5C+%5C+%5C+%288%29&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0' alt='&#92;displaystyle x^{1/2-2&#92;varpi-c} &#92;lessapprox N &#92;lessapprox x^{1/2} &#92; &#92; &#92; &#92; &#92; (8)' title='&#92;displaystyle x^{1/2-2&#92;varpi-c} &#92;lessapprox N &#92;lessapprox x^{1/2} &#92; &#92; &#92; &#92; &#92; (8)' class='latex' /></p> <p></a> for some sufficiently small fixed <img src='http://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7Bc%3E0%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0' alt='{c&gt;0}' title='{c&gt;0}' class='latex' />. </li> <li>(iii) We say that <img src='http://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7BType%27%27_%7BIII%7D%5B%5Cvarpi%2C%5Cdelta%2C%5Csigma%5D%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0' alt='{Type&#039;&#039;_{III}[&#92;varpi,&#92;delta,&#92;sigma]}' title='{Type&#039;&#039;_{III}[&#92;varpi,&#92;delta,&#92;sigma]}' class='latex' /> holds if, whenever <img src='http://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7BM%2C+N_1%2CN_2%2CN_3+%5Cgg+1%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0' alt='{M, N_1,N_2,N_3 &#92;gg 1}' title='{M, N_1,N_2,N_3 &#92;gg 1}' class='latex' /> are quantities with <p align="center"><img src='http://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%5Cdisplaystyle++M+N_1+N_2+N_3+%5Csim+x&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0' alt='&#92;displaystyle M N_1 N_2 N_3 &#92;sim x' title='&#92;displaystyle M N_1 N_2 N_3 &#92;sim x' class='latex' /></p> <p> and <a name="n1-o"> <p align="center"><img src='http://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%5Cdisplaystyle++N_1+N_2%2C+N_1+N_3%2C+N_2+N_3+%5Cgtrapprox+x%5E%7B1%2F2%2B%5Csigma%7D+%5C+%5C+%5C+%5C+%5C+%289%29&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0' alt='&#92;displaystyle N_1 N_2, N_1 N_3, N_2 N_3 &#92;gtrapprox x^{1/2+&#92;sigma} &#92; &#92; &#92; &#92; &#92; (9)' title='&#92;displaystyle N_1 N_2, N_1 N_3, N_2 N_3 &#92;gtrapprox x^{1/2+&#92;sigma} &#92; &#92; &#92; &#92; &#92; (9)' class='latex' /></p> <p></a> and <a name="n2-o"> <p align="center"><img src='http://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%5Cdisplaystyle++x%5E%7B2%5Csigma%7D+%5Clessapprox+N_1%2CN_2%2CN_3+%5Clessapprox+x%5E%7B1%2F2-%5Csigma%7D+%5C+%5C+%5C+%5C+%5C+%2810%29&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0' alt='&#92;displaystyle x^{2&#92;sigma} &#92;lessapprox N_1,N_2,N_3 &#92;lessapprox x^{1/2-&#92;sigma} &#92; &#92; &#92; &#92; &#92; (10)' title='&#92;displaystyle x^{2&#92;sigma} &#92;lessapprox N_1,N_2,N_3 &#92;lessapprox x^{1/2-&#92;sigma} &#92; &#92; &#92; &#92; &#92; (10)' class='latex' /></p> <p></a> and <img src='http://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7B%5Calpha%2C%5Cpsi_1%2C%5Cpsi_2%2C%5Cpsi_3%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0' alt='{&#92;alpha,&#92;psi_1,&#92;psi_2,&#92;psi_3}' title='{&#92;alpha,&#92;psi_1,&#92;psi_2,&#92;psi_3}' class='latex' /> are coefficient sequences at scales <img src='http://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7BM%2CN_1%2CN_2%2CN_3%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0' alt='{M,N_1,N_2,N_3}' title='{M,N_1,N_2,N_3}' class='latex' /> respectively, with <img src='http://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7B%5Cpsi_1%2C%5Cpsi_2%2C%5Cpsi_3%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0' alt='{&#92;psi_1,&#92;psi_2,&#92;psi_3}' title='{&#92;psi_1,&#92;psi_2,&#92;psi_3}' class='latex' /> smooth, we have <a name="psi"> <p align="center"><img src='http://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%5Cdisplaystyle++%5Csum_%7Bq+%5Cin+%7B%5Cmathcal+S%7D_I+%5Ccap+%7B%5Cmathcal+D%7D_%7Bx%5E%5Cdelta%7D%5E2%3A+q+%5Cleq+x%5E%7B1%2F2%2B2%5Cvarpi%7D%7D+%5C+%5C+%5C+%5C+%5C+%2811%29&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0' alt='&#92;displaystyle &#92;sum_{q &#92;in {&#92;mathcal S}_I &#92;cap {&#92;mathcal D}_{x^&#92;delta}^2: q &#92;leq x^{1/2+2&#92;varpi}} &#92; &#92; &#92; &#92; &#92; (11)' title='&#92;displaystyle &#92;sum_{q &#92;in {&#92;mathcal S}_I &#92;cap {&#92;mathcal D}_{x^&#92;delta}^2: q &#92;leq x^{1/2+2&#92;varpi}} &#92; &#92; &#92; &#92; &#92; (11)' class='latex' /></p> <p></a> <p align="center"><img src='http://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%5Cdisplaystyle++%7C%5CDelta%28%5Calpha+%2A+%5Cpsi_1+%2A+%5Cpsi_2+%2A+%5Cpsi_3%3B+a%5C+%28q%29%29%7C+%5Cll+x+%5Clog%5E%7B-A%7D+x.+&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0' alt='&#92;displaystyle |&#92;Delta(&#92;alpha * &#92;psi_1 * &#92;psi_2 * &#92;psi_3; a&#92; (q))| &#92;ll x &#92;log^{-A} x. ' title='&#92;displaystyle |&#92;Delta(&#92;alpha * &#92;psi_1 * &#92;psi_2 * &#92;psi_3; a&#92; (q))| &#92;ll x &#92;log^{-A} x. ' class='latex' /></p> </li> </ul> </blockquote> </p> <p> Theorem <a href="#main">1</a> is then a consequence of the following four statements. </p> <blockquote><p><b>Theorem 4 (Type I estimate)</b> <a name="t1-precise"></a> <img src='http://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7BType%27%27_I%5B%5Cvarpi%2C%5Cdelta%2C%5Csigma%5D%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0' alt='{Type&#039;&#039;_I[&#92;varpi,&#92;delta,&#92;sigma]}' title='{Type&#039;&#039;_I[&#92;varpi,&#92;delta,&#92;sigma]}' class='latex' /> holds whenever <img src='http://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7B%5Cvarpi%2C%5Cdelta%2C%5Csigma+%3E+0%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0' alt='{&#92;varpi,&#92;delta,&#92;sigma &gt; 0}' title='{&#92;varpi,&#92;delta,&#92;sigma &gt; 0}' class='latex' /> are fixed quantities such that <p align="center"><img src='http://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%5Cdisplaystyle++56+%5Cvarpi+%2B+16+%5Cdelta+%2B+4%5Csigma+%3C+1.&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0' alt='&#92;displaystyle 56 &#92;varpi + 16 &#92;delta + 4&#92;sigma &lt; 1.' title='&#92;displaystyle 56 &#92;varpi + 16 &#92;delta + 4&#92;sigma &lt; 1.' class='latex' /></p> </blockquote> </p> <blockquote><p><b>Theorem 5 (Type II estimate)</b> <a name="t2-precise"></a> <img src='http://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7BType%27%27_%7BII%7D%5B%5Cvarpi%2C%5Cdelta%5D%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0' alt='{Type&#039;&#039;_{II}[&#92;varpi,&#92;delta]}' title='{Type&#039;&#039;_{II}[&#92;varpi,&#92;delta]}' class='latex' /> holds whenever <img src='http://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7B%5Cvarpi%2C%5Cdelta+%3E+0%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0' alt='{&#92;varpi,&#92;delta &gt; 0}' title='{&#92;varpi,&#92;delta &gt; 0}' class='latex' /> are fixed quantities such that <p align="center"><img src='http://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%5Cdisplaystyle++68+%5Cvarpi+%2B+14+%5Cdelta+%3C+1.&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0' alt='&#92;displaystyle 68 &#92;varpi + 14 &#92;delta &lt; 1.' title='&#92;displaystyle 68 &#92;varpi + 14 &#92;delta &lt; 1.' class='latex' /></p> </blockquote> </p> <blockquote><p><b>Theorem 6 (Type III estimate)</b> <a name="t3-precise"></a> <img src='http://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7BType%27%27_%7BIII%7D%5B%5Cvarpi%2C%5Cdelta%2C%5Csigma%5D%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0' alt='{Type&#039;&#039;_{III}[&#92;varpi,&#92;delta,&#92;sigma]}' title='{Type&#039;&#039;_{III}[&#92;varpi,&#92;delta,&#92;sigma]}' class='latex' /> holds whenever <img src='http://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7B0+%3C+%5Cvarpi+%3C+1%2F4%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0' alt='{0 &lt; &#92;varpi &lt; 1/4}' title='{0 &lt; &#92;varpi &lt; 1/4}' class='latex' />, <img src='http://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7B0+%3C+%5Cdelta+%3C+1%2F4%2B%5Cvarpi%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0' alt='{0 &lt; &#92;delta &lt; 1/4+&#92;varpi}' title='{0 &lt; &#92;delta &lt; 1/4+&#92;varpi}' class='latex' />, and <img src='http://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7B%5Csigma+%3E+0%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0' alt='{&#92;sigma &gt; 0}' title='{&#92;sigma &gt; 0}' class='latex' /> are fixed quantities such that <a name="sock"> <p align="center"><img src='http://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%5Cdisplaystyle++%5Csigma+%3E+%5Cfrac%7B1%7D%7B18%7D+%2B+%5Cfrac%7B28%7D%7B9%7D+%5Cvarpi+%2B+%5Cfrac%7B2%7D%7B9%7D+%5Cdelta+%5C+%5C+%5C+%5C+%5C+%2812%29&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0' alt='&#92;displaystyle &#92;sigma &gt; &#92;frac{1}{18} + &#92;frac{28}{9} &#92;varpi + &#92;frac{2}{9} &#92;delta &#92; &#92; &#92; &#92; &#92; (12)' title='&#92;displaystyle &#92;sigma &gt; &#92;frac{1}{18} + &#92;frac{28}{9} &#92;varpi + &#92;frac{2}{9} &#92;delta &#92; &#92; &#92; &#92; &#92; (12)' class='latex' /></p> <p></a> and <a name="vp-crude"> <p align="center"><img src='http://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%5Cdisplaystyle++%5Cvarpi%3C+%5Cfrac%7B1%7D%7B12%7D.+%5C+%5C+%5C+%5C+%5C+%2813%29&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0' alt='&#92;displaystyle &#92;varpi&lt; &#92;frac{1}{12}. &#92; &#92; &#92; &#92; &#92; (13)' title='&#92;displaystyle &#92;varpi&lt; &#92;frac{1}{12}. &#92; &#92; &#92; &#92; &#92; (13)' class='latex' /></p> <p></a> In particular, if <p align="center"><img src='http://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%5Cdisplaystyle++70+%5Cvarpi+%2B+5+%5Cdelta+%3C+1.&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0' alt='&#92;displaystyle 70 &#92;varpi + 5 &#92;delta &lt; 1.' title='&#92;displaystyle 70 &#92;varpi + 5 &#92;delta &lt; 1.' class='latex' /></p> <p> then all values of <img src='http://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7B%5Csigma%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0' alt='{&#92;sigma}' title='{&#92;sigma}' class='latex' /> that are sufficiently close to <img src='http://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7B1%2F10%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0' alt='{1/10}' title='{1/10}' class='latex' /> are admissible. </p></blockquote> </p> <blockquote><p><b>Lemma 7 (Combinatorial lemma)</b> <a name="comb"></a> Let <img src='http://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7B0+%3C+%5Cvarpi+%3C+1%2F4%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0' alt='{0 &lt; &#92;varpi &lt; 1/4}' title='{0 &lt; &#92;varpi &lt; 1/4}' class='latex' />, <img src='http://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7B0+%3C+%5Cdelta+%3C+1%2F4%2B%5Cvarpi%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0' alt='{0 &lt; &#92;delta &lt; 1/4+&#92;varpi}' title='{0 &lt; &#92;delta &lt; 1/4+&#92;varpi}' class='latex' />, and <img src='http://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7B1%2F10+%3C+%5Csigma+%3C+1%2F2%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0' alt='{1/10 &lt; &#92;sigma &lt; 1/2}' title='{1/10 &lt; &#92;sigma &lt; 1/2}' class='latex' /> be such that <img src='http://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7BType%27%27_I%5B%5Cvarpi%2C%5Cdelta%2C%5Csigma%5D%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0' alt='{Type&#039;&#039;_I[&#92;varpi,&#92;delta,&#92;sigma]}' title='{Type&#039;&#039;_I[&#92;varpi,&#92;delta,&#92;sigma]}' class='latex' />, <img src='http://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7BType%27%27_%7BII%7D%5B%5Cvarpi%2C%5Cdelta%5D%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0' alt='{Type&#039;&#039;_{II}[&#92;varpi,&#92;delta]}' title='{Type&#039;&#039;_{II}[&#92;varpi,&#92;delta]}' class='latex' />, and <img src='http://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7BType%27%27_%7BIII%7D%5B%5Cvarpi%2C%5Cdelta%2C%5Csigma%5D%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0' alt='{Type&#039;&#039;_{III}[&#92;varpi,&#92;delta,&#92;sigma]}' title='{Type&#039;&#039;_{III}[&#92;varpi,&#92;delta,&#92;sigma]}' class='latex' /> simultaneously hold. Then <img src='http://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7BMPZ%27%27%5B%5Cvarpi%2C%5Cdelta%5D%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0' alt='{MPZ&#039;&#039;[&#92;varpi,&#92;delta]}' title='{MPZ&#039;&#039;[&#92;varpi,&#92;delta]}' class='latex' /> holds. </p></blockquote> </p> <p> Indeed, if <img src='http://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7B%5Cfrac%7B280%7D%7B3%7D+%5Cvarpi+%2B+%5Cfrac%7B80%7D%7B3%7D+%5Cdelta+%3C+1%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0' alt='{&#92;frac{280}{3} &#92;varpi + &#92;frac{80}{3} &#92;delta &lt; 1}' title='{&#92;frac{280}{3} &#92;varpi + &#92;frac{80}{3} &#92;delta &lt; 1}' class='latex' />, one checks that the hypotheses for Theorems <a href="#t1-precise">4</a>, <a href="#t2-precise">5</a>, <a href="#t3-precise">6</a> are obeyed for <img src='http://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7B%5Csigma%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0' alt='{&#92;sigma}' title='{&#92;sigma}' class='latex' /> sufficiently close to <img src='http://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7B1%2F10%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0' alt='{1/10}' title='{1/10}' class='latex' />, at which point the claim follows from Lemma <a href="#comb">7</a>. </p> <p> The proofs of Theorems <a href="#t1-precise">4</a>, <a href="#t2-precise">5</a>, <a href="#t3-precise">6</a> will be given below the fold, while the proof of Lemma <a href="#comb">7</a> follows from the arguments in <a href="http://terrytao.wordpress.com/2013/06/10/a-combinatorial-subset-sum-problem-associated-with-bounded-prime-gaps/">this previous post</a>. We remark that in our current arguments, the double dense divisibility is only fully used in the Type I estimates; the Type II and Type III estimates are also valid just with single dense divisibility. </p> <blockquote><p><b>Remark 1</b> Theorem <a href="#t3-precise">6</a> is vacuously true for <img src='http://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7B%5Csigma+%3E+1%2F6%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0' alt='{&#92;sigma &gt; 1/6}' title='{&#92;sigma &gt; 1/6}' class='latex' />, as the condition <a href="#n2-o">(10)</a> cannot be satisfied in this case. If we use this trivial case of Theorem <a href="#t3-precise">6</a>, while keeping the full strength of Theorems <a href="#t1-precise">4</a> and <a href="#t2-precise">5</a>, we obtain Theorem <a href="#main">1</a> in the regime <p align="center"><img src='http://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%5Cdisplaystyle++168+%5Cvarpi+%2B+48+%5Cdelta+%3C+1.&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0' alt='&#92;displaystyle 168 &#92;varpi + 48 &#92;delta &lt; 1.' title='&#92;displaystyle 168 &#92;varpi + 48 &#92;delta &lt; 1.' class='latex' /></p> </blockquote> </p> <p> <span id="more-6924"></span> </p> </p> <p align="center"><b> &mdash; 1. Exponential sum estimates &mdash; </b></p> <p> It will be convenient to introduce a little bit of formal algebraic notation. Define an <em>integral rational function</em> to be a formal rational function <img src='http://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7Bf%28t%29+%3D+%5Cfrac%7BP%28t%29%7D%7BQ%28t%29%7D%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0' alt='{f(t) = &#92;frac{P(t)}{Q(t)}}' title='{f(t) = &#92;frac{P(t)}{Q(t)}}' class='latex' /> in a formal indeterminate <img src='http://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7Bt%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0' alt='{t}' title='{t}' class='latex' /> where <img src='http://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7BP%2CQ+%5Cin+%7B%5Cbf+Z%7D%5Bt%5D%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0' alt='{P,Q &#92;in {&#92;bf Z}[t]}' title='{P,Q &#92;in {&#92;bf Z}[t]}' class='latex' /> are polynomials with integer coefficients, and <img src='http://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7BQ%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0' alt='{Q}' title='{Q}' class='latex' /> is monic; in particular any polynomial <img src='http://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7BP%28t%29+%5Cin+%7B%5Cbf+Z%7D%5Bt%5D%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0' alt='{P(t) &#92;in {&#92;bf Z}[t]}' title='{P(t) &#92;in {&#92;bf Z}[t]}' class='latex' /> can be identified with the integral rational function <img src='http://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7BP%28t%29+%5Cequiv+%5Cfrac%7BP%28t%29%7D%7B1%7D%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0' alt='{P(t) &#92;equiv &#92;frac{P(t)}{1}}' title='{P(t) &#92;equiv &#92;frac{P(t)}{1}}' class='latex' />. For minor technical reasons we do <em>not</em> equate integral rational functions under cancelling, thus for instance we consider <img src='http://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7B%5Cfrac%7BP%28t%29R%28t%29%7D%7BQ%28t%29R%28t%29%7D%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0' alt='{&#92;frac{P(t)R(t)}{Q(t)R(t)}}' title='{&#92;frac{P(t)R(t)}{Q(t)R(t)}}' class='latex' /> to be distinct from <img src='http://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7B%5Cfrac%7BP%28t%29%7D%7BQ%28t%29%7D%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0' alt='{&#92;frac{P(t)}{Q(t)}}' title='{&#92;frac{P(t)}{Q(t)}}' class='latex' />; we need to do this because the domain of definition of these two functions is a little different (the former is not defined when <img src='http://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7BR%28t%29%3D0%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0' alt='{R(t)=0}' title='{R(t)=0}' class='latex' />, but the latter can still be defined here). Because we refuse to cancel, we have to be a little careful how we define algebraic operations: specifically, we define </p> <p align="center"><img src='http://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%5Cdisplaystyle++%5Cfrac%7BP_1%28t%29%7D%7BQ_1%28t%29%7D+%2B+%5Cfrac%7BP_2%28t%29%7D%7BQ_2%28t%29%7D+%3A%3D+%5Cfrac%7BP_1%28t%29+Q_2%28t%29+%2B+P_2%28t%29+Q_1%28t%29%7D%7BQ_1%28t%29+Q_2%28t%29%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0' alt='&#92;displaystyle &#92;frac{P_1(t)}{Q_1(t)} + &#92;frac{P_2(t)}{Q_2(t)} := &#92;frac{P_1(t) Q_2(t) + P_2(t) Q_1(t)}{Q_1(t) Q_2(t)}' title='&#92;displaystyle &#92;frac{P_1(t)}{Q_1(t)} + &#92;frac{P_2(t)}{Q_2(t)} := &#92;frac{P_1(t) Q_2(t) + P_2(t) Q_1(t)}{Q_1(t) Q_2(t)}' class='latex' /></p> <p align="center"><img src='http://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%5Cdisplaystyle++%5Cfrac%7BP_1%28t%29%7D%7BQ_1%28t%29%7D+-+%5Cfrac%7BP_2%28t%29%7D%7BQ_2%28t%29%7D+%3A%3D+%5Cfrac%7BP_1%28t%29+Q_2%28t%29+-+P_2%28t%29+Q_1%28t%29%7D%7BQ_1%28t%29+Q_2%28t%29%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0' alt='&#92;displaystyle &#92;frac{P_1(t)}{Q_1(t)} - &#92;frac{P_2(t)}{Q_2(t)} := &#92;frac{P_1(t) Q_2(t) - P_2(t) Q_1(t)}{Q_1(t) Q_2(t)}' title='&#92;displaystyle &#92;frac{P_1(t)}{Q_1(t)} - &#92;frac{P_2(t)}{Q_2(t)} := &#92;frac{P_1(t) Q_2(t) - P_2(t) Q_1(t)}{Q_1(t) Q_2(t)}' class='latex' /></p> <p align="center"><img src='http://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%5Cdisplaystyle++%5Cfrac%7BP_1%28t%29%7D%7BQ_1%28t%29%7D+%5Ccdot+%5Cfrac%7BP_2%28t%29%7D%7BQ_2%28t%29%7D+%3A%3D+%5Cfrac%7BP_1%28t%29+P_2%28t%29%7D%7BQ_1%28t%29+Q_2%28t%29%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0' alt='&#92;displaystyle &#92;frac{P_1(t)}{Q_1(t)} &#92;cdot &#92;frac{P_2(t)}{Q_2(t)} := &#92;frac{P_1(t) P_2(t)}{Q_1(t) Q_2(t)}' title='&#92;displaystyle &#92;frac{P_1(t)}{Q_1(t)} &#92;cdot &#92;frac{P_2(t)}{Q_2(t)} := &#92;frac{P_1(t) P_2(t)}{Q_1(t) Q_2(t)}' class='latex' /></p> <p align="center"><img src='http://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%5Cdisplaystyle++%28%5Cfrac%7BP%28t%29%7D%7BQ%28t%29%7D%29%27+%3A%3D+%5Cfrac%7BP%27%28t%29+Q%28t%29+-+P%28t%29+Q%27%28t%29%7D%7BQ%28t%29%5E2%7D.&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0' alt='&#92;displaystyle (&#92;frac{P(t)}{Q(t)})&#039; := &#92;frac{P&#039;(t) Q(t) - P(t) Q&#039;(t)}{Q(t)^2}.' title='&#92;displaystyle (&#92;frac{P(t)}{Q(t)})&#039; := &#92;frac{P&#039;(t) Q(t) - P(t) Q&#039;(t)}{Q(t)^2}.' class='latex' /></p> <p> Note that the denominator always remains monic with respect to these operations. This is not quite a ring with a derivation (the subtraction operation does not quite cancel the addition operation due to the inability to cancel) but this will not bother us in practice. (On the other hand, addition and multiplication remain associative, and the latter continues to distribute over the former, and differentiation obeys the usual sum and product rules.) Note that if <img src='http://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7Bf%28t%29+%3D+%5Cfrac%7BP%28t%29%7D%7BQ%28t%29%7D%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0' alt='{f(t) = &#92;frac{P(t)}{Q(t)}}' title='{f(t) = &#92;frac{P(t)}{Q(t)}}' class='latex' /> is an integral rational function, we can localise it modulo <img src='http://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7Bq%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0' alt='{q}' title='{q}' class='latex' /> for any modulus <img src='http://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7Bq%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0' alt='{q}' title='{q}' class='latex' /> to obtain a rational function <img src='http://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7Bf%28t%29%5C+%28q%29+%3A%3D+%5Cfrac%7BP%28t%29%5C+%28q%29%7D%7BQ%28t%29%5C+%28q%29%7D%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0' alt='{f(t)&#92; (q) := &#92;frac{P(t)&#92; (q)}{Q(t)&#92; (q)}}' title='{f(t)&#92; (q) := &#92;frac{P(t)&#92; (q)}{Q(t)&#92; (q)}}' class='latex' /> that is the ratio of two polynomials <img src='http://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7BP%5C+%28q%29%2C+Q%5C+%28q%29%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0' alt='{P&#92; (q), Q&#92; (q)}' title='{P&#92; (q), Q&#92; (q)}' class='latex' /> in <img src='http://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7B%28%7B%5Cbf+Z%7D%2Fq%7B%5Cbf+Z%7D%29%5Bt%5D%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0' alt='{({&#92;bf Z}/q{&#92;bf Z})[t]}' title='{({&#92;bf Z}/q{&#92;bf Z})[t]}' class='latex' />, with the denominator monic and hence non-vanishing. We can define the algebraic operations of addition, subtraction, multiplication, and differentiation on integral rational functions modulo <img src='http://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7Bq%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0' alt='{q}' title='{q}' class='latex' /> by the same formulae as above, and we observe that these operations are completely compatible with their counterparts over <img src='http://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7B%7B%5Cbf+Z%7D%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0' alt='{{&#92;bf Z}}' title='{{&#92;bf Z}}' class='latex' /> (even without the ability to cancel), thus for instance <img src='http://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7B%28f%2Bg%29%5C+%28q%29+%3D+%28f%5C+%28q%29%29+%2B+%28g%5C+%28q%29%29%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0' alt='{(f+g)&#92; (q) = (f&#92; (q)) + (g&#92; (q))}' title='{(f+g)&#92; (q) = (f&#92; (q)) + (g&#92; (q))}' class='latex' />. We say that <img src='http://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7Bf%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0' alt='{f}' title='{f}' class='latex' /> is <em>divisible</em> by <img src='http://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7Bq%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0' alt='{q}' title='{q}' class='latex' />, and write <img src='http://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7Bq%7Cf%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0' alt='{q|f}' title='{q|f}' class='latex' />, if the numerator <img src='http://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7BP%28t%29%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0' alt='{P(t)}' title='{P(t)}' class='latex' /> of <img src='http://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7Bf%28t%29%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0' alt='{f(t)}' title='{f(t)}' class='latex' /> has all coefficients divisible by <img src='http://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7Bq%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0' alt='{q}' title='{q}' class='latex' />. </p> <p> If <img src='http://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7Bf%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0' alt='{f}' title='{f}' class='latex' /> is an integral rational function and <img src='http://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7Bn+%5Cin+%7B%5Cbf+Z%7D%2Fq%7B%5Cbf+Z%7D%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0' alt='{n &#92;in {&#92;bf Z}/q{&#92;bf Z}}' title='{n &#92;in {&#92;bf Z}/q{&#92;bf Z}}' class='latex' />, then <img src='http://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7Bf%28n%29%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0' alt='{f(n)}' title='{f(n)}' class='latex' /> is well defined as an element of <img src='http://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7B%7B%5Cbf+Z%7D%2Fq%7B%5Cbf+Z%7D%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0' alt='{{&#92;bf Z}/q{&#92;bf Z}}' title='{{&#92;bf Z}/q{&#92;bf Z}}' class='latex' /> except when <img src='http://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7BQ%28n%29%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0' alt='{Q(n)}' title='{Q(n)}' class='latex' /> is a zero divisor in <img src='http://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7B%7B%5Cbf+Z%7D%2Fq%7B%5Cbf+Z%7D%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0' alt='{{&#92;bf Z}/q{&#92;bf Z}}' title='{{&#92;bf Z}/q{&#92;bf Z}}' class='latex' />. We adopt the convention that <img src='http://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7Be_q%28f%28n%29%29+%3D+0%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0' alt='{e_q(f(n)) = 0}' title='{e_q(f(n)) = 0}' class='latex' /> when <img src='http://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7BQ%28n%29%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0' alt='{Q(n)}' title='{Q(n)}' class='latex' /> is a zero divisor in <img src='http://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7B%7B%5Cbf+Z%7D%2Fq%7B%5Cbf+Z%7D%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0' alt='{{&#92;bf Z}/q{&#92;bf Z}}' title='{{&#92;bf Z}/q{&#92;bf Z}}' class='latex' />, thus <img src='http://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7Be_q%28f%28n%29%29%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0' alt='{e_q(f(n))}' title='{e_q(f(n))}' class='latex' /> is really shorthand for <img src='http://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7B1_%7B%28Q%28n%29%2Cq%29%3D1%7D+e_q%28f%28n%29%29%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0' alt='{1_{(Q(n),q)=1} e_q(f(n))}' title='{1_{(Q(n),q)=1} e_q(f(n))}' class='latex' />; by abuse of notation we view <img src='http://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7Bn+%5Cmapsto+e_q%28f%28n%29%29%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0' alt='{n &#92;mapsto e_q(f(n))}' title='{n &#92;mapsto e_q(f(n))}' class='latex' /> both as a function on <img src='http://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7B%7B%5Cbf+Z%7D%2Fq%7B%5Cbf+Z%7D%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0' alt='{{&#92;bf Z}/q{&#92;bf Z}}' title='{{&#92;bf Z}/q{&#92;bf Z}}' class='latex' /> and as a <img src='http://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7Bq%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0' alt='{q}' title='{q}' class='latex' />-periodic function on <img src='http://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7B%7B%5Cbf+Z%7D%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0' alt='{{&#92;bf Z}}' title='{{&#92;bf Z}}' class='latex' />. Thus for instance </p> <p align="center"><img src='http://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%5Cdisplaystyle++e_q%28+%5Cfrac%7B0%7D%7Bn%7D+%29+%3D+1_%7B%28n%2Cq%29%3D1%7D.&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0' alt='&#92;displaystyle e_q( &#92;frac{0}{n} ) = 1_{(n,q)=1}.' title='&#92;displaystyle e_q( &#92;frac{0}{n} ) = 1_{(n,q)=1}.' class='latex' /></p> <p> Note that if <img src='http://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7Bq%7Cf%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0' alt='{q|f}' title='{q|f}' class='latex' />, then <img src='http://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7Bf%28n%29%3D0%5C+%28q%29%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0' alt='{f(n)=0&#92; (q)}' title='{f(n)=0&#92; (q)}' class='latex' /> for all <img src='http://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7Bn+%5Cin+%7B%5Cbf+Z%7D%2Fq%7B%5Cbf+Z%7D%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0' alt='{n &#92;in {&#92;bf Z}/q{&#92;bf Z}}' title='{n &#92;in {&#92;bf Z}/q{&#92;bf Z}}' class='latex' /> for which <img src='http://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7Bf%28n%29%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0' alt='{f(n)}' title='{f(n)}' class='latex' /> is well defined. We define <img src='http://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7B%28f%2Cq%29%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0' alt='{(f,q)}' title='{(f,q)}' class='latex' /> to be the largest factor <img src='http://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7Bq%27%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0' alt='{q&#039;}' title='{q&#039;}' class='latex' /> of <img src='http://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7Bq%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0' alt='{q}' title='{q}' class='latex' /> for which <img src='http://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7Bq%27%7Cf%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0' alt='{q&#039;|f}' title='{q&#039;|f}' class='latex' />; in particular, if <img src='http://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7Bq%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0' alt='{q}' title='{q}' class='latex' /> is square-free, we have <p align="center"><img src='http://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%5Cdisplaystyle++%28f%2Cq%29+%3D+%5Cprod_%7Bp%7Cq%3A+p%7Cf%7D+p.&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0' alt='&#92;displaystyle (f,q) = &#92;prod_{p|q: p|f} p.' title='&#92;displaystyle (f,q) = &#92;prod_{p|q: p|f} p.' class='latex' /></p> <p> Note with these conventions that <img src='http://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7B%280%2Cq%29%3Dq%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0' alt='{(0,q)=q}' title='{(0,q)=q}' class='latex' />.</p> <p> We recall the following Chinese remainder theorem: </p> <blockquote><p><b>Lemma 8 (Chinese remainder theorem)</b> <a name="crt"></a> Let <img src='http://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7Bq+%3D+q_1+q_2%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0' alt='{q = q_1 q_2}' title='{q = q_1 q_2}' class='latex' /> with <img src='http://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7Bq_1%2Cq_2%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0' alt='{q_1,q_2}' title='{q_1,q_2}' class='latex' /> coprime positive integers. If <img src='http://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7Bf%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0' alt='{f}' title='{f}' class='latex' /> is a rational function, then <p align="center"><img src='http://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%5Cdisplaystyle++e_q%28+f%28n%29+%29+%3D+e_%7Bq_1%7D%28+%5Coverline%7Bq_2%7D+f%28n%29+%29+e_%7Bq_2%7D+%28+%5Cbar%7Bq_1%7D+f%28n%29+%29&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0' alt='&#92;displaystyle e_q( f(n) ) = e_{q_1}( &#92;overline{q_2} f(n) ) e_{q_2} ( &#92;bar{q_1} f(n) )' title='&#92;displaystyle e_q( f(n) ) = e_{q_1}( &#92;overline{q_2} f(n) ) e_{q_2} ( &#92;bar{q_1} f(n) )' class='latex' /></p> <p> for all integers <img src='http://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7Bn%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0' alt='{n}' title='{n}' class='latex' />, where <img src='http://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7B%5Coverline%7Bq_2%7D%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0' alt='{&#92;overline{q_2}}' title='{&#92;overline{q_2}}' class='latex' /> is the inverse of <img src='http://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7Bq_2%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0' alt='{q_2}' title='{q_2}' class='latex' /> in <img src='http://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7B%7B%5Cbf+Z%7D%2Fq_1%7B%5Cbf+Z%7D%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0' alt='{{&#92;bf Z}/q_1{&#92;bf Z}}' title='{{&#92;bf Z}/q_1{&#92;bf Z}}' class='latex' /> and similarly for <img src='http://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7B%5Coverline%7Bq_1%7D%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0' alt='{&#92;overline{q_1}}' title='{&#92;overline{q_1}}' class='latex' />. </p></blockquote> </p> <p> When there is no chance of confusion we will write <img src='http://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7Be_%7Bq_1%7D+%28+%5Cfrac%7B1%7D%7Bq_2%7D+f%28n%29+%29%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0' alt='{e_{q_1} ( &#92;frac{1}{q_2} f(n) )}' title='{e_{q_1} ( &#92;frac{1}{q_2} f(n) )}' class='latex' /> for <img src='http://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7Be_%7Bq_1%7D%28+%5Coverline%7Bq_2%7D+f%28n%29+%29%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0' alt='{e_{q_1}( &#92;overline{q_2} f(n) )}' title='{e_{q_1}( &#92;overline{q_2} f(n) )}' class='latex' /> (though note that <img src='http://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7B%5Cfrac%7B1%7D%7Bq_2%7D%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0' alt='{&#92;frac{1}{q_2}}' title='{&#92;frac{1}{q_2}}' class='latex' /> does not qualify as an integral rational function since the constant <img src='http://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7Bq_2%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0' alt='{q_2}' title='{q_2}' class='latex' /> is not monic). </p> <p> <em>Proof:</em> See Lemma 7 of <a href="http://terrytao.wordpress.com/2013/06/12/estimation-of-the-type-i-and-type-ii-sums/">this previous post</a>. <img src='http://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%5CBox&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0' alt='&#92;Box' title='&#92;Box' class='latex' /></p> <p> Now we give an estimate for complete exponential sums, which combines both Ramanujan sum bounds with Weil conjecture bounds. </p> <blockquote><p><b>Proposition 9 (Ramanujan-Weil bounds)</b> <a name="weil"></a> Let <img src='http://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7Bq%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0' alt='{q}' title='{q}' class='latex' /> be a positive square-free integer of polynomial size, and let <img src='http://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7Bf%28t%29+%3D+%5Cfrac%7BP%28t%29%7D%7BQ%28t%29%7D%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0' alt='{f(t) = &#92;frac{P(t)}{Q(t)}}' title='{f(t) = &#92;frac{P(t)}{Q(t)}}' class='latex' /> be an integral rational function with <img src='http://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7BP%2CQ%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0' alt='{P,Q}' title='{P,Q}' class='latex' /> of bounded degree. Then we have <p align="center"><img src='http://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%5Cdisplaystyle++%7C%5Csum_%7Bn+%5Cin+%7B%5Cbf+Z%7D%2Fq%7B%5Cbf+Z%7D%7D+e_q%28+f%28n%29+%29%7C+%5Clessapprox+q%5E%7B1%2F2%7D+%5Cfrac%7B%28f%27%2Cq%29%7D%7B%28f%27%27%2Cq%29%5E%7B1%2F2%7D%7D.&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0' alt='&#92;displaystyle |&#92;sum_{n &#92;in {&#92;bf Z}/q{&#92;bf Z}} e_q( f(n) )| &#92;lessapprox q^{1/2} &#92;frac{(f&#039;,q)}{(f&#039;&#039;,q)^{1/2}}.' title='&#92;displaystyle |&#92;sum_{n &#92;in {&#92;bf Z}/q{&#92;bf Z}} e_q( f(n) )| &#92;lessapprox q^{1/2} &#92;frac{(f&#039;,q)}{(f&#039;&#039;,q)^{1/2}}.' class='latex' /></p> </blockquote> </p> <p> <em>Proof:</em> See Proposition 4 of <a href="http://terrytao.wordpress.com/2013/06/22/bounding-short-exponential-sums-on-smooth-moduli-via-weyl-differencing/">this previous post</a>. <img src='http://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%5CBox&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0' alt='&#92;Box' title='&#92;Box' class='latex' /></p> <blockquote><p><b>Proposition 10 (Incomplete sums)</b> <a name="inc"></a> Let <img src='http://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7Bq%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0' alt='{q}' title='{q}' class='latex' /> be a positive square-free integer of polynomial size, and let <img src='http://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7Bf%28t%29+%3D+%5Cfrac%7BP%28t%29%7D%7BQ%28t%29%7D%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0' alt='{f(t) = &#92;frac{P(t)}{Q(t)}}' title='{f(t) = &#92;frac{P(t)}{Q(t)}}' class='latex' /> be an integral rational function with <img src='http://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7BP%2CQ%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0' alt='{P,Q}' title='{P,Q}' class='latex' /> of bounded degree with <img src='http://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7B%5Chbox%7Bdeg%7D%28P%29+%3C+%5Chbox%7Bdeg%7D%28Q%29%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0' alt='{&#92;hbox{deg}(P) &lt; &#92;hbox{deg}(Q)}' title='{&#92;hbox{deg}(P) &lt; &#92;hbox{deg}(Q)}' class='latex' />. Let <img src='http://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7Bl+%5Cgeq+1%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0' alt='{l &#92;geq 1}' title='{l &#92;geq 1}' class='latex' /> be a fixed integer, and suppose that we have a factorisation <img src='http://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7Bq+%3D+q_1+%5Cldots+q_l%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0' alt='{q = q_1 &#92;ldots q_l}' title='{q = q_1 &#92;ldots q_l}' class='latex' />. Then for any <img src='http://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7BN+%5Cgg+1%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0' alt='{N &#92;gg 1}' title='{N &#92;gg 1}' class='latex' />, and any coefficient sequence <img src='http://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7B%5Cpsi_N%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0' alt='{&#92;psi_N}' title='{&#92;psi_N}' class='latex' /> at scale <img src='http://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7BN%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0' alt='{N}' title='{N}' class='latex' /> of polynomial size, one has <p align="center"><img src='http://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%5Cdisplaystyle++%7C%5Csum_n+%5Cpsi_N%28n%29+e_q%28f%28n%29%29%7C+%5Clessapprox+%5Csum_%7Bi%3D1%7D%5E%7Bl-1%7D+N%5E%7B1-1%2F2%5Ei%7D+%28q%27_i%29%5E%7B1%2F2%5Ei%7D+%2B+N%5E%7B1-1%2F2%5E%7Bl-1%7D%7D+%28q%27_l%29%5E%7B1%2F2%5El%7D+&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0' alt='&#92;displaystyle |&#92;sum_n &#92;psi_N(n) e_q(f(n))| &#92;lessapprox &#92;sum_{i=1}^{l-1} N^{1-1/2^i} (q&#039;_i)^{1/2^i} + N^{1-1/2^{l-1}} (q&#039;_l)^{1/2^l} ' title='&#92;displaystyle |&#92;sum_n &#92;psi_N(n) e_q(f(n))| &#92;lessapprox &#92;sum_{i=1}^{l-1} N^{1-1/2^i} (q&#039;_i)^{1/2^i} + N^{1-1/2^{l-1}} (q&#039;_l)^{1/2^l} ' class='latex' /></p> <p align="center"><img src='http://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%5Cdisplaystyle++%2B+%5Cfrac%7BN%7D%7Bq%27%7D+1_%7BN+%5Cgeq+q%27%7D+%7C%5Csum_%7Bn+%5Cin+%7B%5Cbf+Z%7D%2Fq%27%7B%5Cbf+Z%7D%7D+e_%7Bq%27%7D%28f%28n%29+%2F+%28f%2Cq%29+%29%7C&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0' alt='&#92;displaystyle + &#92;frac{N}{q&#039;} 1_{N &#92;geq q&#039;} |&#92;sum_{n &#92;in {&#92;bf Z}/q&#039;{&#92;bf Z}} e_{q&#039;}(f(n) / (f,q) )|' title='&#92;displaystyle + &#92;frac{N}{q&#039;} 1_{N &#92;geq q&#039;} |&#92;sum_{n &#92;in {&#92;bf Z}/q&#039;{&#92;bf Z}} e_{q&#039;}(f(n) / (f,q) )|' class='latex' /></p> <p> where <img src='http://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7Bq%27+%3A%3D+q+%2F+%28f%2Cq%29%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0' alt='{q&#039; := q / (f,q)}' title='{q&#039; := q / (f,q)}' class='latex' /> and <img src='http://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7Bq%27_i+%3A%3D+%28q_i%2Cq%27%29%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0' alt='{q&#039;_i := (q_i,q&#039;)}' title='{q&#039;_i := (q_i,q&#039;)}' class='latex' />. </p></blockquote> </p> <p> <em>Proof:</em> Let <img src='http://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7BC%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0' alt='{C}' title='{C}' class='latex' /> be a sufficiently large fixed quantity depending on the degrees of <img src='http://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7BP%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0' alt='{P}' title='{P}' class='latex' /> and <img src='http://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7BQ%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0' alt='{Q}' title='{Q}' class='latex' />. We first make the technical reduction that it suffices to establish the claim in the case when <img src='http://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7Bq%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0' alt='{q}' title='{q}' class='latex' /> has no prime factors less than <img src='http://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7BC%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0' alt='{C}' title='{C}' class='latex' />, for otherwise one can factor <img src='http://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7Bq+%3D+q_0+q%27%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0' alt='{q = q_0 q&#039;}' title='{q = q_0 q&#039;}' class='latex' /> where <img src='http://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7Bq_0%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0' alt='{q_0}' title='{q_0}' class='latex' /> is the product of all the prime factors of <img src='http://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7Bq%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0' alt='{q}' title='{q}' class='latex' /> less than <img src='http://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7BC%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0' alt='{C}' title='{C}' class='latex' />, and by splitting the <img src='http://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7Bn%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0' alt='{n}' title='{n}' class='latex' /> summation into residue classes <img src='http://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7Bb%5C+%28q_0%29%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0' alt='{b&#92; (q_0)}' title='{b&#92; (q_0)}' class='latex' /> and performing the substitution <img src='http://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7Bn+%3D+q_0%27+n+%2B+b%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0' alt='{n = q_0&#039; n + b}' title='{n = q_0&#039; n + b}' class='latex' /> and applying the proposition with <img src='http://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7Bq%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0' alt='{q}' title='{q}' class='latex' /> replaced by <img src='http://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7Bq%27%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0' alt='{q&#039;}' title='{q&#039;}' class='latex' /> (and adjusting <img src='http://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7Bq_1%2C%5Cldots+q_l%2CP%2CQ%2Cf%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0' alt='{q_1,&#92;ldots q_l,P,Q,f}' title='{q_1,&#92;ldots q_l,P,Q,f}' class='latex' /> accordingly) we obtain the claim. </p> <p> By dividing <img src='http://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7Bf%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0' alt='{f}' title='{f}' class='latex' /> through by <img src='http://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7B%28f%2Cq%29%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0' alt='{(f,q)}' title='{(f,q)}' class='latex' /> (and replacing <img src='http://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7Bq_i%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0' alt='{q_i}' title='{q_i}' class='latex' /> with <img src='http://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7Bq%27_i%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0' alt='{q&#039;_i}' title='{q&#039;_i}' class='latex' />) we may assume without loss of generality that <img src='http://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7B%28f%2Cq%29%3D1%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0' alt='{(f,q)=1}' title='{(f,q)=1}' class='latex' /> and <img src='http://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7Bq_i+%3D+q%27_i%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0' alt='{q_i = q&#039;_i}' title='{q_i = q&#039;_i}' class='latex' />. As <img src='http://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7Bf%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0' alt='{f}' title='{f}' class='latex' /> vanishes at infinity, this implies that <img src='http://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7B%28f%27%2Cq%29%3D1%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0' alt='{(f&#039;,q)=1}' title='{(f&#039;,q)=1}' class='latex' /> and <img src='http://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7B%28f%27%27%2Cq%29%3D1%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0' alt='{(f&#039;&#039;,q)=1}' title='{(f&#039;&#039;,q)=1}' class='latex' /> (see Lemma 3 from <a href="http://terrytao.wordpress.com/2013/06/22/bounding-short-exponential-sums-on-smooth-moduli-via-weyl-differencing/">this previous post</a>). </p> <p> We induct on <img src='http://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7Bl%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0' alt='{l}' title='{l}' class='latex' />. We begin with the base case <img src='http://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7Bl%3D1%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0' alt='{l=1}' title='{l=1}' class='latex' />, where the task is to show that </p> <p align="center"><img src='http://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%5Cdisplaystyle++%7C%5Csum_n+%5Cpsi_N%28n%29+e_q%28f%28n%29%29%7C+%5Clessapprox+q%5E%7B1%2F2%7D+%2B+%5Cfrac%7BN%7D%7Bq%7D+1_%7BN+%5Cgeq+q%7D+%7C%5Csum_%7Bn+%5Cin+%7B%5Cbf+Z%7D%2Fq%7B%5Cbf+Z%7D%7D+e_%7Bq%7D%28f%28n%29%29%7C.&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0' alt='&#92;displaystyle |&#92;sum_n &#92;psi_N(n) e_q(f(n))| &#92;lessapprox q^{1/2} + &#92;frac{N}{q} 1_{N &#92;geq q} |&#92;sum_{n &#92;in {&#92;bf Z}/q{&#92;bf Z}} e_{q}(f(n))|.' title='&#92;displaystyle |&#92;sum_n &#92;psi_N(n) e_q(f(n))| &#92;lessapprox q^{1/2} + &#92;frac{N}{q} 1_{N &#92;geq q} |&#92;sum_{n &#92;in {&#92;bf Z}/q{&#92;bf Z}} e_{q}(f(n))|.' class='latex' /></p> <p> By Proposition <a href="#weil">9</a>, we have <p align="center"><img src='http://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%5Cdisplaystyle++%7C%5Csum_%7Bn+%5Cin+%7B%5Cbf+Z%7D%2Fq%7B%5Cbf+Z%7D%7D+e_%7Bq%7D%28f%28n%29%29%7C+%5Clessapprox+q%5E%7B1%2F2%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0' alt='&#92;displaystyle |&#92;sum_{n &#92;in {&#92;bf Z}/q{&#92;bf Z}} e_{q}(f(n))| &#92;lessapprox q^{1/2}' title='&#92;displaystyle |&#92;sum_{n &#92;in {&#92;bf Z}/q{&#92;bf Z}} e_{q}(f(n))| &#92;lessapprox q^{1/2}' class='latex' /></p> <p> so we may delete the condition <img src='http://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7B1_%7BN+%5Cgeq+q%7D%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0' alt='{1_{N &#92;geq q}}' title='{1_{N &#92;geq q}}' class='latex' /> on the right-hand side without penalty.</p> <p> By completion of sums (see Lemma 6 of <a href="http://terrytao.wordpress.com/2013/06/12/estimation-of-the-type-i-and-type-ii-sums/">this previous post</a>), the left-hand side is </p> <p align="center"><img src='http://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%5Cdisplaystyle++%5Clessapprox+1+%2B+%5Cfrac%7BN%7D%7Bq%7D+%5Csum_%7B%7Ch%7C+%5Clessapprox+q%2FN%7D+%7C%5Csum_%7Bn+%5Cin+%7B%5Cbf+Z%7D%2Fq%7B%5Cbf+Z%7D%7D+e_q%28f%28n%29+%2B+hn%29%7C&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0' alt='&#92;displaystyle &#92;lessapprox 1 + &#92;frac{N}{q} &#92;sum_{|h| &#92;lessapprox q/N} |&#92;sum_{n &#92;in {&#92;bf Z}/q{&#92;bf Z}} e_q(f(n) + hn)|' title='&#92;displaystyle &#92;lessapprox 1 + &#92;frac{N}{q} &#92;sum_{|h| &#92;lessapprox q/N} |&#92;sum_{n &#92;in {&#92;bf Z}/q{&#92;bf Z}} e_q(f(n) + hn)|' class='latex' /></p> <p> so it will suffice to show that <p align="center"><img src='http://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%5Cdisplaystyle++%5Cfrac%7BN%7D%7Bq%7D+%5Csum_%7B0+%3C+%7Ch%7C+%5Clessapprox+q%2FN%7D+%7C%5Csum_%7Bn+%5Cin+%7B%5Cbf+Z%7D%2Fq%7B%5Cbf+Z%7D%7D+e_q%28f%28n%29+%2B+hn%29%7C+%5Clessapprox+q%5E%7B1%2F2%7D.&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0' alt='&#92;displaystyle &#92;frac{N}{q} &#92;sum_{0 &lt; |h| &#92;lessapprox q/N} |&#92;sum_{n &#92;in {&#92;bf Z}/q{&#92;bf Z}} e_q(f(n) + hn)| &#92;lessapprox q^{1/2}.' title='&#92;displaystyle &#92;frac{N}{q} &#92;sum_{0 &lt; |h| &#92;lessapprox q/N} |&#92;sum_{n &#92;in {&#92;bf Z}/q{&#92;bf Z}} e_q(f(n) + hn)| &#92;lessapprox q^{1/2}.' class='latex' /></p> <p> By Proposition <a href="#weil">9</a> again, the left-hand side is <p align="center"><img src='http://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%5Cdisplaystyle++%5Clessapprox+%5Cfrac%7BN%7D%7Bq%5E%7B1%2F2%7D%7D+%5Csum_%7B0+%3C+%7Ch%7C+%5Clessapprox+q%2FN%7D+%28f%27%2Bh%2Cq%29.&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0' alt='&#92;displaystyle &#92;lessapprox &#92;frac{N}{q^{1/2}} &#92;sum_{0 &lt; |h| &#92;lessapprox q/N} (f&#039;+h,q).' title='&#92;displaystyle &#92;lessapprox &#92;frac{N}{q^{1/2}} &#92;sum_{0 &lt; |h| &#92;lessapprox q/N} (f&#039;+h,q).' class='latex' /></p> <p> Since <img src='http://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7B%28f%27%27%2Cq%29%3D1%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0' alt='{(f&#039;&#039;,q)=1}' title='{(f&#039;&#039;,q)=1}' class='latex' />, we see that <img src='http://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7B%28f%27%2Bh%2Cq%29%3D1%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0' alt='{(f&#039;+h,q)=1}' title='{(f&#039;+h,q)=1}' class='latex' />, and the claim follows.</p> <p> Now suppose that <img src='http://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7Bl+%3E+1%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0' alt='{l &gt; 1}' title='{l &gt; 1}' class='latex' />, and that the claim has already been proven for <img src='http://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7Bl-1%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0' alt='{l-1}' title='{l-1}' class='latex' />. We use the <img src='http://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7Bq%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0' alt='{q}' title='{q}' class='latex' />-van der Corput <img src='http://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7BA%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0' alt='{A}' title='{A}' class='latex' />-process of <a href="http://www.ams.org/mathscinet-getitem?mr=485727">Heath-Brown</a> and <a href="http://www.ams.org/mathscinet-getitem?mr=1084186">Graham-Ringrose</a>. If we have <img src='http://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7BN+%5Cgeq+q_l%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0' alt='{N &#92;geq q_l}' title='{N &#92;geq q_l}' class='latex' />, then </p> <p align="center"><img src='http://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%5Cdisplaystyle++N%5E%7B1-1%2F2%5E%7Bl-1%7D%7D+q_%7Bl-1%7D%5E%7B1%2F2%5E%7Bl-1%7D%7D+%2B+N%5E%7B1-1%2F2%5E%7Bl-1%7D%7D+q_l%5E%7B1%2F2%5El%7D+%5Cgeq+N%5E%7B1-1%2F2%5E%7Bl-2%7D%7D+%28q_%7Bl-1%7D+q_l%29%5E%7B1%2F2%5E%7Bl-1%7D%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0' alt='&#92;displaystyle N^{1-1/2^{l-1}} q_{l-1}^{1/2^{l-1}} + N^{1-1/2^{l-1}} q_l^{1/2^l} &#92;geq N^{1-1/2^{l-2}} (q_{l-1} q_l)^{1/2^{l-1}}' title='&#92;displaystyle N^{1-1/2^{l-1}} q_{l-1}^{1/2^{l-1}} + N^{1-1/2^{l-1}} q_l^{1/2^l} &#92;geq N^{1-1/2^{l-2}} (q_{l-1} q_l)^{1/2^{l-1}}' class='latex' /></p> <p> and the claim then follows by the induction hypothesis (concatenating <img src='http://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7Bq_l%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0' alt='{q_l}' title='{q_l}' class='latex' /> and <img src='http://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7Bq_%7Bl-1%7D%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0' alt='{q_{l-1}}' title='{q_{l-1}}' class='latex' />). Similarly, if <img src='http://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7BN+%5Cleq+q_1%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0' alt='{N &#92;leq q_1}' title='{N &#92;leq q_1}' class='latex' />, then <img src='http://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7BN%5E%7B1%2F2%7D+q_1%5E%7B1%2F2%7D+%5Cgeq+N%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0' alt='{N^{1/2} q_1^{1/2} &#92;geq N}' title='{N^{1/2} q_1^{1/2} &#92;geq N}' class='latex' />, and the claim follows from the triangle inequality. Thus we may assume that <p align="center"><img src='http://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%5Cdisplaystyle++q_1+%3C+N+%3C+q_l.&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0' alt='&#92;displaystyle q_1 &lt; N &lt; q_l.' title='&#92;displaystyle q_1 &lt; N &lt; q_l.' class='latex' /></p> <p> Let <img src='http://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7BK+%3A%3D+%5Clfloor+N%2Fq_1%5Crfloor%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0' alt='{K := &#92;lfloor N/q_1&#92;rfloor}' title='{K := &#92;lfloor N/q_1&#92;rfloor}' class='latex' />. We can rewrite <img src='http://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7B%5Csum_n+%5Cpsi_N%28n%29+e_q%28f%28n%29%29%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0' alt='{&#92;sum_n &#92;psi_N(n) e_q(f(n))}' title='{&#92;sum_n &#92;psi_N(n) e_q(f(n))}' class='latex' /> as <p align="center"><img src='http://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%5Cdisplaystyle++%5Cfrac%7B1%7D%7BK%7D+%5Csum_n+%5Csum_%7Bk%3D1%7D%5EK+%5Cpsi_N%28n%2Bkq_1%29+e_q%28f%28n%2Bkq_1%29%29.&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0' alt='&#92;displaystyle &#92;frac{1}{K} &#92;sum_n &#92;sum_{k=1}^K &#92;psi_N(n+kq_1) e_q(f(n+kq_1)).' title='&#92;displaystyle &#92;frac{1}{K} &#92;sum_n &#92;sum_{k=1}^K &#92;psi_N(n+kq_1) e_q(f(n+kq_1)).' class='latex' /></p> <p> By Lemma <a href="#crt">8</a> we have <img src='http://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7Be_q%28f%28n%2Bkq_1%29%29+%3D+e_%7Bq_1%7D%28%5Coverline%7Bq_2+%5Cldots+q_l%7D+f%28n%29%29+e_%7Bq_2+%5Cldots+q_l%7D%28+%5Coverline%7Bq_1%7D+f%28n%2Bkq_1%29+%29%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0' alt='{e_q(f(n+kq_1)) = e_{q_1}(&#92;overline{q_2 &#92;ldots q_l} f(n)) e_{q_2 &#92;ldots q_l}( &#92;overline{q_1} f(n+kq_1) )}' title='{e_q(f(n+kq_1)) = e_{q_1}(&#92;overline{q_2 &#92;ldots q_l} f(n)) e_{q_2 &#92;ldots q_l}( &#92;overline{q_1} f(n+kq_1) )}' class='latex' />, and so by the triangle inequality and the Cauchy-Schwarz inequality <p align="center"><img src='http://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%5Cdisplaystyle++%7C%5Csum_n+%5Cpsi_N%28n%29+e_q%28f%28n%29%29%7C+%5Cleq+%5Cfrac%7B1%7D%7BK%7D+%5Csum_n+%7C%5Csum_%7Bk%3D1%7D%5EK+%5Cpsi_N%28n%2Bkq_1%29+e_%7Bq_2+%5Cldots+q_l%7D%28+%5Coverline%7Bq_1%7D+f%28n%2Bkq_1%29+%29%7C+&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0' alt='&#92;displaystyle |&#92;sum_n &#92;psi_N(n) e_q(f(n))| &#92;leq &#92;frac{1}{K} &#92;sum_n |&#92;sum_{k=1}^K &#92;psi_N(n+kq_1) e_{q_2 &#92;ldots q_l}( &#92;overline{q_1} f(n+kq_1) )| ' title='&#92;displaystyle |&#92;sum_n &#92;psi_N(n) e_q(f(n))| &#92;leq &#92;frac{1}{K} &#92;sum_n |&#92;sum_{k=1}^K &#92;psi_N(n+kq_1) e_{q_2 &#92;ldots q_l}( &#92;overline{q_1} f(n+kq_1) )| ' class='latex' /></p> <p align="center"><img src='http://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%5Cdisplaystyle++%5Cll+%5Cfrac%7BN%5E%7B1%2F2%7D%7D%7BK%7D+%28%5Csum_n+%7C%5Csum_%7Bk%3D1%7D%5EK+%5Cpsi_N%28n%2Bkq_1%29+e_%7Bq_2+%5Cldots+q_l%7D%28+%5Coverline%7Bq_1%7D+f%28n%2Bkq_1%29+%29%7C%5E2%29%5E%7B1%2F2%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0' alt='&#92;displaystyle &#92;ll &#92;frac{N^{1/2}}{K} (&#92;sum_n |&#92;sum_{k=1}^K &#92;psi_N(n+kq_1) e_{q_2 &#92;ldots q_l}( &#92;overline{q_1} f(n+kq_1) )|^2)^{1/2}' title='&#92;displaystyle &#92;ll &#92;frac{N^{1/2}}{K} (&#92;sum_n |&#92;sum_{k=1}^K &#92;psi_N(n+kq_1) e_{q_2 &#92;ldots q_l}( &#92;overline{q_1} f(n+kq_1) )|^2)^{1/2}' class='latex' /></p> <p> since the summand is only non-zero when <img src='http://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7Bn%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0' alt='{n}' title='{n}' class='latex' /> is supported on an interval of length <img src='http://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7BO%28N%29%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0' alt='{O(N)}' title='{O(N)}' class='latex' />. This last expression may be rearranged as <p align="center"><img src='http://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%5Cdisplaystyle++%5Cfrac%7BN%5E%7B1%2F2%7D%7D%7BK%7D+%7C%5Csum_%7B1+%5Cleq+k%2Ck%27+%5Cleq+K%7D+%5Csum_n+%5Cpsi_N%28n%2Bkq_1%29+%5Coverline%7B%5Cpsi_N%28n%2Bk%27q_1%29%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0' alt='&#92;displaystyle &#92;frac{N^{1/2}}{K} |&#92;sum_{1 &#92;leq k,k&#039; &#92;leq K} &#92;sum_n &#92;psi_N(n+kq_1) &#92;overline{&#92;psi_N(n+k&#039;q_1)}' title='&#92;displaystyle &#92;frac{N^{1/2}}{K} |&#92;sum_{1 &#92;leq k,k&#039; &#92;leq K} &#92;sum_n &#92;psi_N(n+kq_1) &#92;overline{&#92;psi_N(n+k&#039;q_1)}' class='latex' /></p> <p align="center"><img src='http://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%5Cdisplaystyle++e_%7Bq_2+%5Cldots+q_l%7D%28+%5Coverline%7Bq_1%7D+%28f%28n%2Bkq_1%29+-+f%28n%2Bk%27q_1%29+%29+%29%7C%5E%7B1%2F2%7D.&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0' alt='&#92;displaystyle e_{q_2 &#92;ldots q_l}( &#92;overline{q_1} (f(n+kq_1) - f(n+k&#039;q_1) ) )|^{1/2}.' title='&#92;displaystyle e_{q_2 &#92;ldots q_l}( &#92;overline{q_1} (f(n+kq_1) - f(n+k&#039;q_1) ) )|^{1/2}.' class='latex' /></p> <p> The diagonal contribution <img src='http://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7Bk%3Dk%27%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0' alt='{k=k&#039;}' title='{k=k&#039;}' class='latex' /> can be estimated by <img src='http://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7BO%28+%5Cfrac%7BN%5E%7B1%2F2%7D%7D%7BK%7D+%28+K+N+%29%5E%7B1%2F2%7D+%29+%3D+O%28+N%5E%7B1%2F2%7D+q_1%5E%7B1%2F2%7D+%29%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0' alt='{O( &#92;frac{N^{1/2}}{K} ( K N )^{1/2} ) = O( N^{1/2} q_1^{1/2} )}' title='{O( &#92;frac{N^{1/2}}{K} ( K N )^{1/2} ) = O( N^{1/2} q_1^{1/2} )}' class='latex' />, which is acceptable, so it suffices to show that <a name="sail"> <p align="center"><img src='http://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%5Cdisplaystyle++%7C%5Csum_%7B1+%5Cleq+k%2Ck%27+%5Cleq+K%3A+k+%5Cneq+k%27%7D+%5Csum_n+%5Cpsi_N%28n%2Bkq_1%29+%5Coverline%7B%5Cpsi_N%28n%2Bk%27q_1%29%7D+%5C+%5C+%5C+%5C+%5C+%2814%29&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0' alt='&#92;displaystyle |&#92;sum_{1 &#92;leq k,k&#039; &#92;leq K: k &#92;neq k&#039;} &#92;sum_n &#92;psi_N(n+kq_1) &#92;overline{&#92;psi_N(n+k&#039;q_1)} &#92; &#92; &#92; &#92; &#92; (14)' title='&#92;displaystyle |&#92;sum_{1 &#92;leq k,k&#039; &#92;leq K: k &#92;neq k&#039;} &#92;sum_n &#92;psi_N(n+kq_1) &#92;overline{&#92;psi_N(n+k&#039;q_1)} &#92; &#92; &#92; &#92; &#92; (14)' class='latex' /></p> <p></a> <p align="center"><img src='http://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%5Cdisplaystyle++e_%7Bq_2+%5Cldots+q_l%7D%28+%5Coverline%7Bq_1%7D+%28f%28n%2Bkq_1%29+-+f%28n%2Bk%27q_1%29+%29+%29%7C&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0' alt='&#92;displaystyle e_{q_2 &#92;ldots q_l}( &#92;overline{q_1} (f(n+kq_1) - f(n+k&#039;q_1) ) )|' title='&#92;displaystyle e_{q_2 &#92;ldots q_l}( &#92;overline{q_1} (f(n+kq_1) - f(n+k&#039;q_1) ) )|' class='latex' /></p> <p align="center"><img src='http://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%5Cdisplaystyle++%5Clessapprox+K%5E2+%28+%5Csum_%7Bi%3D2%7D%5E%7Bl-1%7D+N%5E%7B1-1%2F2%5E%7Bi-1%7D%7D+q_i%5E%7B1%2F2%5E%7Bi-1%7D%7D+%2B+N%5E%7B1-1%2F2%5E%7Bl-2%7D%7D+q_l%5E%7B1%2F2%5E%7Bl-1%7D%7D+%29.&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0' alt='&#92;displaystyle &#92;lessapprox K^2 ( &#92;sum_{i=2}^{l-1} N^{1-1/2^{i-1}} q_i^{1/2^{i-1}} + N^{1-1/2^{l-2}} q_l^{1/2^{l-1}} ).' title='&#92;displaystyle &#92;lessapprox K^2 ( &#92;sum_{i=2}^{l-1} N^{1-1/2^{i-1}} q_i^{1/2^{i-1}} + N^{1-1/2^{l-2}} q_l^{1/2^{l-1}} ).' class='latex' /></p> <p> We observe that <img src='http://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7Bn+%5Cmapsto+%5Coverline%7Bq_1%7D+%28f%28n%2Bkq_1%29+-+f%28n%2Bk%27q_1%29+%29%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0' alt='{n &#92;mapsto &#92;overline{q_1} (f(n+kq_1) - f(n+k&#039;q_1) )}' title='{n &#92;mapsto &#92;overline{q_1} (f(n+kq_1) - f(n+k&#039;q_1) )}' class='latex' /> is an integral rational function whose numerator has lower degree than the denominator. If a prime <img src='http://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7Bp%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0' alt='{p}' title='{p}' class='latex' /> dividing <img src='http://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7Bq_2+%5Cldots+q_l%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0' alt='{q_2 &#92;ldots q_l}' title='{q_2 &#92;ldots q_l}' class='latex' /> also divides this rational function, then <img src='http://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7Bf%28n%2B%28k-k%27%29q_1%29-f%28n%29%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0' alt='{f(n+(k-k&#039;)q_1)-f(n)}' title='{f(n+(k-k&#039;)q_1)-f(n)}' class='latex' /> is divisible by <img src='http://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7Bp%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0' alt='{p}' title='{p}' class='latex' />; if <img src='http://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7Bk-k%27%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0' alt='{k-k&#039;}' title='{k-k&#039;}' class='latex' /> is not divisible by <img src='http://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7Bp%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0' alt='{p}' title='{p}' class='latex' />, this implies by telescoping series that <img src='http://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7Bp%7Cf%28n%2Ba%29-f%28n%29%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0' alt='{p|f(n+a)-f(n)}' title='{p|f(n+a)-f(n)}' class='latex' /> for all <img src='http://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7Ba%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0' alt='{a}' title='{a}' class='latex' />. This implies that <img src='http://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7Bf%28n%29%5C+%28p%29%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0' alt='{f(n)&#92; (p)}' title='{f(n)&#92; (p)}' class='latex' /> is constant where it is defined; as <img src='http://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7Bf%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0' alt='{f}' title='{f}' class='latex' /> vanishes at infinity and is defined outside of <img src='http://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7BO%281%29%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0' alt='{O(1)}' title='{O(1)}' class='latex' /> elements, this implies that <img src='http://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7Bp%7Cf%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0' alt='{p|f}' title='{p|f}' class='latex' /> (here we use the fact that <img src='http://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7Bp%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0' alt='{p}' title='{p}' class='latex' /> must exceed <img src='http://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7BC%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0' alt='{C}' title='{C}' class='latex' />, since it divides <img src='http://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7Bq%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0' alt='{q}' title='{q}' class='latex' />). We conclude that <p align="center"><img src='http://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%5Cdisplaystyle++%28q_2+%5Cldots+q_l%2C+%5Coverline%7Bq_1%7D+%28f%28%5Ccdot%2Bkq_1%29+-+f%28%5Ccdot%2Bk%27q_1%29+%29%29+%5Cleq+%28q_2+%5Cldots+q_l%2C+k-k%27%29.&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0' alt='&#92;displaystyle (q_2 &#92;ldots q_l, &#92;overline{q_1} (f(&#92;cdot+kq_1) - f(&#92;cdot+k&#039;q_1) )) &#92;leq (q_2 &#92;ldots q_l, k-k&#039;).' title='&#92;displaystyle (q_2 &#92;ldots q_l, &#92;overline{q_1} (f(&#92;cdot+kq_1) - f(&#92;cdot+k&#039;q_1) )) &#92;leq (q_2 &#92;ldots q_l, k-k&#039;).' class='latex' /></p> <p> Applying the induction hypothesis and Proposition <a href="#weil">9</a>, we may thus bound <p align="center"><img src='http://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%5Cdisplaystyle++%7C%5Csum_n+%5Cpsi_N%28n%2Bkq_1%29+%5Coverline%7B%5Cpsi_N%28n%2Bk%27q_1%29%7D+e_%7Bq_2+%5Cldots+q_l%7D%28+%5Coverline%7Bq_1%7D+%28f%28n%2Bkq_1%29+-+f%28n%2Bk%27q_1%29+%29+%29%7C&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0' alt='&#92;displaystyle |&#92;sum_n &#92;psi_N(n+kq_1) &#92;overline{&#92;psi_N(n+k&#039;q_1)} e_{q_2 &#92;ldots q_l}( &#92;overline{q_1} (f(n+kq_1) - f(n+k&#039;q_1) ) )|' title='&#92;displaystyle |&#92;sum_n &#92;psi_N(n+kq_1) &#92;overline{&#92;psi_N(n+k&#039;q_1)} e_{q_2 &#92;ldots q_l}( &#92;overline{q_1} (f(n+kq_1) - f(n+k&#039;q_1) ) )|' class='latex' /></p> <p> by <p align="center"><img src='http://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%5Cdisplaystyle++%5Clessapprox+%5Csum_%7Bi%3D2%7D%5E%7Bl-1%7D+N%5E%7B1-1%2F2%5E%7Bi-1%7D%7D+q_i%5E%7B1%2F2%5E%7Bi-1%7D%7D+%2B+N%5E%7B1-1%2F2%5E%7Bl-2%7D%7D+q_l%5E%7B1%2F2%5E%7Bl-1%7D%7D+&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0' alt='&#92;displaystyle &#92;lessapprox &#92;sum_{i=2}^{l-1} N^{1-1/2^{i-1}} q_i^{1/2^{i-1}} + N^{1-1/2^{l-2}} q_l^{1/2^{l-1}} ' title='&#92;displaystyle &#92;lessapprox &#92;sum_{i=2}^{l-1} N^{1-1/2^{i-1}} q_i^{1/2^{i-1}} + N^{1-1/2^{l-2}} q_l^{1/2^{l-1}} ' class='latex' /></p> <p align="center"><img src='http://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%5Cdisplaystyle++%2B+N+%28q_2+%5Cldots+q_l%29%5E%7B-1%2F2%7D+%28q_2+%5Cldots+q_l%2C+k-k%27%29%5E%7B1%2F2%7D+1_%7BN+%5Cgeq+q_2+%5Cldots+q_l+%2F+%28q_2+%5Cldots+q_l%2C+k-k%27%29%7D.&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0' alt='&#92;displaystyle + N (q_2 &#92;ldots q_l)^{-1/2} (q_2 &#92;ldots q_l, k-k&#039;)^{1/2} 1_{N &#92;geq q_2 &#92;ldots q_l / (q_2 &#92;ldots q_l, k-k&#039;)}.' title='&#92;displaystyle + N (q_2 &#92;ldots q_l)^{-1/2} (q_2 &#92;ldots q_l, k-k&#039;)^{1/2} 1_{N &#92;geq q_2 &#92;ldots q_l / (q_2 &#92;ldots q_l, k-k&#039;)}.' class='latex' /></p> <p> The contribution of the first two terms to <a href="#sail">(14)</a> is acceptable, so the only contribution remaining to control is <p align="center"><img src='http://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%5Cdisplaystyle++N+%28q_2+%5Cldots+q_l%29%5E%7B-1%2F2%7D+%5Csum_%7B1+%5Cleq+k%2Ck%27+%5Cleq+K%3A+k+%5Cneq+k%27%7D+%28q_2+%5Cldots+q_l%2C+k-k%27%29%5E%7B1%2F2%7D+1_%7BN+%5Cgeq+q_2+%5Cldots+q_l+%2F+%28q_2+%5Cldots+q_l%2C+k-k%27%29%7D.&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0' alt='&#92;displaystyle N (q_2 &#92;ldots q_l)^{-1/2} &#92;sum_{1 &#92;leq k,k&#039; &#92;leq K: k &#92;neq k&#039;} (q_2 &#92;ldots q_l, k-k&#039;)^{1/2} 1_{N &#92;geq q_2 &#92;ldots q_l / (q_2 &#92;ldots q_l, k-k&#039;)}.' title='&#92;displaystyle N (q_2 &#92;ldots q_l)^{-1/2} &#92;sum_{1 &#92;leq k,k&#039; &#92;leq K: k &#92;neq k&#039;} (q_2 &#92;ldots q_l, k-k&#039;)^{1/2} 1_{N &#92;geq q_2 &#92;ldots q_l / (q_2 &#92;ldots q_l, k-k&#039;)}.' class='latex' /></p> <p> If we bound <img src='http://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7B1_%7BN+%5Cgeq+q_2+%5Cldots+q_l+%2F+%28q_2+%5Cldots+q_l%2C+k-k%27%29%7D%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0' alt='{1_{N &#92;geq q_2 &#92;ldots q_l / (q_2 &#92;ldots q_l, k-k&#039;)}}' title='{1_{N &#92;geq q_2 &#92;ldots q_l / (q_2 &#92;ldots q_l, k-k&#039;)}}' class='latex' /> by <img src='http://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7B%28q_2+%5Cldots+q_l%2C+k-k%27%29%5E%7B1%2F2%7D+%28q_2+%5Cldots+q_l%29%5E%7B-1%2F2%7D+N%5E%7B1%2F2%7D%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0' alt='{(q_2 &#92;ldots q_l, k-k&#039;)^{1/2} (q_2 &#92;ldots q_l)^{-1/2} N^{1/2}}' title='{(q_2 &#92;ldots q_l, k-k&#039;)^{1/2} (q_2 &#92;ldots q_l)^{-1/2} N^{1/2}}' class='latex' />, we can bound this expression by <p align="center"><img src='http://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%5Cdisplaystyle++N%5E%7B3%2F2%7D+%28q_2+%5Cldots+q_l%29%5E%7B-1%7D+%5Csum_%7B1+%5Cleq+k%2Ck%27+%5Cleq+K%3A+k+%5Cneq+k%27%7D+%28q_2+%5Cldots+q_l%2C+k-k%27%29&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0' alt='&#92;displaystyle N^{3/2} (q_2 &#92;ldots q_l)^{-1} &#92;sum_{1 &#92;leq k,k&#039; &#92;leq K: k &#92;neq k&#039;} (q_2 &#92;ldots q_l, k-k&#039;)' title='&#92;displaystyle N^{3/2} (q_2 &#92;ldots q_l)^{-1} &#92;sum_{1 &#92;leq k,k&#039; &#92;leq K: k &#92;neq k&#039;} (q_2 &#92;ldots q_l, k-k&#039;)' class='latex' /></p> <p> which by Lemma 5 of <a href="http://terrytao.wordpress.com/2013/06/14/estimation-of-the-type-iii-sums/">this previous post</a> and the bound <img src='http://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7BN+%3C+q_l%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0' alt='{N &lt; q_l}' title='{N &lt; q_l}' class='latex' /> is bounded by <p align="center"><img src='http://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%5Cdisplaystyle++%5Clessapprox+K%5E2+N%5E%7B1-1%2F2%5E%7Bl-2%7D%7D+q_l%5E%7B1%2F2%5E%7Bl-1%7D%7D+&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0' alt='&#92;displaystyle &#92;lessapprox K^2 N^{1-1/2^{l-2}} q_l^{1/2^{l-1}} ' title='&#92;displaystyle &#92;lessapprox K^2 N^{1-1/2^{l-2}} q_l^{1/2^{l-1}} ' class='latex' /></p> <p> which is acceptable. <img src='http://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%5CBox&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0' alt='&#92;Box' title='&#92;Box' class='latex' /></p> <p> We record a special case of the above proposition: </p> <blockquote><p><b>Corollary 11</b> <a name="dons"></a> Let <img src='http://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7Bd_1%2Cd_2%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0' alt='{d_1,d_2}' title='{d_1,d_2}' class='latex' /> be square-free numbers (not necessarily coprime) of polynomial size, let <img src='http://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7Bc_1%2Cc_2%2Cl%2Cl%27%2Cm%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0' alt='{c_1,c_2,l,l&#039;,m}' title='{c_1,c_2,l,l&#039;,m}' class='latex' /> be integers, let <img src='http://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7BN+%5Cgg+1%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0' alt='{N &#92;gg 1}' title='{N &#92;gg 1}' class='latex' />, and let <img src='http://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7B%5Cpsi_N%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0' alt='{&#92;psi_N}' title='{&#92;psi_N}' class='latex' /> be a coefficient sequence at scale <img src='http://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7BN%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0' alt='{N}' title='{N}' class='latex' />. Suppose that <img src='http://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7B%5Bd_1%2Cd_2%5D%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0' alt='{[d_1,d_2]}' title='{[d_1,d_2]}' class='latex' /> is <img src='http://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7By%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0' alt='{y}' title='{y}' class='latex' />-densely divisible. Let <img src='http://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7Ba%5C+%28q_0%29%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0' alt='{a&#92; (q_0)}' title='{a&#92; (q_0)}' class='latex' /> be a residue class with <img src='http://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7Bq_0+%7C+%28d_1%2Cd_2%29%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0' alt='{q_0 | (d_1,d_2)}' title='{q_0 | (d_1,d_2)}' class='latex' />. Then <p align="center"><img src='http://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%5Cdisplaystyle++%7C%5Csum_%7Bn+%3A+n+%3D+a%5C+%28q_0%29%7D+%5Cpsi_N%28n%2Bm%29+e_%7Bd_1%7D%28+%5Cfrac%7Bc_1%7D%7Bn%2Bl%7D+%29+e_%7Bd_2%7D%28+%5Cfrac%7Bc_2%7D%7Bn%2Bl%27%7D+%29%7C+%5Clessapprox+&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0' alt='&#92;displaystyle |&#92;sum_{n : n = a&#92; (q_0)} &#92;psi_N(n+m) e_{d_1}( &#92;frac{c_1}{n+l} ) e_{d_2}( &#92;frac{c_2}{n+l&#039;} )| &#92;lessapprox ' title='&#92;displaystyle |&#92;sum_{n : n = a&#92; (q_0)} &#92;psi_N(n+m) e_{d_1}( &#92;frac{c_1}{n+l} ) e_{d_2}( &#92;frac{c_2}{n+l&#039;} )| &#92;lessapprox ' class='latex' /></p> <p align="center"><img src='http://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%5Cdisplaystyle++q_0%5E%7B-1%2F2%7D+N%5E%7B1%2F2%7D+%5Bd_1%2Cd_2%5D%5E%7B1%2F6%7D+y%5E%7B1%2F6%7D+%2B+q_0%5E%7B-1%7D+%5Cfrac%7B%28c_1%2Cd%27_1%29%7D%7Bd%27_1%7D+%5Cfrac%7B%28c_2%2Cd%27_2%29%7D%7Bd%27_2%7D+N+&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0' alt='&#92;displaystyle q_0^{-1/2} N^{1/2} [d_1,d_2]^{1/6} y^{1/6} + q_0^{-1} &#92;frac{(c_1,d&#039;_1)}{d&#039;_1} &#92;frac{(c_2,d&#039;_2)}{d&#039;_2} N ' title='&#92;displaystyle q_0^{-1/2} N^{1/2} [d_1,d_2]^{1/6} y^{1/6} + q_0^{-1} &#92;frac{(c_1,d&#039;_1)}{d&#039;_1} &#92;frac{(c_2,d&#039;_2)}{d&#039;_2} N ' class='latex' /></p> <p> where <img src='http://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7Bd%27_i+%3A%3D+d_i%2F%28d_1%2Cd_2%29%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0' alt='{d&#039;_i := d_i/(d_1,d_2)}' title='{d&#039;_i := d_i/(d_1,d_2)}' class='latex' /> for <img src='http://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7Bi%3D1%2C2%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0' alt='{i=1,2}' title='{i=1,2}' class='latex' />. We also have the variant bound <p align="center"><img src='http://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%5Cdisplaystyle++%7C%5Csum_%7Bn+%3A+n+%3D+a%5C+%28q_0%29%7D+%5Cpsi_N%28n%2Bm%29+e_%7Bd_1%7D%28+%5Cfrac%7Bc_1%7D%7Bn+%2B+l%7D+%29+e_%7Bd_2%7D%28+%5Cfrac%7Bc_2%7D%7Bn%2Bl%27%7D+%29%7C+%5Clessapprox+&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0' alt='&#92;displaystyle |&#92;sum_{n : n = a&#92; (q_0)} &#92;psi_N(n+m) e_{d_1}( &#92;frac{c_1}{n + l} ) e_{d_2}( &#92;frac{c_2}{n+l&#039;} )| &#92;lessapprox ' title='&#92;displaystyle |&#92;sum_{n : n = a&#92; (q_0)} &#92;psi_N(n+m) e_{d_1}( &#92;frac{c_1}{n + l} ) e_{d_2}( &#92;frac{c_2}{n+l&#039;} )| &#92;lessapprox ' class='latex' /></p> <p align="center"><img src='http://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%5Cdisplaystyle++q_0%5E%7B-1%2F2%7D+%5Bd_1%2Cd_2%5D%5E%7B1%2F2%7D+%2B+q_0%5E%7B-1%7D+%5Cfrac%7B%28c_1%2Cd%27_1%29%7D%7Bd%27_1%7D+%5Cfrac%7B%28c_2%2Cd%27_2%29%7D%7Bd%27_2%7D+N.+&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0' alt='&#92;displaystyle q_0^{-1/2} [d_1,d_2]^{1/2} + q_0^{-1} &#92;frac{(c_1,d&#039;_1)}{d&#039;_1} &#92;frac{(c_2,d&#039;_2)}{d&#039;_2} N. ' title='&#92;displaystyle q_0^{-1/2} [d_1,d_2]^{1/2} + q_0^{-1} &#92;frac{(c_1,d&#039;_1)}{d&#039;_1} &#92;frac{(c_2,d&#039;_2)}{d&#039;_2} N. ' class='latex' /></p> </blockquote> </p> <p> <em>Proof:</em> We first consider the case <img src='http://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7Bq_0%3D1%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0' alt='{q_0=1}' title='{q_0=1}' class='latex' />, so that the congruence condition <img src='http://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7Bn+%3D+a%5C+%28q_0%29%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0' alt='{n = a&#92; (q_0)}' title='{n = a&#92; (q_0)}' class='latex' /> can be deleted. By the dense divisibility hypothesis we may factor <img src='http://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7B%5Bd_1%2Cd_2%5D+%3D+q_1+q_2%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0' alt='{[d_1,d_2] = q_1 q_2}' title='{[d_1,d_2] = q_1 q_2}' class='latex' /> for some </p> <p align="center"><img src='http://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%5Cdisplaystyle++y%5E%7B-2%2F3%7D%5Bd_1%2Cd_2%5D%5E%7B1%2F3%7D+%5Cleq+q_1+%5Cleq+y%5E%7B1%2F3%7D+%5Bd_1%2Cd_2%5D%5E%7B1%2F3%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0' alt='&#92;displaystyle y^{-2/3}[d_1,d_2]^{1/3} &#92;leq q_1 &#92;leq y^{1/3} [d_1,d_2]^{1/3}' title='&#92;displaystyle y^{-2/3}[d_1,d_2]^{1/3} &#92;leq q_1 &#92;leq y^{1/3} [d_1,d_2]^{1/3}' class='latex' /></p> <p> and <p align="center"><img src='http://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%5Cdisplaystyle++y%5E%7B-1%2F3%7D%5Bd_1%2Cd_2%5D%5E%7B2%2F3%7D+%5Cleq+q_2+%5Cleq+y%5E%7B2%2F3%7D+%5Bd_1%2Cd_2%5D%5E%7B2%2F3%7D.&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0' alt='&#92;displaystyle y^{-1/3}[d_1,d_2]^{2/3} &#92;leq q_2 &#92;leq y^{2/3} [d_1,d_2]^{2/3}.' title='&#92;displaystyle y^{-1/3}[d_1,d_2]^{2/3} &#92;leq q_2 &#92;leq y^{2/3} [d_1,d_2]^{2/3}.' class='latex' /></p> <p> The first bound then follows from the <img src='http://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7Bl%3D2%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0' alt='{l=2}' title='{l=2}' class='latex' /> case of Proposition <a href="#inc">10</a>, combined with the bound <p align="center"><img src='http://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%5Cdisplaystyle++%7C%5Csum_%7Bn+%5Cin+%7B%5Cbf+Z%7D%2F%5Bd_1%2Cd_2%5D%7B%5Cbf+Z%7D%7D+e_%7Bd_1%7D%28+%5Cfrac%7Bc_1%7D%7Bn%2Bl%7D+%29+e_%7Bd_2%7D%28+%5Cfrac%7Bc_2%7D%7Bn%2Bl%27%7D+%29%7C+%5Clessapprox+%28c_1%2Cd%27_1%29+%28c_2%2Cd%27_2%29+%28d_1%2Cd_2%29&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0' alt='&#92;displaystyle |&#92;sum_{n &#92;in {&#92;bf Z}/[d_1,d_2]{&#92;bf Z}} e_{d_1}( &#92;frac{c_1}{n+l} ) e_{d_2}( &#92;frac{c_2}{n+l&#039;} )| &#92;lessapprox (c_1,d&#039;_1) (c_2,d&#039;_2) (d_1,d_2)' title='&#92;displaystyle |&#92;sum_{n &#92;in {&#92;bf Z}/[d_1,d_2]{&#92;bf Z}} e_{d_1}( &#92;frac{c_1}{n+l} ) e_{d_2}( &#92;frac{c_2}{n+l&#039;} )| &#92;lessapprox (c_1,d&#039;_1) (c_2,d&#039;_2) (d_1,d_2)' class='latex' /></p> <p> that is proven as part of Proposition 5 of <a href="http://terrytao.wordpress.com/2013/06/22/bounding-short-exponential-sums-on-smooth-moduli-via-weyl-differencing/">this previous post</a>. The second bound similarly follows from the <img src='http://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7Bl%3D1%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0' alt='{l=1}' title='{l=1}' class='latex' /> case of Proposition<a href="#inc">10</a>.</p> <p> Now we consider the case when <img src='http://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7Bq_0+%3E+1%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0' alt='{q_0 &gt; 1}' title='{q_0 &gt; 1}' class='latex' />. Writing <img src='http://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7Bn+%3D+n%27+q_0+%2B+a%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0' alt='{n = n&#039; q_0 + a}' title='{n = n&#039; q_0 + a}' class='latex' />, <img src='http://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7Bd_1+%3D+q_0+%5Ctilde+d_1%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0' alt='{d_1 = q_0 &#92;tilde d_1}' title='{d_1 = q_0 &#92;tilde d_1}' class='latex' />, and <img src='http://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7Bd_2+%3Dq_0+%5Ctilde+d_2%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0' alt='{d_2 =q_0 &#92;tilde d_2}' title='{d_2 =q_0 &#92;tilde d_2}' class='latex' />, we have from Lemma <a href="#crt">8</a> that </p> <p align="center"><img src='http://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%5Cdisplaystyle++e_%7Bd_1%7D%28+%5Cfrac%7Bc_1%7D%7Bn%2Bl%7D+%29+%3D+e_%7B%5Ctilde+d_1%7D%28+%5Cfrac%7Bc_1+%5Coverline%7Bq_0%7D%5E2%7D%7Bn%27+%2B+%28a%2Bl%29+%5Coverline%7Bq_0%7D+%7D+%29+e_%7Bq_0%7D%28+%5Cfrac%7Bc_1+%5Coverline%7B%5Ctilde+d_1%7D%7D%7Ba%2Bl%7D+%29&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0' alt='&#92;displaystyle e_{d_1}( &#92;frac{c_1}{n+l} ) = e_{&#92;tilde d_1}( &#92;frac{c_1 &#92;overline{q_0}^2}{n&#039; + (a+l) &#92;overline{q_0} } ) e_{q_0}( &#92;frac{c_1 &#92;overline{&#92;tilde d_1}}{a+l} )' title='&#92;displaystyle e_{d_1}( &#92;frac{c_1}{n+l} ) = e_{&#92;tilde d_1}( &#92;frac{c_1 &#92;overline{q_0}^2}{n&#039; + (a+l) &#92;overline{q_0} } ) e_{q_0}( &#92;frac{c_1 &#92;overline{&#92;tilde d_1}}{a+l} )' class='latex' /></p> <p> and similarly <p align="center"><img src='http://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%5Cdisplaystyle++e_%7Bd_1%7D%28+%5Cfrac%7Bc_2%7D%7Bn%2Bl%27%7D+%29+%3D+e_%7B%5Ctilde+d_2%7D%28+%5Cfrac%7Bc_2+%5Coverline%7Bq_0%7D%5E2%7D%7Bn%27+%2B+%28a%2Bl%27%29+%5Coverline%7Bq_0%7D+%7D+%29+e_%7Bq_0%7D%28+%5Cfrac%7Bc_2+%5Coverline%7B%5Ctilde+d_2%7D%7D%7Ba%2Bl%27%7D+%29.&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0' alt='&#92;displaystyle e_{d_1}( &#92;frac{c_2}{n+l&#039;} ) = e_{&#92;tilde d_2}( &#92;frac{c_2 &#92;overline{q_0}^2}{n&#039; + (a+l&#039;) &#92;overline{q_0} } ) e_{q_0}( &#92;frac{c_2 &#92;overline{&#92;tilde d_2}}{a+l&#039;} ).' title='&#92;displaystyle e_{d_1}( &#92;frac{c_2}{n+l&#039;} ) = e_{&#92;tilde d_2}( &#92;frac{c_2 &#92;overline{q_0}^2}{n&#039; + (a+l&#039;) &#92;overline{q_0} } ) e_{q_0}( &#92;frac{c_2 &#92;overline{&#92;tilde d_2}}{a+l&#039;} ).' class='latex' /></p> <p> If we then apply the previous results with <img src='http://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7Bd_1%2Cd_2%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0' alt='{d_1,d_2}' title='{d_1,d_2}' class='latex' /> replaced by <img src='http://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7B%5Ctilde+d_1%2C%5Ctilde+d_2%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0' alt='{&#92;tilde d_1,&#92;tilde d_2}' title='{&#92;tilde d_1,&#92;tilde d_2}' class='latex' /> (with <img src='http://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7B%5B%5Ctilde+d_1%2C%5Ctilde+d_2%5D+%3D+%5Bd_1%2Cd_2%5D%2Fq_0%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0' alt='{[&#92;tilde d_1,&#92;tilde d_2] = [d_1,d_2]/q_0}' title='{[&#92;tilde d_1,&#92;tilde d_2] = [d_1,d_2]/q_0}' class='latex' /> being <img src='http://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7Bq_0y%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0' alt='{q_0y}' title='{q_0y}' class='latex' />-densely divisible) and <img src='http://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7BN%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0' alt='{N}' title='{N}' class='latex' /> replaced by <img src='http://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7BN%2Fq_0%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0' alt='{N/q_0}' title='{N/q_0}' class='latex' /> (and with suitable alterations to <img src='http://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7Bc_1%2Cc_2%2Cl%2Cl%27%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0' alt='{c_1,c_2,l,l&#039;}' title='{c_1,c_2,l,l&#039;}' class='latex' />), we obtain the required claims. <img src='http://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%5CBox&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0' alt='&#92;Box' title='&#92;Box' class='latex' /></p> <p> For the Type III estimate we will also need a deeper exponential sum estimate, involving the hyper-Kloosterman sums <a name="hyper-kloost"> <p align="center"><img src='http://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%5Cdisplaystyle++K_3%28a%3Bq%29+%3A%3D+%5Cfrac%7B1%7D%7Bq%7D+%5Csum_%7Bx%2Cy%2Cz+%5Cin+%28%7B%5Cbf+Z%7D%2Fq%7B%5Cbf+Z%7D%29%5E%5Ctimes%3A+xyz%3Da%7D+e_q%28x%2By%2Bz%29+%5C+%5C+%5C+%5C+%5C+%2815%29&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0' alt='&#92;displaystyle K_3(a;q) := &#92;frac{1}{q} &#92;sum_{x,y,z &#92;in ({&#92;bf Z}/q{&#92;bf Z})^&#92;times: xyz=a} e_q(x+y+z) &#92; &#92; &#92; &#92; &#92; (15)' title='&#92;displaystyle K_3(a;q) := &#92;frac{1}{q} &#92;sum_{x,y,z &#92;in ({&#92;bf Z}/q{&#92;bf Z})^&#92;times: xyz=a} e_q(x+y+z) &#92; &#92; &#92; &#92; &#92; (15)' class='latex' /></p> <p></a> for square-free <img src='http://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7Bq%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0' alt='{q}' title='{q}' class='latex' /> and <img src='http://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7Ba+%5Cin+%28%7B%5Cbf+Z%7D%2Fq%7B%5Cbf+Z%7D%29%5E%5Ctimes%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0' alt='{a &#92;in ({&#92;bf Z}/q{&#92;bf Z})^&#92;times}' title='{a &#92;in ({&#92;bf Z}/q{&#92;bf Z})^&#92;times}' class='latex' />.) </p> <blockquote><p><b>Lemma 12 (Correlation of hyper-Kloosterman sums)</b> Let <img src='http://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7Bs%2Cr_1%2Cr_2%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0' alt='{s,r_1,r_2}' title='{s,r_1,r_2}' class='latex' /> be square-free numbers of polynomial size with <img src='http://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7B%28s%2Cr_1%29%3D%28s%2Cr_2%29%3D1%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0' alt='{(s,r_1)=(s,r_2)=1}' title='{(s,r_1)=(s,r_2)=1}' class='latex' />. Let <img src='http://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7Ba_1+%5Cin+%28%7B%5Cbf+Z%7D%2Fr_1+s%29%5E%5Ctimes%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0' alt='{a_1 &#92;in ({&#92;bf Z}/r_1 s)^&#92;times}' title='{a_1 &#92;in ({&#92;bf Z}/r_1 s)^&#92;times}' class='latex' />, <img src='http://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7Ba_2+%5Cin+%28%7B%5Cbf+Z%7D%2Fr_2s%29%5E%5Ctimes%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0' alt='{a_2 &#92;in ({&#92;bf Z}/r_2s)^&#92;times}' title='{a_2 &#92;in ({&#92;bf Z}/r_2s)^&#92;times}' class='latex' />, and <img src='http://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7Bn+%5Cin+%7B%5Cbf+Z%7D%2F%28%5Br_1%2Cr_2%5D+s%29%7B%5Cbf+Z%7D%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0' alt='{n &#92;in {&#92;bf Z}/([r_1,r_2] s){&#92;bf Z}}' title='{n &#92;in {&#92;bf Z}/([r_1,r_2] s){&#92;bf Z}}' class='latex' />. Then <p align="center"><img src='http://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%5Cdisplaystyle++%7C%5Csum_%7Bh+%5Cin+%28%7B%5Cbf+Z%7D%2F%5Br_1%2C+r_2%5Ds+%7B%5Cbf+Z%7D%29%5E%5Ctimes%7D+K_3%28a_1+h%3B+r_1+s%29+%5Coverline%7BK_3%28a_2+h%3B+r_2+s%29%7D+e_%7B%5Br_1%2Cr_2%5D+s%7D%28+nh+%29%7C+&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0' alt='&#92;displaystyle |&#92;sum_{h &#92;in ({&#92;bf Z}/[r_1, r_2]s {&#92;bf Z})^&#92;times} K_3(a_1 h; r_1 s) &#92;overline{K_3(a_2 h; r_2 s)} e_{[r_1,r_2] s}( nh )| ' title='&#92;displaystyle |&#92;sum_{h &#92;in ({&#92;bf Z}/[r_1, r_2]s {&#92;bf Z})^&#92;times} K_3(a_1 h; r_1 s) &#92;overline{K_3(a_2 h; r_2 s)} e_{[r_1,r_2] s}( nh )| ' class='latex' /></p> <p align="center"><img src='http://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%5Cdisplaystyle++%5Clessapprox+d%5E%7B1%2F2%7D+s%5E%7B1%2F2%7D+%5Br_1%2Cr_2%5D%5E%7B1%2F2%7D+%28r_1%2Cr_2%2Ca_2-a_1%2Cn%29%5E%7B1%2F2%7D+&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0' alt='&#92;displaystyle &#92;lessapprox d^{1/2} s^{1/2} [r_1,r_2]^{1/2} (r_1,r_2,a_2-a_1,n)^{1/2} ' title='&#92;displaystyle &#92;lessapprox d^{1/2} s^{1/2} [r_1,r_2]^{1/2} (r_1,r_2,a_2-a_1,n)^{1/2} ' class='latex' /></p> <p> where <img src='http://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7Bd+%3A%3D+%28a_2+r_1%5E3+-+a_1+r_2%5E3%2C+n%2C+s%29%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0' alt='{d := (a_2 r_1^3 - a_1 r_2^3, n, s)}' title='{d := (a_2 r_1^3 - a_1 r_2^3, n, s)}' class='latex' />. </p></blockquote> </p> <p> <em>Proof:</em> From Lemma <a href="#crt">8</a> we have </p> <p align="center"><img src='http://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%5Cdisplaystyle++K_3%28+a_i+h%3B+r_i+s+%29+%3D+K_3%28+a_i+%5Cbar%7Bs%7D%5E3+h%3B+r_i%29+K_3%28+a_i+%5Coverline%7Br_i%7D%5E3+h%3B+s+%29&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0' alt='&#92;displaystyle K_3( a_i h; r_i s ) = K_3( a_i &#92;bar{s}^3 h; r_i) K_3( a_i &#92;overline{r_i}^3 h; s )' title='&#92;displaystyle K_3( a_i h; r_i s ) = K_3( a_i &#92;bar{s}^3 h; r_i) K_3( a_i &#92;overline{r_i}^3 h; s )' class='latex' /></p> <p> and so it suffices to prove the estimates <p align="center"><img src='http://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%5Cdisplaystyle++%7C%5Csum_%7Bh+%5Cin+%28%7B%5Cbf+Z%7D%2F%5Br_1%2C+r_2%5D+%7B%5Cbf+Z%7D%29%5E%5Ctimes%7D+K_3%28a_1+%5Cbar%7Bs%7D%5E3+h%3B+r_1%29+%5Coverline%7BK_3%28a_2+%5Cbar%7Bs%7D%5E3+h%3B+r_2%29%7D+e_%7B%5Br_1%2Cr_2%5D%7D%28+%5Cbar%7Bs%7D+nh+%29%7C&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0' alt='&#92;displaystyle |&#92;sum_{h &#92;in ({&#92;bf Z}/[r_1, r_2] {&#92;bf Z})^&#92;times} K_3(a_1 &#92;bar{s}^3 h; r_1) &#92;overline{K_3(a_2 &#92;bar{s}^3 h; r_2)} e_{[r_1,r_2]}( &#92;bar{s} nh )|' title='&#92;displaystyle |&#92;sum_{h &#92;in ({&#92;bf Z}/[r_1, r_2] {&#92;bf Z})^&#92;times} K_3(a_1 &#92;bar{s}^3 h; r_1) &#92;overline{K_3(a_2 &#92;bar{s}^3 h; r_2)} e_{[r_1,r_2]}( &#92;bar{s} nh )|' class='latex' /></p> <p align="center"><img src='http://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%5Cdisplaystyle++%5Clessapprox+%5Br_1%2Cr_2%5D%5E%7B1%2F2%7D+%28r_1%2Cr_2%2Ca_2-a_1%2Cn%29%5E%7B1%2F2%7D+&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0' alt='&#92;displaystyle &#92;lessapprox [r_1,r_2]^{1/2} (r_1,r_2,a_2-a_1,n)^{1/2} ' title='&#92;displaystyle &#92;lessapprox [r_1,r_2]^{1/2} (r_1,r_2,a_2-a_1,n)^{1/2} ' class='latex' /></p> <p> and <p align="center"><img src='http://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%5Cdisplaystyle++%7C%5Csum_%7Bh+%5Cin+%28%7B%5Cbf+Z%7D%2Fs+%7B%5Cbf+Z%7D%29%5E%5Ctimes%7D+K_3%28a_1+%5Coverline%7Br_1%7D%5E3+h%3B+s%29+%5Coverline%7BK_3%28a_2+%5Coverline%7Br_2%7D%5E3+h%3B+s%29%7D+e_%7Bs%7D%28+%5Coverline%7B%5Br_1%2Cr_2%5D%7D+nh+%29%7C+%5Clessapprox+d%5E%7B1%2F2%7D+s%5E%7B1%2F2%7D.&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0' alt='&#92;displaystyle |&#92;sum_{h &#92;in ({&#92;bf Z}/s {&#92;bf Z})^&#92;times} K_3(a_1 &#92;overline{r_1}^3 h; s) &#92;overline{K_3(a_2 &#92;overline{r_2}^3 h; s)} e_{s}( &#92;overline{[r_1,r_2]} nh )| &#92;lessapprox d^{1/2} s^{1/2}.' title='&#92;displaystyle |&#92;sum_{h &#92;in ({&#92;bf Z}/s {&#92;bf Z})^&#92;times} K_3(a_1 &#92;overline{r_1}^3 h; s) &#92;overline{K_3(a_2 &#92;overline{r_2}^3 h; s)} e_{s}( &#92;overline{[r_1,r_2]} nh )| &#92;lessapprox d^{1/2} s^{1/2}.' class='latex' /></p> <p> By further application of Lemma <a href="#crt">8</a>, together with the divisor bound, it suffices to show that <p align="center"><img src='http://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%5Cdisplaystyle++%7C%5Csum_%7Bh+%5Cin+%28%7B%5Cbf+Z%7D%2Fp+%7B%5Cbf+Z%7D%29%5E%5Ctimes%7D+K_3%28b_1+h%3B+d_1%29+%5Coverline%7BK_3%28b_2+h%3B+d_2%29%7D+e_%7Bp%7D%28+mh+%29%7C+%5Cll+p%5E%7B1%2F2%7D+%28b_1-b_2%2Cm%2Cd_1%2Cd_2%29%5E%7B1%2F2%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0' alt='&#92;displaystyle |&#92;sum_{h &#92;in ({&#92;bf Z}/p {&#92;bf Z})^&#92;times} K_3(b_1 h; d_1) &#92;overline{K_3(b_2 h; d_2)} e_{p}( mh )| &#92;ll p^{1/2} (b_1-b_2,m,d_1,d_2)^{1/2}' title='&#92;displaystyle |&#92;sum_{h &#92;in ({&#92;bf Z}/p {&#92;bf Z})^&#92;times} K_3(b_1 h; d_1) &#92;overline{K_3(b_2 h; d_2)} e_{p}( mh )| &#92;ll p^{1/2} (b_1-b_2,m,d_1,d_2)^{1/2}' class='latex' /></p> <p> whenever <img src='http://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7B%5Bd_1%2Cd_2%5D+%3D+p%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0' alt='{[d_1,d_2] = p}' title='{[d_1,d_2] = p}' class='latex' />, <img src='http://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7Bm+%5Cin+%7B%5Cbf+Z%7D%2Fp%7B%5Cbf+Z%7D%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0' alt='{m &#92;in {&#92;bf Z}/p{&#92;bf Z}}' title='{m &#92;in {&#92;bf Z}/p{&#92;bf Z}}' class='latex' />, and <img src='http://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7Bb_1%2Cb_2+%5Cin+%28%7B%5Cbf+Z%7D%2Fp%7B%5Cbf+Z%7D%29%5E%5Ctimes%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0' alt='{b_1,b_2 &#92;in ({&#92;bf Z}/p{&#92;bf Z})^&#92;times}' title='{b_1,b_2 &#92;in ({&#92;bf Z}/p{&#92;bf Z})^&#92;times}' class='latex' />.</p> <p> Suppose first that <img src='http://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7Bd_2%3D1%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0' alt='{d_2=1}' title='{d_2=1}' class='latex' />, so that <img src='http://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7Bd_1%3Dp%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0' alt='{d_1=p}' title='{d_1=p}' class='latex' />. Then <img src='http://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7B%5Coverline%7BK_3%28b_2+h%3B+d_2%29%7D+%3D+1%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0' alt='{&#92;overline{K_3(b_2 h; d_2)} = 1}' title='{&#92;overline{K_3(b_2 h; d_2)} = 1}' class='latex' />, and the left-hand side simplifies to </p> <p align="center"><img src='http://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%5Cdisplaystyle++%7C%5Csum_%7Bh+%5Cin+%28%7B%5Cbf+Z%7D%2Fp+%7B%5Cbf+Z%7D%29%5E%5Ctimes%7D+K_3%28b_1+h%3B+p%29+e_%7Bp%7D%28+mh+%29%7C&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0' alt='&#92;displaystyle |&#92;sum_{h &#92;in ({&#92;bf Z}/p {&#92;bf Z})^&#92;times} K_3(b_1 h; p) e_{p}( mh )|' title='&#92;displaystyle |&#92;sum_{h &#92;in ({&#92;bf Z}/p {&#92;bf Z})^&#92;times} K_3(b_1 h; p) e_{p}( mh )|' class='latex' /></p> <p> which can be expanded as <p align="center"><img src='http://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%5Cdisplaystyle++%5Cfrac%7B1%7D%7Bp%7D+%7C+%5Csum_%7Bx%2Cy%2Cz+%5Cin+%28%7B%7B%5Cbf+Z%7D%2Fp%7B%5Cbf+Z%7D%7D%29%5E%5Ctimes%7D+e_p%28+m+%5Coverline%7Bb_1%7D+xyz+%2B+x+%2B+y+%2B+z+%29+%7C.&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0' alt='&#92;displaystyle &#92;frac{1}{p} | &#92;sum_{x,y,z &#92;in ({{&#92;bf Z}/p{&#92;bf Z}})^&#92;times} e_p( m &#92;overline{b_1} xyz + x + y + z ) |.' title='&#92;displaystyle &#92;frac{1}{p} | &#92;sum_{x,y,z &#92;in ({{&#92;bf Z}/p{&#92;bf Z}})^&#92;times} e_p( m &#92;overline{b_1} xyz + x + y + z ) |.' class='latex' /></p> <p> Performing the Fourier summation in <img src='http://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7Bz%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0' alt='{z}' title='{z}' class='latex' />, this can be bounded by the sum of <p align="center"><img src='http://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%5Cdisplaystyle++%7C+%5Csum_%7Bx%2Cy+%5Cin+%28%7B%7B%5Cbf+Z%7D%2Fp%7B%5Cbf+Z%7D%7D%29%5E%5Ctimes%7D+e_p%28+x+%2B+y+%29+1_%7Bm+%5Coverline%7Bb_1%7D+xy+%3D+-1%7D%7C&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0' alt='&#92;displaystyle | &#92;sum_{x,y &#92;in ({{&#92;bf Z}/p{&#92;bf Z}})^&#92;times} e_p( x + y ) 1_{m &#92;overline{b_1} xy = -1}|' title='&#92;displaystyle | &#92;sum_{x,y &#92;in ({{&#92;bf Z}/p{&#92;bf Z}})^&#92;times} e_p( x + y ) 1_{m &#92;overline{b_1} xy = -1}|' class='latex' /></p> <p> and <p align="center"><img src='http://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%5Cdisplaystyle++%5Cfrac%7B1%7D%7Bp%7D+%7C+%5Csum_%7Bx%2Cy+%5Cin+%28%7B%7B%5Cbf+Z%7D%2Fp%7B%5Cbf+Z%7D%7D%29%5E%5Ctimes%7D+e_p%28+x+%2B+y+%29+%7C.&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0' alt='&#92;displaystyle &#92;frac{1}{p} | &#92;sum_{x,y &#92;in ({{&#92;bf Z}/p{&#92;bf Z}})^&#92;times} e_p( x + y ) |.' title='&#92;displaystyle &#92;frac{1}{p} | &#92;sum_{x,y &#92;in ({{&#92;bf Z}/p{&#92;bf Z}})^&#92;times} e_p( x + y ) |.' class='latex' /></p> <p> The first term either vanishes or is a Kloosterman sum, and is <img src='http://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7BO%28%5Csqrt%7Bp%7D%29%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0' alt='{O(&#92;sqrt{p})}' title='{O(&#92;sqrt{p})}' class='latex' /> in either case, while the second term can be calculated by Fourier series to be <img src='http://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7BO%281%29%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0' alt='{O(1)}' title='{O(1)}' class='latex' />, and the claim follows. Similarly if <img src='http://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7Bd_1%3D1%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0' alt='{d_1=1}' title='{d_1=1}' class='latex' />.</p> <p> Now suppose that <img src='http://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7Bd_1%3Dd_2%3Dp%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0' alt='{d_1=d_2=p}' title='{d_1=d_2=p}' class='latex' /> and <img src='http://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7Bb_1-b_2%3Dm%3D0%5C+%28p%29%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0' alt='{b_1-b_2=m=0&#92; (p)}' title='{b_1-b_2=m=0&#92; (p)}' class='latex' />. Then we use the <a href="http://www.ams.org/mathscinet-getitem?mr=340258">Deligne bound</a> <img src='http://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7B%7CK_3%28h%3B+p%29%7C+%5Cll+1%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0' alt='{|K_3(h; p)| &#92;ll 1}' title='{|K_3(h; p)| &#92;ll 1}' class='latex' /> to obtain the desired claim. The only remaining case is when <img src='http://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7Bd_1%3Dd_2%3Dp%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0' alt='{d_1=d_2=p}' title='{d_1=d_2=p}' class='latex' /> and <img src='http://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7Bb_1-b_2+%5Cneq+0%5C+%28p%29%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0' alt='{b_1-b_2 &#92;neq 0&#92; (p)}' title='{b_1-b_2 &#92;neq 0&#92; (p)}' class='latex' /> or <img src='http://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7Bm+%5Cneq+0%5C+%28p%29%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0' alt='{m &#92;neq 0&#92; (p)}' title='{m &#92;neq 0&#92; (p)}' class='latex' />, so our task is to show that </p> <p align="center"><img src='http://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%5Cdisplaystyle++%7C%5Csum_%7Bh+%5Cin+%28%7B%5Cbf+Z%7D%2Fp+%7B%5Cbf+Z%7D%29%5E%5Ctimes%7D+K_3%28b_1+h%3B+p%29+%5Coverline%7BK_3%28b_2+h%3B+p%29%7D+e_%7Bp%7D%28+mh+%29%7C+%5Cll+p%5E%7B1%2F2%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0' alt='&#92;displaystyle |&#92;sum_{h &#92;in ({&#92;bf Z}/p {&#92;bf Z})^&#92;times} K_3(b_1 h; p) &#92;overline{K_3(b_2 h; p)} e_{p}( mh )| &#92;ll p^{1/2}' title='&#92;displaystyle |&#92;sum_{h &#92;in ({&#92;bf Z}/p {&#92;bf Z})^&#92;times} K_3(b_1 h; p) &#92;overline{K_3(b_2 h; p)} e_{p}( mh )| &#92;ll p^{1/2}' class='latex' /></p> <p> in this case. A proof of this claim (which uses the full strength of Deligne&#8217;s work) can be found in <a href="http://www.ams.org/mathscinet-getitem?mr=1652005">this paper of Michel</a> (see also Proposition 6 of <a href="http://www.math.ethz.ch/~kowalski/friedlander-iwaniec-sum.pdf">this recent expository note of Fouvry, Kowalski, and Michel</a>). <img src='http://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%5CBox&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0' alt='&#92;Box' title='&#92;Box' class='latex' /></p> <p> From this and completion and sums we have </p> <blockquote><p><b>Lemma 13 (Correlation of hyper-Kloosterman sums, II)</b> <a name="corr-2"></a> Let <img src='http://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7Bs%2Cr_1%2Cr_2%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0' alt='{s,r_1,r_2}' title='{s,r_1,r_2}' class='latex' /> be square-free numbers of polynomial size with <img src='http://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7B%28s%2Cr_1%29%3D%28s%2Cr_2%29%3D1%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0' alt='{(s,r_1)=(s,r_2)=1}' title='{(s,r_1)=(s,r_2)=1}' class='latex' />. Let <img src='http://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7Ba_1+%5Cin+%28%7B%5Cbf+Z%7D%2Fr_1+s%29%5E%5Ctimes%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0' alt='{a_1 &#92;in ({&#92;bf Z}/r_1 s)^&#92;times}' title='{a_1 &#92;in ({&#92;bf Z}/r_1 s)^&#92;times}' class='latex' />, <img src='http://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7Ba_2+%5Cin+%28%7B%5Cbf+Z%7D%2Fr_2s%29%5E%5Ctimes%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0' alt='{a_2 &#92;in ({&#92;bf Z}/r_2s)^&#92;times}' title='{a_2 &#92;in ({&#92;bf Z}/r_2s)^&#92;times}' class='latex' />. Let <img src='http://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7B%5CPsi%3A+%7B%5Cbf+Z%7D+%5Crightarrow+%7B%5Cbf+C%7D%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0' alt='{&#92;Psi: {&#92;bf Z} &#92;rightarrow {&#92;bf C}}' title='{&#92;Psi: {&#92;bf Z} &#92;rightarrow {&#92;bf C}}' class='latex' /> be a smooth function adapted to the interval <img src='http://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7B%5B-2H%2C2H%5D%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0' alt='{[-2H,2H]}' title='{[-2H,2H]}' class='latex' /> which equals one on <img src='http://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7B%5B-H%2CH%5D%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0' alt='{[-H,H]}' title='{[-H,H]}' class='latex' />. Then <p align="center"><img src='http://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%5Cdisplaystyle++%7C%5Csum_h+%5CPsi%28h%29+K_3%28a_1+h%3B+r_1+s%29+%5Coverline%7BK_3%28a_2+h%3B+r_2+s%29%7D+e_%7B%5Br_1%2Cr_2%5D+s%7D%28+nh+%29%7C+&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0' alt='&#92;displaystyle |&#92;sum_h &#92;Psi(h) K_3(a_1 h; r_1 s) &#92;overline{K_3(a_2 h; r_2 s)} e_{[r_1,r_2] s}( nh )| ' title='&#92;displaystyle |&#92;sum_h &#92;Psi(h) K_3(a_1 h; r_1 s) &#92;overline{K_3(a_2 h; r_2 s)} e_{[r_1,r_2] s}( nh )| ' class='latex' /></p> <p align="center"><img src='http://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%5Cdisplaystyle++%5Clessapprox+%28%5Cfrac%7BH%7D%7B%5Br_1%2Cr_2%5Ds%7D+%2B+1%29+d%5E%7B1%2F2%7D+s%5E%7B1%2F2%7D+%5Br_1%2Cr_2%5D%5E%7B1%2F2%7D+%28a_2-a_1%2Cr_1%2Cr_2%29%5E%7B1%2F2%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0' alt='&#92;displaystyle &#92;lessapprox (&#92;frac{H}{[r_1,r_2]s} + 1) d^{1/2} s^{1/2} [r_1,r_2]^{1/2} (a_2-a_1,r_1,r_2)^{1/2}' title='&#92;displaystyle &#92;lessapprox (&#92;frac{H}{[r_1,r_2]s} + 1) d^{1/2} s^{1/2} [r_1,r_2]^{1/2} (a_2-a_1,r_1,r_2)^{1/2}' class='latex' /></p> <p> where <img src='http://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7Bd+%3A%3D+%28a_2+r_1%5E3+-+a_1+r_2%5E3%2C+s%29%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0' alt='{d := (a_2 r_1^3 - a_1 r_2^3, s)}' title='{d := (a_2 r_1^3 - a_1 r_2^3, s)}' class='latex' />, and the sum runs over those <img src='http://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7Bh%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0' alt='{h}' title='{h}' class='latex' /> coprime to <img src='http://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7B%5Br_1%2Cr_2%5Ds%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0' alt='{[r_1,r_2]s}' title='{[r_1,r_2]s}' class='latex' />. </p></blockquote> </p> <p align="center"><b> &mdash; 2. Type I estimate &mdash; </b></p> <p> We begin the proof of Theorem <a href="#t1-precise">4</a>, closely following the arguments from Section 5 of <a href="http://terrytao.wordpress.com/2013/06/12/estimation-of-the-type-i-and-type-ii-sums/">this previous post</a>. Let <img src='http://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7BI%2C+a%2C+N%2C+M%2C+%5Calpha%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0' alt='{I, a, N, M, &#92;alpha}' title='{I, a, N, M, &#92;alpha}' class='latex' /> be as in the theorem. We can restrict <img src='http://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7Bq%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0' alt='{q}' title='{q}' class='latex' /> to the range </p> <p align="center"><img src='http://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%5Cdisplaystyle++q+%5Cgtrapprox+x%5E%7B1%2F2%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0' alt='&#92;displaystyle q &#92;gtrapprox x^{1/2}' title='&#92;displaystyle q &#92;gtrapprox x^{1/2}' class='latex' /></p> <p> for some sufficiently slowly decaying <img src='http://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7Bo%281%29%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0' alt='{o(1)}' title='{o(1)}' class='latex' />, since otherwise we may use the Bombieri-Vinogradov theorem (Theorem 4 from <a href="http://terrytao.wordpress.com/2013/06/12/estimation-of-the-type-i-and-type-ii-sums/">this previous post</a>). Thus, by dyadic decomposition, we need to show that <a name="solid"> <p align="center"><img src='http://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%5Cdisplaystyle++%5Csum_%7Bd+%5Cin+%7B%5Cmathcal+S%7D_I+%5Ccap+%7B%5Cmathcal+D%7D_%7Bx%5E%5Cdelta%7D%5E2%3A+D+%5Cleq+d+%3C+2D%7D+%7C%5CDelta%28%5Calpha+%5Cast+%5Cbeta%3B+a%5C+%28d%29%29%7C+%5Cll+NM+%5Clog%5E%7B-A%7D+x.+%5C+%5C+%5C+%5C+%5C+%2816%29&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0' alt='&#92;displaystyle &#92;sum_{d &#92;in {&#92;mathcal S}_I &#92;cap {&#92;mathcal D}_{x^&#92;delta}^2: D &#92;leq d &lt; 2D} |&#92;Delta(&#92;alpha &#92;ast &#92;beta; a&#92; (d))| &#92;ll NM &#92;log^{-A} x. &#92; &#92; &#92; &#92; &#92; (16)' title='&#92;displaystyle &#92;sum_{d &#92;in {&#92;mathcal S}_I &#92;cap {&#92;mathcal D}_{x^&#92;delta}^2: D &#92;leq d &lt; 2D} |&#92;Delta(&#92;alpha &#92;ast &#92;beta; a&#92; (d))| &#92;ll NM &#92;log^{-A} x. &#92; &#92; &#92; &#92; &#92; (16)' class='latex' /></p> <p></a> for any fixed <img src='http://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7BA%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0' alt='{A}' title='{A}' class='latex' /> and for any <img src='http://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7BD%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0' alt='{D}' title='{D}' class='latex' /> in the range <p align="center"><img src='http://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%5Cdisplaystyle++x%5E%7B1%2F2%7D+%5Clessapprox+D+%5Clessapprox+x%5E%7B1%2F2%2B2%5Cvarpi%7D.&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0' alt='&#92;displaystyle x^{1/2} &#92;lessapprox D &#92;lessapprox x^{1/2+2&#92;varpi}.' title='&#92;displaystyle x^{1/2} &#92;lessapprox D &#92;lessapprox x^{1/2+2&#92;varpi}.' class='latex' /></p> <p> Let <a name="mustard"> <p align="center"><img src='http://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%5Cdisplaystyle++%5Cepsilon+%3E+0+%5C+%5C+%5C+%5C+%5C+%2817%29&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0' alt='&#92;displaystyle &#92;epsilon &gt; 0 &#92; &#92; &#92; &#92; &#92; (17)' title='&#92;displaystyle &#92;epsilon &gt; 0 &#92; &#92; &#92; &#92; &#92; (17)' class='latex' /></p> <p></a> be a sufficiently small fixed exponent. </p> <p> By Lemma 11 of <a href="http://terrytao.wordpress.com/2013/06/12/estimation-of-the-type-i-and-type-ii-sums/">this previous post</a>, we know that for all <img src='http://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7Bd%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0' alt='{d}' title='{d}' class='latex' /> in <img src='http://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7B%5BD%2C2D%5D%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0' alt='{[D,2D]}' title='{[D,2D]}' class='latex' /> outside of a small number of exceptions, we have <a name="pdq"> <p align="center"><img src='http://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%5Cdisplaystyle++%5Cprod_%7Bp%7Cd%3A+p+%5Cleq+D_0%7D+p+%5Clessapprox+1+%5C+%5C+%5C+%5C+%5C+%2818%29&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0' alt='&#92;displaystyle &#92;prod_{p|d: p &#92;leq D_0} p &#92;lessapprox 1 &#92; &#92; &#92; &#92; &#92; (18)' title='&#92;displaystyle &#92;prod_{p|d: p &#92;leq D_0} p &#92;lessapprox 1 &#92; &#92; &#92; &#92; &#92; (18)' class='latex' /></p> <p></a> where <a name="d0"> <p align="center"><img src='http://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%5Cdisplaystyle++D_0+%3A%3D+%5Cexp%28%5Clog%5E%7B1%2F3%7D+x%29.+%5C+%5C+%5C+%5C+%5C+%2819%29&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0' alt='&#92;displaystyle D_0 := &#92;exp(&#92;log^{1/3} x). &#92; &#92; &#92; &#92; &#92; (19)' title='&#92;displaystyle D_0 := &#92;exp(&#92;log^{1/3} x). &#92; &#92; &#92; &#92; &#92; (19)' class='latex' /></p> <p></a> Specifically, the number of exceptions in the interval <img src='http://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7B%5BD%2C2D%5D%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0' alt='{[D,2D]}' title='{[D,2D]}' class='latex' /> is <img src='http://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7BO%28D+%5Clog%5E%7B-A%7D+x%29%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0' alt='{O(D &#92;log^{-A} x)}' title='{O(D &#92;log^{-A} x)}' class='latex' /> for any fixed <img src='http://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7BA%3E0%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0' alt='{A&gt;0}' title='{A&gt;0}' class='latex' />. The contribution of the exceptional <img src='http://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7Bd%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0' alt='{d}' title='{d}' class='latex' /> can be shown to be acceptable by Cauchy-Schwarz and trivial estimates (see Section 5 of <a href="http://terrytao.wordpress.com/2013/06/12/estimation-of-the-type-i-and-type-ii-sums/">this previous post</a>), so we restrict attention to those <img src='http://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7Bd%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0' alt='{d}' title='{d}' class='latex' /> for which <a href="#pdq">(18)</a> holds. In particular, as <img src='http://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7Bd%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0' alt='{d}' title='{d}' class='latex' /> is restricted to be doubly <img src='http://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7Bx%5E%5Cdelta%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0' alt='{x^&#92;delta}' title='{x^&#92;delta}' class='latex' />-densely divisible we may factor </p> <p align="center"><img src='http://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%5Cdisplaystyle++d%3Dqr&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0' alt='&#92;displaystyle d=qr' title='&#92;displaystyle d=qr' class='latex' /></p> <p> with <img src='http://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7Bq%2Cr%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0' alt='{q,r}' title='{q,r}' class='latex' /> coprime and square-free, with <img src='http://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7Bq+%5Cin+%7B%5Cmathcal+S%7D_%7BI%27%7D%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0' alt='{q &#92;in {&#92;mathcal S}_{I&#039;}}' title='{q &#92;in {&#92;mathcal S}_{I&#039;}}' class='latex' /> <img src='http://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7Bx%5E%5Cdelta%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0' alt='{x^&#92;delta}' title='{x^&#92;delta}' class='latex' />-densely divisible with <img src='http://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7BI%27+%3A%3D+%5BD_0%2C%5Cinfty%29+%5Ccap+I%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0' alt='{I&#039; := [D_0,&#92;infty) &#92;cap I}' title='{I&#039; := [D_0,&#92;infty) &#92;cap I}' class='latex' />, and <p align="center"><img src='http://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%5Cdisplaystyle++x%5E%7B-%5Cepsilon-%5Cdelta%7D+N+%5Clessapprox+r+%5Clessapprox+x%5E%7B-%5Cepsilon%7D+N&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0' alt='&#92;displaystyle x^{-&#92;epsilon-&#92;delta} N &#92;lessapprox r &#92;lessapprox x^{-&#92;epsilon} N' title='&#92;displaystyle x^{-&#92;epsilon-&#92;delta} N &#92;lessapprox r &#92;lessapprox x^{-&#92;epsilon} N' class='latex' /></p> <p> and <p align="center"><img src='http://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%5Cdisplaystyle++x%5E%7B1%2F2%7D+%5Clessapprox+qr+%5Clessapprox+x%5E%7B1%2F2%2B2%5Cvarpi%7D.&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0' alt='&#92;displaystyle x^{1/2} &#92;lessapprox qr &#92;lessapprox x^{1/2+2&#92;varpi}.' title='&#92;displaystyle x^{1/2} &#92;lessapprox qr &#92;lessapprox x^{1/2+2&#92;varpi}.' class='latex' /></p> <p> Here we use the easily verified fact that <img src='http://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7BN+%5Cgtrapprox+x%5E%5Cepsilon%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0' alt='{N &#92;gtrapprox x^&#92;epsilon}' title='{N &#92;gtrapprox x^&#92;epsilon}' class='latex' />. Since <img src='http://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7Bd%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0' alt='{d}' title='{d}' class='latex' /> is <img src='http://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7Bx%5E%5Cdelta%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0' alt='{x^&#92;delta}' title='{x^&#92;delta}' class='latex' />-densely divisible, we also have <img src='http://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7Bqr+%5Cin+%7B%5Cmathcal+D%7D_%7Bx%5E%5Cdelta%7D%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0' alt='{qr &#92;in {&#92;mathcal D}_{x^&#92;delta}}' title='{qr &#92;in {&#92;mathcal D}_{x^&#92;delta}}' class='latex' />.</p> <p> By dyadic decomposition, it thus sufices to show that </p> <p align="center"><img src='http://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%5Cdisplaystyle++%5Csum_%7Bq+%5Cin+%7B%5Cmathcal+S%7D_%7BI%27%7D+%5Ccap+%7B%5Cmathcal+D%7D_%7Bx%5E%5Cdelta%7D%3A+q+%5Csim+Q%7D+%5Csum_%7Br+%5Cin+%7B%5Cmathcal+S%7D_I%3A+r+%5Csim+R%3B+qr+%5Cin+%7B%5Cmathcal+S%7D_I+%5Ccap+%7B%5Cmathcal+D%7D_%7Bx%5E%5Cdelta%7D%7D+%7C%5CDelta%28%5Calpha+%5Cast+%5Cbeta%3B+a%5C+%28qr%29%29%7C+%5Cll+NM+%5Clog%5E%7B-A%7D+x.+&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0' alt='&#92;displaystyle &#92;sum_{q &#92;in {&#92;mathcal S}_{I&#039;} &#92;cap {&#92;mathcal D}_{x^&#92;delta}: q &#92;sim Q} &#92;sum_{r &#92;in {&#92;mathcal S}_I: r &#92;sim R; qr &#92;in {&#92;mathcal S}_I &#92;cap {&#92;mathcal D}_{x^&#92;delta}} |&#92;Delta(&#92;alpha &#92;ast &#92;beta; a&#92; (qr))| &#92;ll NM &#92;log^{-A} x. ' title='&#92;displaystyle &#92;sum_{q &#92;in {&#92;mathcal S}_{I&#039;} &#92;cap {&#92;mathcal D}_{x^&#92;delta}: q &#92;sim Q} &#92;sum_{r &#92;in {&#92;mathcal S}_I: r &#92;sim R; qr &#92;in {&#92;mathcal S}_I &#92;cap {&#92;mathcal D}_{x^&#92;delta}} |&#92;Delta(&#92;alpha &#92;ast &#92;beta; a&#92; (qr))| &#92;ll NM &#92;log^{-A} x. ' class='latex' /></p> <p> for any fixed <img src='http://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7BA%3E0%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0' alt='{A&gt;0}' title='{A&gt;0}' class='latex' />, where <img src='http://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7BQ%2C+R+%5Cgeq+1%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0' alt='{Q, R &#92;geq 1}' title='{Q, R &#92;geq 1}' class='latex' /> obey the size conditions <a name="crop"> <p align="center"><img src='http://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%5Cdisplaystyle++x%5E%7B-%5Cepsilon-%5Cdelta%7D+N+%5Clessapprox+R+%5Clessapprox+x%5E%7B-%5Cepsilon%7D+N+%5C+%5C+%5C+%5C+%5C+%2820%29&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0' alt='&#92;displaystyle x^{-&#92;epsilon-&#92;delta} N &#92;lessapprox R &#92;lessapprox x^{-&#92;epsilon} N &#92; &#92; &#92; &#92; &#92; (20)' title='&#92;displaystyle x^{-&#92;epsilon-&#92;delta} N &#92;lessapprox R &#92;lessapprox x^{-&#92;epsilon} N &#92; &#92; &#92; &#92; &#92; (20)' class='latex' /></p> <p></a> and <a name="creep"> <p align="center"><img src='http://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%5Cdisplaystyle++x%5E%7B1%2F2%7D+%5Clessapprox+QR+%5Clessapprox+x%5E%7B1%2F2+%2B+2%5Cvarpi%7D.+%5C+%5C+%5C+%5C+%5C+%2821%29&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0' alt='&#92;displaystyle x^{1/2} &#92;lessapprox QR &#92;lessapprox x^{1/2 + 2&#92;varpi}. &#92; &#92; &#92; &#92; &#92; (21)' title='&#92;displaystyle x^{1/2} &#92;lessapprox QR &#92;lessapprox x^{1/2 + 2&#92;varpi}. &#92; &#92; &#92; &#92; &#92; (21)' class='latex' /></p> <p></a></p> <p> Fix <img src='http://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7BQ%2CR%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0' alt='{Q,R}' title='{Q,R}' class='latex' />. We abbreviate <img src='http://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7B%5Csum_%7Bq+%5Cin+%7B%5Cmathcal+S%7D_%7BI%27%7D+%5Ccap+%7B%5Cmathcal+D%7D_%7Bx%5E%5Cdelta%7D%3A+q+%5Csim+Q%7D%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0' alt='{&#92;sum_{q &#92;in {&#92;mathcal S}_{I&#039;} &#92;cap {&#92;mathcal D}_{x^&#92;delta}: q &#92;sim Q}}' title='{&#92;sum_{q &#92;in {&#92;mathcal S}_{I&#039;} &#92;cap {&#92;mathcal D}_{x^&#92;delta}: q &#92;sim Q}}' class='latex' /> and <img src='http://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7B%5Csum_%7Br+%5Cin+%7B%5Cmathcal+S%7D_I%3A+r+%5Csim+R%7D%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0' alt='{&#92;sum_{r &#92;in {&#92;mathcal S}_I: r &#92;sim R}}' title='{&#92;sum_{r &#92;in {&#92;mathcal S}_I: r &#92;sim R}}' class='latex' /> by <img src='http://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7B%5Csum_q%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0' alt='{&#92;sum_q}' title='{&#92;sum_q}' class='latex' /> and <img src='http://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7B%5Csum_r%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0' alt='{&#92;sum_r}' title='{&#92;sum_r}' class='latex' /> respectively, thus our task is to show that </p> <p align="center"><img src='http://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%5Cdisplaystyle++%5Csum_q+%5Csum_%7Br%3A+qr+%5Cin+%7B%5Cmathcal+S%7D_I+%5Ccap+%7B%5Cmathcal+D%7D_%7Bx%5E%5Cdelta%7D%7D+%7C%5CDelta%28%5Calpha+%5Cast+%5Cbeta%3B+a%5C+%28qr%29%29%7C+%5Cll+NM+%5Clog%5E%7B-A%7D+x.&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0' alt='&#92;displaystyle &#92;sum_q &#92;sum_{r: qr &#92;in {&#92;mathcal S}_I &#92;cap {&#92;mathcal D}_{x^&#92;delta}} |&#92;Delta(&#92;alpha &#92;ast &#92;beta; a&#92; (qr))| &#92;ll NM &#92;log^{-A} x.' title='&#92;displaystyle &#92;sum_q &#92;sum_{r: qr &#92;in {&#92;mathcal S}_I &#92;cap {&#92;mathcal D}_{x^&#92;delta}} |&#92;Delta(&#92;alpha &#92;ast &#92;beta; a&#92; (qr))| &#92;ll NM &#92;log^{-A} x.' class='latex' /></p> <p> We now split the discrepancy </p> <p align="center"><img src='http://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%5Cdisplaystyle++%5CDelta%28%5Calpha+%5Cast+%5Cbeta%3B+a%5C+%28qr%29%29+%3D+%5Csum_%7Bn+%3D+a%5C+%28qr%29%7D+%5Calpha+%5Cast+%5Cbeta%28n%29+-+%5Cfrac%7B1%7D%7B%5Cphi%28qr%29%7D+%5Csum_%7Bn%3A+%28n%2Cqr%29%3D1%7D+%5Calpha+%5Cast+%5Cbeta%28n%29&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0' alt='&#92;displaystyle &#92;Delta(&#92;alpha &#92;ast &#92;beta; a&#92; (qr)) = &#92;sum_{n = a&#92; (qr)} &#92;alpha &#92;ast &#92;beta(n) - &#92;frac{1}{&#92;phi(qr)} &#92;sum_{n: (n,qr)=1} &#92;alpha &#92;ast &#92;beta(n)' title='&#92;displaystyle &#92;Delta(&#92;alpha &#92;ast &#92;beta; a&#92; (qr)) = &#92;sum_{n = a&#92; (qr)} &#92;alpha &#92;ast &#92;beta(n) - &#92;frac{1}{&#92;phi(qr)} &#92;sum_{n: (n,qr)=1} &#92;alpha &#92;ast &#92;beta(n)' class='latex' /></p> <p> as the sum of the subdiscrepancies <p align="center"><img src='http://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%5Cdisplaystyle++%5Csum_%7Bn%3A+n+%3D+a%5C+%28qr%29%7D+%5Calpha+%5Cast+%5Cbeta%28n%29+-+%5Cfrac%7B1%7D%7B%5Cphi%28q%29%7D+%5Csum_%7Bn%3A+%28n%2Cq%29%3D1%3B+n+%3D+a%5C+%28r%29%7D+%5Calpha+%5Cast+%5Cbeta%28n%29&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0' alt='&#92;displaystyle &#92;sum_{n: n = a&#92; (qr)} &#92;alpha &#92;ast &#92;beta(n) - &#92;frac{1}{&#92;phi(q)} &#92;sum_{n: (n,q)=1; n = a&#92; (r)} &#92;alpha &#92;ast &#92;beta(n)' title='&#92;displaystyle &#92;sum_{n: n = a&#92; (qr)} &#92;alpha &#92;ast &#92;beta(n) - &#92;frac{1}{&#92;phi(q)} &#92;sum_{n: (n,q)=1; n = a&#92; (r)} &#92;alpha &#92;ast &#92;beta(n)' class='latex' /></p> <p> and <p align="center"><img src='http://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%5Cdisplaystyle++%5Cfrac%7B1%7D%7B%5Cphi%28q%29%7D+%5Csum_%7Bn%3A+%28n%2Cq%29%3D1%3B+n+%3D+a%5C+%28r%29%7D+%5Calpha+%5Cast+%5Cbeta%28n%29+-+%5Cfrac%7B1%7D%7B%5Cphi%28qr%29%7D+%5Csum_%7Bn%3A+%28n%2Cqr%29%3D1%7D+%5Calpha+%5Cast+%5Cbeta%28n%29.&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0' alt='&#92;displaystyle &#92;frac{1}{&#92;phi(q)} &#92;sum_{n: (n,q)=1; n = a&#92; (r)} &#92;alpha &#92;ast &#92;beta(n) - &#92;frac{1}{&#92;phi(qr)} &#92;sum_{n: (n,qr)=1} &#92;alpha &#92;ast &#92;beta(n).' title='&#92;displaystyle &#92;frac{1}{&#92;phi(q)} &#92;sum_{n: (n,q)=1; n = a&#92; (r)} &#92;alpha &#92;ast &#92;beta(n) - &#92;frac{1}{&#92;phi(qr)} &#92;sum_{n: (n,qr)=1} &#92;alpha &#92;ast &#92;beta(n).' class='latex' /></p> <p> In Section 5 of <a href="http://terrytao.wordpress.com/2013/06/12/estimation-of-the-type-i-and-type-ii-sums/">this previous post</a>, it was established (using the Bombieri-Vinogradov theorem) that </p> <p align="center"><img src='http://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%5Cdisplaystyle++%5Csum_%7Bq%7D+%5Csum_%7Br%3B+%28q%2Cr%29%3D1%7D+%7C%5Cfrac%7B1%7D%7B%5Cphi%28q%29%7D+%5Csum_%7Bn%3A+%28n%2Cq%29%3D1%3B+n+%3D+a%5C+%28r%29%7D+%5Calpha+%5Cast+%5Cbeta%28n%29+-+%5Cfrac%7B1%7D%7B%5Cphi%28qr%29%7D+%5Csum_%7Bn%3A+%28n%2Cqr%29%3D1%7D+%5Calpha+%5Cast+%5Cbeta%28n%29%7C+%5Cll+&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0' alt='&#92;displaystyle &#92;sum_{q} &#92;sum_{r; (q,r)=1} |&#92;frac{1}{&#92;phi(q)} &#92;sum_{n: (n,q)=1; n = a&#92; (r)} &#92;alpha &#92;ast &#92;beta(n) - &#92;frac{1}{&#92;phi(qr)} &#92;sum_{n: (n,qr)=1} &#92;alpha &#92;ast &#92;beta(n)| &#92;ll ' title='&#92;displaystyle &#92;sum_{q} &#92;sum_{r; (q,r)=1} |&#92;frac{1}{&#92;phi(q)} &#92;sum_{n: (n,q)=1; n = a&#92; (r)} &#92;alpha &#92;ast &#92;beta(n) - &#92;frac{1}{&#92;phi(qr)} &#92;sum_{n: (n,qr)=1} &#92;alpha &#92;ast &#92;beta(n)| &#92;ll ' class='latex' /></p> <p align="center"><img src='http://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%5Cdisplaystyle++NM+%5Clog%5E%7B-A%7D+x&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0' alt='&#92;displaystyle NM &#92;log^{-A} x' title='&#92;displaystyle NM &#92;log^{-A} x' class='latex' /></p> <p> so it suffices to show that <a name="q1"> <p align="center"><img src='http://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%5Cdisplaystyle++%5Csum_%7Bq%7D+%5Csum_%7Br%3B+qr+%5Cin+%7B%5Cmathcal+S%7D_I+%5Ccap+%7B%5Cmathcal+D%7D_%7Bx%5E%5Cdelta%7D%7D+%7C%5Csum_%7Bn%3A+n+%3D+a%5C+%28qr%29%7D+%5Calpha+%5Cast+%5Cbeta%28n%29+-+%5Cfrac%7B1%7D%7B%5Cphi%28q%29%7D+%5Csum_%7Bn%3A+%28n%2Cq%29%3D1%3B+n+%3D+a%5C+%28r%29%7D+%5Calpha+%5Cast+%5Cbeta%28n%29%7C+%5C+%5C+%5C+%5C+%5C+%2822%29&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0' alt='&#92;displaystyle &#92;sum_{q} &#92;sum_{r; qr &#92;in {&#92;mathcal S}_I &#92;cap {&#92;mathcal D}_{x^&#92;delta}} |&#92;sum_{n: n = a&#92; (qr)} &#92;alpha &#92;ast &#92;beta(n) - &#92;frac{1}{&#92;phi(q)} &#92;sum_{n: (n,q)=1; n = a&#92; (r)} &#92;alpha &#92;ast &#92;beta(n)| &#92; &#92; &#92; &#92; &#92; (22)' title='&#92;displaystyle &#92;sum_{q} &#92;sum_{r; qr &#92;in {&#92;mathcal S}_I &#92;cap {&#92;mathcal D}_{x^&#92;delta}} |&#92;sum_{n: n = a&#92; (qr)} &#92;alpha &#92;ast &#92;beta(n) - &#92;frac{1}{&#92;phi(q)} &#92;sum_{n: (n,q)=1; n = a&#92; (r)} &#92;alpha &#92;ast &#92;beta(n)| &#92; &#92; &#92; &#92; &#92; (22)' class='latex' /></p> <p></a> <p align="center"><img src='http://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%5Cdisplaystyle++%5Cll+NM+%5Clog%5E%7B-A%7D+x.+&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0' alt='&#92;displaystyle &#92;ll NM &#92;log^{-A} x. ' title='&#92;displaystyle &#92;ll NM &#92;log^{-A} x. ' class='latex' /></p> <p> As in the previous notes, we will not take advantage of the <img src='http://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7Br%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0' alt='{r}' title='{r}' class='latex' /> summation, and use crude estimates to reduce to showing that <a name="straw"> <p align="center"><img src='http://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%5Cdisplaystyle++%5Csum_%7Bq%3A+qr+%5Cin+%7B%5Cmathcal+S%7D_I+%5Ccap+%7B%5Cmathcal+D%7D_%7Bx%5E%5Cdelta%7D%7D+%7C%5Csum_%7Bn%3A+n+%3D+a%5C+%28qr%29%7D+%5Calpha+%5Cast+%5Cbeta%28n%29+-+%5Cfrac%7B1%7D%7B%5Cphi%28q%29%7D+%5Csum_%7Bn%3A+%28n%2Cq%29%3D1%3B+n+%3D+a%5C+%28r%29%7D+%5Calpha+%5Cast+%5Cbeta%28n%29%7C+%5C+%5C+%5C+%5C+%5C+%2823%29&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0' alt='&#92;displaystyle &#92;sum_{q: qr &#92;in {&#92;mathcal S}_I &#92;cap {&#92;mathcal D}_{x^&#92;delta}} |&#92;sum_{n: n = a&#92; (qr)} &#92;alpha &#92;ast &#92;beta(n) - &#92;frac{1}{&#92;phi(q)} &#92;sum_{n: (n,q)=1; n = a&#92; (r)} &#92;alpha &#92;ast &#92;beta(n)| &#92; &#92; &#92; &#92; &#92; (23)' title='&#92;displaystyle &#92;sum_{q: qr &#92;in {&#92;mathcal S}_I &#92;cap {&#92;mathcal D}_{x^&#92;delta}} |&#92;sum_{n: n = a&#92; (qr)} &#92;alpha &#92;ast &#92;beta(n) - &#92;frac{1}{&#92;phi(q)} &#92;sum_{n: (n,q)=1; n = a&#92; (r)} &#92;alpha &#92;ast &#92;beta(n)| &#92; &#92; &#92; &#92; &#92; (23)' class='latex' /></p> <p></a> <p align="center"><img src='http://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%5Cdisplaystyle+%5Cll+NM+R%5E%7B-1%7D+%5Ctau%28r%29%5E%7BO%281%29%7D+%5Clog%5E%7B-A%7D+x&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0' alt='&#92;displaystyle &#92;ll NM R^{-1} &#92;tau(r)^{O(1)} &#92;log^{-A} x' title='&#92;displaystyle &#92;ll NM R^{-1} &#92;tau(r)^{O(1)} &#92;log^{-A} x' class='latex' /></p> <p> for each individual <img src='http://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7Br+%5Cin+%7B%5Cmathcal+S%7D_I%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0' alt='{r &#92;in {&#92;mathcal S}_I}' title='{r &#92;in {&#92;mathcal S}_I}' class='latex' /> with <img src='http://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7Br+%5Csim+R%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0' alt='{r &#92;sim R}' title='{r &#92;sim R}' class='latex' />, which we now select. It will suffice to prove the slightly stronger statement</p> <p> <a name="straw-2"> <p align="center"><img src='http://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%5Cdisplaystyle++%5Csum_%7Bq%3A+qr+%5Cin+%7B%5Cmathcal+S%7D_I+%5Ccap+%7B%5Cmathcal+D%7D_%7Bx%5E%5Cdelta%7D%7D+%7C%5Csum_%7Bn%3A+n+%3D+a%5C+%28r%29%3B+n%3D+b%5C+%28q%29%7D+%5Calpha+%5Cast+%5Cbeta%28n%29+-+%5Csum_%7Bn%3A+%28n%2Cq%29%3D1%3B+n+%3D+a%5C+%28r%29%3B+n+%3D+b%27%5C+%28q%29%7D+%5Calpha+%5Cast+%5Cbeta%28n%29%7C+%5C+%5C+%5C+%5C+%5C+%2824%29&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0' alt='&#92;displaystyle &#92;sum_{q: qr &#92;in {&#92;mathcal S}_I &#92;cap {&#92;mathcal D}_{x^&#92;delta}} |&#92;sum_{n: n = a&#92; (r); n= b&#92; (q)} &#92;alpha &#92;ast &#92;beta(n) - &#92;sum_{n: (n,q)=1; n = a&#92; (r); n = b&#039;&#92; (q)} &#92;alpha &#92;ast &#92;beta(n)| &#92; &#92; &#92; &#92; &#92; (24)' title='&#92;displaystyle &#92;sum_{q: qr &#92;in {&#92;mathcal S}_I &#92;cap {&#92;mathcal D}_{x^&#92;delta}} |&#92;sum_{n: n = a&#92; (r); n= b&#92; (q)} &#92;alpha &#92;ast &#92;beta(n) - &#92;sum_{n: (n,q)=1; n = a&#92; (r); n = b&#039;&#92; (q)} &#92;alpha &#92;ast &#92;beta(n)| &#92; &#92; &#92; &#92; &#92; (24)' class='latex' /></p> <p></a> </p> <p align="center"><img src='http://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%5Cdisplaystyle+%5Cll+NM+R%5E%7B-1%7D+%5Ctau%28r%29%5E%7BO%281%29%7D+%5Clog%5E%7B-A%7D+x&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0' alt='&#92;displaystyle &#92;ll NM R^{-1} &#92;tau(r)^{O(1)} &#92;log^{-A} x' title='&#92;displaystyle &#92;ll NM R^{-1} &#92;tau(r)^{O(1)} &#92;log^{-A} x' class='latex' /></p> <p> for all <img src='http://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7Ba%2Cb%2Cb%27%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0' alt='{a,b,b&#039;}' title='{a,b,b&#039;}' class='latex' /> coprime to <img src='http://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7BP_I%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0' alt='{P_I}' title='{P_I}' class='latex' />, since if one then specialises to the case when <img src='http://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7Bb%3Da%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0' alt='{b=a}' title='{b=a}' class='latex' /> and averages over all primitive <img src='http://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7Bb%27%5C+%28P_I%29%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0' alt='{b&#039;&#92; (P_I)}' title='{b&#039;&#92; (P_I)}' class='latex' /> we obtain <a href="#straw">(23)</a> from the triangle inequality.</p> <p> We use the dispersion method. We write the left-hand side of <a href="#straw-2">(24)</a> as </p> <p align="center"><img src='http://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%5Cdisplaystyle+%5Csum_%7Bq%3A+qr+%5Cin+%7B%5Cmathcal+S%7D_I+%5Ccap+%7B%5Cmathcal+D%7D_%7Bx%5E%5Cdelta%7D%7D+c_q+%28%5Csum_%7Bn%3A+n+%3D+a%5C+%28r%29%3B+n%3D+b%5C+%28q%29%7D+%5Calpha+%5Cast+%5Cbeta%28n%29+-+%5Csum_%7Bn%3A+n+%3D+a%5C+%28r%29%3B+n+%3D+b%27%5C+%28q%29%7D+%5Calpha+%5Cast+%5Cbeta%28n%29%29&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0' alt='&#92;displaystyle &#92;sum_{q: qr &#92;in {&#92;mathcal S}_I &#92;cap {&#92;mathcal D}_{x^&#92;delta}} c_q (&#92;sum_{n: n = a&#92; (r); n= b&#92; (q)} &#92;alpha &#92;ast &#92;beta(n) - &#92;sum_{n: n = a&#92; (r); n = b&#039;&#92; (q)} &#92;alpha &#92;ast &#92;beta(n))' title='&#92;displaystyle &#92;sum_{q: qr &#92;in {&#92;mathcal S}_I &#92;cap {&#92;mathcal D}_{x^&#92;delta}} c_q (&#92;sum_{n: n = a&#92; (r); n= b&#92; (q)} &#92;alpha &#92;ast &#92;beta(n) - &#92;sum_{n: n = a&#92; (r); n = b&#039;&#92; (q)} &#92;alpha &#92;ast &#92;beta(n))' class='latex' /></p> <p> for some bounded sequence <img src='http://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7Bc_q%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0' alt='{c_q}' title='{c_q}' class='latex' /> (which may also depend on <img src='http://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7Br%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0' alt='{r}' title='{r}' class='latex' />, but we suppress this dependence). This expression may be rearranged as <p align="center"><img src='http://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%5Cdisplaystyle++%5Csum_m+%5Calpha%28m%29+%28%5Csum_%7Bq%2Cn%3A+mn+%3D+a%5C+%28r%29%3B+qr+%5Cin+%7B%5Cmathcal+S%7D_I+%5Ccap+%7B%5Cmathcal+D%7D_%7Bx%5E%5Cdelta%7D%7D+c_%7Bq%7D+%5Cbeta%28n%29+%281_%7Bmn+%3D+b%5C+%28q%29%7D+-+1_%7Bmn+%3D+b%27%5C+%28q%29%7D%29%29%2C&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0' alt='&#92;displaystyle &#92;sum_m &#92;alpha(m) (&#92;sum_{q,n: mn = a&#92; (r); qr &#92;in {&#92;mathcal S}_I &#92;cap {&#92;mathcal D}_{x^&#92;delta}} c_{q} &#92;beta(n) (1_{mn = b&#92; (q)} - 1_{mn = b&#039;&#92; (q)})),' title='&#92;displaystyle &#92;sum_m &#92;alpha(m) (&#92;sum_{q,n: mn = a&#92; (r); qr &#92;in {&#92;mathcal S}_I &#92;cap {&#92;mathcal D}_{x^&#92;delta}} c_{q} &#92;beta(n) (1_{mn = b&#92; (q)} - 1_{mn = b&#039;&#92; (q)})),' class='latex' /></p> <p> so from the Cauchy-Schwarz inequality and crude estimates it suffices to show that <a name="sq"> <p align="center"><img src='http://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%5Cdisplaystyle++%5Csum_%7Bm%7D+%5Cpsi_M%28m%29+%7C%5Csum_%7Bq%2Cn%3A+mn+%3D+a%5C+%28r%29%3B+qr+%5Cin+%7B%5Cmathcal+S%7D_I+%5Ccap+%7B%5Cmathcal+D%7D_%7Bx%5E%5Cdelta%7D%7D+c_%7Bq%7D+%5Cbeta%28n%29+%281_%7Bmn+%3D+b%5C+%28q%29%7D+-+1_%7Bmn+%3D+b%27%5C+%28q%29%7D%29%7C%5E2+%5C+%5C+%5C+%5C+%5C+%2825%29&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0' alt='&#92;displaystyle &#92;sum_{m} &#92;psi_M(m) |&#92;sum_{q,n: mn = a&#92; (r); qr &#92;in {&#92;mathcal S}_I &#92;cap {&#92;mathcal D}_{x^&#92;delta}} c_{q} &#92;beta(n) (1_{mn = b&#92; (q)} - 1_{mn = b&#039;&#92; (q)})|^2 &#92; &#92; &#92; &#92; &#92; (25)' title='&#92;displaystyle &#92;sum_{m} &#92;psi_M(m) |&#92;sum_{q,n: mn = a&#92; (r); qr &#92;in {&#92;mathcal S}_I &#92;cap {&#92;mathcal D}_{x^&#92;delta}} c_{q} &#92;beta(n) (1_{mn = b&#92; (q)} - 1_{mn = b&#039;&#92; (q)})|^2 &#92; &#92; &#92; &#92; &#92; (25)' class='latex' /></p> <p></a> <p align="center"><img src='http://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%5Cdisplaystyle++%5Cll+N%5E2+M+R%5E%7B-2%7D+%5Ctau%28r%29%5E%7BO%281%29%7D+%5Clog%5E%7B-A%7D+x&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0' alt='&#92;displaystyle &#92;ll N^2 M R^{-2} &#92;tau(r)^{O(1)} &#92;log^{-A} x' title='&#92;displaystyle &#92;ll N^2 M R^{-2} &#92;tau(r)^{O(1)} &#92;log^{-A} x' class='latex' /></p> <p> for any fixed <img src='http://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7BA%3E0%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0' alt='{A&gt;0}' title='{A&gt;0}' class='latex' />, where <img src='http://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7B%5Cpsi_M%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0' alt='{&#92;psi_M}' title='{&#92;psi_M}' class='latex' /> is a smooth coefficient sequence at scale <img src='http://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7BM%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0' alt='{M}' title='{M}' class='latex' />. Expanding out the square, it suffices to show that <a name="sq2"> <p align="center"><img src='http://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%5Cdisplaystyle++%5Csum_%7Bm%7D+%5Cpsi_M%28m%29+%5Csum_%7Bq_1%2Cq_2%2Cn_1%2Cn_2%3A+mn_1%3Dmn_2+%3D+a%5C+%28r%29%3B+q_1r%2Cq_2r+%5Cin+%7B%5Cmathcal+S%7D_I+%5Ccap+%7B%5Cmathcal+D%7D_%7Bx%5E%5Cdelta%7D%7D+%5C+%5C+%5C+%5C+%5C+%2826%29&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0' alt='&#92;displaystyle &#92;sum_{m} &#92;psi_M(m) &#92;sum_{q_1,q_2,n_1,n_2: mn_1=mn_2 = a&#92; (r); q_1r,q_2r &#92;in {&#92;mathcal S}_I &#92;cap {&#92;mathcal D}_{x^&#92;delta}} &#92; &#92; &#92; &#92; &#92; (26)' title='&#92;displaystyle &#92;sum_{m} &#92;psi_M(m) &#92;sum_{q_1,q_2,n_1,n_2: mn_1=mn_2 = a&#92; (r); q_1r,q_2r &#92;in {&#92;mathcal S}_I &#92;cap {&#92;mathcal D}_{x^&#92;delta}} &#92; &#92; &#92; &#92; &#92; (26)' class='latex' /></p> <p></a> <p align="center"><img src='http://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%5Cdisplaystyle++c_%7Bq_1%7D+%5Coverline%7Bc_%7Bq_2%7D%7D+%5Cbeta%28n_1%29+%5Coverline%7B%5Cbeta%28n_2%29%7D+1_%7Bmn_1+%3D+b%5C+%28q_1%29%7D+1_%7Bmn_2+%3D+b%27%5C+%28q_2%29%7D+&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0' alt='&#92;displaystyle c_{q_1} &#92;overline{c_{q_2}} &#92;beta(n_1) &#92;overline{&#92;beta(n_2)} 1_{mn_1 = b&#92; (q_1)} 1_{mn_2 = b&#039;&#92; (q_2)} ' title='&#92;displaystyle c_{q_1} &#92;overline{c_{q_2}} &#92;beta(n_1) &#92;overline{&#92;beta(n_2)} 1_{mn_1 = b&#92; (q_1)} 1_{mn_2 = b&#039;&#92; (q_2)} ' class='latex' /></p> <p align="center"><img src='http://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%5Cdisplaystyle++%3D+X+%2B+O%28+N%5E2+M+R%5E%7B-2%7D+%5Ctau%28r%29%5E%7BO%281%29%7D+%5Clog%5E%7B-A%7D+x+%29&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0' alt='&#92;displaystyle = X + O( N^2 M R^{-2} &#92;tau(r)^{O(1)} &#92;log^{-A} x )' title='&#92;displaystyle = X + O( N^2 M R^{-2} &#92;tau(r)^{O(1)} &#92;log^{-A} x )' class='latex' /></p> <p> where <img src='http://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7Bq_1%2Cq_2%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0' alt='{q_1,q_2}' title='{q_1,q_2}' class='latex' /> is subject to the same constraints as <img src='http://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7Bq%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0' alt='{q}' title='{q}' class='latex' /> (thus <img src='http://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7Bq_i+%5Cin+%7B%5Cmathcal+S%7D_%7BI%27%7D+%5Ccap+%7B%5Cmathcal+D%7D_%7Bx%5E%5Cdelta%7D%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0' alt='{q_i &#92;in {&#92;mathcal S}_{I&#039;} &#92;cap {&#92;mathcal D}_{x^&#92;delta}}' title='{q_i &#92;in {&#92;mathcal S}_{I&#039;} &#92;cap {&#92;mathcal D}_{x^&#92;delta}}' class='latex' /> and <img src='http://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7Bq_i+%5Csim+Q%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0' alt='{q_i &#92;sim Q}' title='{q_i &#92;sim Q}' class='latex' /> for <img src='http://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7Bi%3D1%2C2%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0' alt='{i=1,2}' title='{i=1,2}' class='latex' />), and <img src='http://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7BX%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0' alt='{X}' title='{X}' class='latex' /> is some quantity that is independent of <img src='http://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7Bb%2Cb%27%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0' alt='{b,b&#039;}' title='{b,b&#039;}' class='latex' />.</p> <p> Observe that <img src='http://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7Bn_1%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0' alt='{n_1}' title='{n_1}' class='latex' /> must be coprime to <img src='http://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7Bq_1r%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0' alt='{q_1r}' title='{q_1r}' class='latex' /> and <img src='http://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7Bn_2%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0' alt='{n_2}' title='{n_2}' class='latex' /> coprime to <img src='http://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7Bq_2r%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0' alt='{q_2r}' title='{q_2r}' class='latex' />, with <img src='http://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7Bn_1+%3D+n_2%5C+%28r%29%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0' alt='{n_1 = n_2&#92; (r)}' title='{n_1 = n_2&#92; (r)}' class='latex' />, to have a non-zero contribution to <a href="#sq2">(26)</a>. We then rearrange the left-hand side as </p> <p align="center"><img src='http://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%5Cdisplaystyle++%5Csum_%7Bq_1%2Cq_2%3A+q_1r%2Cq_2r+%5Cin+%7B%5Cmathcal+S%7D_I+%5Ccap+%7B%5Cmathcal+D%7D_%7Bx%5E%5Cdelta%7D%7D+%5Csum_%7Bm%7D+%5Cpsi_M%28m%29+%5Csum_%7Bn_1%2Cn_2%3A+n_1%3Dn_2%5C+%28r%29%3B+%28n_1%2Cq_1r%29%3D%28n_2%2Cq_2%29%3D1%7D+&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0' alt='&#92;displaystyle &#92;sum_{q_1,q_2: q_1r,q_2r &#92;in {&#92;mathcal S}_I &#92;cap {&#92;mathcal D}_{x^&#92;delta}} &#92;sum_{m} &#92;psi_M(m) &#92;sum_{n_1,n_2: n_1=n_2&#92; (r); (n_1,q_1r)=(n_2,q_2)=1} ' title='&#92;displaystyle &#92;sum_{q_1,q_2: q_1r,q_2r &#92;in {&#92;mathcal S}_I &#92;cap {&#92;mathcal D}_{x^&#92;delta}} &#92;sum_{m} &#92;psi_M(m) &#92;sum_{n_1,n_2: n_1=n_2&#92; (r); (n_1,q_1r)=(n_2,q_2)=1} ' class='latex' /></p> <p align="center"><img src='http://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%5Cdisplaystyle+c_%7Bq_1%7D+%5Coverline%7Bc_%7Bq_2%7D%7D+%5Coverline%7B%5Cbeta%28n_1%29%7D+%5Coverline%7B%5Cbeta%28n_2%29%7D+1_%7Bm+%3D+a%2Fn_1%5C+%28r%29%3B+m+%3D+b%2Fn_1%5C+%28q_1%29%3B+m+%3D+b%27%2Fn_2+%28q_2%29%7D%3B&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0' alt='&#92;displaystyle c_{q_1} &#92;overline{c_{q_2}} &#92;overline{&#92;beta(n_1)} &#92;overline{&#92;beta(n_2)} 1_{m = a/n_1&#92; (r); m = b/n_1&#92; (q_1); m = b&#039;/n_2 (q_2)};' title='&#92;displaystyle c_{q_1} &#92;overline{c_{q_2}} &#92;overline{&#92;beta(n_1)} &#92;overline{&#92;beta(n_2)} 1_{m = a/n_1&#92; (r); m = b/n_1&#92; (q_1); m = b&#039;/n_2 (q_2)};' class='latex' /></p> <p> note that these inverses in the various rings <img src='http://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7B%7B%5Cbf+Z%7D%2Fr%7B%5Cbf+Z%7D%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0' alt='{{&#92;bf Z}/r{&#92;bf Z}}' title='{{&#92;bf Z}/r{&#92;bf Z}}' class='latex' />, <img src='http://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7B%7B%5Cbf+Z%7D%2Fq_1%7B%5Cbf+Z%7D%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0' alt='{{&#92;bf Z}/q_1{&#92;bf Z}}' title='{{&#92;bf Z}/q_1{&#92;bf Z}}' class='latex' />, <img src='http://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7B%7B%5Cbf+Z%7D%2Fq_2%7B%5Cbf+Z%7D%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0' alt='{{&#92;bf Z}/q_2{&#92;bf Z}}' title='{{&#92;bf Z}/q_2{&#92;bf Z}}' class='latex' /> are well-defined thanks to the coprimality hypotheses. </p> <p> We may write <img src='http://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7Bn_2+%3D+n_1%2Bkr%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0' alt='{n_2 = n_1+kr}' title='{n_2 = n_1+kr}' class='latex' /> for some <img src='http://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7Bk+%3D+O%28N%2FR%29%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0' alt='{k = O(N/R)}' title='{k = O(N/R)}' class='latex' />. By the triangle inequality, and relabeling <img src='http://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7Bn_1%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0' alt='{n_1}' title='{n_1}' class='latex' /> as <img src='http://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7Bn%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0' alt='{n}' title='{n}' class='latex' />, it thus suffices to show that for any particular <a name="k-bound"> <p align="center"><img src='http://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%5Cdisplaystyle++k+%3D+O%28N%2FR%29%2C+%5C+%5C+%5C+%5C+%5C+%2827%29&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0' alt='&#92;displaystyle k = O(N/R), &#92; &#92; &#92; &#92; &#92; (27)' title='&#92;displaystyle k = O(N/R), &#92; &#92; &#92; &#92; &#92; (27)' class='latex' /></p> <p></a> one has <a name="sss"> <p align="center"><img src='http://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%5Cdisplaystyle++%5Csum_%7Bk+%3D+O%28N%2FR%29%7D+%5Csum_%7Bq_1%2Cq_2%3A+q_1r%2Cq_2r+%5Cin+%7B%5Cmathcal+S%7D_I+%5Ccap+%7B%5Cmathcal+D%7D_%7Bx%5E%5Cdelta%7D%7D+%7C%5Csum_%7Bn%3B+%28n%2Cq_1r%29%3D%28n%2Bkr%2Cq_2%29%3D1%7D+%5C+%5C+%5C+%5C+%5C+%2828%29&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0' alt='&#92;displaystyle &#92;sum_{k = O(N/R)} &#92;sum_{q_1,q_2: q_1r,q_2r &#92;in {&#92;mathcal S}_I &#92;cap {&#92;mathcal D}_{x^&#92;delta}} |&#92;sum_{n; (n,q_1r)=(n+kr,q_2)=1} &#92; &#92; &#92; &#92; &#92; (28)' title='&#92;displaystyle &#92;sum_{k = O(N/R)} &#92;sum_{q_1,q_2: q_1r,q_2r &#92;in {&#92;mathcal S}_I &#92;cap {&#92;mathcal D}_{x^&#92;delta}} |&#92;sum_{n; (n,q_1r)=(n+kr,q_2)=1} &#92; &#92; &#92; &#92; &#92; (28)' class='latex' /></p> <p></a> </p> <p align="center"><img src='http://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%5Cdisplaystyle++c_%7Bq_1%7D+%5Coverline%7Bc_%7Bq_2%7D%7D+%5Cbeta%28n%29+%5Coverline%7B%5Cbeta%28n%2Bkr%29%7D+%5Csum_%7Bm%7D+%5Cpsi_M%28m%29+1_%7Bm+%3D+a%2Fn%5C+%28r%29%3B+m+%3D+b%2Fn%5C+%28q_1%29%3B+m+%3D+b%27%2F%28n%2Bkr%29+%28q_2%29%7D%7C&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0' alt='&#92;displaystyle c_{q_1} &#92;overline{c_{q_2}} &#92;beta(n) &#92;overline{&#92;beta(n+kr)} &#92;sum_{m} &#92;psi_M(m) 1_{m = a/n&#92; (r); m = b/n&#92; (q_1); m = b&#039;/(n+kr) (q_2)}|' title='&#92;displaystyle c_{q_1} &#92;overline{c_{q_2}} &#92;beta(n) &#92;overline{&#92;beta(n+kr)} &#92;sum_{m} &#92;psi_M(m) 1_{m = a/n&#92; (r); m = b/n&#92; (q_1); m = b&#039;/(n+kr) (q_2)}|' class='latex' /></p> <p align="center"><img src='http://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%5Cdisplaystyle++%3D+X+%2B+O%28+N%5E2+M+R%5E%7B-2%7D+%5Clog%5E%7B-A%7D+x+%29&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0' alt='&#92;displaystyle = X + O( N^2 M R^{-2} &#92;log^{-A} x )' title='&#92;displaystyle = X + O( N^2 M R^{-2} &#92;log^{-A} x )' class='latex' /></p> <p> for some <img src='http://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7BX%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0' alt='{X}' title='{X}' class='latex' /> independent of <img src='http://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7Bb%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0' alt='{b}' title='{b}' class='latex' />, <img src='http://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7Bb%27%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0' alt='{b&#039;}' title='{b&#039;}' class='latex' />. </p> <p> At this stage in previous posts we isolated the coprime case <img src='http://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7B%28q_1%2Cq_2%29%3D1%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0' alt='{(q_1,q_2)=1}' title='{(q_1,q_2)=1}' class='latex' /> as the dominant case, using a controlled multiplicity hypothesis to deal with the non-coprime case. Here, we will carry the non-coprime case with us for a little longer so as not to rely on a controlled multiplicity hypothesis; this introduces some additional factors of <img src='http://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7Bq_0+%3A%3D+%28q_1%2Cq_2%29%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0' alt='{q_0 := (q_1,q_2)}' title='{q_0 := (q_1,q_2)}' class='latex' /> into the analysis but they should be ignored on a first reading. </p> <p> Applying completion of sums (Section 2 from <a href="http://terrytao.wordpress.com/2013/06/12/estimation-of-the-type-i-and-type-ii-sums/">this previous post</a>), we can express the left-hand side of <a href="#sss">(28)</a> as a main term <a name="main-term"> <p align="center"><img src='http://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%5Cdisplaystyle++%5Csum_%7Bk+%3D+O%28N%2FR%29%7D+%5Csum_%7Bq_1%2Cq_2%3A+q_1r%2Cq_2r+%5Cin+%7B%5Cmathcal+S%7D_I+%5Ccap+%7B%5Cmathcal+D%7D_%7Bx%5E%5Cdelta%7D%7D+%7C%5Csum_%7Bn%3B+%28n%2Cq_1r%29%3D%28n%2Bkr%2Cq_2%29%3D1%7D+%5C+%5C+%5C+%5C+%5C+%2829%29&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0' alt='&#92;displaystyle &#92;sum_{k = O(N/R)} &#92;sum_{q_1,q_2: q_1r,q_2r &#92;in {&#92;mathcal S}_I &#92;cap {&#92;mathcal D}_{x^&#92;delta}} |&#92;sum_{n; (n,q_1r)=(n+kr,q_2)=1} &#92; &#92; &#92; &#92; &#92; (29)' title='&#92;displaystyle &#92;sum_{k = O(N/R)} &#92;sum_{q_1,q_2: q_1r,q_2r &#92;in {&#92;mathcal S}_I &#92;cap {&#92;mathcal D}_{x^&#92;delta}} |&#92;sum_{n; (n,q_1r)=(n+kr,q_2)=1} &#92; &#92; &#92; &#92; &#92; (29)' class='latex' /></p> <p></a> </p> <p align="center"><img src='http://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%5Cdisplaystyle++c_%7Bq_1%7D+%5Coverline%7Bc_%7Bq_2%7D%7D+%5Cbeta%28n%29+%5Coverline%7B%5Cbeta%28n%2Bkr%29%7D+%28%5Csum_%7Bm%7D+%5Cpsi_M%28m%29%29+%5Cfrac%7B1%7D%7Br%5Bq_1%2Cq_2%5D%7D+1_%7Bb%2Fn+%3D+b%27%2F%28n%2Bkr%29%5C+%28%28q_1%2Cq_2%29%29%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0' alt='&#92;displaystyle c_{q_1} &#92;overline{c_{q_2}} &#92;beta(n) &#92;overline{&#92;beta(n+kr)} (&#92;sum_{m} &#92;psi_M(m)) &#92;frac{1}{r[q_1,q_2]} 1_{b/n = b&#039;/(n+kr)&#92; ((q_1,q_2))}' title='&#92;displaystyle c_{q_1} &#92;overline{c_{q_2}} &#92;beta(n) &#92;overline{&#92;beta(n+kr)} (&#92;sum_{m} &#92;psi_M(m)) &#92;frac{1}{r[q_1,q_2]} 1_{b/n = b&#039;/(n+kr)&#92; ((q_1,q_2))}' class='latex' /></p> <p> plus an error term <a name="lal"> <p align="center"><img src='http://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%5Cdisplaystyle++O%28+%5Cfrac%7B1%7D%7BH%7D+%5Csum_%7Bk%3DO%28N%2FR%29%7D+%5Csum_%7B1+%5Cleq+h+%5Cleq+H%7D+%5Csum_%7Bq_1%2Cq_2%7D+%7C%5Csum_%7Bn%7D+%5Cbeta%28n%29+%5Cbeta%28n%2Bkr%29+%5CPhi_%7Bk%2Cr%7D%28h%2Cq_1%2Cq_2%3B+n%29%7C+%29+%5C+%5C+%5C+%5C+%5C+%2830%29&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0' alt='&#92;displaystyle O( &#92;frac{1}{H} &#92;sum_{k=O(N/R)} &#92;sum_{1 &#92;leq h &#92;leq H} &#92;sum_{q_1,q_2} |&#92;sum_{n} &#92;beta(n) &#92;beta(n+kr) &#92;Phi_{k,r}(h,q_1,q_2; n)| ) &#92; &#92; &#92; &#92; &#92; (30)' title='&#92;displaystyle O( &#92;frac{1}{H} &#92;sum_{k=O(N/R)} &#92;sum_{1 &#92;leq h &#92;leq H} &#92;sum_{q_1,q_2} |&#92;sum_{n} &#92;beta(n) &#92;beta(n+kr) &#92;Phi_{k,r}(h,q_1,q_2; n)| ) &#92; &#92; &#92; &#92; &#92; (30)' class='latex' /></p> <p></a> <p align="center"><img src='http://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%5Cdisplaystyle++%2B+O%28+x%5E%7B-A%7D+%29%2C&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0' alt='&#92;displaystyle + O( x^{-A} ),' title='&#92;displaystyle + O( x^{-A} ),' class='latex' /></p> <p> where <a name="hqq"> <p align="center"><img src='http://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%5Cdisplaystyle++H+%3A%3D+x%5E%5Cepsilon+Q%5E2+R%2FM+%5C+%5C+%5C+%5C+%5C+%2831%29&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0' alt='&#92;displaystyle H := x^&#92;epsilon Q^2 R/M &#92; &#92; &#92; &#92; &#92; (31)' title='&#92;displaystyle H := x^&#92;epsilon Q^2 R/M &#92; &#92; &#92; &#92; &#92; (31)' class='latex' /></p> <p></a> and <img src='http://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7B%5CPhi+%3D+%5CPhi_%7Bk%2Cr%7D%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0' alt='{&#92;Phi = &#92;Phi_{k,r}}' title='{&#92;Phi = &#92;Phi_{k,r}}' class='latex' /> is the phase <a name="phi-def"> <p align="center"><img src='http://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%5Cdisplaystyle++%5CPhi%28h%2Cq_1%2Cq_2%3Bn%29+%3A%3D+1_%7B%28n%2Cr%29%3D%28n%2Cq_1%29%3D%28n%2Bkr%2Cq_2%29%3D1%7D+1_%7Bq_1%2Cq_2%2Cq_1r%2Cq_2r+%5Cin+%7B%5Cmathcal+S%7D_I+%5Ccap+%7B%5Cmathcal+D%7D_%7Bx%5E%5Cdelta%7D%7D+%5C+%5C+%5C+%5C+%5C+%2832%29&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0' alt='&#92;displaystyle &#92;Phi(h,q_1,q_2;n) := 1_{(n,r)=(n,q_1)=(n+kr,q_2)=1} 1_{q_1,q_2,q_1r,q_2r &#92;in {&#92;mathcal S}_I &#92;cap {&#92;mathcal D}_{x^&#92;delta}} &#92; &#92; &#92; &#92; &#92; (32)' title='&#92;displaystyle &#92;Phi(h,q_1,q_2;n) := 1_{(n,r)=(n,q_1)=(n+kr,q_2)=1} 1_{q_1,q_2,q_1r,q_2r &#92;in {&#92;mathcal S}_I &#92;cap {&#92;mathcal D}_{x^&#92;delta}} &#92; &#92; &#92; &#92; &#92; (32)' class='latex' /></p> <p></a> <p align="center"><img src='http://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%5Cdisplaystyle++1_%7Bb%2Fn%3Db%27%2F%28n%2Bkr%29%5C+%28%28q_1%2Cq_2%29%29%7D+&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0' alt='&#92;displaystyle 1_{b/n=b&#039;/(n+kr)&#92; ((q_1,q_2))} ' title='&#92;displaystyle 1_{b/n=b&#039;/(n+kr)&#92; ((q_1,q_2))} ' class='latex' /></p> <p align="center"><img src='http://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%5Cdisplaystyle++e_r%28+%5Cfrac%7Bah%7D%7Bnq_1+q%27_2%7D+%29+e_%7Bq_1%7D%28+%5Cfrac%7Bbh%7D%7Bn+r+q%27_2%7D+%29+e_%7Bq%27_2%7D%28+%5Cfrac%7Bb%27+h%7D%7B%28n%2Bkr%29+r+q_1%7D+%29%2C&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0' alt='&#92;displaystyle e_r( &#92;frac{ah}{nq_1 q&#039;_2} ) e_{q_1}( &#92;frac{bh}{n r q&#039;_2} ) e_{q&#039;_2}( &#92;frac{b&#039; h}{(n+kr) r q_1} ),' title='&#92;displaystyle e_r( &#92;frac{ah}{nq_1 q&#039;_2} ) e_{q_1}( &#92;frac{bh}{n r q&#039;_2} ) e_{q&#039;_2}( &#92;frac{b&#039; h}{(n+kr) r q_1} ),' class='latex' /></p> <p> where <img src='http://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7Bq%27_2+%3A%3D+q_2%2F%28q_1%2Cq_2%29%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0' alt='{q&#039;_2 := q_2/(q_1,q_2)}' title='{q&#039;_2 := q_2/(q_1,q_2)}' class='latex' />. </p> <p> Let us first deal with the main term <a href="#main-term">(29)</a>. The contribution of the coprime case <img src='http://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7B%28q_1%2Cq_2%29%3D1%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0' alt='{(q_1,q_2)=1}' title='{(q_1,q_2)=1}' class='latex' /> does not depend on <img src='http://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7Bb%2Cb%27%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0' alt='{b,b&#039;}' title='{b,b&#039;}' class='latex' /> and can thus be absorbed into the <img src='http://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7BX%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0' alt='{X}' title='{X}' class='latex' /> term. Now we consider the contribution of the non-coprime case when <img src='http://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7Bq_0+%3D+%28q_1%2Cq_2%29+%3E+1%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0' alt='{q_0 = (q_1,q_2) &gt; 1}' title='{q_0 = (q_1,q_2) &gt; 1}' class='latex' />. We may estimate the contribution of this case by </p> <p align="center"><img src='http://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%5Cdisplaystyle++O%28+%5Csum_%7Bk+%3D+O%28N%2FR%29%7D+%5Csum_%7Bq_0+%5Cin+%7B%5Cmathcal+S%7D_%7BI%27%7D%3A+1+%3C+q_0+%5Cll+Q%2C+%28q_0%2Cr%29%3D1%7D+%5Csum_%7Bq%27_1%2Cq%27_2+%5Csim+Q%2Fq_0%7D+%7C%5Csum_%7Bn%3A+b%2Fn+%3D+b%27%2F%28n%2Bkr%29%5C+%28q_0%29%7D+&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0' alt='&#92;displaystyle O( &#92;sum_{k = O(N/R)} &#92;sum_{q_0 &#92;in {&#92;mathcal S}_{I&#039;}: 1 &lt; q_0 &#92;ll Q, (q_0,r)=1} &#92;sum_{q&#039;_1,q&#039;_2 &#92;sim Q/q_0} |&#92;sum_{n: b/n = b&#039;/(n+kr)&#92; (q_0)} ' title='&#92;displaystyle O( &#92;sum_{k = O(N/R)} &#92;sum_{q_0 &#92;in {&#92;mathcal S}_{I&#039;}: 1 &lt; q_0 &#92;ll Q, (q_0,r)=1} &#92;sum_{q&#039;_1,q&#039;_2 &#92;sim Q/q_0} |&#92;sum_{n: b/n = b&#039;/(n+kr)&#92; (q_0)} ' class='latex' /></p> <p align="center"><img src='http://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%5Cdisplaystyle++%7C%5Cbeta%28n%29%7C+%7C%5Cbeta%28n%2Bkr%29%7C+M+%5Cfrac%7B1%7D%7Brq_0+q%27_1+q%27_2%7D+%29.&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0' alt='&#92;displaystyle |&#92;beta(n)| |&#92;beta(n+kr)| M &#92;frac{1}{rq_0 q&#039;_1 q&#039;_2} ).' title='&#92;displaystyle |&#92;beta(n)| |&#92;beta(n+kr)| M &#92;frac{1}{rq_0 q&#039;_1 q&#039;_2} ).' class='latex' /></p> <p> We may estimate <img src='http://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7B%7C%5Cbeta%28n%29%7C+%7C%5Cbeta%28n%2Bkr%29%7C%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0' alt='{|&#92;beta(n)| |&#92;beta(n+kr)|}' title='{|&#92;beta(n)| |&#92;beta(n+kr)|}' class='latex' /> by <img src='http://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7B%7C%5Cbeta%28n%29%7C%5E2+%2B+%7C%5Cbeta%28n%2Bkr%29%7C%5E2%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0' alt='{|&#92;beta(n)|^2 + |&#92;beta(n+kr)|^2}' title='{|&#92;beta(n)|^2 + |&#92;beta(n+kr)|^2}' class='latex' />. We just estimate the contribution of <img src='http://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7B%7C%5Cbeta%28n%29%7C%5E2%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0' alt='{|&#92;beta(n)|^2}' title='{|&#92;beta(n)|^2}' class='latex' />, as the other case is treated similarly (after shifting <img src='http://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7Bn%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0' alt='{n}' title='{n}' class='latex' /> by <img src='http://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7Bkr%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0' alt='{kr}' title='{kr}' class='latex' />). We rearrange this contribution as <p align="center"><img src='http://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%5Cdisplaystyle++O%28+%5Csum_%7Bq_0+%5Cin+%7B%5Cmathcal+S%7D_%7BI%27%7D%3A+1+%3C+q_0+%5Cll+Q%2C+%28q_0%2Cr%29%3D1%7D+%5Csum_%7Bq%27_1%2Cq%27_2+%5Csim+Q%2Fq_0%7D+%7C%5Csum_%7Bn%7D+&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0' alt='&#92;displaystyle O( &#92;sum_{q_0 &#92;in {&#92;mathcal S}_{I&#039;}: 1 &lt; q_0 &#92;ll Q, (q_0,r)=1} &#92;sum_{q&#039;_1,q&#039;_2 &#92;sim Q/q_0} |&#92;sum_{n} ' title='&#92;displaystyle O( &#92;sum_{q_0 &#92;in {&#92;mathcal S}_{I&#039;}: 1 &lt; q_0 &#92;ll Q, (q_0,r)=1} &#92;sum_{q&#039;_1,q&#039;_2 &#92;sim Q/q_0} |&#92;sum_{n} ' class='latex' /></p> <p align="center"><img src='http://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%5Cdisplaystyle++%7C%5Cbeta%28n%29%7C%5E2+M+%5Cfrac%7B1%7D%7BRq_0+q%27_1+q%27_2%7D+%5Csum_%7Bk+%3D+O%28N%2FR%29%7D+1_%7Bb%2Fn+%3D+b%27%2F%28n%2Bkr%29%5C+%28q_0%29%7D+%29.&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0' alt='&#92;displaystyle |&#92;beta(n)|^2 M &#92;frac{1}{Rq_0 q&#039;_1 q&#039;_2} &#92;sum_{k = O(N/R)} 1_{b/n = b&#039;/(n+kr)&#92; (q_0)} ).' title='&#92;displaystyle |&#92;beta(n)|^2 M &#92;frac{1}{Rq_0 q&#039;_1 q&#039;_2} &#92;sum_{k = O(N/R)} 1_{b/n = b&#039;/(n+kr)&#92; (q_0)} ).' class='latex' /></p> <p> The <img src='http://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7Bk%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0' alt='{k}' title='{k}' class='latex' /> summation is <img src='http://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7BO%28+1+%2B+%5Cfrac%7BN%7D%7BRq_0%7D+%29%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0' alt='{O( 1 + &#92;frac{N}{Rq_0} )}' title='{O( 1 + &#92;frac{N}{Rq_0} )}' class='latex' />. Evaluating the <img src='http://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7Bn%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0' alt='{n}' title='{n}' class='latex' /> and <img src='http://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7Bq%27_1%2Cq%27_2%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0' alt='{q&#039;_1,q&#039;_2}' title='{q&#039;_1,q&#039;_2}' class='latex' /> summations, we obtain a bound of <p align="center"><img src='http://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%5Cdisplaystyle++O%28+%5Cfrac%7BMN%7D%7BR%7D+%5Clog%5E%7BO%281%29%7D+x+%5Csum_%7Bq_0+%5Cin+%7B%5Cmathcal+S%7D_%7BI%27%7D%3A+1+%3C+q_0+%5Cll+Q%7D+%5Cfrac%7B1%7D%7Bq_0%7D+%28+1+%2B+%5Cfrac%7BN%7D%7BRq_0%7D+%29+%29.&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0' alt='&#92;displaystyle O( &#92;frac{MN}{R} &#92;log^{O(1)} x &#92;sum_{q_0 &#92;in {&#92;mathcal S}_{I&#039;}: 1 &lt; q_0 &#92;ll Q} &#92;frac{1}{q_0} ( 1 + &#92;frac{N}{Rq_0} ) ).' title='&#92;displaystyle O( &#92;frac{MN}{R} &#92;log^{O(1)} x &#92;sum_{q_0 &#92;in {&#92;mathcal S}_{I&#039;}: 1 &lt; q_0 &#92;ll Q} &#92;frac{1}{q_0} ( 1 + &#92;frac{N}{Rq_0} ) ).' class='latex' /></p> <p> Since <img src='http://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7Bq_0+%3E+1%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0' alt='{q_0 &gt; 1}' title='{q_0 &gt; 1}' class='latex' /> and <img src='http://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7Bq_0+%5Cin+%7B%5Cmathcal+S%7D_%7BI%27%7D%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0' alt='{q_0 &#92;in {&#92;mathcal S}_{I&#039;}}' title='{q_0 &#92;in {&#92;mathcal S}_{I&#039;}}' class='latex' />, we have <img src='http://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7Bq_0+%5Cgeq+D_0%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0' alt='{q_0 &#92;geq D_0}' title='{q_0 &#92;geq D_0}' class='latex' />, and so we may evaluate the <img src='http://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7Bq_0%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0' alt='{q_0}' title='{q_0}' class='latex' /> summation as <p align="center"><img src='http://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%5Cdisplaystyle++O%28+%5Cfrac%7BMN%7D%7BR%7D+%5Clog%5E%7BO%281%29%7D+x+%281+%2B+%5Cfrac%7BN%7D%7BRD_0%7D+%29+%29.&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0' alt='&#92;displaystyle O( &#92;frac{MN}{R} &#92;log^{O(1)} x (1 + &#92;frac{N}{RD_0} ) ).' title='&#92;displaystyle O( &#92;frac{MN}{R} &#92;log^{O(1)} x (1 + &#92;frac{N}{RD_0} ) ).' class='latex' /></p> <p> By <a href="#crop">(20)</a> and <a href="#d0">(19)</a>, this is <img src='http://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7BO%28+N%5E2+M+R%5E%7B-2%7D+%5Clog%5E%7B-A%7D+x+%29%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0' alt='{O( N^2 M R^{-2} &#92;log^{-A} x )}' title='{O( N^2 M R^{-2} &#92;log^{-A} x )}' class='latex' /> as required.</p> <p> It remains to control <a href="#lal">(30)</a>. We may assume that <img src='http://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7BH+%5Cgeq+1%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0' alt='{H &#92;geq 1}' title='{H &#92;geq 1}' class='latex' />, as the claim is trivial otherwise. It will suffice to obtain the bound </p> <p align="center"><img src='http://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%5Cdisplaystyle++%5Cfrac%7B1%7D%7BH%7D+%5Csum_%7Bk%3DO%28N%2FR%29%7D+%5Csum_%7B1+%5Cleq+h+%5Cleq+H%7D+%5Csum_%7Bq_1%2Cq_2+%5Csim+Q%7D+%7C%5Csum_%7Bn%7D+%5Cbeta%28n%29+%5Coverline%7B%5Cbeta%28n%2Bkr%29%7D+%5CPhi_%7Bk%2Cr%7D%28h%2Cq_1%2Cq_2%3B+n%29%7C+&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0' alt='&#92;displaystyle &#92;frac{1}{H} &#92;sum_{k=O(N/R)} &#92;sum_{1 &#92;leq h &#92;leq H} &#92;sum_{q_1,q_2 &#92;sim Q} |&#92;sum_{n} &#92;beta(n) &#92;overline{&#92;beta(n+kr)} &#92;Phi_{k,r}(h,q_1,q_2; n)| ' title='&#92;displaystyle &#92;frac{1}{H} &#92;sum_{k=O(N/R)} &#92;sum_{1 &#92;leq h &#92;leq H} &#92;sum_{q_1,q_2 &#92;sim Q} |&#92;sum_{n} &#92;beta(n) &#92;overline{&#92;beta(n+kr)} &#92;Phi_{k,r}(h,q_1,q_2; n)| ' class='latex' /></p> <p align="center"><img src='http://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%5Cdisplaystyle++%5Clessapprox+x%5E%7B-%5Cepsilon%7D+N%5E2+M+R%5E%7B-2%7D.&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0' alt='&#92;displaystyle &#92;lessapprox x^{-&#92;epsilon} N^2 M R^{-2}.' title='&#92;displaystyle &#92;lessapprox x^{-&#92;epsilon} N^2 M R^{-2}.' class='latex' /></p> <p> Using <a href="#hqq">(31)</a>, it will suffice to show that <p align="center"><img src='http://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%5Cdisplaystyle++%5Csum_%7B1+%5Cleq+h+%5Cleq+H%7D+%5Csum_%7Bq_1%2Cq_2+%5Csim+Q%7D+%7C%5Csum_%7Bn%7D+%5Cbeta%28n%29+%5Coverline%7B%5Cbeta%28n%2Bkr%29%7D+%5CPhi_%7Bk%2Cr%7D%28h%2Cq_1%2Cq_2%3B+n%29%7C+&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0' alt='&#92;displaystyle &#92;sum_{1 &#92;leq h &#92;leq H} &#92;sum_{q_1,q_2 &#92;sim Q} |&#92;sum_{n} &#92;beta(n) &#92;overline{&#92;beta(n+kr)} &#92;Phi_{k,r}(h,q_1,q_2; n)| ' title='&#92;displaystyle &#92;sum_{1 &#92;leq h &#92;leq H} &#92;sum_{q_1,q_2 &#92;sim Q} |&#92;sum_{n} &#92;beta(n) &#92;overline{&#92;beta(n+kr)} &#92;Phi_{k,r}(h,q_1,q_2; n)| ' class='latex' /></p> <p align="center"><img src='http://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%5Cdisplaystyle++%5Clessapprox+Q%5E2+N+&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0' alt='&#92;displaystyle &#92;lessapprox Q^2 N ' title='&#92;displaystyle &#92;lessapprox Q^2 N ' class='latex' /></p> <p> for each <img src='http://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7Bk+%3D+O%28N%2FR%29%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0' alt='{k = O(N/R)}' title='{k = O(N/R)}' class='latex' />.</p> <p> We now work with a single <img src='http://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7Bk%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0' alt='{k}' title='{k}' class='latex' />, and abbreviate <img src='http://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7B%5CPhi_%7Bk%2Cr%7D%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0' alt='{&#92;Phi_{k,r}}' title='{&#92;Phi_{k,r}}' class='latex' /> as <img src='http://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7B%5CPhi%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0' alt='{&#92;Phi}' title='{&#92;Phi}' class='latex' />. To proceed further, we write <img src='http://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7Bq_0+%3A%3D+%28q_1%2Cq_2%29%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0' alt='{q_0 := (q_1,q_2)}' title='{q_0 := (q_1,q_2)}' class='latex' /> and <img src='http://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7Bq_1+%3D+q_0+q%27_1%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0' alt='{q_1 = q_0 q&#039;_1}' title='{q_1 = q_0 q&#039;_1}' class='latex' />, <img src='http://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7Bq_2+%3D+q_0+q%27_2%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0' alt='{q_2 = q_0 q&#039;_2}' title='{q_2 = q_0 q&#039;_2}' class='latex' />; it then suffices to show that <a name="aaa"> <p align="center"><img src='http://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%5Cdisplaystyle++%5Csum_%7B1+%5Cleq+h+%5Cleq+H%7D+%5Csum_%7Bq%27_1%2Cq%27_2+%5Csim+Q%2Fq_0%3A+%28q%27_1%2Cq%27_2%29+%3D+1%7D+%5C+%5C+%5C+%5C+%5C+%2833%29&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0' alt='&#92;displaystyle &#92;sum_{1 &#92;leq h &#92;leq H} &#92;sum_{q&#039;_1,q&#039;_2 &#92;sim Q/q_0: (q&#039;_1,q&#039;_2) = 1} &#92; &#92; &#92; &#92; &#92; (33)' title='&#92;displaystyle &#92;sum_{1 &#92;leq h &#92;leq H} &#92;sum_{q&#039;_1,q&#039;_2 &#92;sim Q/q_0: (q&#039;_1,q&#039;_2) = 1} &#92; &#92; &#92; &#92; &#92; (33)' class='latex' /></p> <p></a> </p> <p align="center"><img src='http://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%5Cdisplaystyle++%7C%5Csum_%7Bn%7D+%5Cbeta%28n%29+%5Coverline%7B%5Cbeta%28n%2Bkr%29%7D+%5CPhi%28h%2Cq_0+q%27_1%2Cq_0+q%27_2%3B+n%29%7C+&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0' alt='&#92;displaystyle |&#92;sum_{n} &#92;beta(n) &#92;overline{&#92;beta(n+kr)} &#92;Phi(h,q_0 q&#039;_1,q_0 q&#039;_2; n)| ' title='&#92;displaystyle |&#92;sum_{n} &#92;beta(n) &#92;overline{&#92;beta(n+kr)} &#92;Phi(h,q_0 q&#039;_1,q_0 q&#039;_2; n)| ' class='latex' /></p> <p align="center"><img src='http://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%5Cdisplaystyle++%5Clessapprox+Q%5E2+N+%2F+q_0&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0' alt='&#92;displaystyle &#92;lessapprox Q^2 N / q_0' title='&#92;displaystyle &#92;lessapprox Q^2 N / q_0' class='latex' /></p> <p> for each <img src='http://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7Bq_0+%5Cgeq+1%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0' alt='{q_0 &#92;geq 1}' title='{q_0 &#92;geq 1}' class='latex' />.</p> <p> Henceforth we work with a single choice of <img src='http://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7Bq_0%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0' alt='{q_0}' title='{q_0}' class='latex' />. We pause to verify the relationship </p> <p align="center"><img src='http://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%5Cdisplaystyle++H+%5Clessapprox+Q.&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0' alt='&#92;displaystyle H &#92;lessapprox Q.' title='&#92;displaystyle H &#92;lessapprox Q.' class='latex' /></p> <p> From <a href="#hqq">(31)</a> and <a href="#creep">(21)</a>, this follows from the assertion that <p align="center"><img src='http://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%5Cdisplaystyle++x%5E%7B1%2F2%2B2%5Cvarpi%2B%5Cepsilon%7D+%5Clessapprox+M%2C&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0' alt='&#92;displaystyle x^{1/2+2&#92;varpi+&#92;epsilon} &#92;lessapprox M,' title='&#92;displaystyle x^{1/2+2&#92;varpi+&#92;epsilon} &#92;lessapprox M,' class='latex' /></p> <p> but this follows from <a href="#lin">(5)</a>, <a href="#xss">(6)</a> if <img src='http://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7B%5Cepsilon%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0' alt='{&#92;epsilon}' title='{&#92;epsilon}' class='latex' /> is sufficiently small depending on <img src='http://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7Bc%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0' alt='{c}' title='{c}' class='latex' />.</p> <p> As <img src='http://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7Bq_1%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0' alt='{q_1}' title='{q_1}' class='latex' /> is <img src='http://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7Bx%5E%5Cdelta%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0' alt='{x^&#92;delta}' title='{x^&#92;delta}' class='latex' />-densely divisible, we may now factor <img src='http://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7Bq_1+%3D+s_1+t_1%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0' alt='{q_1 = s_1 t_1}' title='{q_1 = s_1 t_1}' class='latex' /> where </p> <p align="center"><img src='http://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%5Cdisplaystyle++x%5E%7B-%5Cdelta%7D+Q%2FH+%5Clessapprox+s_1+%5Clessapprox+Q%2FH&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0' alt='&#92;displaystyle x^{-&#92;delta} Q/H &#92;lessapprox s_1 &#92;lessapprox Q/H' title='&#92;displaystyle x^{-&#92;delta} Q/H &#92;lessapprox s_1 &#92;lessapprox Q/H' class='latex' /></p> <p> and thus <p align="center"><img src='http://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%5Cdisplaystyle++H+%5Clessapprox+t_1+%5Clessapprox+x%5E%5Cdelta+H.&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0' alt='&#92;displaystyle H &#92;lessapprox t_1 &#92;lessapprox x^&#92;delta H.' title='&#92;displaystyle H &#92;lessapprox t_1 &#92;lessapprox x^&#92;delta H.' class='latex' /></p> <p> Factoring out <img src='http://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7Bq_0%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0' alt='{q_0}' title='{q_0}' class='latex' />, we may then write <img src='http://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7Bq%27_1+%3D+s%27_1+t%27_1%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0' alt='{q&#039;_1 = s&#039;_1 t&#039;_1}' title='{q&#039;_1 = s&#039;_1 t&#039;_1}' class='latex' /> where <p align="center"><img src='http://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%5Cdisplaystyle++q_0%5E%7B-1%7D+x%5E%7B-%5Cdelta%7D+Q%2FH+%5Clessapprox+s%27_1+%5Clessapprox+Q%2FH&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0' alt='&#92;displaystyle q_0^{-1} x^{-&#92;delta} Q/H &#92;lessapprox s&#039;_1 &#92;lessapprox Q/H' title='&#92;displaystyle q_0^{-1} x^{-&#92;delta} Q/H &#92;lessapprox s&#039;_1 &#92;lessapprox Q/H' class='latex' /></p> <p> and <p align="center"><img src='http://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%5Cdisplaystyle++q_0%5E%7B-1%7D+H+%5Clessapprox+t%27_1+%5Clessapprox+x%5E%5Cdelta+H.&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0' alt='&#92;displaystyle q_0^{-1} H &#92;lessapprox t&#039;_1 &#92;lessapprox x^&#92;delta H.' title='&#92;displaystyle q_0^{-1} H &#92;lessapprox t&#039;_1 &#92;lessapprox x^&#92;delta H.' class='latex' /></p> <p> By dyadic decomposition, it thus suffices to show that </p> <p align="center"><img src='http://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%5Cdisplaystyle++%5Csum_%7B1+%5Cleq+h+%5Cleq+H%7D+%5Csum_%7Bs%27_1+%5Csim+S%3B+t%27_1+%5Csim+T%3B+q%27_2+%5Csim+Q%2Fq_0%3A+%28s%27_1+t%27_1%2Cq%27_2%29+%3D+1%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0' alt='&#92;displaystyle &#92;sum_{1 &#92;leq h &#92;leq H} &#92;sum_{s&#039;_1 &#92;sim S; t&#039;_1 &#92;sim T; q&#039;_2 &#92;sim Q/q_0: (s&#039;_1 t&#039;_1,q&#039;_2) = 1}' title='&#92;displaystyle &#92;sum_{1 &#92;leq h &#92;leq H} &#92;sum_{s&#039;_1 &#92;sim S; t&#039;_1 &#92;sim T; q&#039;_2 &#92;sim Q/q_0: (s&#039;_1 t&#039;_1,q&#039;_2) = 1}' class='latex' /></p> <p align="center"><img src='http://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%5Cdisplaystyle+%7C%5Csum_%7Bn%7D+%5Cbeta%28n%29+%5Coverline%7B%5Cbeta%28n%2Bkr%29%7D+%5CPhi%28h%2Cq_0+s%27_1+t%27_1%2Cq_0+q%27_2%3B+n%29%7C+&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0' alt='&#92;displaystyle |&#92;sum_{n} &#92;beta(n) &#92;overline{&#92;beta(n+kr)} &#92;Phi(h,q_0 s&#039;_1 t&#039;_1,q_0 q&#039;_2; n)| ' title='&#92;displaystyle |&#92;sum_{n} &#92;beta(n) &#92;overline{&#92;beta(n+kr)} &#92;Phi(h,q_0 s&#039;_1 t&#039;_1,q_0 q&#039;_2; n)| ' class='latex' /></p> <p align="center"><img src='http://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%5Cdisplaystyle++%5Clessapprox+Q%5E2+N+%2F+q_0&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0' alt='&#92;displaystyle &#92;lessapprox Q^2 N / q_0' title='&#92;displaystyle &#92;lessapprox Q^2 N / q_0' class='latex' /></p> <p> whenever <img src='http://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7BS%2CT%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0' alt='{S,T}' title='{S,T}' class='latex' /> are such that <p align="center"><img src='http://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%5Cdisplaystyle++q_0%5E%7B-1%7D+x%5E%7B-%5Cdelta%7D+Q%2FH+%5Clessapprox+S+%5Clessapprox+Q%2FH&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0' alt='&#92;displaystyle q_0^{-1} x^{-&#92;delta} Q/H &#92;lessapprox S &#92;lessapprox Q/H' title='&#92;displaystyle q_0^{-1} x^{-&#92;delta} Q/H &#92;lessapprox S &#92;lessapprox Q/H' class='latex' /></p> <p> and <p align="center"><img src='http://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%5Cdisplaystyle++q_0%5E%7B-1%7D+H+%5Clessapprox+T+%5Clessapprox+x%5E%5Cdelta+H.&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0' alt='&#92;displaystyle q_0^{-1} H &#92;lessapprox T &#92;lessapprox x^&#92;delta H.' title='&#92;displaystyle q_0^{-1} H &#92;lessapprox T &#92;lessapprox x^&#92;delta H.' class='latex' /></p> <p> and <p align="center"><img src='http://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%5Cdisplaystyle++ST+%5Csim+Q%2Fq_0.&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0' alt='&#92;displaystyle ST &#92;sim Q/q_0.' title='&#92;displaystyle ST &#92;sim Q/q_0.' class='latex' /></p> <p> We rearrange this estimate as <p align="center"><img src='http://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%5Cdisplaystyle++%7C%5Csum_%7Bn%3B+s%27_1+%5Csim+S%3B+q%27_2+%5Csim+Q%2Fq_0%7D+%5Cbeta%28n%29+%5Coverline%7B%5Cbeta%28n%2Bkr%29%7D+%5Csum_%7B1+%5Cleq+h+%5Cleq+H%3B+t%27_1+%5Csim+T%7D+c_%7Bh%2Cs%27_1%2Ct%27_1%2Cq%27_2%7D+%5CPhi%28h%2Cq_0+s%27_1+t%27_1%2Cq_0+q%27_2%3B+n%29%7C+&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0' alt='&#92;displaystyle |&#92;sum_{n; s&#039;_1 &#92;sim S; q&#039;_2 &#92;sim Q/q_0} &#92;beta(n) &#92;overline{&#92;beta(n+kr)} &#92;sum_{1 &#92;leq h &#92;leq H; t&#039;_1 &#92;sim T} c_{h,s&#039;_1,t&#039;_1,q&#039;_2} &#92;Phi(h,q_0 s&#039;_1 t&#039;_1,q_0 q&#039;_2; n)| ' title='&#92;displaystyle |&#92;sum_{n; s&#039;_1 &#92;sim S; q&#039;_2 &#92;sim Q/q_0} &#92;beta(n) &#92;overline{&#92;beta(n+kr)} &#92;sum_{1 &#92;leq h &#92;leq H; t&#039;_1 &#92;sim T} c_{h,s&#039;_1,t&#039;_1,q&#039;_2} &#92;Phi(h,q_0 s&#039;_1 t&#039;_1,q_0 q&#039;_2; n)| ' class='latex' /></p> <p align="center"><img src='http://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%5Cdisplaystyle++%5Clessapprox+QSTN+&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0' alt='&#92;displaystyle &#92;lessapprox QSTN ' title='&#92;displaystyle &#92;lessapprox QSTN ' class='latex' /></p> <p> for some bounded sequence <img src='http://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7Bc_%7Bh%2Cs_1%2Ct_1%2Cq_2%7D%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0' alt='{c_{h,s_1,t_1,q_2}}' title='{c_{h,s_1,t_1,q_2}}' class='latex' /> which is only non-zero when <p align="center"><img src='http://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%5Cdisplaystyle++%28s%27_1+t%27_1%2Cq%27_2%29+%3D+%28q_0%2Cs%27_1t%27_1%29+%3D+%28q_0%2Cq%27_2%29+%3D+1.&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0' alt='&#92;displaystyle (s&#039;_1 t&#039;_1,q&#039;_2) = (q_0,s&#039;_1t&#039;_1) = (q_0,q&#039;_2) = 1.' title='&#92;displaystyle (s&#039;_1 t&#039;_1,q&#039;_2) = (q_0,s&#039;_1t&#039;_1) = (q_0,q&#039;_2) = 1.' class='latex' /></p> <p> By Cauchy-Schwarz and crude estimates, it then suffices to show that <p align="center"><img src='http://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%5Cdisplaystyle++%5Csum_%7Bn%3B+s%27_1+%5Csim+S%3B+q%27_2+%5Csim+Q%2Fq_0%7D+%5Cpsi_N%28n%29+%7C%5Csum_%7B1+%5Cleq+h+%5Cleq+H%3B+t%27_1+%5Csim+T%7D+c_%7Bh%2Cs%27_1%2Ct%27_1%2Cq%27_2%7D+%5CPhi%28h%2Cq_0+s%27_1+t%27_1%2Cq_0+q_2%3B+n%29%7C%5E2+&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0' alt='&#92;displaystyle &#92;sum_{n; s&#039;_1 &#92;sim S; q&#039;_2 &#92;sim Q/q_0} &#92;psi_N(n) |&#92;sum_{1 &#92;leq h &#92;leq H; t&#039;_1 &#92;sim T} c_{h,s&#039;_1,t&#039;_1,q&#039;_2} &#92;Phi(h,q_0 s&#039;_1 t&#039;_1,q_0 q_2; n)|^2 ' title='&#92;displaystyle &#92;sum_{n; s&#039;_1 &#92;sim S; q&#039;_2 &#92;sim Q/q_0} &#92;psi_N(n) |&#92;sum_{1 &#92;leq h &#92;leq H; t&#039;_1 &#92;sim T} c_{h,s&#039;_1,t&#039;_1,q&#039;_2} &#92;Phi(h,q_0 s&#039;_1 t&#039;_1,q_0 q_2; n)|^2 ' class='latex' /></p> <p align="center"><img src='http://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%5Cdisplaystyle++%5Clessapprox+QST%5E2+N+q_0+&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0' alt='&#92;displaystyle &#92;lessapprox QST^2 N q_0 ' title='&#92;displaystyle &#92;lessapprox QST^2 N q_0 ' class='latex' /></p> <p> where <img src='http://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7B%5Cpsi_N%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0' alt='{&#92;psi_N}' title='{&#92;psi_N}' class='latex' /> is a coefficient sequence at scale <img src='http://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7BN%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0' alt='{N}' title='{N}' class='latex' />. The left-hand side may be bounded by <a name="los"> <p align="center"><img src='http://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%5Cdisplaystyle++%5Csum_%7B1+%5Cleq+h%2C%5Ctilde+h+%5Cleq+H%3B+t%27_1%2C%5Ctilde+t%27_1+%5Csim+T%3B+s%27_1+%5Csim+S%3B+q%27_2+%5Csim+Q%2Fq_0%3B+%28s%27_1t%27_1%5Ctilde+t%27_1%2Cq%27_2%29%3D1%7D+%5C+%5C+%5C+%5C+%5C+%2834%29&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0' alt='&#92;displaystyle &#92;sum_{1 &#92;leq h,&#92;tilde h &#92;leq H; t&#039;_1,&#92;tilde t&#039;_1 &#92;sim T; s&#039;_1 &#92;sim S; q&#039;_2 &#92;sim Q/q_0; (s&#039;_1t&#039;_1&#92;tilde t&#039;_1,q&#039;_2)=1} &#92; &#92; &#92; &#92; &#92; (34)' title='&#92;displaystyle &#92;sum_{1 &#92;leq h,&#92;tilde h &#92;leq H; t&#039;_1,&#92;tilde t&#039;_1 &#92;sim T; s&#039;_1 &#92;sim S; q&#039;_2 &#92;sim Q/q_0; (s&#039;_1t&#039;_1&#92;tilde t&#039;_1,q&#039;_2)=1} &#92; &#92; &#92; &#92; &#92; (34)' class='latex' /></p> <p></a> <p align="center"><img src='http://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%5Cdisplaystyle++%7C%5Csum_n+%5Cpsi_N%28n%29+%5CPhi%28h%2C+q_0+s%27_1+t%27_1%2Cq_0+q%27_2%3B+n%29+%5Coverline%7B+%5CPhi%28%5Ctilde+h%2Cq_0+s%27_1+%5Ctilde+t%27_1%2Cq_0+q%27_2%3B+n%29+%7D+%7C.&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0' alt='&#92;displaystyle |&#92;sum_n &#92;psi_N(n) &#92;Phi(h, q_0 s&#039;_1 t&#039;_1,q_0 q&#039;_2; n) &#92;overline{ &#92;Phi(&#92;tilde h,q_0 s&#039;_1 &#92;tilde t&#039;_1,q_0 q&#039;_2; n) } |.' title='&#92;displaystyle |&#92;sum_n &#92;psi_N(n) &#92;Phi(h, q_0 s&#039;_1 t&#039;_1,q_0 q&#039;_2; n) &#92;overline{ &#92;Phi(&#92;tilde h,q_0 s&#039;_1 &#92;tilde t&#039;_1,q_0 q&#039;_2; n) } |.' class='latex' /></p> <p> The contribution of the diagonal case <img src='http://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7Bh+%5Ctilde+t%27_1+%3D+%5Ctilde+h+t%27_1%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0' alt='{h &#92;tilde t&#039;_1 = &#92;tilde h t&#039;_1}' title='{h &#92;tilde t&#039;_1 = &#92;tilde h t&#039;_1}' class='latex' /> is <img src='http://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7B%5Clessapprox+HTSQ+N%2Fq_0%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0' alt='{&#92;lessapprox HTSQ N/q_0}' title='{&#92;lessapprox HTSQ N/q_0}' class='latex' /> by the divisor bound, which is acceptable since <img src='http://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7Bq_0+T+%5Cgtrapprox+H%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0' alt='{q_0 T &#92;gtrapprox H}' title='{q_0 T &#92;gtrapprox H}' class='latex' />. Thus it suffices to control the off-diagonal case <img src='http://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7Bh%5Ctilde+t%27_1+%5Cneq+%5Ctilde+ht%27_1%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0' alt='{h&#92;tilde t&#039;_1 &#92;neq &#92;tilde ht&#039;_1}' title='{h&#92;tilde t&#039;_1 &#92;neq &#92;tilde ht&#039;_1}' class='latex' />. Observe that for a given choice of <img src='http://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7Bh%2C%5Ctilde+h%2Cs%27_1%2Ct%27_1%2C%5Ctilde+t%27_1%2Cq%27_2%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0' alt='{h,&#92;tilde h,s&#039;_1,t&#039;_1,&#92;tilde t&#039;_1,q&#039;_2}' title='{h,&#92;tilde h,s&#039;_1,t&#039;_1,&#92;tilde t&#039;_1,q&#039;_2}' class='latex' />, the phase <img src='http://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7B%5CPhi%28h%2Cq_0+s%27_1+t%27_1%2Cq_0+q%27_2%3B+n%29+%5Coverline%7B+%5CPhi%28%5Ctilde+h%2Cq_0+s%27_1+%5Ctilde+t%27_1%2Cq_0+q%27_2%3B+n%29+%7D%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0' alt='{&#92;Phi(h,q_0 s&#039;_1 t&#039;_1,q_0 q&#039;_2; n) &#92;overline{ &#92;Phi(&#92;tilde h,q_0 s&#039;_1 &#92;tilde t&#039;_1,q_0 q&#039;_2; n) }}' title='{&#92;Phi(h,q_0 s&#039;_1 t&#039;_1,q_0 q&#039;_2; n) &#92;overline{ &#92;Phi(&#92;tilde h,q_0 s&#039;_1 &#92;tilde t&#039;_1,q_0 q&#039;_2; n) }}' class='latex' /> either vanishes identically, or is equal to <p align="center"><img src='http://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%5Cdisplaystyle++1_%7Bb%2Fn%3Db%27%2F%28n%2Bkr%29%5C+%28q_0%29%7D+e_%7Br+q_0+s%27_1+%5Bt%27_1%2C+%5Ctilde+t%27_1%5D%7D%28%5Cfrac%7Bc_1%7D%7Bn%7D+%29+e_%7Bq_0+q%27_2%7D%28%5Cfrac%7Bc_2%7D%7Bn%2Bkr%7D+%29+&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0' alt='&#92;displaystyle 1_{b/n=b&#039;/(n+kr)&#92; (q_0)} e_{r q_0 s&#039;_1 [t&#039;_1, &#92;tilde t&#039;_1]}(&#92;frac{c_1}{n} ) e_{q_0 q&#039;_2}(&#92;frac{c_2}{n+kr} ) ' title='&#92;displaystyle 1_{b/n=b&#039;/(n+kr)&#92; (q_0)} e_{r q_0 s&#039;_1 [t&#039;_1, &#92;tilde t&#039;_1]}(&#92;frac{c_1}{n} ) e_{q_0 q&#039;_2}(&#92;frac{c_2}{n+kr} ) ' class='latex' /></p> <p> for some quantities <img src='http://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7Bc_1%2Cc_2%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0' alt='{c_1,c_2}' title='{c_1,c_2}' class='latex' /> with <p align="center"><img src='http://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%5Cdisplaystyle++%28c_1%2Cr%29+%3D+%28h%5Ctilde+t%27_1-%5Ctilde+ht%27_1%2C+r%29.&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0' alt='&#92;displaystyle (c_1,r) = (h&#92;tilde t&#039;_1-&#92;tilde ht&#039;_1, r).' title='&#92;displaystyle (c_1,r) = (h&#92;tilde t&#039;_1-&#92;tilde ht&#039;_1, r).' class='latex' /></p> <p> Also, by construction, <img src='http://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7Brq_0+s%27_1+t%27_1%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0' alt='{rq_0 s&#039;_1 t&#039;_1}' title='{rq_0 s&#039;_1 t&#039;_1}' class='latex' />, <img src='http://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7Brq_0+s%27_1+%5Ctilde+t%27_1%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0' alt='{rq_0 s&#039;_1 &#92;tilde t&#039;_1}' title='{rq_0 s&#039;_1 &#92;tilde t&#039;_1}' class='latex' /> and <img src='http://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7Bq_0+q%27_2%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0' alt='{q_0 q&#039;_2}' title='{q_0 q&#039;_2}' class='latex' /> are <img src='http://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7Bx%5E%5Cdelta%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0' alt='{x^&#92;delta}' title='{x^&#92;delta}' class='latex' />-densely divisible, so <img src='http://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7B%5Brq_0+s%27_1+t%27_1+%5Ctilde+t%27_1%2Cq_0+q%27_2%5D%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0' alt='{[rq_0 s&#039;_1 t&#039;_1 &#92;tilde t&#039;_1,q_0 q&#039;_2]}' title='{[rq_0 s&#039;_1 t&#039;_1 &#92;tilde t&#039;_1,q_0 q&#039;_2]}' class='latex' /> is as well. (Here we use the fact that the least common multiple of two <img src='http://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7Bx%5E%5Cdelta%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0' alt='{x^&#92;delta}' title='{x^&#92;delta}' class='latex' />-densely divisible numbers is again <img src='http://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7Bx%5E%5Cdelta%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0' alt='{x^&#92;delta}' title='{x^&#92;delta}' class='latex' />-densely divisible, which follows from the more general fact that if <img src='http://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7Bq%3Dq_1+q_2%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0' alt='{q=q_1 q_2}' title='{q=q_1 q_2}' class='latex' />, <img src='http://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7Bq_2+%5Cleq+%5Csqrt%7Bq%7D%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0' alt='{q_2 &#92;leq &#92;sqrt{q}}' title='{q_2 &#92;leq &#92;sqrt{q}}' class='latex' />, and <img src='http://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7Bq_1%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0' alt='{q_1}' title='{q_1}' class='latex' /> is <img src='http://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7Bx%5E%5Cdelta%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0' alt='{x^&#92;delta}' title='{x^&#92;delta}' class='latex' />-densely divisible, then <img src='http://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7Bq%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0' alt='{q}' title='{q}' class='latex' /> is also.) The condition <img src='http://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7B1_%7Bb%2Fn%3Db%27%2F%28n%2Bkr%29%5C+%28q_0%29%7D%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0' alt='{1_{b/n=b&#039;/(n+kr)&#92; (q_0)}}' title='{1_{b/n=b&#039;/(n+kr)&#92; (q_0)}}' class='latex' /> is either not satisfiable, or restricts <img src='http://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7Bn%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0' alt='{n}' title='{n}' class='latex' /> to a congruence class <img src='http://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7Ba%5C+%28q%29%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0' alt='{a&#92; (q)}' title='{a&#92; (q)}' class='latex' /> for some <img src='http://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7Bq%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0' alt='{q}' title='{q}' class='latex' /> dividing <img src='http://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7Bq_0%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0' alt='{q_0}' title='{q_0}' class='latex' />. We can thus apply Corollary <a href="#dons">11</a> and bound <p align="center"><img src='http://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%5Cdisplaystyle++%7C%5Csum_n+%5Cpsi_N%28n%29+%5CPhi%28h%2C+q_0+s%27_1+t%27_1%2Cq_0+q%27_2%3B+n%29+%5Coverline%7B+%5CPhi%28%5Ctilde+h%2Cq_0+s%27_1+%5Ctilde+t%27_1%2Cq_0+q%27_2%3B+n%29+%7D+%7C&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0' alt='&#92;displaystyle |&#92;sum_n &#92;psi_N(n) &#92;Phi(h, q_0 s&#039;_1 t&#039;_1,q_0 q&#039;_2; n) &#92;overline{ &#92;Phi(&#92;tilde h,q_0 s&#039;_1 &#92;tilde t&#039;_1,q_0 q&#039;_2; n) } |' title='&#92;displaystyle |&#92;sum_n &#92;psi_N(n) &#92;Phi(h, q_0 s&#039;_1 t&#039;_1,q_0 q&#039;_2; n) &#92;overline{ &#92;Phi(&#92;tilde h,q_0 s&#039;_1 &#92;tilde t&#039;_1,q_0 q&#039;_2; n) } |' class='latex' /></p> <p> by <p align="center"><img src='http://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%5Cdisplaystyle++%5Clessapprox+N%5E%7B1%2F2%7D+%28Rq_0+ST%5E2+Q%2Fq_0%29%5E%7B1%2F6%7D+x%5E%7B%5Cdelta%2F6%7D+%2B+%5Cfrac%7B%28h%5Ctilde+t%27_1-%5Ctilde+ht%27_1%2C+r%29%7D%7BR%7D+N.&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0' alt='&#92;displaystyle &#92;lessapprox N^{1/2} (Rq_0 ST^2 Q/q_0)^{1/6} x^{&#92;delta/6} + &#92;frac{(h&#92;tilde t&#039;_1-&#92;tilde ht&#039;_1, r)}{R} N.' title='&#92;displaystyle &#92;lessapprox N^{1/2} (Rq_0 ST^2 Q/q_0)^{1/6} x^{&#92;delta/6} + &#92;frac{(h&#92;tilde t&#039;_1-&#92;tilde ht&#039;_1, r)}{R} N.' class='latex' /></p> <p> Bounding <img src='http://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7BRq_0+ST%5E2+Q%2Fq_0%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0' alt='{Rq_0 ST^2 Q/q_0}' title='{Rq_0 ST^2 Q/q_0}' class='latex' /> by <img src='http://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7Bx%5E%5Cdelta+RQ%5E2+H%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0' alt='{x^&#92;delta RQ^2 H}' title='{x^&#92;delta RQ^2 H}' class='latex' />, we can thus bound the off-diagonal contribution to <a href="#los">(34)</a> by <p align="center"><img src='http://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%5Cdisplaystyle++%5Clessapprox+%5Csum_%7B1+%5Cleq+h%2C%5Ctilde+h+%5Cleq+H%3B+t%27_1%2C%5Ctilde+t%27_1+%5Csim+T%3A+h+%5Ctilde+t%27_1+%5Cneq+%5Ctilde+h+t%27_1%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0' alt='&#92;displaystyle &#92;lessapprox &#92;sum_{1 &#92;leq h,&#92;tilde h &#92;leq H; t&#039;_1,&#92;tilde t&#039;_1 &#92;sim T: h &#92;tilde t&#039;_1 &#92;neq &#92;tilde h t&#039;_1}' title='&#92;displaystyle &#92;lessapprox &#92;sum_{1 &#92;leq h,&#92;tilde h &#92;leq H; t&#039;_1,&#92;tilde t&#039;_1 &#92;sim T: h &#92;tilde t&#039;_1 &#92;neq &#92;tilde h t&#039;_1}' class='latex' /></p> <p align="center"><img src='http://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%5Cdisplaystyle++%5Csum_%7Bs%27_1+%5Csim+S%3B+q%27_2+%5Csim+Q%2Fq_0%7D+N%5E%7B1%2F2%7D+x%5E%7B%5Cdelta%2F3%7D+%28RQ%5E2+H%29%5E%7B1%2F6%7D+%2B+%5Cfrac%7B%28h%5Ctilde+t%27_1-%5Ctilde+ht%27_1%2C+r%29%7D%7BR%7D+N&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0' alt='&#92;displaystyle &#92;sum_{s&#039;_1 &#92;sim S; q&#039;_2 &#92;sim Q/q_0} N^{1/2} x^{&#92;delta/3} (RQ^2 H)^{1/6} + &#92;frac{(h&#92;tilde t&#039;_1-&#92;tilde ht&#039;_1, r)}{R} N' title='&#92;displaystyle &#92;sum_{s&#039;_1 &#92;sim S; q&#039;_2 &#92;sim Q/q_0} N^{1/2} x^{&#92;delta/3} (RQ^2 H)^{1/6} + &#92;frac{(h&#92;tilde t&#039;_1-&#92;tilde ht&#039;_1, r)}{R} N' class='latex' /></p> <p> which sums (using Lemma 5 of <a href="http://terrytao.wordpress.com/2013/06/14/estimation-of-the-type-iii-sums/">this previous post</a> and the divisor bound) to <p align="center"><img src='http://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%5Cdisplaystyle++%5Clessapprox+%28H%5E2+T%5E2+S+Q+%2F+q_0+%29+%28N%5E%7B1%2F2%7D+x%5E%7B%5Cdelta%2F3%7D+%28RQ%5E2+H%29%5E%7B1%2F6%7D+%2B+%5Cfrac%7B1%7D%7BR%7D+N+%29.&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0' alt='&#92;displaystyle &#92;lessapprox (H^2 T^2 S Q / q_0 ) (N^{1/2} x^{&#92;delta/3} (RQ^2 H)^{1/6} + &#92;frac{1}{R} N ).' title='&#92;displaystyle &#92;lessapprox (H^2 T^2 S Q / q_0 ) (N^{1/2} x^{&#92;delta/3} (RQ^2 H)^{1/6} + &#92;frac{1}{R} N ).' class='latex' /></p> <p> Discarding some factors of <img src='http://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7Bq_0%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0' alt='{q_0}' title='{q_0}' class='latex' />, we reduce to showing that <p align="center"><img src='http://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%5Cdisplaystyle++N%5E%7B1%2F2%7D+x%5E%7B%5Cdelta%2F3%7D+%28RQ%5E2+H%29%5E%7B1%2F6%7D+%2B+%5Cfrac%7B1%7D%7BR%7D+N+%5Clessapprox+H%5E%7B-2%7D+N.&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0' alt='&#92;displaystyle N^{1/2} x^{&#92;delta/3} (RQ^2 H)^{1/6} + &#92;frac{1}{R} N &#92;lessapprox H^{-2} N.' title='&#92;displaystyle N^{1/2} x^{&#92;delta/3} (RQ^2 H)^{1/6} + &#92;frac{1}{R} N &#92;lessapprox H^{-2} N.' class='latex' /></p> <p> From <a href="#hqq">(31)</a>, <a href="#creep">(21)</a>, <a href="#lin">(5)</a> we have <img src='http://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7BQ+%5Clessapprox+x%5E%7B1%2F2%2B2%5Cvarpi%7D+R%5E%7B-1%7D%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0' alt='{Q &#92;lessapprox x^{1/2+2&#92;varpi} R^{-1}}' title='{Q &#92;lessapprox x^{1/2+2&#92;varpi} R^{-1}}' class='latex' /> and <img src='http://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7BH+%5Clessapprox+x%5E%7B4%5Cvarpi%2B%5Cepsilon%7D+N+R%5E%7B-1%7D%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0' alt='{H &#92;lessapprox x^{4&#92;varpi+&#92;epsilon} N R^{-1}}' title='{H &#92;lessapprox x^{4&#92;varpi+&#92;epsilon} N R^{-1}}' class='latex' />, so the previous estimate will be implied by </p> <p align="center"><img src='http://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%5Cdisplaystyle++N%5E%7B1%2F2%7D+x%5E%7B%5Cdelta%2F3%7D+%28x%5E%7B1%2B8%5Cvarpi%2B%5Cepsilon%7D+N+R%5E%7B-2%7D%29%5E%7B1%2F6%7D+%2B+%5Cfrac%7B1%7D%7BR%7D+N+%5Clessapprox+x%5E%7B-8%5Cvarpi-2%5Cepsilon%7D+R%5E2+N%5E%7B-1%7D.&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0' alt='&#92;displaystyle N^{1/2} x^{&#92;delta/3} (x^{1+8&#92;varpi+&#92;epsilon} N R^{-2})^{1/6} + &#92;frac{1}{R} N &#92;lessapprox x^{-8&#92;varpi-2&#92;epsilon} R^2 N^{-1}.' title='&#92;displaystyle N^{1/2} x^{&#92;delta/3} (x^{1+8&#92;varpi+&#92;epsilon} N R^{-2})^{1/6} + &#92;frac{1}{R} N &#92;lessapprox x^{-8&#92;varpi-2&#92;epsilon} R^2 N^{-1}.' class='latex' /></p> <p> From <a href="#crop">(20)</a>, this will be implied by <p align="center"><img src='http://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%5Cdisplaystyle++N%5E%7B1%2F2%7D+x%5E%7B%5Cdelta%2F3%7D+%28x%5E%7B1%2B8%5Cvarpi%2B2%5Cdelta%2B3%5Cepsilon%7D+N%5E%7B-1%7D%29%5E%7B1%2F6%7D+%2B+x%5E%7B%5Cdelta%2B%5Cepsilon%7D+%5Clessapprox+x%5E%7B-8%5Cvarpi-2%5Cdelta-4%5Cepsilon%7D+N&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0' alt='&#92;displaystyle N^{1/2} x^{&#92;delta/3} (x^{1+8&#92;varpi+2&#92;delta+3&#92;epsilon} N^{-1})^{1/6} + x^{&#92;delta+&#92;epsilon} &#92;lessapprox x^{-8&#92;varpi-2&#92;delta-4&#92;epsilon} N' title='&#92;displaystyle N^{1/2} x^{&#92;delta/3} (x^{1+8&#92;varpi+2&#92;delta+3&#92;epsilon} N^{-1})^{1/6} + x^{&#92;delta+&#92;epsilon} &#92;lessapprox x^{-8&#92;varpi-2&#92;delta-4&#92;epsilon} N' class='latex' /></p> <p> or equivalently that <p align="center"><img src='http://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%5Cdisplaystyle++x%5E%7B%5Cfrac%7B1%7D%7B4%7D+%2B+14+%5Cvarpi+%2B+4+%5Cdelta+%2B+%5Cfrac%7B27%7D%7B4%7D+%5Cepsilon%7D+%5Clessapprox+N&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0' alt='&#92;displaystyle x^{&#92;frac{1}{4} + 14 &#92;varpi + 4 &#92;delta + &#92;frac{27}{4} &#92;epsilon} &#92;lessapprox N' title='&#92;displaystyle x^{&#92;frac{1}{4} + 14 &#92;varpi + 4 &#92;delta + &#92;frac{27}{4} &#92;epsilon} &#92;lessapprox N' class='latex' /></p> <p> and <p align="center"><img src='http://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%5Cdisplaystyle++x%5E%7B8+%5Cvarpi+%2B+3+%5Cdelta+%2B+5+%5Cepsilon%7D+%5Clessapprox+N&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0' alt='&#92;displaystyle x^{8 &#92;varpi + 3 &#92;delta + 5 &#92;epsilon} &#92;lessapprox N' title='&#92;displaystyle x^{8 &#92;varpi + 3 &#92;delta + 5 &#92;epsilon} &#92;lessapprox N' class='latex' /></p> <p> which by <a href="#xss">(6)</a> is obeyed whenever <p align="center"><img src='http://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%5Cdisplaystyle++56+%5Cvarpi+%2B+16+%5Cdelta+%2B+4%5Csigma+%3C+1&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0' alt='&#92;displaystyle 56 &#92;varpi + 16 &#92;delta + 4&#92;sigma &lt; 1' title='&#92;displaystyle 56 &#92;varpi + 16 &#92;delta + 4&#92;sigma &lt; 1' class='latex' /></p> <p> and <p align="center"><img src='http://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%5Cdisplaystyle++16+%5Cvarpi+%2B+6+%5Cdelta+%2B+2+%5Csigma+%3C+1.&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0' alt='&#92;displaystyle 16 &#92;varpi + 6 &#92;delta + 2 &#92;sigma &lt; 1.' title='&#92;displaystyle 16 &#92;varpi + 6 &#92;delta + 2 &#92;sigma &lt; 1.' class='latex' /></p> <p> The second condition is implied by the first and may be deleted. The proof of Theorem <a href="#t1-precise">4</a> is now complete.</p> <p align="center"><b> &mdash; 3. Type II estimate &mdash; </b></p> <p> Now we prove Theorem <a href="#t2-precise">5</a>. We repeat the Type I arguments through to <a href="#aaa">(33)</a> (noting that the hypothesis <a href="#xss">(6)</a> is never used until that point, other than to ensure that <img src='http://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7BN+%5Cgtrapprox+x%5E%5Cepsilon%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0' alt='{N &#92;gtrapprox x^&#92;epsilon}' title='{N &#92;gtrapprox x^&#92;epsilon}' class='latex' />), thus we are again faced with the task of proving </p> <p align="center"><img src='http://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%5Cdisplaystyle++%5Csum_%7B1+%5Cleq+h+%5Cleq+H%7D+%5Csum_%7Bq%27_1%2Cq%27_2+%5Csim+Q%2Fq_0%3A+%28q%27_1%2Cq%27_2%29+%3D+1%7D+%7C%5Csum_%7Bn%7D+%5Cbeta%28n%29+%5Coverline%7B%5Cbeta%28n%2Bkr%29%7D+%5CPhi%28h%2Cq_0+q%27_1%2Cq_0+q%27_2%3B+n%29%7C+&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0' alt='&#92;displaystyle &#92;sum_{1 &#92;leq h &#92;leq H} &#92;sum_{q&#039;_1,q&#039;_2 &#92;sim Q/q_0: (q&#039;_1,q&#039;_2) = 1} |&#92;sum_{n} &#92;beta(n) &#92;overline{&#92;beta(n+kr)} &#92;Phi(h,q_0 q&#039;_1,q_0 q&#039;_2; n)| ' title='&#92;displaystyle &#92;sum_{1 &#92;leq h &#92;leq H} &#92;sum_{q&#039;_1,q&#039;_2 &#92;sim Q/q_0: (q&#039;_1,q&#039;_2) = 1} |&#92;sum_{n} &#92;beta(n) &#92;overline{&#92;beta(n+kr)} &#92;Phi(h,q_0 q&#039;_1,q_0 q&#039;_2; n)| ' class='latex' /></p> <p align="center"><img src='http://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%5Cdisplaystyle++%5Clessapprox+Q%5E2+N+%2F+q_0.&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0' alt='&#92;displaystyle &#92;lessapprox Q^2 N / q_0.' title='&#92;displaystyle &#92;lessapprox Q^2 N / q_0.' class='latex' /></p> <p> This time, however, we do not have <img src='http://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7BH+%5Clessapprox+Q%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0' alt='{H &#92;lessapprox Q}' title='{H &#92;lessapprox Q}' class='latex' />; however we claim the weaker bound <a name="hqq2"> <p align="center"><img src='http://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%5Cdisplaystyle++H+%5Clessapprox+Q%5E2.+%5C+%5C+%5C+%5C+%5C+%2835%29&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0' alt='&#92;displaystyle H &#92;lessapprox Q^2. &#92; &#92; &#92; &#92; &#92; (35)' title='&#92;displaystyle H &#92;lessapprox Q^2. &#92; &#92; &#92; &#92; &#92; (35)' class='latex' /></p> <p></a> Indeed by <a href="#hqq">(31)</a> this is equivalent to </p> <p align="center"><img src='http://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%5Cdisplaystyle++x%5E%5Cepsilon+R+%5Clessapprox+M&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0' alt='&#92;displaystyle x^&#92;epsilon R &#92;lessapprox M' title='&#92;displaystyle x^&#92;epsilon R &#92;lessapprox M' class='latex' /></p> <p> and this follows from <a href="#crop">(20)</a> and <a href="#lin">(5)</a>, <a href="#xss-2">(8)</a>.</p> <p> With this weaker bound <a href="#hqq2">(35)</a> we have to perform Cauchy-Schwarz differently. We rearrange the left-hand side as </p> <p align="center"><img src='http://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%5Cdisplaystyle++%5Csum_n+%5Cbeta%28n%29+%5Coverline%7B%5Cbeta%28n%2Bkr%29%7D+%28+%5Csum_%7B1+%5Cleq+h+%5Cleq+H%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0' alt='&#92;displaystyle &#92;sum_n &#92;beta(n) &#92;overline{&#92;beta(n+kr)} ( &#92;sum_{1 &#92;leq h &#92;leq H}' title='&#92;displaystyle &#92;sum_n &#92;beta(n) &#92;overline{&#92;beta(n+kr)} ( &#92;sum_{1 &#92;leq h &#92;leq H}' class='latex' /></p> <p align="center"><img src='http://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%5Cdisplaystyle++%5Csum_%7Bq%27_1%2Cq%27_2+%5Csim+Q%2Fq_0%3A+%28q%27_1%2Cq%27_2%29+%3D+1%7D+c_%7Bh%2Cq%27_1%2Cq%27_2%7D+%5CPhi%28h%2Cq_0+q%27_1%2Cq_0+q%27_2%3B+n%29+%29+&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0' alt='&#92;displaystyle &#92;sum_{q&#039;_1,q&#039;_2 &#92;sim Q/q_0: (q&#039;_1,q&#039;_2) = 1} c_{h,q&#039;_1,q&#039;_2} &#92;Phi(h,q_0 q&#039;_1,q_0 q&#039;_2; n) ) ' title='&#92;displaystyle &#92;sum_{q&#039;_1,q&#039;_2 &#92;sim Q/q_0: (q&#039;_1,q&#039;_2) = 1} c_{h,q&#039;_1,q&#039;_2} &#92;Phi(h,q_0 q&#039;_1,q_0 q&#039;_2; n) ) ' class='latex' /></p> <p> for some bounded coefficients <img src='http://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7Bc_%7Bh%2Cq%27_1%2Cq%27_2%7D%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0' alt='{c_{h,q&#039;_1,q&#039;_2}}' title='{c_{h,q&#039;_1,q&#039;_2}}' class='latex' />. Applying Cauchy-Schwarz, it then suffices to show that <p align="center"><img src='http://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%5Cdisplaystyle++%5Csum_n+%5Cpsi_N%28n%29+%7C%5Csum_%7B1+%5Cleq+h+%5Cleq+H%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0' alt='&#92;displaystyle &#92;sum_n &#92;psi_N(n) |&#92;sum_{1 &#92;leq h &#92;leq H}' title='&#92;displaystyle &#92;sum_n &#92;psi_N(n) |&#92;sum_{1 &#92;leq h &#92;leq H}' class='latex' /></p> <p align="center"><img src='http://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%5Cdisplaystyle++%5Csum_%7Bq%27_1%2Cq%27_2+%5Csim+Q%2Fq_0%3A+%28q%27_1%2Cq%27_2%29+%3D+1%7D+c_%7Bh%2Cq%27_1%2Cq%27_2%7D+%5CPhi%28h%2Cq_0+q%27_1%2Cq_0+q%27_2%3B+n%29%7C%5E2+&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0' alt='&#92;displaystyle &#92;sum_{q&#039;_1,q&#039;_2 &#92;sim Q/q_0: (q&#039;_1,q&#039;_2) = 1} c_{h,q&#039;_1,q&#039;_2} &#92;Phi(h,q_0 q&#039;_1,q_0 q&#039;_2; n)|^2 ' title='&#92;displaystyle &#92;sum_{q&#039;_1,q&#039;_2 &#92;sim Q/q_0: (q&#039;_1,q&#039;_2) = 1} c_{h,q&#039;_1,q&#039;_2} &#92;Phi(h,q_0 q&#039;_1,q_0 q&#039;_2; n)|^2 ' class='latex' /></p> <p align="center"><img src='http://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%5Cdisplaystyle++%5Clessapprox+Q%5E4+N+%2F+q_0%5E2.&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0' alt='&#92;displaystyle &#92;lessapprox Q^4 N / q_0^2.' title='&#92;displaystyle &#92;lessapprox Q^4 N / q_0^2.' class='latex' /></p> <p> The left-hand side may be bounded by <p align="center"><img src='http://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%5Cdisplaystyle++%5Csum_%7B1+%5Cleq+h%2C+%5Ctilde+h+%5Cleq+H%7D+%5Csum_%7Bq%27_1%2Cq%27_2%2C%5Ctilde+q%27_1%2C%5Ctilde+q%27_2+%5Csim+Q%2Fq_0%3A+%28q%27_1%2Cq%27_2%29+%3D+%28%5Ctilde+q%27_1%2C%5Ctilde+q%27_2%29+%3D+1%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0' alt='&#92;displaystyle &#92;sum_{1 &#92;leq h, &#92;tilde h &#92;leq H} &#92;sum_{q&#039;_1,q&#039;_2,&#92;tilde q&#039;_1,&#92;tilde q&#039;_2 &#92;sim Q/q_0: (q&#039;_1,q&#039;_2) = (&#92;tilde q&#039;_1,&#92;tilde q&#039;_2) = 1}' title='&#92;displaystyle &#92;sum_{1 &#92;leq h, &#92;tilde h &#92;leq H} &#92;sum_{q&#039;_1,q&#039;_2,&#92;tilde q&#039;_1,&#92;tilde q&#039;_2 &#92;sim Q/q_0: (q&#039;_1,q&#039;_2) = (&#92;tilde q&#039;_1,&#92;tilde q&#039;_2) = 1}' class='latex' /></p> <p align="center"><img src='http://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%5Cdisplaystyle++%7C+%5Csum_n+%5Cpsi_N%28n%29+%5CPhi%28h%2Cq_0+q%27_1%2Cq_0+q%27_2%3B+n%29+%5Coverline%7B%5CPhi%28%5Ctilde+h%2Cq_0+%5Ctilde+q%27_1%2Cq_0+%5Ctilde+q%27_2%3B+n%29%7D+%7C.&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0' alt='&#92;displaystyle | &#92;sum_n &#92;psi_N(n) &#92;Phi(h,q_0 q&#039;_1,q_0 q&#039;_2; n) &#92;overline{&#92;Phi(&#92;tilde h,q_0 &#92;tilde q&#039;_1,q_0 &#92;tilde q&#039;_2; n)} |.' title='&#92;displaystyle | &#92;sum_n &#92;psi_N(n) &#92;Phi(h,q_0 q&#039;_1,q_0 q&#039;_2; n) &#92;overline{&#92;Phi(&#92;tilde h,q_0 &#92;tilde q&#039;_1,q_0 &#92;tilde q&#039;_2; n)} |.' class='latex' /></p> <p> We isolate the diagonal case <img src='http://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7Bh+%5Ctilde+q%27_1+%5Ctilde+q%27_2+%3D+%5Ctilde+h+q%27_1+q%27_2%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0' alt='{h &#92;tilde q&#039;_1 &#92;tilde q&#039;_2 = &#92;tilde h q&#039;_1 q&#039;_2}' title='{h &#92;tilde q&#039;_1 &#92;tilde q&#039;_2 = &#92;tilde h q&#039;_1 q&#039;_2}' class='latex' />. By the divisor bound, the contribution of this case is <img src='http://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7B%5Clessapprox+HN+%28Q%2Fq_0%29%5E2%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0' alt='{&#92;lessapprox HN (Q/q_0)^2}' title='{&#92;lessapprox HN (Q/q_0)^2}' class='latex' />, which is acceptable by <a href="#hqq2">(35)</a>. So we now restrict attention to the off-diagonal case <img src='http://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7Bh+%5Ctilde+q%27_1+%5Ctilde+q%27_2+%5Cneq+%5Ctilde+h+q%27_1+q%27_2%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0' alt='{h &#92;tilde q&#039;_1 &#92;tilde q&#039;_2 &#92;neq &#92;tilde h q&#039;_1 q&#039;_2}' title='{h &#92;tilde q&#039;_1 &#92;tilde q&#039;_2 &#92;neq &#92;tilde h q&#039;_1 q&#039;_2}' class='latex' />. The phase <img src='http://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7B%5CPhi%28h%2Cq_0+q%27_1%2Cq_0+q%27_2%3B+n%29+%5Coverline%7B%5CPhi%28%5Ctilde+h%2Cq_0+%5Ctilde+q%27_1%2Cq_0+%5Ctilde+q%27_2%3B+n%29%7D%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0' alt='{&#92;Phi(h,q_0 q&#039;_1,q_0 q&#039;_2; n) &#92;overline{&#92;Phi(&#92;tilde h,q_0 &#92;tilde q&#039;_1,q_0 &#92;tilde q&#039;_2; n)}}' title='{&#92;Phi(h,q_0 q&#039;_1,q_0 q&#039;_2; n) &#92;overline{&#92;Phi(&#92;tilde h,q_0 &#92;tilde q&#039;_1,q_0 &#92;tilde q&#039;_2; n)}}' class='latex' /> either vanishes identically, or takes the form <p align="center"><img src='http://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%5Cdisplaystyle++1_%7Bb%2Fn%3Db%27%2F%28n%2Bkr%29%5C+%28q_0%29%7D+e_%7Br+q_0+%5Bq%27_1%2C+%5Ctilde+q%27_1%5D%7D%28%5Cfrac%7Bc_1%7D%7Bn%7D+%29+e_%7Bq_0+%5Bq%27_2%2C+%5Ctilde+q%27_2%5D%7D%28%5Cfrac%7Bc_2%7D%7Bn%2Bkr%7D+%29&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0' alt='&#92;displaystyle 1_{b/n=b&#039;/(n+kr)&#92; (q_0)} e_{r q_0 [q&#039;_1, &#92;tilde q&#039;_1]}(&#92;frac{c_1}{n} ) e_{q_0 [q&#039;_2, &#92;tilde q&#039;_2]}(&#92;frac{c_2}{n+kr} )' title='&#92;displaystyle 1_{b/n=b&#039;/(n+kr)&#92; (q_0)} e_{r q_0 [q&#039;_1, &#92;tilde q&#039;_1]}(&#92;frac{c_1}{n} ) e_{q_0 [q&#039;_2, &#92;tilde q&#039;_2]}(&#92;frac{c_2}{n+kr} )' class='latex' /></p> <p> for some <img src='http://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7Bc_1%2Cc_2%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0' alt='{c_1,c_2}' title='{c_1,c_2}' class='latex' /> with <img src='http://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7B%28c_1%2Cr%29+%3D+%28h+%5Ctilde+q%27_1+%5Ctilde+q%27_2+-+%5Ctilde+h+q%27_1+q%27_2%2C+r%29%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0' alt='{(c_1,r) = (h &#92;tilde q&#039;_1 &#92;tilde q&#039;_2 - &#92;tilde h q&#039;_1 q&#039;_2, r)}' title='{(c_1,r) = (h &#92;tilde q&#039;_1 &#92;tilde q&#039;_2 - &#92;tilde h q&#039;_1 q&#039;_2, r)}' class='latex' />. By the second part of Corollary <a href="#dons">11</a> we may thus bound the previous expression by <p align="center"><img src='http://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%5Cdisplaystyle++%5Csum_%7B1+%5Cleq+h%2C+%5Ctilde+h+%5Cleq+H%7D+%5Csum_%7Bq%27_1%2Cq%27_2%2C%5Ctilde+q%27_1%2C%5Ctilde+q%27_2+%5Csim+Q%2Fq_0%3A+%28q%27_1%2Cq%27_2%29+%3D+%28%5Ctilde+q%27_1%2C%5Ctilde+q%27_2%29+%3D+1%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0' alt='&#92;displaystyle &#92;sum_{1 &#92;leq h, &#92;tilde h &#92;leq H} &#92;sum_{q&#039;_1,q&#039;_2,&#92;tilde q&#039;_1,&#92;tilde q&#039;_2 &#92;sim Q/q_0: (q&#039;_1,q&#039;_2) = (&#92;tilde q&#039;_1,&#92;tilde q&#039;_2) = 1}' title='&#92;displaystyle &#92;sum_{1 &#92;leq h, &#92;tilde h &#92;leq H} &#92;sum_{q&#039;_1,q&#039;_2,&#92;tilde q&#039;_1,&#92;tilde q&#039;_2 &#92;sim Q/q_0: (q&#039;_1,q&#039;_2) = (&#92;tilde q&#039;_1,&#92;tilde q&#039;_2) = 1}' class='latex' /></p> <p align="center"><img src='http://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%5Cdisplaystyle+%28r+q_0+q%27_1+q%27_2+%5Ctilde+q%27_1+%5Ctilde+q%27_2%29%5E%7B1%2F2%7D+%2B+%28h+%5Ctilde+q%27_1+%5Ctilde+q%27_2+-+%5Ctilde+h+q%27_1+q%27_2%2C+r%29+R%5E%7B-1%7D+N.&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0' alt='&#92;displaystyle (r q_0 q&#039;_1 q&#039;_2 &#92;tilde q&#039;_1 &#92;tilde q&#039;_2)^{1/2} + (h &#92;tilde q&#039;_1 &#92;tilde q&#039;_2 - &#92;tilde h q&#039;_1 q&#039;_2, r) R^{-1} N.' title='&#92;displaystyle (r q_0 q&#039;_1 q&#039;_2 &#92;tilde q&#039;_1 &#92;tilde q&#039;_2)^{1/2} + (h &#92;tilde q&#039;_1 &#92;tilde q&#039;_2 - &#92;tilde h q&#039;_1 q&#039;_2, r) R^{-1} N.' class='latex' /></p> <p> By the divisor bound and Lemma 5 of <a href="http://terrytao.wordpress.com/2013/06/14/estimation-of-the-type-iii-sums/">this previous post</a>, this sums to <p align="center"><img src='http://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%5Cdisplaystyle++%5Clessapprox+H%5E2+%28Q%2Fq_0%29%5E4+%28+%28+R+q_0+%28Q%2Fq_0%29%5E4+%29%5E%7B1%2F2%7D+%2B+R%5E%7B-1%7D+N+%29.&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0' alt='&#92;displaystyle &#92;lessapprox H^2 (Q/q_0)^4 ( ( R q_0 (Q/q_0)^4 )^{1/2} + R^{-1} N ).' title='&#92;displaystyle &#92;lessapprox H^2 (Q/q_0)^4 ( ( R q_0 (Q/q_0)^4 )^{1/2} + R^{-1} N ).' class='latex' /></p> <p> Discarding some factors of <img src='http://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7Bq_0%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0' alt='{q_0}' title='{q_0}' class='latex' />, it suffices to show that <p align="center"><img src='http://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%5Cdisplaystyle++%28RQ%5E4%29%5E%7B1%2F2%7D+%2B+R%5E%7B-1%7D+N+%5Clessapprox+H%5E%7B-2%7D+N.&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0' alt='&#92;displaystyle (RQ^4)^{1/2} + R^{-1} N &#92;lessapprox H^{-2} N.' title='&#92;displaystyle (RQ^4)^{1/2} + R^{-1} N &#92;lessapprox H^{-2} N.' class='latex' /></p> <p> From <a href="#hqq">(31)</a>, <a href="#creep">(21)</a>, <a href="#lin">(5)</a> we have <img src='http://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7BQ+%5Clessapprox+x%5E%7B1%2F2%2B2%5Cvarpi%7D+R%5E%7B-1%7D%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0' alt='{Q &#92;lessapprox x^{1/2+2&#92;varpi} R^{-1}}' title='{Q &#92;lessapprox x^{1/2+2&#92;varpi} R^{-1}}' class='latex' /> and <img src='http://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7BH+%5Clessapprox+x%5E%7B4%5Cvarpi%2B%5Cepsilon%7D+N+R%5E%7B-1%7D%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0' alt='{H &#92;lessapprox x^{4&#92;varpi+&#92;epsilon} N R^{-1}}' title='{H &#92;lessapprox x^{4&#92;varpi+&#92;epsilon} N R^{-1}}' class='latex' />, so the previous estimate will be implied by <p align="center"><img src='http://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%5Cdisplaystyle++%28x%5E%7B2%2B8%5Cvarpi%7D+R%5E%7B-3%7D%29%5E%7B1%2F2%7D+%2B+%5Cfrac%7B1%7D%7BR%7D+N+%5Clessapprox+x%5E%7B-8%5Cvarpi-2%5Cepsilon%7D+R%5E2+N%5E%7B-1%7D.&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0' alt='&#92;displaystyle (x^{2+8&#92;varpi} R^{-3})^{1/2} + &#92;frac{1}{R} N &#92;lessapprox x^{-8&#92;varpi-2&#92;epsilon} R^2 N^{-1}.' title='&#92;displaystyle (x^{2+8&#92;varpi} R^{-3})^{1/2} + &#92;frac{1}{R} N &#92;lessapprox x^{-8&#92;varpi-2&#92;epsilon} R^2 N^{-1}.' class='latex' /></p> <p> From <a href="#crop">(20)</a>, this will be implied by <p align="center"><img src='http://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%5Cdisplaystyle++%28x%5E%7B2%2B8%5Cvarpi%2B3%5Cdelta%2B3%5Cepsilon%7D%29%5E%7B1%2F2%7D+N%5E%7B-3%2F2%7D+%2B+x%5E%7B%5Cdelta%2B%5Cepsilon%7D+%5Clessapprox+x%5E%7B-8%5Cvarpi-2%5Cdelta-4%5Cepsilon%7D+N&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0' alt='&#92;displaystyle (x^{2+8&#92;varpi+3&#92;delta+3&#92;epsilon})^{1/2} N^{-3/2} + x^{&#92;delta+&#92;epsilon} &#92;lessapprox x^{-8&#92;varpi-2&#92;delta-4&#92;epsilon} N' title='&#92;displaystyle (x^{2+8&#92;varpi+3&#92;delta+3&#92;epsilon})^{1/2} N^{-3/2} + x^{&#92;delta+&#92;epsilon} &#92;lessapprox x^{-8&#92;varpi-2&#92;delta-4&#92;epsilon} N' class='latex' /></p> <p> or equivalently that <p align="center"><img src='http://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%5Cdisplaystyle++x%5E%7B%5Cfrac%7B2%7D%7B5%7D+%2B+%5Cfrac%7B24%7D%7B5%7D+%5Cvarpi+%2B+%5Cfrac%7B7%7D%7B5%7D+%5Cdelta+%2B+%5Cfrac%7B11%7D%7B5%7D+%5Cepsilon%7D+%5Clessapprox+N&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0' alt='&#92;displaystyle x^{&#92;frac{2}{5} + &#92;frac{24}{5} &#92;varpi + &#92;frac{7}{5} &#92;delta + &#92;frac{11}{5} &#92;epsilon} &#92;lessapprox N' title='&#92;displaystyle x^{&#92;frac{2}{5} + &#92;frac{24}{5} &#92;varpi + &#92;frac{7}{5} &#92;delta + &#92;frac{11}{5} &#92;epsilon} &#92;lessapprox N' class='latex' /></p> <p> and <p align="center"><img src='http://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%5Cdisplaystyle++x%5E%7B8+%5Cvarpi+%2B+3+%5Cdelta+%2B+5+%5Cepsilon%7D+%5Clessapprox+N&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0' alt='&#92;displaystyle x^{8 &#92;varpi + 3 &#92;delta + 5 &#92;epsilon} &#92;lessapprox N' title='&#92;displaystyle x^{8 &#92;varpi + 3 &#92;delta + 5 &#92;epsilon} &#92;lessapprox N' class='latex' /></p> <p> which by <a href="#xss-2">(8)</a> is obeyed whenever <p align="center"><img src='http://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%5Cdisplaystyle++68+%5Cvarpi+%2B+14+%5Cdelta+%3C+1&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0' alt='&#92;displaystyle 68 &#92;varpi + 14 &#92;delta &lt; 1' title='&#92;displaystyle 68 &#92;varpi + 14 &#92;delta &lt; 1' class='latex' /></p> <p> and <p align="center"><img src='http://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%5Cdisplaystyle++20+%5Cvarpi+%2B+6+%5Cdelta+%3C+1.&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0' alt='&#92;displaystyle 20 &#92;varpi + 6 &#92;delta &lt; 1.' title='&#92;displaystyle 20 &#92;varpi + 6 &#92;delta &lt; 1.' class='latex' /></p> <p> The second condition is implied by the first and may be deleted. The proof of Theorem <a href="#t2-precise">5</a> is now complete.</p> <p align="center"><b> &mdash; 4. Type III estimate &mdash; </b></p> <p> We now prove Theorem <a href="#t3-precise">6</a>. Let <img src='http://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7BM%2CN_1%2CN_2%2CN_3%2C%5Calpha%2C%5Cpsi_1%2C%5Cpsi_2%2C%5Cpsi_3%2CI%2Ca%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0' alt='{M,N_1,N_2,N_3,&#92;alpha,&#92;psi_1,&#92;psi_2,&#92;psi_3,I,a}' title='{M,N_1,N_2,N_3,&#92;alpha,&#92;psi_1,&#92;psi_2,&#92;psi_3,I,a}' class='latex' /> be as in the definition of <img src='http://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7BType%27%27_%7BIII%7D%5B%5Cvarpi%2C%5Cdelta%2C%5Csigma%5D%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0' alt='{Type&#039;&#039;_{III}[&#92;varpi,&#92;delta,&#92;sigma]}' title='{Type&#039;&#039;_{III}[&#92;varpi,&#92;delta,&#92;sigma]}' class='latex' />. We will not need the full strength of double dense divisibility here, and work instead with single dense divisibility. By a finer-than-dyadic decomposition (and using the Bombieri-Vinogradov theorem to handle small moduli), it suffices to show that </p> <p align="center"><img src='http://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%5Cdisplaystyle++%5Csum_%7Bq+%5Cin+%7B%5Cmathcal+S%7D_I+%5Ccap+%7B%5Cmathcal+D%7D_%7Bx%5E%5Cdelta%7D%3A+q+%3D+%281%2BO%28x%5E%7B-%5Cepsilon%7D%29%29+Q%7D+%7C%5CDelta%28%5Calpha+%2A+%5Cpsi_1+%2A+%5Cpsi_2+%2A+%5Cpsi_3%3B+a%5C+%28q%29%29%7C+%5Clessapprox+x%5E%7B-2%5Cepsilon%7D+M+N&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0' alt='&#92;displaystyle &#92;sum_{q &#92;in {&#92;mathcal S}_I &#92;cap {&#92;mathcal D}_{x^&#92;delta}: q = (1+O(x^{-&#92;epsilon})) Q} |&#92;Delta(&#92;alpha * &#92;psi_1 * &#92;psi_2 * &#92;psi_3; a&#92; (q))| &#92;lessapprox x^{-2&#92;epsilon} M N' title='&#92;displaystyle &#92;sum_{q &#92;in {&#92;mathcal S}_I &#92;cap {&#92;mathcal D}_{x^&#92;delta}: q = (1+O(x^{-&#92;epsilon})) Q} |&#92;Delta(&#92;alpha * &#92;psi_1 * &#92;psi_2 * &#92;psi_3; a&#92; (q))| &#92;lessapprox x^{-2&#92;epsilon} M N' class='latex' /></p> <p> for some sufficiently small fixed <img src='http://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7B%5Cepsilon%3E0%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0' alt='{&#92;epsilon&gt;0}' title='{&#92;epsilon&gt;0}' class='latex' /> and all <a name="qp"> <p align="center"><img src='http://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%5Cdisplaystyle++x%5E%7B1%2F2%7D+%5Clessapprox+Q+%5Cll+x%5E%7B1%2F2%2B2%5Cvarpi%7D%2C+%5C+%5C+%5C+%5C+%5C+%2836%29&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0' alt='&#92;displaystyle x^{1/2} &#92;lessapprox Q &#92;ll x^{1/2+2&#92;varpi}, &#92; &#92; &#92; &#92; &#92; (36)' title='&#92;displaystyle x^{1/2} &#92;lessapprox Q &#92;ll x^{1/2+2&#92;varpi}, &#92; &#92; &#92; &#92; &#92; (36)' class='latex' /></p> <p></a> where <img src='http://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7BN+%3A%3D+N_1+N_2+N_3%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0' alt='{N := N_1 N_2 N_3}' title='{N := N_1 N_2 N_3}' class='latex' />.</p> <p> Henceforth we work with a single choice of <img src='http://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7BQ%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0' alt='{Q}' title='{Q}' class='latex' />, and abbreviate the <img src='http://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7Bq%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0' alt='{q}' title='{q}' class='latex' /> summation as <img src='http://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7B%5Csum_q%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0' alt='{&#92;sum_q}' title='{&#92;sum_q}' class='latex' />. The left-hand side may then be written as </p> <p align="center"><img src='http://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%5Cdisplaystyle++%5Csum_q+c_q+%5CDelta%28%5Calpha+%2A+%5Cpsi_1+%2A+%5Cpsi_2+%2A+%5Cpsi_3%3B+a%5C+%28q%29%29&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0' alt='&#92;displaystyle &#92;sum_q c_q &#92;Delta(&#92;alpha * &#92;psi_1 * &#92;psi_2 * &#92;psi_3; a&#92; (q))' title='&#92;displaystyle &#92;sum_q c_q &#92;Delta(&#92;alpha * &#92;psi_1 * &#92;psi_2 * &#92;psi_3; a&#92; (q))' class='latex' /></p> <p> for some bounded sequence <img src='http://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7Bc_q%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0' alt='{c_q}' title='{c_q}' class='latex' />. So it suffices to show that <p align="center"><img src='http://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%5Cdisplaystyle++%5Csum_q+c_q+%5Csum_%7Bn+%3D+a%5C+%28q%29%7D+%5Calpha+%2A+%5Cpsi_1+%2A+%5Cpsi_2+%2A+%5Cpsi_3%28n%29+%3D+X+%2B+O%28+x%5E%7B-2%5Cepsilon%2Bo%281%29%7D+M+N+%29&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0' alt='&#92;displaystyle &#92;sum_q c_q &#92;sum_{n = a&#92; (q)} &#92;alpha * &#92;psi_1 * &#92;psi_2 * &#92;psi_3(n) = X + O( x^{-2&#92;epsilon+o(1)} M N )' title='&#92;displaystyle &#92;sum_q c_q &#92;sum_{n = a&#92; (q)} &#92;alpha * &#92;psi_1 * &#92;psi_2 * &#92;psi_3(n) = X + O( x^{-2&#92;epsilon+o(1)} M N )' class='latex' /></p> <p> for some <img src='http://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7BX%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0' alt='{X}' title='{X}' class='latex' /> that is independent of <img src='http://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7Ba%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0' alt='{a}' title='{a}' class='latex' />, as the claim then follows by averaging in <img src='http://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7Ba%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0' alt='{a}' title='{a}' class='latex' />.</p> <p> The left-hand side may be rewritten as <a name="tin"> <p align="center"><img src='http://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%5Cdisplaystyle++%5Csum_q+c_q+%5Csum_%7Bm%3A+%28m%2Cq%29%3D1%7D+%5Calpha%28m%29+%5Csum_%7Bn_1%2Cn_2%2Cn_3%7D+%5Cpsi_1%28n_1%29+%5Cpsi_2%28n_2%29+%5Cpsi_3%28n_3%29+1_%7Bmn_1n_2n_3+%3D+a%5C+%28q%29%7D.+%5C+%5C+%5C+%5C+%5C+%2837%29&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0' alt='&#92;displaystyle &#92;sum_q c_q &#92;sum_{m: (m,q)=1} &#92;alpha(m) &#92;sum_{n_1,n_2,n_3} &#92;psi_1(n_1) &#92;psi_2(n_2) &#92;psi_3(n_3) 1_{mn_1n_2n_3 = a&#92; (q)}. &#92; &#92; &#92; &#92; &#92; (37)' title='&#92;displaystyle &#92;sum_q c_q &#92;sum_{m: (m,q)=1} &#92;alpha(m) &#92;sum_{n_1,n_2,n_3} &#92;psi_1(n_1) &#92;psi_2(n_2) &#92;psi_3(n_3) 1_{mn_1n_2n_3 = a&#92; (q)}. &#92; &#92; &#92; &#92; &#92; (37)' class='latex' /></p> <p></a> Note that for <img src='http://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7Bi%3D1%2C2%2C3%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0' alt='{i=1,2,3}' title='{i=1,2,3}' class='latex' /> one has </p> <p align="center"><img src='http://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%5Cdisplaystyle++N_i+%5Clessapprox+x%5E%7B1%2F2-%5Csigma%7D+%5Clessapprox+x%5E%7B-%5Csigma%7D+x%5E%7B1%2F2%7D+%5Clessapprox+x%5E%7B-%5Csigma%7D+Q.&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0' alt='&#92;displaystyle N_i &#92;lessapprox x^{1/2-&#92;sigma} &#92;lessapprox x^{-&#92;sigma} x^{1/2} &#92;lessapprox x^{-&#92;sigma} Q.' title='&#92;displaystyle N_i &#92;lessapprox x^{1/2-&#92;sigma} &#92;lessapprox x^{-&#92;sigma} x^{1/2} &#92;lessapprox x^{-&#92;sigma} Q.' class='latex' /></p> <p> By Fourier inversion we have <p align="center"><img src='http://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%5Cdisplaystyle++%5Cpsi_i%28n_i%29+%3D+%5Cfrac%7B1%7D%7Bq%7D+%5Csum_%7B-q%2F2+%3C+h_i+%5Cleq+q%2F2%7D+%5Chat+%5Cpsi_i%28h_i%2Fq%29+e_%7Bq%7D%28+h_i+n_i+%29+&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0' alt='&#92;displaystyle &#92;psi_i(n_i) = &#92;frac{1}{q} &#92;sum_{-q/2 &lt; h_i &#92;leq q/2} &#92;hat &#92;psi_i(h_i/q) e_{q}( h_i n_i ) ' title='&#92;displaystyle &#92;psi_i(n_i) = &#92;frac{1}{q} &#92;sum_{-q/2 &lt; h_i &#92;leq q/2} &#92;hat &#92;psi_i(h_i/q) e_{q}( h_i n_i ) ' class='latex' /></p> <p> for all <img src='http://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7B-q%2F2+%3C+n_i+%5Cleq+q%2F2%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0' alt='{-q/2 &lt; n_i &#92;leq q/2}' title='{-q/2 &lt; n_i &#92;leq q/2}' class='latex' />, where <img src='http://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7B%5Chat+%5Cpsi_i%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0' alt='{&#92;hat &#92;psi_i}' title='{&#92;hat &#92;psi_i}' class='latex' /> is the Fourier transform <p align="center"><img src='http://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%5Cdisplaystyle++%5Chat+%5Cpsi_i%28%5Ctheta%29+%3A%3D+%5Csum_%7Bn_i%7D+%5Cpsi_i%28n_i%29+e%28-%5Ctheta+n_i%29.&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0' alt='&#92;displaystyle &#92;hat &#92;psi_i(&#92;theta) := &#92;sum_{n_i} &#92;psi_i(n_i) e(-&#92;theta n_i).' title='&#92;displaystyle &#92;hat &#92;psi_i(&#92;theta) := &#92;sum_{n_i} &#92;psi_i(n_i) e(-&#92;theta n_i).' class='latex' /></p> <p> From the smoothness of <img src='http://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7B%5Cpsi_i%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0' alt='{&#92;psi_i}' title='{&#92;psi_i}' class='latex' />, Poisson summation, and integration by parts we have the decay estimates <p align="center"><img src='http://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%5Cdisplaystyle++%7C%5Chat+%5Cpsi_i%28%5Ctheta%29%7C+%5Clessapprox+N_i+%281+%2B+N_i+%7C%5Ctheta%7C%29%5E%7B-C%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0' alt='&#92;displaystyle |&#92;hat &#92;psi_i(&#92;theta)| &#92;lessapprox N_i (1 + N_i |&#92;theta|)^{-C}' title='&#92;displaystyle |&#92;hat &#92;psi_i(&#92;theta)| &#92;lessapprox N_i (1 + N_i |&#92;theta|)^{-C}' class='latex' /></p> <p> for any fixed <img src='http://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7BC+%5Cgeq+0%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0' alt='{C &#92;geq 0}' title='{C &#92;geq 0}' class='latex' /> and any <img src='http://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7B-1%2F2+%5Cleq+%5Ctheta+%5Cleq+1%2F2%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0' alt='{-1/2 &#92;leq &#92;theta &#92;leq 1/2}' title='{-1/2 &#92;leq &#92;theta &#92;leq 1/2}' class='latex' />. More generally, we also have the derivative estimates <p align="center"><img src='http://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%5Cdisplaystyle++%7C%5Cfrac%7Bd%5Ej%7D%7Bd%5Ctheta%5Ej%7D+%5Chat+%5Cpsi_i%28%5Ctheta%29%7C+%5Clessapprox+N_i%5E%7B1%2Bj%7D+%281+%2B+N_i+%7C%5Ctheta%7C%29%5E%7B-C%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0' alt='&#92;displaystyle |&#92;frac{d^j}{d&#92;theta^j} &#92;hat &#92;psi_i(&#92;theta)| &#92;lessapprox N_i^{1+j} (1 + N_i |&#92;theta|)^{-C}' title='&#92;displaystyle |&#92;frac{d^j}{d&#92;theta^j} &#92;hat &#92;psi_i(&#92;theta)| &#92;lessapprox N_i^{1+j} (1 + N_i |&#92;theta|)^{-C}' class='latex' /></p> <p> for any fixed <img src='http://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7BC%2Cj+%5Cgeq+0%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0' alt='{C,j &#92;geq 0}' title='{C,j &#92;geq 0}' class='latex' /> and any <img src='http://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7B-1%2F2+%5Cleq+%5Ctheta+%5Cleq+1%2F2%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0' alt='{-1/2 &#92;leq &#92;theta &#92;leq 1/2}' title='{-1/2 &#92;leq &#92;theta &#92;leq 1/2}' class='latex' />. We thus have <p align="center"><img src='http://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%5Cdisplaystyle++%5Chat+%5Cpsi_i%28h_i%2Fq%29+%3D+O%28x%5E%7B-100%7D%29&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0' alt='&#92;displaystyle &#92;hat &#92;psi_i(h_i/q) = O(x^{-100})' title='&#92;displaystyle &#92;hat &#92;psi_i(h_i/q) = O(x^{-100})' class='latex' /></p> <p> (say) when <img src='http://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7B%7Ch_i%7C+%3E+x%5E%5Cepsilon+H_i%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0' alt='{|h_i| &gt; x^&#92;epsilon H_i}' title='{|h_i| &gt; x^&#92;epsilon H_i}' class='latex' />, where <p align="center"><img src='http://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%5Cdisplaystyle++H_i+%3A%3D+Q+%2F+N_i.&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0' alt='&#92;displaystyle H_i := Q / N_i.' title='&#92;displaystyle H_i := Q / N_i.' class='latex' /></p> <p> Furthermore, for <img src='http://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7B%7Ch_i%7C+%5Cleq+x%5E%5Cepsilon+H_i%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0' alt='{|h_i| &#92;leq x^&#92;epsilon H_i}' title='{|h_i| &#92;leq x^&#92;epsilon H_i}' class='latex' />, we can perform a Taylor expansion around <img src='http://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7Bq%3DQ%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0' alt='{q=Q}' title='{q=Q}' class='latex' /> and conclude that <p align="center"><img src='http://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%5Cdisplaystyle++%5Cfrac%7B1%7D%7Bq%7D+%5Chat+%5Cpsi_i%28h_i%2Fq%29+%3D+%5Cfrac%7B1%7D%7BH_i%7D+%5Csum_%7Bj%3D0%7D%5EJ+c_%7Bi%2Cj%2Ch_i%7D+%28%5Cfrac%7Bq-Q%7D%7BQ%7D%29%5Ej+%2B+O%28+x%5E%7B-100%7D+%29+&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0' alt='&#92;displaystyle &#92;frac{1}{q} &#92;hat &#92;psi_i(h_i/q) = &#92;frac{1}{H_i} &#92;sum_{j=0}^J c_{i,j,h_i} (&#92;frac{q-Q}{Q})^j + O( x^{-100} ) ' title='&#92;displaystyle &#92;frac{1}{q} &#92;hat &#92;psi_i(h_i/q) = &#92;frac{1}{H_i} &#92;sum_{j=0}^J c_{i,j,h_i} (&#92;frac{q-Q}{Q})^j + O( x^{-100} ) ' class='latex' /></p> <p> for some fixed <img src='http://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7BJ+%3E+0%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0' alt='{J &gt; 0}' title='{J &gt; 0}' class='latex' /> (depending on <img src='http://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7B%5Cepsilon%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0' alt='{&#92;epsilon}' title='{&#92;epsilon}' class='latex' />), any <img src='http://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7Bq+%3D+%281%2BO%28x%5E%7B-%5Cepsilon%7D%29%29+Q%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0' alt='{q = (1+O(x^{-&#92;epsilon})) Q}' title='{q = (1+O(x^{-&#92;epsilon})) Q}' class='latex' />, and some coefficients <img src='http://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7Bc_%7Bi%2Cj%2Ch_i%7D+%3D+O%281%29%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0' alt='{c_{i,j,h_i} = O(1)}' title='{c_{i,j,h_i} = O(1)}' class='latex' /> whose exact value will not be of importance to us. We may thus express <a href="#tin">(37)</a>, up to negligible errors, as the sum of a bounded number of expressions of the form <p align="center"><img src='http://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%5Cdisplaystyle++%5Cfrac%7B1%7D%7BH%7D+%5Csum_q+c%27_q+%5Csum_%7Bm%3A+%28m%2Cq%29%3D1%7D+%5Calpha%28m%29+%5Csum_%7Bh_1%2Ch_2%2Ch_3%7D+c%27%27_%7Bh_1%2Ch_2%2Ch_3%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0' alt='&#92;displaystyle &#92;frac{1}{H} &#92;sum_q c&#039;_q &#92;sum_{m: (m,q)=1} &#92;alpha(m) &#92;sum_{h_1,h_2,h_3} c&#039;&#039;_{h_1,h_2,h_3}' title='&#92;displaystyle &#92;frac{1}{H} &#92;sum_q c&#039;_q &#92;sum_{m: (m,q)=1} &#92;alpha(m) &#92;sum_{h_1,h_2,h_3} c&#039;&#039;_{h_1,h_2,h_3}' class='latex' /></p> <p align="center"><img src='http://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%5Cdisplaystyle++%5Csum_%7Bn_1%2Cn_2%2Cn_3+%5Cin+%7B%5Cbf+Z%7D%2Fq%7B%5Cbf+Z%7D%7D+e_%7Bq%7D%28+h_1+n_1+%2B+h_2+n_2+%2B+h_3+n_3+%29+1_%7Bmn_1n_2n_3+%3D+a%5C+%28q%29%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0' alt='&#92;displaystyle &#92;sum_{n_1,n_2,n_3 &#92;in {&#92;bf Z}/q{&#92;bf Z}} e_{q}( h_1 n_1 + h_2 n_2 + h_3 n_3 ) 1_{mn_1n_2n_3 = a&#92; (q)}' title='&#92;displaystyle &#92;sum_{n_1,n_2,n_3 &#92;in {&#92;bf Z}/q{&#92;bf Z}} e_{q}( h_1 n_1 + h_2 n_2 + h_3 n_3 ) 1_{mn_1n_2n_3 = a&#92; (q)}' class='latex' /></p> <p> for some bounded sequences <img src='http://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7Bc%27_q%2C+c%27%27_%7Bh_1%2Ch_2%2Ch_3%7D%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0' alt='{c&#039;_q, c&#039;&#039;_{h_1,h_2,h_3}}' title='{c&#039;_q, c&#039;&#039;_{h_1,h_2,h_3}}' class='latex' /> whose exact value will not be of importance to us other than their support, which is contained in the sets <p align="center"><img src='http://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%5Cdisplaystyle++%5C%7B+q+%3D+%281+%2B+O%28x%5E%7B-%5Cepsilon%7D%29%29+Q%3A+q+%5Cin+%7B%5Cmathcal+S%7D_I+%5Ccap+%7B%5Cmathcal+D%7D_%7Bx%5E%5Cdelta%7D+%5C%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0' alt='&#92;displaystyle &#92;{ q = (1 + O(x^{-&#92;epsilon})) Q: q &#92;in {&#92;mathcal S}_I &#92;cap {&#92;mathcal D}_{x^&#92;delta} &#92;}' title='&#92;displaystyle &#92;{ q = (1 + O(x^{-&#92;epsilon})) Q: q &#92;in {&#92;mathcal S}_I &#92;cap {&#92;mathcal D}_{x^&#92;delta} &#92;}' class='latex' /></p> <p> and <p align="center"><img src='http://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%5Cdisplaystyle++%5C%7B+%28h_1%2Ch_2%2Ch_3%29%3A+%7Ch_1%7C+%5Cleq+x%5E%5Cepsilon+H_1%2C+%7Ch_2%7C+%5Cleq+x%5E%5Cepsilon+H_2%2C+%7Ch_3%7C+%5Cleq+x%5E%5Cepsilon+H_3+%5C%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0' alt='&#92;displaystyle &#92;{ (h_1,h_2,h_3): |h_1| &#92;leq x^&#92;epsilon H_1, |h_2| &#92;leq x^&#92;epsilon H_2, |h_3| &#92;leq x^&#92;epsilon H_3 &#92;}' title='&#92;displaystyle &#92;{ (h_1,h_2,h_3): |h_1| &#92;leq x^&#92;epsilon H_1, |h_2| &#92;leq x^&#92;epsilon H_2, |h_3| &#92;leq x^&#92;epsilon H_3 &#92;}' class='latex' /></p> <p> respectively, and where <p align="center"><img src='http://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%5Cdisplaystyle++H+%3A%3D+H_1+H_2+H_3+%3D+Q%5E3+%2F+N.&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0' alt='&#92;displaystyle H := H_1 H_2 H_3 = Q^3 / N.' title='&#92;displaystyle H := H_1 H_2 H_3 = Q^3 / N.' class='latex' /></p> <p> If we then introduce the modified hyper-Kloosterman sum <p align="center"><img src='http://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%5Cdisplaystyle++F%28+h_1%2Ch_2%2Ch_3%2C+a%3B+q%29+%3A%3D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0' alt='&#92;displaystyle F( h_1,h_2,h_3, a; q) :=' title='&#92;displaystyle F( h_1,h_2,h_3, a; q) :=' class='latex' /></p> <p align="center"><img src='http://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%5Cdisplaystyle++%5Cfrac%7B1%7D%7Bq%7D+%5Csum_%7Bn_1%2Cn_2%2Cn_3+%5Cin+%28%7B%5Cbf+Z%7D%2Fq%7B%5Cbf+Z%7D%29%5E%5Ctimes%7D+e_%7Bq%7D%28+h_1+n_1+%2B+h_2+n_2+%2B+h_3+n_3+%29+1_%7Bn_1n_2n_3+%3D+a%5C+%28q%29%7D+&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0' alt='&#92;displaystyle &#92;frac{1}{q} &#92;sum_{n_1,n_2,n_3 &#92;in ({&#92;bf Z}/q{&#92;bf Z})^&#92;times} e_{q}( h_1 n_1 + h_2 n_2 + h_3 n_3 ) 1_{n_1n_2n_3 = a&#92; (q)} ' title='&#92;displaystyle &#92;frac{1}{q} &#92;sum_{n_1,n_2,n_3 &#92;in ({&#92;bf Z}/q{&#92;bf Z})^&#92;times} e_{q}( h_1 n_1 + h_2 n_2 + h_3 n_3 ) 1_{n_1n_2n_3 = a&#92; (q)} ' class='latex' /></p> <p> defined for <img src='http://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7Bh_1%2Ch_2%2Ch_3+%5Cin+%7B%5Cbf+Z%7D%2Fq%7B%5Cbf+Z%7D%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0' alt='{h_1,h_2,h_3 &#92;in {&#92;bf Z}/q{&#92;bf Z}}' title='{h_1,h_2,h_3 &#92;in {&#92;bf Z}/q{&#92;bf Z}}' class='latex' /> and <img src='http://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7Ba+%5Cin+%28%7B%5Cbf+Z%7D%2Fq%7B%5Cbf+Z%7D%29%5E%5Ctimes%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0' alt='{a &#92;in ({&#92;bf Z}/q{&#92;bf Z})^&#92;times}' title='{a &#92;in ({&#92;bf Z}/q{&#92;bf Z})^&#92;times}' class='latex' />, then our objective is now to show that <p align="center"><img src='http://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%5Cdisplaystyle++%5Csum_q+%5Ctilde+c%27_q+%5Csum_%7Bm%3A+%28m%2Cq%29%3D1%7D+%5Calpha%28m%29+%5Csum_%7Bh_1%2Ch_2%2Ch_3%7D+c%27%27_%7Bh_1%2Ch_2%2Ch_3%7D+F%28+h_1%2Ch_2%2Ch_3%2C+a+%5Coverline%7Bm%7D%2C+q%29+&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0' alt='&#92;displaystyle &#92;sum_q &#92;tilde c&#039;_q &#92;sum_{m: (m,q)=1} &#92;alpha(m) &#92;sum_{h_1,h_2,h_3} c&#039;&#039;_{h_1,h_2,h_3} F( h_1,h_2,h_3, a &#92;overline{m}, q) ' title='&#92;displaystyle &#92;sum_q &#92;tilde c&#039;_q &#92;sum_{m: (m,q)=1} &#92;alpha(m) &#92;sum_{h_1,h_2,h_3} c&#039;&#039;_{h_1,h_2,h_3} F( h_1,h_2,h_3, a &#92;overline{m}, q) ' class='latex' /></p> <p align="center"><img src='http://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%5Cdisplaystyle+%3D+X%27+%2B+O%28+x%5E%7B-2%5Cepsilon%2Bo%281%29%7D+H+MN+%2F+Q%29&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0' alt='&#92;displaystyle = X&#039; + O( x^{-2&#92;epsilon+o(1)} H MN / Q)' title='&#92;displaystyle = X&#039; + O( x^{-2&#92;epsilon+o(1)} H MN / Q)' class='latex' /></p> <p> for some <img src='http://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7BX%27%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0' alt='{X&#039;}' title='{X&#039;}' class='latex' /> that does not depend on <img src='http://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7Ba%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0' alt='{a}' title='{a}' class='latex' />, where <img src='http://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7B%5Coverline%7Bm%7D%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0' alt='{&#92;overline{m}}' title='{&#92;overline{m}}' class='latex' /> is the reciprocal of <img src='http://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7Bm%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0' alt='{m}' title='{m}' class='latex' /> in <img src='http://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7B%7B%5Cbf+Z%7D%2Fq%7B%5Cbf+Z%7D%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0' alt='{{&#92;bf Z}/q{&#92;bf Z}}' title='{{&#92;bf Z}/q{&#92;bf Z}}' class='latex' /> and <img src='http://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7B%5Ctilde+c%27_q+%3A%3D+%5Cfrac%7Bq%7D%7BQ%7D+c%27_q%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0' alt='{&#92;tilde c&#039;_q := &#92;frac{q}{Q} c&#039;_q}' title='{&#92;tilde c&#039;_q := &#92;frac{q}{Q} c&#039;_q}' class='latex' />.</p> <p> We may rewrite <img src='http://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7BHMN%2FQ%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0' alt='{HMN/Q}' title='{HMN/Q}' class='latex' /> as <img src='http://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7BM+Q%5E2%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0' alt='{M Q^2}' title='{M Q^2}' class='latex' />. Observe that <img src='http://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7BF%28h_1%2Ch_2%2Ch_3%2C+a+%5Coverline%7Bm%7D%3B+q%29%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0' alt='{F(h_1,h_2,h_3, a &#92;overline{m}; q)}' title='{F(h_1,h_2,h_3, a &#92;overline{m}; q)}' class='latex' /> is independent of <img src='http://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7Ba%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0' alt='{a}' title='{a}' class='latex' /> if one of <img src='http://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7Bh_1%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0' alt='{h_1}' title='{h_1}' class='latex' /> vanishes (as can be seen by dilating <img src='http://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7Bn_1%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0' alt='{n_1}' title='{n_1}' class='latex' />), and similarly if <img src='http://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7Bh_2%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0' alt='{h_2}' title='{h_2}' class='latex' /> or <img src='http://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7Bh_3%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0' alt='{h_3}' title='{h_3}' class='latex' /> vanishes. Thus we may delete the case <img src='http://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7Bh_1h_2h_3%3D0%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0' alt='{h_1h_2h_3=0}' title='{h_1h_2h_3=0}' class='latex' /> from the above sum, and reduce to showing that <a name="snore"> <p align="center"><img src='http://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%5Cdisplaystyle++%7C%5Csum_q+%5Ctilde+c%27_q+%5Csum_%7Bm%3A+%28m%2Cq%29%3D1%7D+%5Calpha%28m%29+%5Csum_%7Bh_1%2Ch_2%2Ch_3%3A+h_1h_2h_3+%5Cneq+0%7D+c%27%27_%7Bh_1%2Ch_2%2Ch_3%7D+F%28+h_1%2Ch_2%2Ch_3%2C+a+%5Coverline%7Bm%7D%3B+q%29%7C+%5C+%5C+%5C+%5C+%5C+%2838%29&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0' alt='&#92;displaystyle |&#92;sum_q &#92;tilde c&#039;_q &#92;sum_{m: (m,q)=1} &#92;alpha(m) &#92;sum_{h_1,h_2,h_3: h_1h_2h_3 &#92;neq 0} c&#039;&#039;_{h_1,h_2,h_3} F( h_1,h_2,h_3, a &#92;overline{m}; q)| &#92; &#92; &#92; &#92; &#92; (38)' title='&#92;displaystyle |&#92;sum_q &#92;tilde c&#039;_q &#92;sum_{m: (m,q)=1} &#92;alpha(m) &#92;sum_{h_1,h_2,h_3: h_1h_2h_3 &#92;neq 0} c&#039;&#039;_{h_1,h_2,h_3} F( h_1,h_2,h_3, a &#92;overline{m}; q)| &#92; &#92; &#92; &#92; &#92; (38)' class='latex' /></p> <p></a> </p> <p align="center"><img src='http://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%5Cdisplaystyle++%5Clessapprox+x%5E%7B-2%5Cepsilon%7D+M+Q%5E2.&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0' alt='&#92;displaystyle &#92;lessapprox x^{-2&#92;epsilon} M Q^2.' title='&#92;displaystyle &#92;lessapprox x^{-2&#92;epsilon} M Q^2.' class='latex' /></p> <p> At this point we need to account for a technical problem that the <img src='http://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7Bh_1%2Ch_2%2Ch_3%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0' alt='{h_1,h_2,h_3}' title='{h_1,h_2,h_3}' class='latex' /> may still share a common factor with <img src='http://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7Bq%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0' alt='{q}' title='{q}' class='latex' /> even after being restricted to be non-zero. For <img src='http://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7Bi%3D1%2C2%2C3%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0' alt='{i=1,2,3}' title='{i=1,2,3}' class='latex' />, let <img src='http://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7Bb_i+%3A%3D+%5Cprod_%7Bp%7Cq%3B+p%5Ej+%7C%7C+h_i%7D+p%5Ej%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0' alt='{b_i := &#92;prod_{p|q; p^j || h_i} p^j}' title='{b_i := &#92;prod_{p|q; p^j || h_i} p^j}' class='latex' /> be the product of all the primes in <img src='http://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7Bh_i%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0' alt='{h_i}' title='{h_i}' class='latex' /> (counting multiplicity) that also divide <img src='http://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7Bq%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0' alt='{q}' title='{q}' class='latex' />; thus <img src='http://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7Bh_i+%3D+b_i+h%27_i%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0' alt='{h_i = b_i h&#039;_i}' title='{h_i = b_i h&#039;_i}' class='latex' /> where <img src='http://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7Bh%27_i%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0' alt='{h&#039;_i}' title='{h&#039;_i}' class='latex' /> is coprime to <img src='http://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7Bq%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0' alt='{q}' title='{q}' class='latex' />. As we shall see, the case <img src='http://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7Bb_1%3Db_2%3Db_3%3D1%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0' alt='{b_1=b_2=b_3=1}' title='{b_1=b_2=b_3=1}' class='latex' /> is dominant, and on a first reading one may wish to focus exclusively on this case in what follows to simplify the discussion. We then write <img src='http://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7Bb+%3A%3D+%5Cprod_%7Bp%7Cb_1b_2b_3%7D+p+%3D+%28h_1h_2h_3%2Cq%29%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0' alt='{b := &#92;prod_{p|b_1b_2b_3} p = (h_1h_2h_3,q)}' title='{b := &#92;prod_{p|b_1b_2b_3} p = (h_1h_2h_3,q)}' class='latex' />; this divides <img src='http://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7Bq%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0' alt='{q}' title='{q}' class='latex' />, so we may write <img src='http://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7Bq+%3D+bq%27%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0' alt='{q = bq&#039;}' title='{q = bq&#039;}' class='latex' />. Note that as <img src='http://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7Bq%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0' alt='{q}' title='{q}' class='latex' /> is <img src='http://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7Bx%5E%5Cdelta%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0' alt='{x^&#92;delta}' title='{x^&#92;delta}' class='latex' />-densely divisible, <img src='http://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7Bq%27%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0' alt='{q&#039;}' title='{q&#039;}' class='latex' /> is <img src='http://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7Bbx%5E%5Cdelta%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0' alt='{bx^&#92;delta}' title='{bx^&#92;delta}' class='latex' />-densely divisible, thus <img src='http://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7Bq%27+%5Cin+%7B%5Cmathcal+S%7D_I+%5Ccap+%7B%5Cmathcal+D%7D_%7Bbx%5E%5Cdelta%7D%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0' alt='{q&#039; &#92;in {&#92;mathcal S}_I &#92;cap {&#92;mathcal D}_{bx^&#92;delta}}' title='{q&#039; &#92;in {&#92;mathcal S}_I &#92;cap {&#92;mathcal D}_{bx^&#92;delta}}' class='latex' />. </p> <p> Now we factor <img src='http://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7BF%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0' alt='{F}' title='{F}' class='latex' />. From Lemma <a href="#crt">8</a> we see that </p> <p align="center"><img src='http://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%5Cdisplaystyle++F%28+h_1%2Ch_2%2Ch_3%2C+a+%5Coverline%7Bm%7D%3B+q%29+%3D+F%28+h_1+%5Coverline%7Bq%27%7D%2Ch_2+%5Coverline%7Bq%27%7D%2Ch_3+%5Coverline%7Bq%27%7D%2C+a+%5Coverline%7Bm%7D%3B+b%29+F%28+h_1+%5Coverline%7Bb%7D%2Ch_2+%5Coverline%7Bb%7D%2Ch_3+%5Coverline%7Bb%7D%2C+a+%5Coverline%7Bm%7D%3B+q%27%29.&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0' alt='&#92;displaystyle F( h_1,h_2,h_3, a &#92;overline{m}; q) = F( h_1 &#92;overline{q&#039;},h_2 &#92;overline{q&#039;},h_3 &#92;overline{q&#039;}, a &#92;overline{m}; b) F( h_1 &#92;overline{b},h_2 &#92;overline{b},h_3 &#92;overline{b}, a &#92;overline{m}; q&#039;).' title='&#92;displaystyle F( h_1,h_2,h_3, a &#92;overline{m}; q) = F( h_1 &#92;overline{q&#039;},h_2 &#92;overline{q&#039;},h_3 &#92;overline{q&#039;}, a &#92;overline{m}; b) F( h_1 &#92;overline{b},h_2 &#92;overline{b},h_3 &#92;overline{b}, a &#92;overline{m}; q&#039;).' class='latex' /></p> <p> For the second term, we observe that <img src='http://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7Bh_i+%5Coverline%7Bb%7D%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0' alt='{h_i &#92;overline{b}}' title='{h_i &#92;overline{b}}' class='latex' /> is coprime to <img src='http://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7Bq%27%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0' alt='{q&#039;}' title='{q&#039;}' class='latex' /> for <img src='http://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7Bi%3D1%2C2%2C3%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0' alt='{i=1,2,3}' title='{i=1,2,3}' class='latex' />, and so by dilating the variables <img src='http://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7Bn_1%2Cn_2%2Cn_3%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0' alt='{n_1,n_2,n_3}' title='{n_1,n_2,n_3}' class='latex' /> we have </p> <p align="center"><img src='http://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%5Cdisplaystyle++F%28+h_1+%5Coverline%7Bb%7D%2Ch_2+%5Coverline%7Bb%7D%2Ch_3+%5Coverline%7Bb%7D%2C+a+%5Coverline%7Bm%7D%3B+q%27%29+%3D+K_3%28+a+h_1+h_2+h_3+%5Coverline%7Bb%7D%5E3+%5Coverline%7Bm%7D%3B+q%27+%29&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0' alt='&#92;displaystyle F( h_1 &#92;overline{b},h_2 &#92;overline{b},h_3 &#92;overline{b}, a &#92;overline{m}; q&#039;) = K_3( a h_1 h_2 h_3 &#92;overline{b}^3 &#92;overline{m}; q&#039; )' title='&#92;displaystyle F( h_1 &#92;overline{b},h_2 &#92;overline{b},h_3 &#92;overline{b}, a &#92;overline{m}; q&#039;) = K_3( a h_1 h_2 h_3 &#92;overline{b}^3 &#92;overline{m}; q&#039; )' class='latex' /></p> <p align="center"><img src='http://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%5Cdisplaystyle++%3D+K_3%28+a_%7Bb_1%2Cb_2%2Cb_3%2Cq%27%7D+h%27_1+h%27_2+h%27_3+%5Coverline%7Bm%7D%3B+q%27%29&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0' alt='&#92;displaystyle = K_3( a_{b_1,b_2,b_3,q&#039;} h&#039;_1 h&#039;_2 h&#039;_3 &#92;overline{m}; q&#039;)' title='&#92;displaystyle = K_3( a_{b_1,b_2,b_3,q&#039;} h&#039;_1 h&#039;_2 h&#039;_3 &#92;overline{m}; q&#039;)' class='latex' /></p> <p> where <img src='http://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7Ba_%7Bb_1%2Cb_2%2Cb_3%2Cq%27%7D%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0' alt='{a_{b_1,b_2,b_3,q&#039;}}' title='{a_{b_1,b_2,b_3,q&#039;}}' class='latex' /> is the residue class <p align="center"><img src='http://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%5Cdisplaystyle++a_%7Bb_1%2Cb_2%2Cb_3%2Cq%27%7D+%3A%3D+%5Cfrac%7Ba+b_1+b_2+b_3%7D%7Bb%5E3%7D%5C+%28q%27%29&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0' alt='&#92;displaystyle a_{b_1,b_2,b_3,q&#039;} := &#92;frac{a b_1 b_2 b_3}{b^3}&#92; (q&#039;)' title='&#92;displaystyle a_{b_1,b_2,b_3,q&#039;} := &#92;frac{a b_1 b_2 b_3}{b^3}&#92; (q&#039;)' class='latex' /></p> <p> and we recall that <img src='http://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7BK_3%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0' alt='{K_3}' title='{K_3}' class='latex' /> is the normalised hyper-Kloosterman sum <p align="center"><img src='http://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%5Cdisplaystyle++K_3%28+a%3Bq%29+%3A%3D+%5Cfrac%7B1%7D%7Bq%7D+%5Csum_%7Bx%2Cy%2Cz+%5Cin+%28%7B%5Cbf+Z%7D%2Fq%7B%5Cbf+Z%7D%29%5E%5Ctimes%3A+xyz+%3D+a%5C+%28q%29%7D+e_q%28x%2By%2Bz%29.&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0' alt='&#92;displaystyle K_3( a;q) := &#92;frac{1}{q} &#92;sum_{x,y,z &#92;in ({&#92;bf Z}/q{&#92;bf Z})^&#92;times: xyz = a&#92; (q)} e_q(x+y+z).' title='&#92;displaystyle K_3( a;q) := &#92;frac{1}{q} &#92;sum_{x,y,z &#92;in ({&#92;bf Z}/q{&#92;bf Z})^&#92;times: xyz = a&#92; (q)} e_q(x+y+z).' class='latex' /></p> <p> As for the first term, we have the following estimate: </p> <blockquote><p><b>Lemma 14</b> We have <p align="center"><img src='http://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%5Cdisplaystyle++%7CF%28+h_1+%5Coverline%7Bq%27%7D%2Ch_2+%5Coverline%7Bq%27%7D%2Ch_3+%5Coverline%7Bq%27%7D%2C+a+%5Coverline%7Bm%7D%3B+b%29%7C+%5Cleq+%5Cfrac%7B%5Chbox%7Brad%7D%28b_1%29+%5Chbox%7Brad%7D%28b_2%29+%5Chbox%7Brad%7D%28b_3%29%7D%7B%5Chbox%7Brad%7D%28b_1+b_2+b_3%29%5E2%7D.&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0' alt='&#92;displaystyle |F( h_1 &#92;overline{q&#039;},h_2 &#92;overline{q&#039;},h_3 &#92;overline{q&#039;}, a &#92;overline{m}; b)| &#92;leq &#92;frac{&#92;hbox{rad}(b_1) &#92;hbox{rad}(b_2) &#92;hbox{rad}(b_3)}{&#92;hbox{rad}(b_1 b_2 b_3)^2}.' title='&#92;displaystyle |F( h_1 &#92;overline{q&#039;},h_2 &#92;overline{q&#039;},h_3 &#92;overline{q&#039;}, a &#92;overline{m}; b)| &#92;leq &#92;frac{&#92;hbox{rad}(b_1) &#92;hbox{rad}(b_2) &#92;hbox{rad}(b_3)}{&#92;hbox{rad}(b_1 b_2 b_3)^2}.' class='latex' /></p> <p> where <img src='http://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7B%5Chbox%7Brad%7D%28a%29+%3A%3D+%5Cprod_%7Bp%7Ca%7D+p%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0' alt='{&#92;hbox{rad}(a) := &#92;prod_{p|a} p}' title='{&#92;hbox{rad}(a) := &#92;prod_{p|a} p}' class='latex' /> (thus for instance <img src='http://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7Bb+%3D+%5Chbox%7Brad%7D%28b_1+b_2+b_3%29%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0' alt='{b = &#92;hbox{rad}(b_1 b_2 b_3)}' title='{b = &#92;hbox{rad}(b_1 b_2 b_3)}' class='latex' />). </p></blockquote> </p> <p> <em>Proof:</em> By further applications of Lemma <a href="#crt">8</a> it suffices to show that </p> <p align="center"><img src='http://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%5Cdisplaystyle++%7CF%28+c_1%2C+c_2%2C+c_3%2C+a%3B+p%29%7C+%5Cleq+%5Cfrac%7B%28c_1%2Cp%29+%28c_2%2Cp%29+%28c_3%2Cp%29%7D%7Bp%5E2%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0' alt='&#92;displaystyle |F( c_1, c_2, c_3, a; p)| &#92;leq &#92;frac{(c_1,p) (c_2,p) (c_3,p)}{p^2}' title='&#92;displaystyle |F( c_1, c_2, c_3, a; p)| &#92;leq &#92;frac{(c_1,p) (c_2,p) (c_3,p)}{p^2}' class='latex' /></p> <p> whenever <img src='http://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7Bp%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0' alt='{p}' title='{p}' class='latex' /> is prime, <img src='http://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7Bc_1%2Cc_2%2Cc_3+%5Cin+%7B%5Cbf+Z%7D%2Fp%7B%5Cbf+Z%7D%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0' alt='{c_1,c_2,c_3 &#92;in {&#92;bf Z}/p{&#92;bf Z}}' title='{c_1,c_2,c_3 &#92;in {&#92;bf Z}/p{&#92;bf Z}}' class='latex' /> with <img src='http://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7Bc_1c_2c_3+%3D+0%5C+%28p%29%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0' alt='{c_1c_2c_3 = 0&#92; (p)}' title='{c_1c_2c_3 = 0&#92; (p)}' class='latex' />, and <img src='http://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7Ba+%5Cin+%28%7B%5Cbf+Z%7D%2Fp%7B%5Cbf+Z%7D%29%5E%5Ctimes%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0' alt='{a &#92;in ({&#92;bf Z}/p{&#92;bf Z})^&#92;times}' title='{a &#92;in ({&#92;bf Z}/p{&#92;bf Z})^&#92;times}' class='latex' />.</p> <p> Without loss of generality we may assume that <img src='http://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7Bc_3+%3D+0%5C+%28p%29%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0' alt='{c_3 = 0&#92; (p)}' title='{c_3 = 0&#92; (p)}' class='latex' />, then we may rewrite <img src='http://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7BF%28c_1%2Cc_2%2Cc_3%2Ca%3Bp%29%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0' alt='{F(c_1,c_2,c_3,a;p)}' title='{F(c_1,c_2,c_3,a;p)}' class='latex' /> as </p> <p align="center"><img src='http://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%5Cdisplaystyle++%5Cfrac%7B1%7D%7Bp%7D+%5Csum_%7Bn_1%2Cn_2+%5Cin+%28%7B%5Cbf+Z%7D%2Fp%7B%5Cbf+Z%7D%29%5E%5Ctimes%7D+e_p%28+c_1+n_1+%2B+c_2+n_2+%29.&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0' alt='&#92;displaystyle &#92;frac{1}{p} &#92;sum_{n_1,n_2 &#92;in ({&#92;bf Z}/p{&#92;bf Z})^&#92;times} e_p( c_1 n_1 + c_2 n_2 ).' title='&#92;displaystyle &#92;frac{1}{p} &#92;sum_{n_1,n_2 &#92;in ({&#92;bf Z}/p{&#92;bf Z})^&#92;times} e_p( c_1 n_1 + c_2 n_2 ).' class='latex' /></p> <p> But this factors as the product of two Ramanujan sums divided by <img src='http://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7Bp%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0' alt='{p}' title='{p}' class='latex' />, and the claim then follows by direct computation. <img src='http://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%5CBox&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0' alt='&#92;Box' title='&#92;Box' class='latex' /></p> <p> For brevity we write <img src='http://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7B%5Cvec+b%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0' alt='{&#92;vec b}' title='{&#92;vec b}' class='latex' /> for <img src='http://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7Bb_1%2Cb_2%2Cb_3%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0' alt='{b_1,b_2,b_3}' title='{b_1,b_2,b_3}' class='latex' />. We may thus bound the left-hand side of <a href="#snore">(38)</a> by </p> <p align="center"><img src='http://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%5Cdisplaystyle++%5Csum_%7B%5Cvec+b%7D+%5Cfrac%7B%5Chbox%7Brad%7D%28b_1%29+%5Chbox%7Brad%7D%28b_2%29+%5Chbox%7Brad%7D%28b_3%29%7D%7B%5Chbox%7Brad%7D%28b_1+b_2+b_3%29%5E2%7D+%5Csum_%7Bh%27_1%2Ch%27_2%2Ch%27_3%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0' alt='&#92;displaystyle &#92;sum_{&#92;vec b} &#92;frac{&#92;hbox{rad}(b_1) &#92;hbox{rad}(b_2) &#92;hbox{rad}(b_3)}{&#92;hbox{rad}(b_1 b_2 b_3)^2} &#92;sum_{h&#039;_1,h&#039;_2,h&#039;_3}' title='&#92;displaystyle &#92;sum_{&#92;vec b} &#92;frac{&#92;hbox{rad}(b_1) &#92;hbox{rad}(b_2) &#92;hbox{rad}(b_3)}{&#92;hbox{rad}(b_1 b_2 b_3)^2} &#92;sum_{h&#039;_1,h&#039;_2,h&#039;_3}' class='latex' /></p> <p align="center"><img src='http://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%5Cdisplaystyle++%7C%5Csum_%7Bq%27%5Cin+%7B%5Cmathcal+S%7D_I+%5Ccap+%7B%5Cmathcal+D%7D_%7Bbx%5E%5Cdelta%7D%3A+%28b+h%27_1+h%27_2+h%27_3%2Cq%27%29%3D1%7D+%5Ctilde+c%27_%7Bbq%27%7D+&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0' alt='&#92;displaystyle |&#92;sum_{q&#039;&#92;in {&#92;mathcal S}_I &#92;cap {&#92;mathcal D}_{bx^&#92;delta}: (b h&#039;_1 h&#039;_2 h&#039;_3,q&#039;)=1} &#92;tilde c&#039;_{bq&#039;} ' title='&#92;displaystyle |&#92;sum_{q&#039;&#92;in {&#92;mathcal S}_I &#92;cap {&#92;mathcal D}_{bx^&#92;delta}: (b h&#039;_1 h&#039;_2 h&#039;_3,q&#039;)=1} &#92;tilde c&#039;_{bq&#039;} ' class='latex' /></p> <p align="center"><img src='http://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%5Cdisplaystyle++%5Csum_%7Bm%3A+%28bq%27%2Cm%29%3D1%7D+%5Calpha%28m%29+K_3%28+a_%7B%5Cvec+b%2Cq%27%7D+h%27_1+h%27_2+h%27_3+%5Coverline%7Bm%7D%3B+q%27+%29%7C&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0' alt='&#92;displaystyle &#92;sum_{m: (bq&#039;,m)=1} &#92;alpha(m) K_3( a_{&#92;vec b,q&#039;} h&#039;_1 h&#039;_2 h&#039;_3 &#92;overline{m}; q&#039; )|' title='&#92;displaystyle &#92;sum_{m: (bq&#039;,m)=1} &#92;alpha(m) K_3( a_{&#92;vec b,q&#039;} h&#039;_1 h&#039;_2 h&#039;_3 &#92;overline{m}; q&#039; )|' class='latex' /></p> <p> where the <img src='http://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7Bh%27_i%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0' alt='{h&#039;_i}' title='{h&#039;_i}' class='latex' /> summations are over the ranges <p align="center"><img src='http://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%5Cdisplaystyle++0+%3C+%7Ch%27_i%7C+%5Cleq+%5Cfrac%7Bx%5E%5Cepsilon+H_i%7D%7Bb_i%7D.&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0' alt='&#92;displaystyle 0 &lt; |h&#039;_i| &#92;leq &#92;frac{x^&#92;epsilon H_i}{b_i}.' title='&#92;displaystyle 0 &lt; |h&#039;_i| &#92;leq &#92;frac{x^&#92;epsilon H_i}{b_i}.' class='latex' /></p> <p> Writing <img src='http://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7Bh+%3A%3D+h%27_1+h%27_2+h%27_3%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0' alt='{h := h&#039;_1 h&#039;_2 h&#039;_3}' title='{h := h&#039;_1 h&#039;_2 h&#039;_3}' class='latex' />, so that <p align="center"><img src='http://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%5Cdisplaystyle++0+%3C+%7Ch%7C+%5Cleq+%5Cfrac%7Bx%5E%7B3%5Cepsilon%7D+H%7D%7Bb_1+b_2+b_3%7D%2C&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0' alt='&#92;displaystyle 0 &lt; |h| &#92;leq &#92;frac{x^{3&#92;epsilon} H}{b_1 b_2 b_3},' title='&#92;displaystyle 0 &lt; |h| &#92;leq &#92;frac{x^{3&#92;epsilon} H}{b_1 b_2 b_3},' class='latex' /></p> <p> and recalling that <img src='http://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7Bb+%3D+%5Chbox%7Brad%7D%28b_1b_2b_3%29%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0' alt='{b = &#92;hbox{rad}(b_1b_2b_3)}' title='{b = &#92;hbox{rad}(b_1b_2b_3)}' class='latex' />, we may thus estimate the previous expression by <p align="center"><img src='http://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%5Cdisplaystyle++%5Csum_%7B%5Cvec+b%7D+%5Cfrac%7B%5Chbox%7Brad%7D%28b_1%29+%5Chbox%7Brad%7D%28b_2%29+%5Chbox%7Brad%7D%28b_3%29%7D%7Bb%5E2%7D+S_%7B%5Cvec+b%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0' alt='&#92;displaystyle &#92;sum_{&#92;vec b} &#92;frac{&#92;hbox{rad}(b_1) &#92;hbox{rad}(b_2) &#92;hbox{rad}(b_3)}{b^2} S_{&#92;vec b}' title='&#92;displaystyle &#92;sum_{&#92;vec b} &#92;frac{&#92;hbox{rad}(b_1) &#92;hbox{rad}(b_2) &#92;hbox{rad}(b_3)}{b^2} S_{&#92;vec b}' class='latex' /></p> <p> where <img src='http://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7BS_%7B%5Cvec+b%7D%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0' alt='{S_{&#92;vec b}}' title='{S_{&#92;vec b}}' class='latex' /> is the quantity <p align="center"><img src='http://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%5Cdisplaystyle++S_%7B%5Cvec+b%7D+%3A%3D+%5Csum_%7B0+%3C+%7Ch%7C+%5Cleq+H_%7B%5Cvec+b%7D%7D+%5Ctau_3%28h%29+%7C%5Csum_%7Bq%27%5Cin+%7B%5Cmathcal+S%7D_I+%5Ccap+%7B%5Cmathcal+D%7D_%7Bbx%5E%5Cdelta%7D%3A+%28b+h%2Cq%27%29%3D1%7D+%5Ctilde+c%27_%7Bbq%27%7D+&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0' alt='&#92;displaystyle S_{&#92;vec b} := &#92;sum_{0 &lt; |h| &#92;leq H_{&#92;vec b}} &#92;tau_3(h) |&#92;sum_{q&#039;&#92;in {&#92;mathcal S}_I &#92;cap {&#92;mathcal D}_{bx^&#92;delta}: (b h,q&#039;)=1} &#92;tilde c&#039;_{bq&#039;} ' title='&#92;displaystyle S_{&#92;vec b} := &#92;sum_{0 &lt; |h| &#92;leq H_{&#92;vec b}} &#92;tau_3(h) |&#92;sum_{q&#039;&#92;in {&#92;mathcal S}_I &#92;cap {&#92;mathcal D}_{bx^&#92;delta}: (b h,q&#039;)=1} &#92;tilde c&#039;_{bq&#039;} ' class='latex' /></p> <p align="center"><img src='http://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%5Cdisplaystyle++%5Csum_%7Bm%3A+%28bq%27%2Cm%29%3D1%7D+%5Calpha%28m%29+K_3%28+a_%7B%5Cvec+b%2Cq%27%7D+h+%5Coverline%7Bm%7D%3B+q%27+%29%7C&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0' alt='&#92;displaystyle &#92;sum_{m: (bq&#039;,m)=1} &#92;alpha(m) K_3( a_{&#92;vec b,q&#039;} h &#92;overline{m}; q&#039; )|' title='&#92;displaystyle &#92;sum_{m: (bq&#039;,m)=1} &#92;alpha(m) K_3( a_{&#92;vec b,q&#039;} h &#92;overline{m}; q&#039; )|' class='latex' /></p> <p> where <img src='http://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7B%5Ctau_3%28h%29+%3A%3D+%5Csum_%7Bh_1%2Ch_2%2Ch_3%3A+h_1h_2h_3%3D1%7D+1%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0' alt='{&#92;tau_3(h) := &#92;sum_{h_1,h_2,h_3: h_1h_2h_3=1} 1}' title='{&#92;tau_3(h) := &#92;sum_{h_1,h_2,h_3: h_1h_2h_3=1} 1}' class='latex' /> is the third divisor function and <p align="center"><img src='http://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%5Cdisplaystyle++H_%7B%5Cvec+b%7D+%3A%3D+%5Cfrac%7Bx%5E%7B3%5Cepsilon%7D+H%7D%7Bb_1+b_2+b_3%7D.&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0' alt='&#92;displaystyle H_{&#92;vec b} := &#92;frac{x^{3&#92;epsilon} H}{b_1 b_2 b_3}.' title='&#92;displaystyle H_{&#92;vec b} := &#92;frac{x^{3&#92;epsilon} H}{b_1 b_2 b_3}.' class='latex' /></p> <p> Our task is now to show that <a name="task"> <p align="center"><img src='http://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%5Cdisplaystyle++%5Csum_%7B%5Cvec+b%7D+%5Cfrac%7B%5Chbox%7Brad%7D%28b_1%29+%5Chbox%7Brad%7D%28b_2%29+%5Chbox%7Brad%7D%28b_3%29%7D%7Bb%5E2%7D+S_%7B%5Cvec+b%7D+%5Clessapprox+x%5E%7B-2%5Cepsilon%7D+M+Q%5E2.+%5C+%5C+%5C+%5C+%5C+%2839%29&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0' alt='&#92;displaystyle &#92;sum_{&#92;vec b} &#92;frac{&#92;hbox{rad}(b_1) &#92;hbox{rad}(b_2) &#92;hbox{rad}(b_3)}{b^2} S_{&#92;vec b} &#92;lessapprox x^{-2&#92;epsilon} M Q^2. &#92; &#92; &#92; &#92; &#92; (39)' title='&#92;displaystyle &#92;sum_{&#92;vec b} &#92;frac{&#92;hbox{rad}(b_1) &#92;hbox{rad}(b_2) &#92;hbox{rad}(b_3)}{b^2} S_{&#92;vec b} &#92;lessapprox x^{-2&#92;epsilon} M Q^2. &#92; &#92; &#92; &#92; &#92; (39)' class='latex' /></p> <p></a> We now focus on estimating <img src='http://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7BS_%7B%5Cvec+b%7D%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0' alt='{S_{&#92;vec b}}' title='{S_{&#92;vec b}}' class='latex' />. </p> <p> We let <a name="q"> <p align="center"><img src='http://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%5Cdisplaystyle++1+%5Cleq+S_0+%5Cleq+y+Q_%7B%5Cvec+b%7D+%5C+%5C+%5C+%5C+%5C+%2840%29&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0' alt='&#92;displaystyle 1 &#92;leq S_0 &#92;leq y Q_{&#92;vec b} &#92; &#92; &#92; &#92; &#92; (40)' title='&#92;displaystyle 1 &#92;leq S_0 &#92;leq y Q_{&#92;vec b} &#92; &#92; &#92; &#92; &#92; (40)' class='latex' /></p> <p></a> be a quantity to optimise in later, where </p> <p align="center"><img src='http://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%5Cdisplaystyle++Q_%7B%5Cvec+b%7D+%3A%3D+%5Cfrac%7BQ%7D%7Bb%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0' alt='&#92;displaystyle Q_{&#92;vec b} := &#92;frac{Q}{b}' title='&#92;displaystyle Q_{&#92;vec b} := &#92;frac{Q}{b}' class='latex' /></p> <p> and <p align="center"><img src='http://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%5Cdisplaystyle+y+%3A%3D+x%5E%5Cdelta+b.+&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0' alt='&#92;displaystyle y := x^&#92;delta b. ' title='&#92;displaystyle y := x^&#92;delta b. ' class='latex' /></p> <p> We may assume that <a name="bqb"> <p align="center"><img src='http://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%5Cdisplaystyle++Q_%7B%5Cvec+b%7D%2C+H_%7B%5Cvec+b%7D+%5Cgg+1+%5C+%5C+%5C+%5C+%5C+%2841%29&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0' alt='&#92;displaystyle Q_{&#92;vec b}, H_{&#92;vec b} &#92;gg 1 &#92; &#92; &#92; &#92; &#92; (41)' title='&#92;displaystyle Q_{&#92;vec b}, H_{&#92;vec b} &#92;gg 1 &#92; &#92; &#92; &#92; &#92; (41)' class='latex' /></p> <p></a></p> <p> Observe that every <img src='http://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7Bq%27%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0' alt='{q&#039;}' title='{q&#039;}' class='latex' /> that appears in the expression for <img src='http://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7BS_%7B%5Cvec+b%7D%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0' alt='{S_{&#92;vec b}}' title='{S_{&#92;vec b}}' class='latex' /> is <img src='http://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7By%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0' alt='{y}' title='{y}' class='latex' />-densely divisible and may thus be factored as <img src='http://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7Bq%27%3Drs%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0' alt='{q&#039;=rs}' title='{q&#039;=rs}' class='latex' /> for some coprime <img src='http://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7Br%2Cs%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0' alt='{r,s}' title='{r,s}' class='latex' /> with </p> <p align="center"><img src='http://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%5Cdisplaystyle++y%5E%7B-1%7D+S_0+%5Cll+s+%5Cll+S_0&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0' alt='&#92;displaystyle y^{-1} S_0 &#92;ll s &#92;ll S_0' title='&#92;displaystyle y^{-1} S_0 &#92;ll s &#92;ll S_0' class='latex' /></p> <p> with <img src='http://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7Brs+%5Csim+Q_%7B%5Cvec+b%7D%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0' alt='{rs &#92;sim Q_{&#92;vec b}}' title='{rs &#92;sim Q_{&#92;vec b}}' class='latex' />. Thus we may write <p align="center"><img src='http://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%5Cdisplaystyle++S_%7B%5Cvec+b%7D+%5Cll+%5Csum_%7By%5E%7B-1%7D+S_0+%5Cll+s+%5Cll+S_0%7D+%5Csum_%7B0+%3C+%7Ch%7C+%5Cleq+H_%7B%5Cvec+b%7D%7D+%5Ctau_3%28h%29+%7C%5Csum_%7Br+%5Cin+%7B%5Cmathcal+S%7D_I%3A+%28b+h%2Crs%29%3D%28r%2Cs%29%3D1%7D+%5Ctilde+c%27_%7Bbrs%7D+%5Csum_%7Bm%3A+%28brs%2Cm%29%3D1%7D+%5Calpha%28m%29&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0' alt='&#92;displaystyle S_{&#92;vec b} &#92;ll &#92;sum_{y^{-1} S_0 &#92;ll s &#92;ll S_0} &#92;sum_{0 &lt; |h| &#92;leq H_{&#92;vec b}} &#92;tau_3(h) |&#92;sum_{r &#92;in {&#92;mathcal S}_I: (b h,rs)=(r,s)=1} &#92;tilde c&#039;_{brs} &#92;sum_{m: (brs,m)=1} &#92;alpha(m)' title='&#92;displaystyle S_{&#92;vec b} &#92;ll &#92;sum_{y^{-1} S_0 &#92;ll s &#92;ll S_0} &#92;sum_{0 &lt; |h| &#92;leq H_{&#92;vec b}} &#92;tau_3(h) |&#92;sum_{r &#92;in {&#92;mathcal S}_I: (b h,rs)=(r,s)=1} &#92;tilde c&#039;_{brs} &#92;sum_{m: (brs,m)=1} &#92;alpha(m)' class='latex' /></p> <p align="center"><img src='http://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%5Cdisplaystyle++K_3%28+a_%7B%5Cvec+b%2Crs%7D+h+%5Coverline%7Bm%7D%3B+rs+%29%7C&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0' alt='&#92;displaystyle K_3( a_{&#92;vec b,rs} h &#92;overline{m}; rs )|' title='&#92;displaystyle K_3( a_{&#92;vec b,rs} h &#92;overline{m}; rs )|' class='latex' /></p> <p> where <p align="center"><img src='http://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%5Cdisplaystyle++H_%7B%5Cvec+b%7D+%3A%3D+%5Cfrac%7Bx%5E%7B3%5Cepsilon%7D+H%7D%7Bb_1+b_2+b_3%7D.&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0' alt='&#92;displaystyle H_{&#92;vec b} := &#92;frac{x^{3&#92;epsilon} H}{b_1 b_2 b_3}.' title='&#92;displaystyle H_{&#92;vec b} := &#92;frac{x^{3&#92;epsilon} H}{b_1 b_2 b_3}.' class='latex' /></p> <p> From crude estimates we have </p> <p align="center"><img src='http://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%5Cdisplaystyle++%5Csum_%7By%5E%7B-1%7D+S_0+%5Cll+s+%5Cll+S_0%7D+%5Csum_%7B0+%3C+%7Ch%7C+%5Cleq+H_%7B%5Cvec+b%7D%7D+%5Cfrac%7B%5Ctau_3%28h%29%5E2%7D%7Bs%7D+%5Clessapprox+H_%7B%5Cvec+b%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0' alt='&#92;displaystyle &#92;sum_{y^{-1} S_0 &#92;ll s &#92;ll S_0} &#92;sum_{0 &lt; |h| &#92;leq H_{&#92;vec b}} &#92;frac{&#92;tau_3(h)^2}{s} &#92;lessapprox H_{&#92;vec b}' title='&#92;displaystyle &#92;sum_{y^{-1} S_0 &#92;ll s &#92;ll S_0} &#92;sum_{0 &lt; |h| &#92;leq H_{&#92;vec b}} &#92;frac{&#92;tau_3(h)^2}{s} &#92;lessapprox H_{&#92;vec b}' class='latex' /></p> <p> so from the Cauchy-Schwarz inequality we have <a name="moo"> <p align="center"><img src='http://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%5Cdisplaystyle++S_%7B%5Cvec+b%7D+%5Clessapprox+H_%7B%5Cvec+b%7D%5E%7B1%2F2%7D+%28S%27_%7B%5Cvec+b%7D%29%5E%7B1%2F2%7D+%5C+%5C+%5C+%5C+%5C+%2842%29&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0' alt='&#92;displaystyle S_{&#92;vec b} &#92;lessapprox H_{&#92;vec b}^{1/2} (S&#039;_{&#92;vec b})^{1/2} &#92; &#92; &#92; &#92; &#92; (42)' title='&#92;displaystyle S_{&#92;vec b} &#92;lessapprox H_{&#92;vec b}^{1/2} (S&#039;_{&#92;vec b})^{1/2} &#92; &#92; &#92; &#92; &#92; (42)' class='latex' /></p> <p></a> where <p align="center"><img src='http://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%5Cdisplaystyle++S%27_%7B%5Cvec+b%7D+%3D+%5Csum_%7By%5E%7B-1%7D+S_0+%5Cll+s+%5Cll+S_0%7D+%5Csum_h+%5CPsi%28h%29+s+%7C%5Csum_%7Br%5Cin+%7B%5Cmathcal+S%7D_I%3A+%28b+h%2Crs%29%3D%28r%2Cs%29%3D1%7D+%5Ctilde+c%27_%7Bbrs%7D+&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0' alt='&#92;displaystyle S&#039;_{&#92;vec b} = &#92;sum_{y^{-1} S_0 &#92;ll s &#92;ll S_0} &#92;sum_h &#92;Psi(h) s |&#92;sum_{r&#92;in {&#92;mathcal S}_I: (b h,rs)=(r,s)=1} &#92;tilde c&#039;_{brs} ' title='&#92;displaystyle S&#039;_{&#92;vec b} = &#92;sum_{y^{-1} S_0 &#92;ll s &#92;ll S_0} &#92;sum_h &#92;Psi(h) s |&#92;sum_{r&#92;in {&#92;mathcal S}_I: (b h,rs)=(r,s)=1} &#92;tilde c&#039;_{brs} ' class='latex' /></p> <p align="center"><img src='http://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%5Cdisplaystyle++%5Csum_%7Bm%3A+%28brs%2Cm%29%3D1%7D+%5Calpha%28m%29+K_3%28+a_%7B%5Cvec+b%2Crs%7D+h+%5Coverline%7Bm%7D%3B+rs+%29%7C%5E2+&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0' alt='&#92;displaystyle &#92;sum_{m: (brs,m)=1} &#92;alpha(m) K_3( a_{&#92;vec b,rs} h &#92;overline{m}; rs )|^2 ' title='&#92;displaystyle &#92;sum_{m: (brs,m)=1} &#92;alpha(m) K_3( a_{&#92;vec b,rs} h &#92;overline{m}; rs )|^2 ' class='latex' /></p> <p> and <img src='http://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7B%5CPsi+%3D+%5CPsi_%7B%5Cvec+b%7D%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0' alt='{&#92;Psi = &#92;Psi_{&#92;vec b}}' title='{&#92;Psi = &#92;Psi_{&#92;vec b}}' class='latex' /> is a smooth cutoff function supported on the interval <img src='http://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7B%5B-2H_%7B%5Cvec+b%7D%2C2H_%7B%5Cvec+b%7D%5D%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0' alt='{[-2H_{&#92;vec b},2H_{&#92;vec b}]}' title='{[-2H_{&#92;vec b},2H_{&#92;vec b}]}' class='latex' /> which equals one on <img src='http://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7B%5B-H_%7B%5Cvec+b%7D%2CH_%7B%5Cvec+b%7D%5D%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0' alt='{[-H_{&#92;vec b},H_{&#92;vec b}]}' title='{[-H_{&#92;vec b},H_{&#92;vec b}]}' class='latex' />.</p> <p> Now we estimate <img src='http://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7BS%27_%7B%5Cvec+b%7D%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0' alt='{S&#039;_{&#92;vec b}}' title='{S&#039;_{&#92;vec b}}' class='latex' />. We can expand this expression as </p> <p align="center"><img src='http://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%5Cdisplaystyle++%5Csum_%7Br_1%2Cr_2+%5Cin+%7B%5Cmathcal+S%7D_I%3A+Q_%7B%5Cvec+b%7D%2FS_0+%5Cll+r_1+%5Csim+r_2+%5Cll+yQ_%7B%5Cvec+b%7D%2FS_0%7D+%5Csum_%7Bs+%5Csim+Q_%7B%5Cvec+b%7D%2Fr_1%3A+%28r_1r_2%2Cs%29%3D1+%3D+%28r_1r_2+s%2C+b%29%3D1%7D+&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0' alt='&#92;displaystyle &#92;sum_{r_1,r_2 &#92;in {&#92;mathcal S}_I: Q_{&#92;vec b}/S_0 &#92;ll r_1 &#92;sim r_2 &#92;ll yQ_{&#92;vec b}/S_0} &#92;sum_{s &#92;sim Q_{&#92;vec b}/r_1: (r_1r_2,s)=1 = (r_1r_2 s, b)=1} ' title='&#92;displaystyle &#92;sum_{r_1,r_2 &#92;in {&#92;mathcal S}_I: Q_{&#92;vec b}/S_0 &#92;ll r_1 &#92;sim r_2 &#92;ll yQ_{&#92;vec b}/S_0} &#92;sum_{s &#92;sim Q_{&#92;vec b}/r_1: (r_1r_2,s)=1 = (r_1r_2 s, b)=1} ' class='latex' /></p> <p align="center"><img src='http://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%5Cdisplaystyle++%5Csum_%7Bm_1%2Cm_2%3A+%28br_1s%2Cm_1%29%3D%28br_2s%2Cm_2%29%3D1%7D+%5Ctilde+c%27_%7Bbr_1s%7D+%5Coverline%7B%5Ctilde+c%27_%7Bbr_2+s%7D%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0' alt='&#92;displaystyle &#92;sum_{m_1,m_2: (br_1s,m_1)=(br_2s,m_2)=1} &#92;tilde c&#039;_{br_1s} &#92;overline{&#92;tilde c&#039;_{br_2 s}}' title='&#92;displaystyle &#92;sum_{m_1,m_2: (br_1s,m_1)=(br_2s,m_2)=1} &#92;tilde c&#039;_{br_1s} &#92;overline{&#92;tilde c&#039;_{br_2 s}}' class='latex' /></p> <p align="center"><img src='http://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%5Cdisplaystyle++s+%5Calpha%28m_1%29+%5Coverline%7B%5Calpha%28m_2%29%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0' alt='&#92;displaystyle s &#92;alpha(m_1) &#92;overline{&#92;alpha(m_2)}' title='&#92;displaystyle s &#92;alpha(m_1) &#92;overline{&#92;alpha(m_2)}' class='latex' /></p> <p align="center"><img src='http://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%5Cdisplaystyle++%5Csum_%7Bh%3A+%28r_1r_2+s%2Ch%29%3D1%7D+%5CPsi%28h%29+K_3%28+a_%7B%5Cvec+b%2Cr_1s%7D+h+%5Coverline%7Bm_1%7D%3B+r_1s+%29+%5Coverline%7BK_3%28+a_%7B%5Cvec+b%2Cr_2s%7D+h+%5Coverline%7Bm_2%7D%3B+r_2s+%29%7D.&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0' alt='&#92;displaystyle &#92;sum_{h: (r_1r_2 s,h)=1} &#92;Psi(h) K_3( a_{&#92;vec b,r_1s} h &#92;overline{m_1}; r_1s ) &#92;overline{K_3( a_{&#92;vec b,r_2s} h &#92;overline{m_2}; r_2s )}.' title='&#92;displaystyle &#92;sum_{h: (r_1r_2 s,h)=1} &#92;Psi(h) K_3( a_{&#92;vec b,r_1s} h &#92;overline{m_1}; r_1s ) &#92;overline{K_3( a_{&#92;vec b,r_2s} h &#92;overline{m_2}; r_2s )}.' class='latex' /></p> <p> We first dispose of the diagonal case <img src='http://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7Bm_1+r_1%5E3+-+m_2+r_2%5E3+%3D+0%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0' alt='{m_1 r_1^3 - m_2 r_2^3 = 0}' title='{m_1 r_1^3 - m_2 r_2^3 = 0}' class='latex' />. Here we use the Deligne bound <img src='http://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7B%7CK_3%7C+%5Clessapprox+1%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0' alt='{|K_3| &#92;lessapprox 1}' title='{|K_3| &#92;lessapprox 1}' class='latex' /> to bound this case in magnitude by <p align="center"><img src='http://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%5Cdisplaystyle++%5Clessapprox+%5Csum_%7Br_1%2Cr_2+%5Cin+%7B%5Cmathcal+S%7D_I%3A+Q_%7B%5Cvec+b%7D%2FS_0+%5Cll+r_1+%5Csim+r_2+%5Cll+yQ_%7B%5Cvec+b%7D%2FS_0%7D+%5Csum_%7Bs+%5Csim+Q_%7B%5Cvec+b%7D%2Fr_1%7D+%5Csum_%7Bm_1%2Cm_2%3A+m_1+r_1%5E3+%3D+m_2+r_2%5E3%7D+s+H_%7B%5Cvec+b%7D.&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0' alt='&#92;displaystyle &#92;lessapprox &#92;sum_{r_1,r_2 &#92;in {&#92;mathcal S}_I: Q_{&#92;vec b}/S_0 &#92;ll r_1 &#92;sim r_2 &#92;ll yQ_{&#92;vec b}/S_0} &#92;sum_{s &#92;sim Q_{&#92;vec b}/r_1} &#92;sum_{m_1,m_2: m_1 r_1^3 = m_2 r_2^3} s H_{&#92;vec b}.' title='&#92;displaystyle &#92;lessapprox &#92;sum_{r_1,r_2 &#92;in {&#92;mathcal S}_I: Q_{&#92;vec b}/S_0 &#92;ll r_1 &#92;sim r_2 &#92;ll yQ_{&#92;vec b}/S_0} &#92;sum_{s &#92;sim Q_{&#92;vec b}/r_1} &#92;sum_{m_1,m_2: m_1 r_1^3 = m_2 r_2^3} s H_{&#92;vec b}.' class='latex' /></p> <p> By the divisor bound, for each <img src='http://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7Br_1%2Cm_1%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0' alt='{r_1,m_1}' title='{r_1,m_1}' class='latex' /> there are <img src='http://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7B%5Clessapprox+1%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0' alt='{&#92;lessapprox 1}' title='{&#92;lessapprox 1}' class='latex' /> choices for <img src='http://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7Bm_2%2Cr_2%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0' alt='{m_2,r_2}' title='{m_2,r_2}' class='latex' />, so this expression is <p align="center"><img src='http://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%5Cdisplaystyle++%5Clessapprox+%5Csum_%7Br_1+%5Cin+%7B%5Cmathcal+S%7D_I%3A+Q_%7B%5Cvec+b%7D%2FS_0+%5Cll+r_1+%5Cll+yQ_%7B%5Cvec+b%7D%2FS_0%7D+M+%28Q_%7B%5Cvec+b%7D%2Fr_1%29%5E2+H_%7B%5Cvec+b%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0' alt='&#92;displaystyle &#92;lessapprox &#92;sum_{r_1 &#92;in {&#92;mathcal S}_I: Q_{&#92;vec b}/S_0 &#92;ll r_1 &#92;ll yQ_{&#92;vec b}/S_0} M (Q_{&#92;vec b}/r_1)^2 H_{&#92;vec b}' title='&#92;displaystyle &#92;lessapprox &#92;sum_{r_1 &#92;in {&#92;mathcal S}_I: Q_{&#92;vec b}/S_0 &#92;ll r_1 &#92;ll yQ_{&#92;vec b}/S_0} M (Q_{&#92;vec b}/r_1)^2 H_{&#92;vec b}' class='latex' /></p> <p> which sums to <img src='http://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7B%5Clessapprox+M+S_0+Q_%7B%5Cvec+b%7D+H_%7B%5Cvec+b%7D%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0' alt='{&#92;lessapprox M S_0 Q_{&#92;vec b} H_{&#92;vec b}}' title='{&#92;lessapprox M S_0 Q_{&#92;vec b} H_{&#92;vec b}}' class='latex' />.</p> <p> Applying Lemma <a href="#corr-2">13</a> for the off-diagonal case <img src='http://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7Bm_1+r_1%5E3+-+m_2+r_2%5E3+%5Cneq+0%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0' alt='{m_1 r_1^3 - m_2 r_2^3 &#92;neq 0}' title='{m_1 r_1^3 - m_2 r_2^3 &#92;neq 0}' class='latex' />, we thus have </p> <p align="center"><img src='http://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%5Cdisplaystyle++S%27_%7B%5Cvec+b%7D%5Clessapprox+M+S_0+Q_%7B%5Cvec+b%7D+H_%7B%5Cvec+b%7D+%2B+%5Csum_%7Br_1%2Cr_2+%5Cin+%7B%5Cmathcal+S%7D_I%3A+Q_%7B%5Cvec+b%7D%2FS_0+%5Cll+r_1+%5Csim+r_2+%5Cll+yQ_%7B%5Cvec+b%7D%2FS_0%7D+%5Csum_%7Bs+%5Csim+Q_%7B%5Cvec+b%7D%2Fr_1%3A+%28r_1r_2%2Cs%29%3D%28r_1r_2s%2Cb%29%3D1%7D+%5Csum_%7Bm_1%2Cm_2+%5Csim+M%3A+m_1+r_1%5E3+-+m_2+r_2%5E3+%5Cneq+0%7D+s+&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0' alt='&#92;displaystyle S&#039;_{&#92;vec b}&#92;lessapprox M S_0 Q_{&#92;vec b} H_{&#92;vec b} + &#92;sum_{r_1,r_2 &#92;in {&#92;mathcal S}_I: Q_{&#92;vec b}/S_0 &#92;ll r_1 &#92;sim r_2 &#92;ll yQ_{&#92;vec b}/S_0} &#92;sum_{s &#92;sim Q_{&#92;vec b}/r_1: (r_1r_2,s)=(r_1r_2s,b)=1} &#92;sum_{m_1,m_2 &#92;sim M: m_1 r_1^3 - m_2 r_2^3 &#92;neq 0} s ' title='&#92;displaystyle S&#039;_{&#92;vec b}&#92;lessapprox M S_0 Q_{&#92;vec b} H_{&#92;vec b} + &#92;sum_{r_1,r_2 &#92;in {&#92;mathcal S}_I: Q_{&#92;vec b}/S_0 &#92;ll r_1 &#92;sim r_2 &#92;ll yQ_{&#92;vec b}/S_0} &#92;sum_{s &#92;sim Q_{&#92;vec b}/r_1: (r_1r_2,s)=(r_1r_2s,b)=1} &#92;sum_{m_1,m_2 &#92;sim M: m_1 r_1^3 - m_2 r_2^3 &#92;neq 0} s ' class='latex' /></p> <p align="center"><img src='http://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%5Cdisplaystyle++%28%5Cfrac%7B+H_%7B%5Cvec+b%7D%7D%7B%5Br_1%2Cr_2%5D+s%7D+%2B+1%29+d%5E%7B1%2F2%7D+s%5E%7B1%2F2%7D+%5Br_1%2Cr_2%5D%5E%7B1%2F2%7D+%28r_1%2Cr_2%2Cm_2-m_1%29%5E%7B1%2F2%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0' alt='&#92;displaystyle (&#92;frac{ H_{&#92;vec b}}{[r_1,r_2] s} + 1) d^{1/2} s^{1/2} [r_1,r_2]^{1/2} (r_1,r_2,m_2-m_1)^{1/2}' title='&#92;displaystyle (&#92;frac{ H_{&#92;vec b}}{[r_1,r_2] s} + 1) d^{1/2} s^{1/2} [r_1,r_2]^{1/2} (r_1,r_2,m_2-m_1)^{1/2}' class='latex' /></p> <p> where <p align="center"><img src='http://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%5Cdisplaystyle++d+%3A%3D+%28a_%7B%5Cvec+b%2Cr_2s%7D+%5Coverline%7Bm_2%7D+r_1%5E3+-+a_%7B%5Cvec+b%2Cr_1s%7D+%5Coverline%7Bm_1%7D+r_2%5E3%2C+s+%29&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0' alt='&#92;displaystyle d := (a_{&#92;vec b,r_2s} &#92;overline{m_2} r_1^3 - a_{&#92;vec b,r_1s} &#92;overline{m_1} r_2^3, s )' title='&#92;displaystyle d := (a_{&#92;vec b,r_2s} &#92;overline{m_2} r_1^3 - a_{&#92;vec b,r_1s} &#92;overline{m_1} r_2^3, s )' class='latex' /></p> <p align="center"><img src='http://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%5Cdisplaystyle++%3D+%28m_1+r_1%5E3+-+m_2+r_2%5E3%2C+s+%29.&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0' alt='&#92;displaystyle = (m_1 r_1^3 - m_2 r_2^3, s ).' title='&#92;displaystyle = (m_1 r_1^3 - m_2 r_2^3, s ).' class='latex' /></p> <p> Using the bound <img src='http://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7Bs+%5Csim+Q_%7B%5Cvec+b%7D%2Fr_1%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0' alt='{s &#92;sim Q_{&#92;vec b}/r_1}' title='{s &#92;sim Q_{&#92;vec b}/r_1}' class='latex' />, this becomes <p align="center"><img src='http://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%5Cdisplaystyle++S%27_%7B%5Cvec+b%7D%5Clessapprox+M+S_0+Q_%7B%5Cvec+b%7D+H_%7B%5Cvec+b%7D+%2B+%5Csum_%7Br_1%2Cr_2+%5Cin+%7B%5Cmathcal+S%7D_I%3A+Q_%7B%5Cvec+b%7D%2FS_0+%5Cll+r_1+%5Csim+r_2+%5Cll+yQ_%7B%5Cvec+b%7D%2FS_0%3B+m_1r_1%5E3-m_2r_2%5E3+%5Cneq+0%7D+%5Csum_%7Bs+%5Csim+Q_%7B%5Cvec+b%7D%2Fr_1%7D+%5Csum_%7Bm_1%2Cm_2+%5Csim+M%7D+&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0' alt='&#92;displaystyle S&#039;_{&#92;vec b}&#92;lessapprox M S_0 Q_{&#92;vec b} H_{&#92;vec b} + &#92;sum_{r_1,r_2 &#92;in {&#92;mathcal S}_I: Q_{&#92;vec b}/S_0 &#92;ll r_1 &#92;sim r_2 &#92;ll yQ_{&#92;vec b}/S_0; m_1r_1^3-m_2r_2^3 &#92;neq 0} &#92;sum_{s &#92;sim Q_{&#92;vec b}/r_1} &#92;sum_{m_1,m_2 &#92;sim M} ' title='&#92;displaystyle S&#039;_{&#92;vec b}&#92;lessapprox M S_0 Q_{&#92;vec b} H_{&#92;vec b} + &#92;sum_{r_1,r_2 &#92;in {&#92;mathcal S}_I: Q_{&#92;vec b}/S_0 &#92;ll r_1 &#92;sim r_2 &#92;ll yQ_{&#92;vec b}/S_0; m_1r_1^3-m_2r_2^3 &#92;neq 0} &#92;sum_{s &#92;sim Q_{&#92;vec b}/r_1} &#92;sum_{m_1,m_2 &#92;sim M} ' class='latex' /></p> <p align="center"><img src='http://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%5Cdisplaystyle++%28Q_%7B%5Cvec+b%7D%2Fr_1%29+%28%5Cfrac%7B+H_%7B%5Cvec+b%7D%7D%7B%5Br_1%2Cr_2%5D%5E%7B1%2F2%7D+%28Q_%7B%5Cvec+b%7D%2Fr_1%29%5E%7B1%2F2%7D%7D+%2B+%5Br_1%2Cr_2%5D%5E%7B1%2F2%7D+%28Q_%7B%5Cvec+b%7D%2Fr_1%29%5E%7B1%2F2%7D%29+&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0' alt='&#92;displaystyle (Q_{&#92;vec b}/r_1) (&#92;frac{ H_{&#92;vec b}}{[r_1,r_2]^{1/2} (Q_{&#92;vec b}/r_1)^{1/2}} + [r_1,r_2]^{1/2} (Q_{&#92;vec b}/r_1)^{1/2}) ' title='&#92;displaystyle (Q_{&#92;vec b}/r_1) (&#92;frac{ H_{&#92;vec b}}{[r_1,r_2]^{1/2} (Q_{&#92;vec b}/r_1)^{1/2}} + [r_1,r_2]^{1/2} (Q_{&#92;vec b}/r_1)^{1/2}) ' class='latex' /></p> <p align="center"><img src='http://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%5Cdisplaystyle++%28m_1r_1%5E3+-m_2r_2%5E3%2C+s%29%5E%7B1%2F2%7D+%28r_1%2Cr_2%2Cm_2-m_1%29%5E%7B1%2F2%7D.&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0' alt='&#92;displaystyle (m_1r_1^3 -m_2r_2^3, s)^{1/2} (r_1,r_2,m_2-m_1)^{1/2}.' title='&#92;displaystyle (m_1r_1^3 -m_2r_2^3, s)^{1/2} (r_1,r_2,m_2-m_1)^{1/2}.' class='latex' /></p> <p> By Lemma 5 from <a href="http://terrytao.wordpress.com/2013/06/14/estimation-of-the-type-iii-sums/">this previous post</a> we have <p align="center"><img src='http://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%5Cdisplaystyle++%5Csum_%7Bs+%5Csim+Q_%7B%5Cvec+b%7D%2Fr_1%7D+%28m_1r_1%5E3+-m_2r_2%5E3%2C+s%29+%5Clessapprox+Q_%7B%5Cvec+b%7D%2Fr_1&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0' alt='&#92;displaystyle &#92;sum_{s &#92;sim Q_{&#92;vec b}/r_1} (m_1r_1^3 -m_2r_2^3, s) &#92;lessapprox Q_{&#92;vec b}/r_1' title='&#92;displaystyle &#92;sum_{s &#92;sim Q_{&#92;vec b}/r_1} (m_1r_1^3 -m_2r_2^3, s) &#92;lessapprox Q_{&#92;vec b}/r_1' class='latex' /></p> <p> and hence also <p align="center"><img src='http://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%5Cdisplaystyle++%5Csum_%7Bs+%5Csim+Q_%7B%5Cvec+b%7D%2Fr_1%7D+%28m_1r_1%5E3+-m_2r_2%5E3%2C+s%29%5E%7B1%2F2%7D+%5Clessapprox+Q_%7B%5Cvec+b%7D%2Fr_1&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0' alt='&#92;displaystyle &#92;sum_{s &#92;sim Q_{&#92;vec b}/r_1} (m_1r_1^3 -m_2r_2^3, s)^{1/2} &#92;lessapprox Q_{&#92;vec b}/r_1' title='&#92;displaystyle &#92;sum_{s &#92;sim Q_{&#92;vec b}/r_1} (m_1r_1^3 -m_2r_2^3, s)^{1/2} &#92;lessapprox Q_{&#92;vec b}/r_1' class='latex' /></p> <p> and thus <p align="center"><img src='http://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%5Cdisplaystyle++S%27_%7B%5Cvec+b%7D%5Clessapprox+M+S_0+Q_%7B%5Cvec+b%7D+H_%7B%5Cvec+b%7D+%2B+%5Csum_%7Br_1%2Cr_2+%5Cin+%7B%5Cmathcal+S%7D_I%3A+Q_%7B%5Cvec+b%7D%2FS_0+%5Cll+r_1+%5Csim+r_2+%5Cll+yQ_%7B%5Cvec+b%7D%2FS_0%7D+%5Csum_%7Bm_1%2Cm_2+%5Csim+M%7D+%28Q_%7B%5Cvec+b%7D%2Fr_1%29%5E2+&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0' alt='&#92;displaystyle S&#039;_{&#92;vec b}&#92;lessapprox M S_0 Q_{&#92;vec b} H_{&#92;vec b} + &#92;sum_{r_1,r_2 &#92;in {&#92;mathcal S}_I: Q_{&#92;vec b}/S_0 &#92;ll r_1 &#92;sim r_2 &#92;ll yQ_{&#92;vec b}/S_0} &#92;sum_{m_1,m_2 &#92;sim M} (Q_{&#92;vec b}/r_1)^2 ' title='&#92;displaystyle S&#039;_{&#92;vec b}&#92;lessapprox M S_0 Q_{&#92;vec b} H_{&#92;vec b} + &#92;sum_{r_1,r_2 &#92;in {&#92;mathcal S}_I: Q_{&#92;vec b}/S_0 &#92;ll r_1 &#92;sim r_2 &#92;ll yQ_{&#92;vec b}/S_0} &#92;sum_{m_1,m_2 &#92;sim M} (Q_{&#92;vec b}/r_1)^2 ' class='latex' /></p> <p align="center"><img src='http://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%5Cdisplaystyle++%28%5Cfrac%7B+H_%7B%5Cvec+b%7D%7D%7B%5Br_1%2Cr_2%5D%5E%7B1%2F2%7D+%28Q_%7B%5Cvec+b%7D%2Fr_1%29%5E%7B1%2F2%7D%7D+%2B+%5Br_1%2Cr_2%5D%5E%7B1%2F2%7D+%28Q_%7B%5Cvec+b%7D%2Fr_1%29%5E%7B1%2F2%7D%29+%28r_1%2Cr_2%2Cm_2-m_1%29%5E%7B1%2F2%7D.&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0' alt='&#92;displaystyle (&#92;frac{ H_{&#92;vec b}}{[r_1,r_2]^{1/2} (Q_{&#92;vec b}/r_1)^{1/2}} + [r_1,r_2]^{1/2} (Q_{&#92;vec b}/r_1)^{1/2}) (r_1,r_2,m_2-m_1)^{1/2}.' title='&#92;displaystyle (&#92;frac{ H_{&#92;vec b}}{[r_1,r_2]^{1/2} (Q_{&#92;vec b}/r_1)^{1/2}} + [r_1,r_2]^{1/2} (Q_{&#92;vec b}/r_1)^{1/2}) (r_1,r_2,m_2-m_1)^{1/2}.' class='latex' /></p> <p> Similarly, we have <p align="center"><img src='http://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%5Cdisplaystyle++%5Csum_%7Bm_1%2Cm_2+%5Csim+M%3A+d+%7C+m_2-m_1%7D+d%5E%7B1%2F2%7D+%5Clessapprox+%5Cfrac%7BM%5E2%7D%7Bd%5E%7B1%2F2%7D%7D+%2B+M+d%5E%7B1%2F2%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0' alt='&#92;displaystyle &#92;sum_{m_1,m_2 &#92;sim M: d | m_2-m_1} d^{1/2} &#92;lessapprox &#92;frac{M^2}{d^{1/2}} + M d^{1/2}' title='&#92;displaystyle &#92;sum_{m_1,m_2 &#92;sim M: d | m_2-m_1} d^{1/2} &#92;lessapprox &#92;frac{M^2}{d^{1/2}} + M d^{1/2}' class='latex' /></p> <p> for all <img src='http://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7Bd%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0' alt='{d}' title='{d}' class='latex' />, so on summing over all <img src='http://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7Bd%7C%28r_1%2Cr_2%29%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0' alt='{d|(r_1,r_2)}' title='{d|(r_1,r_2)}' class='latex' /> we have <p align="center"><img src='http://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%5Cdisplaystyle++%5Csum_%7Bm_1%2Cm_2+%5Csim+M%7D+%28r_1%2Cr_2%2Cm_2-m_1%29%5E%7B1%2F2%7D+%5Clessapprox+M%5E2+%2B+M+%28r_1%2Cr_2%29%5E%7B1%2F2%7D.&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0' alt='&#92;displaystyle &#92;sum_{m_1,m_2 &#92;sim M} (r_1,r_2,m_2-m_1)^{1/2} &#92;lessapprox M^2 + M (r_1,r_2)^{1/2}.' title='&#92;displaystyle &#92;sum_{m_1,m_2 &#92;sim M} (r_1,r_2,m_2-m_1)^{1/2} &#92;lessapprox M^2 + M (r_1,r_2)^{1/2}.' class='latex' /></p> <p> We thus have <p align="center"><img src='http://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%5Cdisplaystyle++S%27_%7B%5Cvec+b%7D%5Clessapprox+M+S_0+Q_%7B%5Cvec+b%7D+H_%7B%5Cvec+b%7D+%2B+%5Csum_%7Br_1%2Cr_2+%5Cin+%7B%5Cmathcal+S%7D_I%3A+Q_%7B%5Cvec+b%7D%2FS_0+%5Cll+r_1+%5Csim+r_2+%5Cll+yQ_%7B%5Cvec+b%7D%2FS_0%7D+%28Q_%7B%5Cvec+b%7D%2Fr_1%29%5E2+&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0' alt='&#92;displaystyle S&#039;_{&#92;vec b}&#92;lessapprox M S_0 Q_{&#92;vec b} H_{&#92;vec b} + &#92;sum_{r_1,r_2 &#92;in {&#92;mathcal S}_I: Q_{&#92;vec b}/S_0 &#92;ll r_1 &#92;sim r_2 &#92;ll yQ_{&#92;vec b}/S_0} (Q_{&#92;vec b}/r_1)^2 ' title='&#92;displaystyle S&#039;_{&#92;vec b}&#92;lessapprox M S_0 Q_{&#92;vec b} H_{&#92;vec b} + &#92;sum_{r_1,r_2 &#92;in {&#92;mathcal S}_I: Q_{&#92;vec b}/S_0 &#92;ll r_1 &#92;sim r_2 &#92;ll yQ_{&#92;vec b}/S_0} (Q_{&#92;vec b}/r_1)^2 ' class='latex' /></p> <p align="center"><img src='http://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%5Cdisplaystyle++%28%5Cfrac%7B+H_%7B%5Cvec+b%7D%7D%7B%5Br_1%2Cr_2%5D%5E%7B1%2F2%7D+%28Q_%7B%5Cvec+b%7D%2Fr_1%29%5E%7B1%2F2%7D%7D+%2B+%5Br_1%2Cr_2%5D%5E%7B1%2F2%7D+%28Q_%7B%5Cvec+b%7D%2Fr_1%29%5E%7B1%2F2%7D%29+%28M%5E2+%2B+M+%28r_1%2Cr_2%29%5E%7B1%2F2%7D%29.&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0' alt='&#92;displaystyle (&#92;frac{ H_{&#92;vec b}}{[r_1,r_2]^{1/2} (Q_{&#92;vec b}/r_1)^{1/2}} + [r_1,r_2]^{1/2} (Q_{&#92;vec b}/r_1)^{1/2}) (M^2 + M (r_1,r_2)^{1/2}).' title='&#92;displaystyle (&#92;frac{ H_{&#92;vec b}}{[r_1,r_2]^{1/2} (Q_{&#92;vec b}/r_1)^{1/2}} + [r_1,r_2]^{1/2} (Q_{&#92;vec b}/r_1)^{1/2}) (M^2 + M (r_1,r_2)^{1/2}).' class='latex' /></p> <p> Writing <img src='http://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7Br_0+%3A%3D+%28r_1%2Cr_2%29%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0' alt='{r_0 := (r_1,r_2)}' title='{r_0 := (r_1,r_2)}' class='latex' />, <img src='http://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7Br_1+%3D+r_0+r%27_1%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0' alt='{r_1 = r_0 r&#039;_1}' title='{r_1 = r_0 r&#039;_1}' class='latex' /> and <img src='http://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7Br_2+%3D+r_0+r%27_2%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0' alt='{r_2 = r_0 r&#039;_2}' title='{r_2 = r_0 r&#039;_2}' class='latex' />, we thus have <p align="center"><img src='http://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%5Cdisplaystyle++S%27_%7B%5Cvec+b%7D%5Clessapprox+M+S_0Q_%7B%5Cvec+b%7D+H_%7B%5Cvec+b%7D+%2B+%5Csum_%7Br_0+%5Cll+yQ_%7B%5Cvec+b%7D%2FS_0%7D+%5Csum_%7Br%27_1%2Cr%27_2+%5Cin+%7B%5Cmathcal+S%7D_I%3A+%5Cfrac%7BQ_%7B%5Cvec+b%7D%7D%7BS_0+r_0%7D+%5Cll+r%27_1+%5Csim+r%27_2+%5Cll+%5Cfrac%7ByQ_%7B%5Cvec+b%7D%7D%7BS_0r_0%7D%7D+%28%5Cfrac%7BQ_%7B%5Cvec+b%7D%7D%7Br_0r%27_1%7D%29%5E2+&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0' alt='&#92;displaystyle S&#039;_{&#92;vec b}&#92;lessapprox M S_0Q_{&#92;vec b} H_{&#92;vec b} + &#92;sum_{r_0 &#92;ll yQ_{&#92;vec b}/S_0} &#92;sum_{r&#039;_1,r&#039;_2 &#92;in {&#92;mathcal S}_I: &#92;frac{Q_{&#92;vec b}}{S_0 r_0} &#92;ll r&#039;_1 &#92;sim r&#039;_2 &#92;ll &#92;frac{yQ_{&#92;vec b}}{S_0r_0}} (&#92;frac{Q_{&#92;vec b}}{r_0r&#039;_1})^2 ' title='&#92;displaystyle S&#039;_{&#92;vec b}&#92;lessapprox M S_0Q_{&#92;vec b} H_{&#92;vec b} + &#92;sum_{r_0 &#92;ll yQ_{&#92;vec b}/S_0} &#92;sum_{r&#039;_1,r&#039;_2 &#92;in {&#92;mathcal S}_I: &#92;frac{Q_{&#92;vec b}}{S_0 r_0} &#92;ll r&#039;_1 &#92;sim r&#039;_2 &#92;ll &#92;frac{yQ_{&#92;vec b}}{S_0r_0}} (&#92;frac{Q_{&#92;vec b}}{r_0r&#039;_1})^2 ' class='latex' /></p> <p align="center"><img src='http://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%5Cdisplaystyle++%28%5Cfrac%7B+H_%7B%5Cvec+b%7D%7D%7B%28Q_%7B%5Cvec+b%7D+r%27_2%29%5E%7B1%2F2%7D%7D+%2B+%28Q_%7B%5Cvec+b%7D+r%27_2%29%5E%7B1%2F2%7D%29+%28M%5E2+%2B+M+r_0%5E%7B1%2F2%7D%29.&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0' alt='&#92;displaystyle (&#92;frac{ H_{&#92;vec b}}{(Q_{&#92;vec b} r&#039;_2)^{1/2}} + (Q_{&#92;vec b} r&#039;_2)^{1/2}) (M^2 + M r_0^{1/2}).' title='&#92;displaystyle (&#92;frac{ H_{&#92;vec b}}{(Q_{&#92;vec b} r&#039;_2)^{1/2}} + (Q_{&#92;vec b} r&#039;_2)^{1/2}) (M^2 + M r_0^{1/2}).' class='latex' /></p> <p> Performing the <img src='http://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7Br%27_2%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0' alt='{r&#039;_2}' title='{r&#039;_2}' class='latex' /> summation, this becomes <p align="center"><img src='http://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%5Cdisplaystyle++S%27_%7B%5Cvec+b%7D%5Clessapprox+M+S_0+Q_%7B%5Cvec+b%7D+H_%7B%5Cvec+b%7D+%2B+%5Csum_%7Br_0+%5Cll+yQ_%7B%5Cvec+b%7D%2FS_0%7D+%5Csum_%7Br%27_1+%5Cin+%7B%5Cmathcal+S%7D_I%3A+%5Cfrac%7BQ_%7B%5Cvec+b%7D%7D%7BS_0+r_0%7D+%5Cll+r%27_1+%5Cll+%5Cfrac%7ByQ_%7B%5Cvec+b%7D%7D%7BS_0r_0%7D%7D+%28%5Cfrac%7BQ_%7B%5Cvec+b%7D%7D%7Br_0%7D%29%5E2+&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0' alt='&#92;displaystyle S&#039;_{&#92;vec b}&#92;lessapprox M S_0 Q_{&#92;vec b} H_{&#92;vec b} + &#92;sum_{r_0 &#92;ll yQ_{&#92;vec b}/S_0} &#92;sum_{r&#039;_1 &#92;in {&#92;mathcal S}_I: &#92;frac{Q_{&#92;vec b}}{S_0 r_0} &#92;ll r&#039;_1 &#92;ll &#92;frac{yQ_{&#92;vec b}}{S_0r_0}} (&#92;frac{Q_{&#92;vec b}}{r_0})^2 ' title='&#92;displaystyle S&#039;_{&#92;vec b}&#92;lessapprox M S_0 Q_{&#92;vec b} H_{&#92;vec b} + &#92;sum_{r_0 &#92;ll yQ_{&#92;vec b}/S_0} &#92;sum_{r&#039;_1 &#92;in {&#92;mathcal S}_I: &#92;frac{Q_{&#92;vec b}}{S_0 r_0} &#92;ll r&#039;_1 &#92;ll &#92;frac{yQ_{&#92;vec b}}{S_0r_0}} (&#92;frac{Q_{&#92;vec b}}{r_0})^2 ' class='latex' /></p> <p align="center"><img src='http://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%5Cdisplaystyle++%28%5Cfrac%7B+H_%7B%5Cvec+b%7D%7D%7BQ_%7B%5Cvec+b%7D%5E%7B1%2F2%7D%7D+%28r%27_1%29%5E%7B-3%2F2%7D+%2B+Q_%7B%5Cvec+b%7D%5E%7B1%2F2%7D+%28r%27_1%29%5E%7B-1%2F2%7D%29+%28M%5E2+%2B+M+r_0%5E%7B1%2F2%7D%29&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0' alt='&#92;displaystyle (&#92;frac{ H_{&#92;vec b}}{Q_{&#92;vec b}^{1/2}} (r&#039;_1)^{-3/2} + Q_{&#92;vec b}^{1/2} (r&#039;_1)^{-1/2}) (M^2 + M r_0^{1/2})' title='&#92;displaystyle (&#92;frac{ H_{&#92;vec b}}{Q_{&#92;vec b}^{1/2}} (r&#039;_1)^{-3/2} + Q_{&#92;vec b}^{1/2} (r&#039;_1)^{-1/2}) (M^2 + M r_0^{1/2})' class='latex' /></p> <p> and then performing the <img src='http://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7Br%27_1%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0' alt='{r&#039;_1}' title='{r&#039;_1}' class='latex' /> summation we obtain <p align="center"><img src='http://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%5Cdisplaystyle++S%27_%7B%5Cvec+b%7D%5Clessapprox+M+S_0+Q_%7B%5Cvec+b%7D+H_%7B%5Cvec+b%7D+%2B+%5Csum_%7Br_0+%5Cll+yQ_%7B%5Cvec+b%7D%2FS_0%7D+%28%5Cfrac%7BQ_%7B%5Cvec+b%7D%7D%7Br_0%7D%29%5E2+&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0' alt='&#92;displaystyle S&#039;_{&#92;vec b}&#92;lessapprox M S_0 Q_{&#92;vec b} H_{&#92;vec b} + &#92;sum_{r_0 &#92;ll yQ_{&#92;vec b}/S_0} (&#92;frac{Q_{&#92;vec b}}{r_0})^2 ' title='&#92;displaystyle S&#039;_{&#92;vec b}&#92;lessapprox M S_0 Q_{&#92;vec b} H_{&#92;vec b} + &#92;sum_{r_0 &#92;ll yQ_{&#92;vec b}/S_0} (&#92;frac{Q_{&#92;vec b}}{r_0})^2 ' class='latex' /></p> <p align="center"><img src='http://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%5Cdisplaystyle++%28%5Cfrac%7B+H_%7B%5Cvec+b%7D%7D%7BQ_%7B%5Cvec+b%7D%5E%7B1%2F2%7D%7D+%28%5Cfrac%7BQ_%7B%5Cvec+b%7D%7D%7BS_0+r_0%7D%29%5E%7B-1%2F2%7D+%2B+Q_%7B%5Cvec+b%7D%5E%7B1%2F2%7D+%28%5Cfrac%7ByQ_%7B%5Cvec+b%7D%7D%7BS_0+r_0%7D%29%5E%7B1%2F2%7D%29+%28M%5E2+%2B+M+r_0%5E%7B1%2F2%7D%29.&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0' alt='&#92;displaystyle (&#92;frac{ H_{&#92;vec b}}{Q_{&#92;vec b}^{1/2}} (&#92;frac{Q_{&#92;vec b}}{S_0 r_0})^{-1/2} + Q_{&#92;vec b}^{1/2} (&#92;frac{yQ_{&#92;vec b}}{S_0 r_0})^{1/2}) (M^2 + M r_0^{1/2}).' title='&#92;displaystyle (&#92;frac{ H_{&#92;vec b}}{Q_{&#92;vec b}^{1/2}} (&#92;frac{Q_{&#92;vec b}}{S_0 r_0})^{-1/2} + Q_{&#92;vec b}^{1/2} (&#92;frac{yQ_{&#92;vec b}}{S_0 r_0})^{1/2}) (M^2 + M r_0^{1/2}).' class='latex' /></p> <p> The net power of <img src='http://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7Br_0%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0' alt='{r_0}' title='{r_0}' class='latex' /> here is always at most <img src='http://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7B-1%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0' alt='{-1}' title='{-1}' class='latex' />, so the <img src='http://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7Br_0%3D1%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0' alt='{r_0=1}' title='{r_0=1}' class='latex' /> term in the summation dominates: <p align="center"><img src='http://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%5Cdisplaystyle++S%27_%7B%5Cvec+b%7D%5Clessapprox+M+S_0+Q_%7B%5Cvec+b%7D+H_%7B%5Cvec+b%7D+%2B+Q_%7B%5Cvec+b%7D%5E2+&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0' alt='&#92;displaystyle S&#039;_{&#92;vec b}&#92;lessapprox M S_0 Q_{&#92;vec b} H_{&#92;vec b} + Q_{&#92;vec b}^2 ' title='&#92;displaystyle S&#039;_{&#92;vec b}&#92;lessapprox M S_0 Q_{&#92;vec b} H_{&#92;vec b} + Q_{&#92;vec b}^2 ' class='latex' /></p> <p align="center"><img src='http://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%5Cdisplaystyle++%28%5Cfrac%7B+H_%7B%5Cvec+b%7D%7D%7BQ_%7B%5Cvec+b%7D%5E%7B1%2F2%7D%7D+%28%5Cfrac%7BQ_%7B%5Cvec+b%7D%7D%7BS_0%7D%29%5E%7B-1%2F2%7D+%2B+Q_%7B%5Cvec+b%7D%5E%7B1%2F2%7D+%28%5Cfrac%7ByQ_%7B%5Cvec+b%7D%7D%7BS_0%7D%29%5E%7B1%2F2%7D%29+M%5E2.&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0' alt='&#92;displaystyle (&#92;frac{ H_{&#92;vec b}}{Q_{&#92;vec b}^{1/2}} (&#92;frac{Q_{&#92;vec b}}{S_0})^{-1/2} + Q_{&#92;vec b}^{1/2} (&#92;frac{yQ_{&#92;vec b}}{S_0})^{1/2}) M^2.' title='&#92;displaystyle (&#92;frac{ H_{&#92;vec b}}{Q_{&#92;vec b}^{1/2}} (&#92;frac{Q_{&#92;vec b}}{S_0})^{-1/2} + Q_{&#92;vec b}^{1/2} (&#92;frac{yQ_{&#92;vec b}}{S_0})^{1/2}) M^2.' class='latex' /></p> <p> We simplify this as <a name="spb"> <p align="center"><img src='http://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%5Cdisplaystyle++S%27_%7B%5Cvec+b%7D+%5Clessapprox+M+S_0+Q_%7B%5Cvec+b%7D+H_%7B%5Cvec+b%7D+%2B+M%5E2+H_%7B%5Cvec+b%7D+Q_%7B%5Cvec+b%7D+S_0%5E%7B1%2F2%7D+%2B+y%5E%7B1%2F2%7D+M%5E2+Q_%7B%5Cvec+b%7D%5E3+S_0%5E%7B-1%2F2%7D.+%5C+%5C+%5C+%5C+%5C+%2843%29&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0' alt='&#92;displaystyle S&#039;_{&#92;vec b} &#92;lessapprox M S_0 Q_{&#92;vec b} H_{&#92;vec b} + M^2 H_{&#92;vec b} Q_{&#92;vec b} S_0^{1/2} + y^{1/2} M^2 Q_{&#92;vec b}^3 S_0^{-1/2}. &#92; &#92; &#92; &#92; &#92; (43)' title='&#92;displaystyle S&#039;_{&#92;vec b} &#92;lessapprox M S_0 Q_{&#92;vec b} H_{&#92;vec b} + M^2 H_{&#92;vec b} Q_{&#92;vec b} S_0^{1/2} + y^{1/2} M^2 Q_{&#92;vec b}^3 S_0^{-1/2}. &#92; &#92; &#92; &#92; &#92; (43)' class='latex' /></p> <p></a> To optimise this in <img src='http://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7BS_0%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0' alt='{S_0}' title='{S_0}' class='latex' />, we select <p align="center"><img src='http://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%5Cdisplaystyle++S_0+%3A%3D+%5Cmin%28+Q_%7B%5Cvec+b%7D%5E%7B4%2F3%7D+M%5E%7B2%2F3%7D+H_%7B%5Cvec+b%7D%5E%7B-2%2F3%7D+y%5E%7B1%2F3%7D%2C+yQ_%7B%5Cvec+b%7D+%29.&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0' alt='&#92;displaystyle S_0 := &#92;min( Q_{&#92;vec b}^{4/3} M^{2/3} H_{&#92;vec b}^{-2/3} y^{1/3}, yQ_{&#92;vec b} ).' title='&#92;displaystyle S_0 := &#92;min( Q_{&#92;vec b}^{4/3} M^{2/3} H_{&#92;vec b}^{-2/3} y^{1/3}, yQ_{&#92;vec b} ).' class='latex' /></p> <p> (The quantity <img src='http://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7BQ_%7B%5Cvec+b%7D%5E%7B4%2F3%7D+M%5E%7B2%2F3%7D+H_%7B%5Cvec+b%7D%5E%7B-2%2F3%7D+y%5E%7B1%2F3%7D%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0' alt='{Q_{&#92;vec b}^{4/3} M^{2/3} H_{&#92;vec b}^{-2/3} y^{1/3}}' title='{Q_{&#92;vec b}^{4/3} M^{2/3} H_{&#92;vec b}^{-2/3} y^{1/3}}' class='latex' /> comes from equating <img src='http://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7BMS_0+Q_%7B%5Cvec+b%7D+H_%7B%5Cvec+b%7D%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0' alt='{MS_0 Q_{&#92;vec b} H_{&#92;vec b}}' title='{MS_0 Q_{&#92;vec b} H_{&#92;vec b}}' class='latex' /> and <img src='http://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7By%5E%7B1%2F2%7D+M%5E2+Q_%7B%5Cvec+b%7D%5E3+S_0%5E%7B-1%2F2%7D%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0' alt='{y^{1/2} M^2 Q_{&#92;vec b}^3 S_0^{-1/2}}' title='{y^{1/2} M^2 Q_{&#92;vec b}^3 S_0^{-1/2}}' class='latex' />.) By construction, we have the second inequality in <a href="#q">(40)</a>. We also claim the first inequality, since this is equivalent to <p align="center"><img src='http://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%5Cdisplaystyle++H_%7B%5Cvec+b%7D+%5Cleq+Q_%7B%5Cvec+b%7D%5E2+M+y%5E%7B1%2F2%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0' alt='&#92;displaystyle H_{&#92;vec b} &#92;leq Q_{&#92;vec b}^2 M y^{1/2}' title='&#92;displaystyle H_{&#92;vec b} &#92;leq Q_{&#92;vec b}^2 M y^{1/2}' class='latex' /></p> <p> which would follow if <p align="center"><img src='http://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%5Cdisplaystyle++b%5E%7B1%2F2%7D+Q+%5Cfrac%7Bb%7D%7Bb_1+b_2+b_3%7D+%5Cleq+x%5E%7B1%2B%5Cdelta%2F2-4%5Cepsilon%7D.&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0' alt='&#92;displaystyle b^{1/2} Q &#92;frac{b}{b_1 b_2 b_3} &#92;leq x^{1+&#92;delta/2-4&#92;epsilon}.' title='&#92;displaystyle b^{1/2} Q &#92;frac{b}{b_1 b_2 b_3} &#92;leq x^{1+&#92;delta/2-4&#92;epsilon}.' class='latex' /></p> <p> But from <a href="#bqb">(41)</a> one has <img src='http://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7Bb%5E%7B1%2F2%7D+%5Cll+Q%5E%7B1%2F2%7D%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0' alt='{b^{1/2} &#92;ll Q^{1/2}}' title='{b^{1/2} &#92;ll Q^{1/2}}' class='latex' /> and <img src='http://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7B%5Cfrac%7Bb%7D%7Bb_1+b_2+b_3%7D+%5Cleq+1%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0' alt='{&#92;frac{b}{b_1 b_2 b_3} &#92;leq 1}' title='{&#92;frac{b}{b_1 b_2 b_3} &#92;leq 1}' class='latex' />, and the claim now follows from <a href="#qp">(36)</a> and <a href="#vp-crude">(13)</a>.</p> <p> Inserting this value of <img src='http://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7BS_0%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0' alt='{S_0}' title='{S_0}' class='latex' /> (using <img src='http://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7BS_0+%5Cleq+Q_%7B%5Cvec+b%7D%5E%7B4%2F3%7D+M%5E%7B2%2F3%7D+H_%7B%5Cvec+b%7D%5E%7B-2%2F3%7D+y%5E%7B1%2F3%7D%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0' alt='{S_0 &#92;leq Q_{&#92;vec b}^{4/3} M^{2/3} H_{&#92;vec b}^{-2/3} y^{1/3}}' title='{S_0 &#92;leq Q_{&#92;vec b}^{4/3} M^{2/3} H_{&#92;vec b}^{-2/3} y^{1/3}}' class='latex' /> for the first two terms in <a href="#spb">(43)</a>), we conclude that </p> <p align="center"><img src='http://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%5Cdisplaystyle++S%27_%7B%5Cvec+b%7D+%5Clessapprox+M%5E%7B5%2F3%7D+Q_%7B%5Cvec+b%7D%5E%7B7%2F3%7D+H_%7B%5Cvec+b%7D%5E%7B1%2F3%7D+y%5E%7B1%2F3%7D+%2B+M%5E%7B7%2F3%7D+H_%7B%5Cvec+b%7D%5E%7B2%2F3%7D+Q_%7B%5Cvec+b%7D%5E%7B5%2F3%7D+y%5E%7B1%2F6%7D+%2B+M%5E2+Q_%7B%5Cvec+b%7D%5E%7B5%2F2%7D.&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0' alt='&#92;displaystyle S&#039;_{&#92;vec b} &#92;lessapprox M^{5/3} Q_{&#92;vec b}^{7/3} H_{&#92;vec b}^{1/3} y^{1/3} + M^{7/3} H_{&#92;vec b}^{2/3} Q_{&#92;vec b}^{5/3} y^{1/6} + M^2 Q_{&#92;vec b}^{5/2}.' title='&#92;displaystyle S&#039;_{&#92;vec b} &#92;lessapprox M^{5/3} Q_{&#92;vec b}^{7/3} H_{&#92;vec b}^{1/3} y^{1/3} + M^{7/3} H_{&#92;vec b}^{2/3} Q_{&#92;vec b}^{5/3} y^{1/6} + M^2 Q_{&#92;vec b}^{5/2}.' class='latex' /></p> <p> One should view the first term here as the main term. By <a href="#moo">(42)</a>, we conclude that <p align="center"><img src='http://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%5Cdisplaystyle++S_%7B%5Cvec+b%7D+%5Clessapprox+M%5E%7B5%2F6%7D+Q_%7B%5Cvec+b%7D%5E%7B7%2F6%7D+H_%7B%5Cvec+b%7D%5E%7B2%2F3%7D+y%5E%7B1%2F6%7D+%2B+M%5E%7B7%2F6%7D+H_%7B%5Cvec+b%7D%5E%7B5%2F6%7D+Q_%7B%5Cvec+b%7D%5E%7B5%2F6%7D+y%5E%7B1%2F12%7D+%2B+M+H_%7B%5Cvec+b%7D%5E%7B1%2F2%7D+Q_%7B%5Cvec+b%7D%5E%7B5%2F4%7D.&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0' alt='&#92;displaystyle S_{&#92;vec b} &#92;lessapprox M^{5/6} Q_{&#92;vec b}^{7/6} H_{&#92;vec b}^{2/3} y^{1/6} + M^{7/6} H_{&#92;vec b}^{5/6} Q_{&#92;vec b}^{5/6} y^{1/12} + M H_{&#92;vec b}^{1/2} Q_{&#92;vec b}^{5/4}.' title='&#92;displaystyle S_{&#92;vec b} &#92;lessapprox M^{5/6} Q_{&#92;vec b}^{7/6} H_{&#92;vec b}^{2/3} y^{1/6} + M^{7/6} H_{&#92;vec b}^{5/6} Q_{&#92;vec b}^{5/6} y^{1/12} + M H_{&#92;vec b}^{1/2} Q_{&#92;vec b}^{5/4}.' class='latex' /></p> <p> Since <img src='http://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7BH_%7B%5Cvec+b%7D+%3D+x%5E%7B3%5Cepsilon%7D+H+%28b_1+b_2+b_3%29%5E%7B-1%7D+%5Cleq+x%5E%7B3%5Cepsilon%7D+H+b%5E%7B-1%7D%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0' alt='{H_{&#92;vec b} = x^{3&#92;epsilon} H (b_1 b_2 b_3)^{-1} &#92;leq x^{3&#92;epsilon} H b^{-1}}' title='{H_{&#92;vec b} = x^{3&#92;epsilon} H (b_1 b_2 b_3)^{-1} &#92;leq x^{3&#92;epsilon} H b^{-1}}' class='latex' />, <img src='http://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7BQ_%7B%5Cvec+b%7D+%3D+Q+b%5E%7B-1%7D%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0' alt='{Q_{&#92;vec b} = Q b^{-1}}' title='{Q_{&#92;vec b} = Q b^{-1}}' class='latex' />, and <img src='http://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7By+%3D+x%5E%5Cdelta+b%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0' alt='{y = x^&#92;delta b}' title='{y = x^&#92;delta b}' class='latex' />, we thus have <p align="center"><img src='http://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%5Cdisplaystyle++S_%7B%5Cvec+b%7D+%5Clessapprox+x%5E%7B5%5Cepsilon%2F2%7D+b%5E%7B-1%7D+%28b_1+b_2+b_3%29%5E%7B-1%2F2%7D+%28+M%5E%7B5%2F6%7D+Q%5E%7B7%2F6%7D+H%5E%7B2%2F3%7D+x%5E%7B%5Cdelta%2F6%7D+%2B+M%5E%7B7%2F6%7D+H%5E%7B5%2F6%7D+Q%5E%7B5%2F6%7D+x%5E%7B%5Cdelta%2F12%7D+%2B+M+H%5E%7B1%2F2%7D+Q%5E%7B5%2F4%7D+%29.&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0' alt='&#92;displaystyle S_{&#92;vec b} &#92;lessapprox x^{5&#92;epsilon/2} b^{-1} (b_1 b_2 b_3)^{-1/2} ( M^{5/6} Q^{7/6} H^{2/3} x^{&#92;delta/6} + M^{7/6} H^{5/6} Q^{5/6} x^{&#92;delta/12} + M H^{1/2} Q^{5/4} ).' title='&#92;displaystyle S_{&#92;vec b} &#92;lessapprox x^{5&#92;epsilon/2} b^{-1} (b_1 b_2 b_3)^{-1/2} ( M^{5/6} Q^{7/6} H^{2/3} x^{&#92;delta/6} + M^{7/6} H^{5/6} Q^{5/6} x^{&#92;delta/12} + M H^{1/2} Q^{5/4} ).' class='latex' /></p> <p> From Euler products we see that <p align="center"><img src='http://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%5Cdisplaystyle++%5Csum_%7B%5Cvec+b%7D+%5Cfrac%7B%5Chbox%7Brad%7D%28b_1%29+%5Chbox%7Brad%7D%28b_2%29+%5Chbox%7Brad%7D%28b_3%29%7D%7Bb%5E2%7D+b%5E%7B-1%7D+%28b_1+b_2+b_3%29%5E%7B-1%2F2%7D+%5Cll+1&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0' alt='&#92;displaystyle &#92;sum_{&#92;vec b} &#92;frac{&#92;hbox{rad}(b_1) &#92;hbox{rad}(b_2) &#92;hbox{rad}(b_3)}{b^2} b^{-1} (b_1 b_2 b_3)^{-1/2} &#92;ll 1' title='&#92;displaystyle &#92;sum_{&#92;vec b} &#92;frac{&#92;hbox{rad}(b_1) &#92;hbox{rad}(b_2) &#92;hbox{rad}(b_3)}{b^2} b^{-1} (b_1 b_2 b_3)^{-1/2} &#92;ll 1' class='latex' /></p> <p> and so to prove <a href="#task">(39)</a> it will suffice to show that <p align="center"><img src='http://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%5Cdisplaystyle++M%5E%7B5%2F6%7D+Q%5E%7B7%2F6%7D+H%5E%7B2%2F3%7D+x%5E%7B%5Cdelta%2F6%7D+%2B+M%5E%7B7%2F6%7D+H%5E%7B5%2F6%7D+Q%5E%7B5%2F6%7D+x%5E%7B%5Cdelta%2F12%7D+%2B+M+H%5E%7B1%2F2%7D+Q%5E%7B5%2F4%7D+%5Clessapprox+x%5E%7B-5%5Cepsilon%7D+M+Q%5E2.&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0' alt='&#92;displaystyle M^{5/6} Q^{7/6} H^{2/3} x^{&#92;delta/6} + M^{7/6} H^{5/6} Q^{5/6} x^{&#92;delta/12} + M H^{1/2} Q^{5/4} &#92;lessapprox x^{-5&#92;epsilon} M Q^2.' title='&#92;displaystyle M^{5/6} Q^{7/6} H^{2/3} x^{&#92;delta/6} + M^{7/6} H^{5/6} Q^{5/6} x^{&#92;delta/12} + M H^{1/2} Q^{5/4} &#92;lessapprox x^{-5&#92;epsilon} M Q^2.' class='latex' /></p> <p> We can rewrite these conditions as upper bounds on <img src='http://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7BH%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0' alt='{H}' title='{H}' class='latex' />: </p> <p align="center"><img src='http://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%5Cdisplaystyle++H+%5Clessapprox+x%5E%7B-%5Cdelta%2F4+-+15+%5Cepsilon%2F2%7D+M%5E%7B1%2F4%7D+Q%5E%7B5%2F4%7D+&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0' alt='&#92;displaystyle H &#92;lessapprox x^{-&#92;delta/4 - 15 &#92;epsilon/2} M^{1/4} Q^{5/4} ' title='&#92;displaystyle H &#92;lessapprox x^{-&#92;delta/4 - 15 &#92;epsilon/2} M^{1/4} Q^{5/4} ' class='latex' /></p> <p align="center"><img src='http://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%5Cdisplaystyle++H+%5Clessapprox+x%5E%7B-%5Cdelta%2F10+-+6+%5Cepsilon%7D+M%5E%7B-1%2F5%7D+Q%5E%7B7%2F5%7D+&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0' alt='&#92;displaystyle H &#92;lessapprox x^{-&#92;delta/10 - 6 &#92;epsilon} M^{-1/5} Q^{7/5} ' title='&#92;displaystyle H &#92;lessapprox x^{-&#92;delta/10 - 6 &#92;epsilon} M^{-1/5} Q^{7/5} ' class='latex' /></p> <p align="center"><img src='http://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%5Cdisplaystyle++H+%5Clessapprox+x%5E%7B-10%5Cepsilon%7D+Q%5E%7B3%2F2%7D.&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0' alt='&#92;displaystyle H &#92;lessapprox x^{-10&#92;epsilon} Q^{3/2}.' title='&#92;displaystyle H &#92;lessapprox x^{-10&#92;epsilon} Q^{3/2}.' class='latex' /></p> <p> As <img src='http://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7BH+%3D+Q%5E3+%2F+N%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0' alt='{H = Q^3 / N}' title='{H = Q^3 / N}' class='latex' /> and <img src='http://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7BMN+%5Csim+x%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0' alt='{MN &#92;sim x}' title='{MN &#92;sim x}' class='latex' />, we can rewrite these conditions as upper bounds on <img src='http://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7BQ%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0' alt='{Q}' title='{Q}' class='latex' />: <p align="center"><img src='http://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%5Cdisplaystyle++Q%5E%7B7%2F4%7D+%5Clessapprox+x%5E%7B1%2F4-%5Cdelta%2F4+-+15+%5Cepsilon%2F2%7D+N%5E%7B3%2F4%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0' alt='&#92;displaystyle Q^{7/4} &#92;lessapprox x^{1/4-&#92;delta/4 - 15 &#92;epsilon/2} N^{3/4}' title='&#92;displaystyle Q^{7/4} &#92;lessapprox x^{1/4-&#92;delta/4 - 15 &#92;epsilon/2} N^{3/4}' class='latex' /></p> <p align="center"><img src='http://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%5Cdisplaystyle++Q%5E%7B8%2F5%7D+%5Clessapprox+x%5E%7B-1%2F5-%5Cdelta%2F10+-+6+%5Cepsilon%7D+N%5E%7B6%2F5%7D+&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0' alt='&#92;displaystyle Q^{8/5} &#92;lessapprox x^{-1/5-&#92;delta/10 - 6 &#92;epsilon} N^{6/5} ' title='&#92;displaystyle Q^{8/5} &#92;lessapprox x^{-1/5-&#92;delta/10 - 6 &#92;epsilon} N^{6/5} ' class='latex' /></p> <p align="center"><img src='http://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%5Cdisplaystyle++Q%5E%7B3%2F2%7D+%5Clessapprox+x%5E%7B-10%5Cepsilon%7D+N.&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0' alt='&#92;displaystyle Q^{3/2} &#92;lessapprox x^{-10&#92;epsilon} N.' title='&#92;displaystyle Q^{3/2} &#92;lessapprox x^{-10&#92;epsilon} N.' class='latex' /></p> <p> Since <img src='http://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7BN+%5Cgtrapprox+x%5E%7B%5Cfrac%7B3%7D%7B2%7D+%28%5Cfrac%7B1%7D%7B2%7D%2B%5Csigma%29%7D%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0' alt='{N &#92;gtrapprox x^{&#92;frac{3}{2} (&#92;frac{1}{2}+&#92;sigma)}}' title='{N &#92;gtrapprox x^{&#92;frac{3}{2} (&#92;frac{1}{2}+&#92;sigma)}}' class='latex' /> and <img src='http://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7BQ+%5Clessapprox+x%5E%7B1%2F2%2B2%5Cvarpi%7D%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0' alt='{Q &#92;lessapprox x^{1/2+2&#92;varpi}}' title='{Q &#92;lessapprox x^{1/2+2&#92;varpi}}' class='latex' />, these conditions become <p align="center"><img src='http://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%5Cdisplaystyle++%5Cfrac%7B7%7D%7B4%7D+%28%5Cfrac%7B1%7D%7B2%7D%2B2%5Cvarpi%29+%3C+%5Cfrac%7B1%7D%7B4%7D+-+%5Cfrac%7B%5Cdelta%7D%7B4%7D+%2B+%5Cfrac%7B3%7D%7B4%7D+%5Cfrac%7B3%7D%7B2%7D+%28%5Cfrac%7B1%7D%7B2%7D+%2B+%5Csigma%29+&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0' alt='&#92;displaystyle &#92;frac{7}{4} (&#92;frac{1}{2}+2&#92;varpi) &lt; &#92;frac{1}{4} - &#92;frac{&#92;delta}{4} + &#92;frac{3}{4} &#92;frac{3}{2} (&#92;frac{1}{2} + &#92;sigma) ' title='&#92;displaystyle &#92;frac{7}{4} (&#92;frac{1}{2}+2&#92;varpi) &lt; &#92;frac{1}{4} - &#92;frac{&#92;delta}{4} + &#92;frac{3}{4} &#92;frac{3}{2} (&#92;frac{1}{2} + &#92;sigma) ' class='latex' /></p> <p align="center"><img src='http://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%5Cdisplaystyle++%5Cfrac%7B8%7D%7B5%7D+%28%5Cfrac%7B1%7D%7B2%7D%2B2%5Cvarpi%29+%3C+-%5Cfrac%7B1%7D%7B5%7D+-+%5Cfrac%7B%5Cdelta%7D%7B10%7D+%2B+%5Cfrac%7B6%7D%7B5%7D+%5Cfrac%7B3%7D%7B2%7D+%28%5Cfrac%7B1%7D%7B2%7D+%2B+%5Csigma%29+&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0' alt='&#92;displaystyle &#92;frac{8}{5} (&#92;frac{1}{2}+2&#92;varpi) &lt; -&#92;frac{1}{5} - &#92;frac{&#92;delta}{10} + &#92;frac{6}{5} &#92;frac{3}{2} (&#92;frac{1}{2} + &#92;sigma) ' title='&#92;displaystyle &#92;frac{8}{5} (&#92;frac{1}{2}+2&#92;varpi) &lt; -&#92;frac{1}{5} - &#92;frac{&#92;delta}{10} + &#92;frac{6}{5} &#92;frac{3}{2} (&#92;frac{1}{2} + &#92;sigma) ' class='latex' /></p> <p align="center"><img src='http://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%5Cdisplaystyle++%5Cfrac%7B3%7D%7B2%7D+%28%5Cfrac%7B1%7D%7B2%7D%2B2%5Cvarpi%29+%3C+%5Cfrac%7B3%7D%7B2%7D+%28%5Cfrac%7B1%7D%7B2%7D+%2B+%5Csigma%29+&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0' alt='&#92;displaystyle &#92;frac{3}{2} (&#92;frac{1}{2}+2&#92;varpi) &lt; &#92;frac{3}{2} (&#92;frac{1}{2} + &#92;sigma) ' title='&#92;displaystyle &#92;frac{3}{2} (&#92;frac{1}{2}+2&#92;varpi) &lt; &#92;frac{3}{2} (&#92;frac{1}{2} + &#92;sigma) ' class='latex' /></p> <p> which we may rearrange as <p align="center"><img src='http://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%5Cdisplaystyle++%5Csigma+%3E+%5Cfrac%7B1%7D%7B18%7D+%2B+%5Cfrac%7B28%7D%7B9%7D+%5Cvarpi+%2B+%5Cfrac%7B2%7D%7B9%7D+%5Cdelta&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0' alt='&#92;displaystyle &#92;sigma &gt; &#92;frac{1}{18} + &#92;frac{28}{9} &#92;varpi + &#92;frac{2}{9} &#92;delta' title='&#92;displaystyle &#92;sigma &gt; &#92;frac{1}{18} + &#92;frac{28}{9} &#92;varpi + &#92;frac{2}{9} &#92;delta' class='latex' /></p> <p align="center"><img src='http://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%5Cdisplaystyle++%5Csigma+%3E+%5Cfrac%7B1%7D%7B18%7D+%2B+%5Cfrac%7B16%7D%7B9%7D+%5Cvarpi+%2B+%5Cfrac%7B1%7D%7B18%7D+%5Cdelta&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0' alt='&#92;displaystyle &#92;sigma &gt; &#92;frac{1}{18} + &#92;frac{16}{9} &#92;varpi + &#92;frac{1}{18} &#92;delta' title='&#92;displaystyle &#92;sigma &gt; &#92;frac{1}{18} + &#92;frac{16}{9} &#92;varpi + &#92;frac{1}{18} &#92;delta' class='latex' /></p> <p align="center"><img src='http://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%5Cdisplaystyle++%5Csigma+%3E+2+%5Cvarpi&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0' alt='&#92;displaystyle &#92;sigma &gt; 2 &#92;varpi' title='&#92;displaystyle &#92;sigma &gt; 2 &#92;varpi' class='latex' /></p> <p> but these follow from <a href="#sock">(12)</a>. The proof of Theorem <a href="#t3-precise">6</a> is complete.</p> <br />Filed under: <a href='http://terrytao.wordpress.com/category/mathematics/mathnt/'>math.NT</a>, <a href='http://terrytao.wordpress.com/category/question/polymath/'>polymath</a> Tagged: <a href='http://terrytao.wordpress.com/tag/exponential-sums/'>exponential sums</a>, <a href='http://terrytao.wordpress.com/tag/polymath8/'>polymath8</a> <a rel="nofollow" href="http://feeds.wordpress.com/1.0/gocomments/terrytao.wordpress.com/6924/"><img alt="" border="0" src="http://feeds.wordpress.com/1.0/comments/terrytao.wordpress.com/6924/" /></a> <img alt="" border="0" src="http://stats.wordpress.com/b.gif?host=terrytao.wordpress.com&#038;blog=817149&#038;post=6924&#038;subd=terrytao&#038;ref=&#038;feed=1" width="1" height="1" />
