tex' /> is <img src='http://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7B%5Clessapprox+1%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0' alt='{&#92;lessapprox 1}' title='{&#92;lessapprox 1}' class='latex' />. </p> <p> This post is intended to highlight a phenomenon unearthed in the ongoing <a href="http://michaelnielsen.org/polymath1/index.php?title=Bounded_gaps_between_primes">polymath8 project</a> (and is in fact a key component of <a href="http://annals.math.princeton.edu/wp-content/uploads/YitangZhang.pdf">Zhang&#8217;s proof</a> that there are bounded gaps between primes infinitely often), namely that one can get quite good bounds on relatively short exponential sums when the modulus <img src='http://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7Bq%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0' alt='{q}' title='{q}' class='latex' /> is smooth, through the basic technique of <em>Weyl differencing</em> (ultimately based on the Cauchy-Schwarz inequality, and also related to the van der Corput lemma in equidistribution theory). Improvements in the case of smooth moduli have appeared before in the literature (e.g. in this <a href="http://www.ams.org/mathscinet-getitem?mr=485727">paper of Heath-Brown</a>, <a href="http://www.ams.org/mathscinet-getitem?mr=1084186">paper of Graham and Ringrose</a>, this <a href="http://www.ams.org/mathscinet-getitem?mr=2753656">later paper of Heath-Brown</a>, this <a href="http://arxiv.org/abs/1201.0299">paper of Chang</a>, or this <a href="http://www.ams.org/mathscinet-getitem?mr=2730358">paper of Goldmakher</a>); the arguments here are particularly close to that of the first paper of Heath-Brown. It now also appears that further optimisation of this Weyl differencing trick could lead to noticeable improvements in the numerology for the polymath8 project, so I am devoting this post to explaining this trick further. </p> <p> To illustrate the method, let us begin with the classical problem in analytic number theory of estimating an <em>incomplete character sum</em> </p> <p align="center"><img src='http://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%5Cdisplaystyle++%5Csum_%7BM%2B1+%5Cleq+n+%5Cleq+M%2BN%7D+%5Cchi%28n%29&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0' alt='&#92;displaystyle &#92;sum_{M+1 &#92;leq n &#92;leq M+N} &#92;chi(n)' title='&#92;displaystyle &#92;sum_{M+1 &#92;leq n &#92;leq M+N} &#92;chi(n)' class='latex' /></p> <p> where <img src='http://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7B%5Cchi%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0' alt='{&#92;chi}' title='{&#92;chi}' class='latex' /> is a primitive <a href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Dirichlet_character">Dirichlet character</a> of some conductor <img src='http://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7Bq%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0' alt='{q}' title='{q}' class='latex' />, <img src='http://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7BM%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0' alt='{M}' title='{M}' class='latex' /> is an integer, and <img src='http://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7BN%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0' alt='{N}' title='{N}' class='latex' /> is some quantity between <img src='http://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7B1%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0' alt='{1}' title='{1}' class='latex' /> and <img src='http://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7Bq%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0' alt='{q}' title='{q}' class='latex' />. Clearly we have the trivial bound <a name="chin"> <p align="center"><img src='http://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%5Cdisplaystyle++%7C%5Csum_%7BM%2B1+%5Cleq+n+%5Cleq+M%2BN%7D+%5Cchi%28n%29%7C+%5Cleq+N%3B+%5C+%5C+%5C+%5C+%5C+%281%29&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0' alt='&#92;displaystyle |&#92;sum_{M+1 &#92;leq n &#92;leq M+N} &#92;chi(n)| &#92;leq N; &#92; &#92; &#92; &#92; &#92; (1)' title='&#92;displaystyle |&#92;sum_{M+1 &#92;leq n &#92;leq M+N} &#92;chi(n)| &#92;leq N; &#92; &#92; &#92; &#92; &#92; (1)' class='latex' /></p> <p></a> we also have the classical <a href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Polya-Vinogradov_inequality">P&oacute;lya-Vinogradov inequality</a> <a name="polya"> <p align="center"><img src='http://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%5Cdisplaystyle++%7C%5Csum_%7BM%2B1+%5Cleq+n+%5Cleq+M%2BN%7D+%5Cchi%28n%29%7C+%5Cll+q%5E%7B1%2F2%7D+%5Clog+q.+%5C+%5C+%5C+%5C+%5C+%282%29&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0' alt='&#92;displaystyle |&#92;sum_{M+1 &#92;leq n &#92;leq M+N} &#92;chi(n)| &#92;ll q^{1/2} &#92;log q. &#92; &#92; &#92; &#92; &#92; (2)' title='&#92;displaystyle |&#92;sum_{M+1 &#92;leq n &#92;leq M+N} &#92;chi(n)| &#92;ll q^{1/2} &#92;log q. &#92; &#92; &#92; &#92; &#92; (2)' class='latex' /></p> <p></a> This latter inequality gives improvements over the trivial bound when <img src='http://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7BN%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0' alt='{N}' title='{N}' class='latex' /> is much larger than <img src='http://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7Bq%5E%7B1%2F2%7D%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0' alt='{q^{1/2}}' title='{q^{1/2}}' class='latex' />, but not for <img src='http://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7BN%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0' alt='{N}' title='{N}' class='latex' /> much smaller than <img src='http://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7Bq%5E%7B1%2F2%7D%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0' alt='{q^{1/2}}' title='{q^{1/2}}' class='latex' />. The P&oacute;lya-Vinogradov inequality can be deduced via a little Fourier analysis from the completed exponential sum bound <p align="center"><img src='http://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%5Cdisplaystyle++%7C+%5Csum_%7Bn+%5Cin+%7B%5Cbf+Z%7D%2Fq%7B%5Cbf+Z%7D%7D+%5Cchi%28n%29+e_q%28+an+%29%7C+%5Cll+q%5E%7B1%2F2%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0' alt='&#92;displaystyle | &#92;sum_{n &#92;in {&#92;bf Z}/q{&#92;bf Z}} &#92;chi(n) e_q( an )| &#92;ll q^{1/2}' title='&#92;displaystyle | &#92;sum_{n &#92;in {&#92;bf Z}/q{&#92;bf Z}} &#92;chi(n) e_q( an )| &#92;ll q^{1/2}' class='latex' /></p> <p> for any <img src='http://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7Ba+%5Cin+%7B%5Cbf+Z%7D%2Fq%7B%5Cbf+Z%7D%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0' alt='{a &#92;in {&#92;bf Z}/q{&#92;bf Z}}' title='{a &#92;in {&#92;bf Z}/q{&#92;bf Z}}' class='latex' />, where <img src='http://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7Be_q%28n%29+%3A%3De%5E%7B2%5Cpi+i+n%2Fq%7D%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0' alt='{e_q(n) :=e^{2&#92;pi i n/q}}' title='{e_q(n) :=e^{2&#92;pi i n/q}}' class='latex' />. (In fact, from the classical theory of <a href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Gaussian_sum">Gauss sums</a>, this exponential sum is equal to <img src='http://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7B%5Ctau%28%5Cchi%29+%5Coverline%7B%5Cchi%28a%29%7D%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0' alt='{&#92;tau(&#92;chi) &#92;overline{&#92;chi(a)}}' title='{&#92;tau(&#92;chi) &#92;overline{&#92;chi(a)}}' class='latex' /> for some complex number <img src='http://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7B%5Ctau%28%5Cchi%29%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0' alt='{&#92;tau(&#92;chi)}' title='{&#92;tau(&#92;chi)}' class='latex' /> of norm <img src='http://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7B%5Csqrt%7Bq%7D%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0' alt='{&#92;sqrt{q}}' title='{&#92;sqrt{q}}' class='latex' />.)</p> <p> In the case when <img src='http://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7Bq%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0' alt='{q}' title='{q}' class='latex' /> is a prime, improving upon the above two inequalities is an important but difficult problem, with only partially satisfactory results so far. To give just one indication of the difficulty, the seemingly modest improvement </p> <p align="center"><img src='http://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%5Cdisplaystyle+%7C%5Csum_%7BM%2B1+%5Cleq+n+%5Cleq+M%2BN%7D+%5Cchi%28n%29%7C+%5Cll+p%5E%7B1%2F2%7D+%5Clog+%5Clog+p&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0' alt='&#92;displaystyle |&#92;sum_{M+1 &#92;leq n &#92;leq M+N} &#92;chi(n)| &#92;ll p^{1/2} &#92;log &#92;log p' title='&#92;displaystyle |&#92;sum_{M+1 &#92;leq n &#92;leq M+N} &#92;chi(n)| &#92;ll p^{1/2} &#92;log &#92;log p' class='latex' /></p> <p> to the P&oacute;lya-Vinogradov inequality when <img src='http://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7Bq%3Dp%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0' alt='{q=p}' title='{q=p}' class='latex' /> was a prime required a <a href="http://www.ams.org/mathscinet-getitem?mr=457371">14-page paper in Inventiones by Montgomery and Vaughan</a> to prove, and even then it was only conditional on the generalised Riemann hypothesis! See also this more <a href="http://www.ams.org/mathscinet-getitem?mr=2276774">recent paper of Granville and Soundararajan</a> for an unconditional variant of this result in the case that <img src='http://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7B%5Cchi%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0' alt='{&#92;chi}' title='{&#92;chi}' class='latex' /> has odd order.</p> <p> Another important improvement is the <a href="http://www.ams.org/mathscinet-getitem?mr=148626">Burgess bound</a>, which in our notation asserts that <a name="burg"> <p align="center"><img src='http://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%5Cdisplaystyle++%7C%5Csum_%7BM%2B1+%5Cleq+n+%5Cleq+M%2BN%7D+%5Cchi%28n%29%7C+%5Clessapprox+N%5E%7B1-1%2Fr%7D+q%5E%7B%5Cfrac%7Br%2B1%7D%7B4r%5E2%7D%7D+%5C+%5C+%5C+%5C+%5C+%283%29&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0' alt='&#92;displaystyle |&#92;sum_{M+1 &#92;leq n &#92;leq M+N} &#92;chi(n)| &#92;lessapprox N^{1-1/r} q^{&#92;frac{r+1}{4r^2}} &#92; &#92; &#92; &#92; &#92; (3)' title='&#92;displaystyle |&#92;sum_{M+1 &#92;leq n &#92;leq M+N} &#92;chi(n)| &#92;lessapprox N^{1-1/r} q^{&#92;frac{r+1}{4r^2}} &#92; &#92; &#92; &#92; &#92; (3)' class='latex' /></p> <p></a> for any fixed integer <img src='http://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7Br+%5Cgeq+2%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0' alt='{r &#92;geq 2}' title='{r &#92;geq 2}' class='latex' />, assuming that <img src='http://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7Bq%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0' alt='{q}' title='{q}' class='latex' /> is square-free (for simplicity) and of polynomial size; see <a href="http://terrytao.wordpress.com/2009/08/18/the-least-quadratic-nonresidue-and-the-square-root-barrier/">this previous post</a> for a discussion of the Burgess argument. This is non-trivial for <img src='http://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7BN%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0' alt='{N}' title='{N}' class='latex' /> as small as <img src='http://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7Bq%5E%7B1%2F4%2Bo%281%29%7D%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0' alt='{q^{1/4+o(1)}}' title='{q^{1/4+o(1)}}' class='latex' />. </p> <p> In the case when <img src='http://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7Bq%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0' alt='{q}' title='{q}' class='latex' /> is prime, there has been very little improvement to the Burgess bound (or its Fourier dual, which can give bounds for <img src='http://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7BN%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0' alt='{N}' title='{N}' class='latex' /> as large as <img src='http://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7Bq%5E%7B3%2F4-o%281%29%7D%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0' alt='{q^{3/4-o(1)}}' title='{q^{3/4-o(1)}}' class='latex' />) in the last fifty years; an improvement to the exponents in <a href="#burg">(3)</a> in this case (particularly anything that gave a power saving for <img src='http://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7BN%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0' alt='{N}' title='{N}' class='latex' /> below <img src='http://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7Bq%5E%7B1%2F4%7D%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0' alt='{q^{1/4}}' title='{q^{1/4}}' class='latex' />) would in fact be rather significant news in analytic number theory. </p> <p> However, in the opposite case when <img src='http://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7Bq%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0' alt='{q}' title='{q}' class='latex' /> is <em>smooth</em> &#8211; that is to say, all of its factors are much smaller than <img src='http://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7Bq%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0' alt='{q}' title='{q}' class='latex' /> &#8211; then one can do better than the Burgess bound in some regimes. This fact has been observed in several places in the literature (in particular, in the papers of <a href="http://www.ams.org/mathscinet-getitem?mr=485727">Heath-Brown</a>, <a href="http://www.ams.org/mathscinet-getitem?mr=1084186">Graham-Ringrose</a>, <a href="http://arxiv.org/abs/1201.0299">Chang</a>, and <a href="http://www.ams.org/mathscinet-getitem?mr=2730358">Goldmakher</a> mentioned previously), but also turns out to (implicitly) be a key insight in Zhang&#8217;s paper on bounded prime gaps. In the case of character sums, one such improved estimate (closely related to Theorem 2 of the <a href="http://www.ams.org/mathscinet-getitem?mr=485727">Heath-Brown paper</a>) is as follows: </p> <blockquote><p><b>Proposition 1</b> <a name="pcc"></a> Let <img src='http://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7Bq%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0' alt='{q}' title='{q}' class='latex' /> be square-free with a factorisation <img src='http://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7Bq+%3D+q_1+q_2%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0' alt='{q = q_1 q_2}' title='{q = q_1 q_2}' class='latex' /> and of polynomial size, and let <img src='http://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7BM%2CN%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0' alt='{M,N}' title='{M,N}' class='latex' /> be integers with <img src='http://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7B1+%5Cleq+N+%5Cleq+q%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0' alt='{1 &#92;leq N &#92;leq q}' title='{1 &#92;leq N &#92;leq q}' class='latex' />. Then for any primitive character <img src='http://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7B%5Cchi%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0' alt='{&#92;chi}' title='{&#92;chi}' class='latex' /> with conductor <img src='http://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7Bq%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0' alt='{q}' title='{q}' class='latex' />, one has <p align="center"><img src='http://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%5Cdisplaystyle++%7C+%5Csum_%7BM%2B1+%5Cleq+n+%5Cleq+M%2BN%7D+%5Cchi%28n%29+%7C+%5Clessapprox+N%5E%7B1%2F2%7D+q_1%5E%7B1%2F2%7D+%2B+N%5E%7B1%2F2%7D+q_2%5E%7B1%2F4%7D.&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0' alt='&#92;displaystyle | &#92;sum_{M+1 &#92;leq n &#92;leq M+N} &#92;chi(n) | &#92;lessapprox N^{1/2} q_1^{1/2} + N^{1/2} q_2^{1/4}.' title='&#92;displaystyle | &#92;sum_{M+1 &#92;leq n &#92;leq M+N} &#92;chi(n) | &#92;lessapprox N^{1/2} q_1^{1/2} + N^{1/2} q_2^{1/4}.' class='latex' /></p> </blockquote> </p> <p> This proposition is particularly powerful when <img src='http://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7Bq%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0' alt='{q}' title='{q}' class='latex' /> is smooth, as this gives many factorisations <img src='http://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7Bq+%3D+q_1+q_2%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0' alt='{q = q_1 q_2}' title='{q = q_1 q_2}' class='latex' /> with the ability to specify <img src='http://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7Bq_1%2Cq_2%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0' alt='{q_1,q_2}' title='{q_1,q_2}' class='latex' /> with a fair amount of accuracy. For instance, if <img src='http://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7Bq%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0' alt='{q}' title='{q}' class='latex' /> is <img src='http://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7By%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0' alt='{y}' title='{y}' class='latex' />-smooth (i.e. all prime factors are at most <img src='http://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7By%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0' alt='{y}' title='{y}' class='latex' />), then by the greedy algorithm one can find a divisor <img src='http://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7Bq_1%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0' alt='{q_1}' title='{q_1}' class='latex' /> of <img src='http://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7Bq%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0' alt='{q}' title='{q}' class='latex' /> with <img src='http://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7By%5E%7B-2%2F3%7D+q%5E%7B1%2F3%7D+%5Cleq+q_1+%5Cleq+y%5E%7B1%2F3%7D+q%5E%7B1%2F3%7D%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0' alt='{y^{-2/3} q^{1/3} &#92;leq q_1 &#92;leq y^{1/3} q^{1/3}}' title='{y^{-2/3} q^{1/3} &#92;leq q_1 &#92;leq y^{1/3} q^{1/3}}' class='latex' />; if we set <img src='http://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7Bq_2+%3A%3D+q%2Fq_1%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0' alt='{q_2 := q/q_1}' title='{q_2 := q/q_1}' class='latex' />, then <img src='http://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7By%5E%7B-1%2F3%7D+q%5E%7B2%2F3%7D+%5Cleq+q_2+%5Cleq+y%5E%7B2%2F3%7D+q%5E%7B2%2F3%7D%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0' alt='{y^{-1/3} q^{2/3} &#92;leq q_2 &#92;leq y^{2/3} q^{2/3}}' title='{y^{-1/3} q^{2/3} &#92;leq q_2 &#92;leq y^{2/3} q^{2/3}}' class='latex' />, and the above proposition then gives </p> <p align="center"><img src='http://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%5Cdisplaystyle++%7C+%5Csum_%7BM%2B1+%5Cleq+n+%5Cleq+M%2BN%7D+%5Cchi%28n%29+%7C+%5Clessapprox+y%5E%7B1%2F6%7D+N%5E%7B1%2F2%7D+q%5E%7B1%2F6%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0' alt='&#92;displaystyle | &#92;sum_{M+1 &#92;leq n &#92;leq M+N} &#92;chi(n) | &#92;lessapprox y^{1/6} N^{1/2} q^{1/6}' title='&#92;displaystyle | &#92;sum_{M+1 &#92;leq n &#92;leq M+N} &#92;chi(n) | &#92;lessapprox y^{1/6} N^{1/2} q^{1/6}' class='latex' /></p> <p> which can improve upon the Burgess bound when <img src='http://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7By%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0' alt='{y}' title='{y}' class='latex' /> is small. For instance, if <img src='http://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7BN+%3D+q%5E%7B1%2F2%7D%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0' alt='{N = q^{1/2}}' title='{N = q^{1/2}}' class='latex' />, then this bound becomes <img src='http://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7B%5Clessapprox+y%5E%7B1%2F6%7D+q%5E%7B5%2F12%7D%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0' alt='{&#92;lessapprox y^{1/6} q^{5/12}}' title='{&#92;lessapprox y^{1/6} q^{5/12}}' class='latex' />; in contrast the Burgess bound only gives <img src='http://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7B%5Clessapprox+q%5E%7B7%2F16%7D%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0' alt='{&#92;lessapprox q^{7/16}}' title='{&#92;lessapprox q^{7/16}}' class='latex' /> for this value of <img src='http://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7BN%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0' alt='{N}' title='{N}' class='latex' /> (using the optimal choice <img src='http://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7Br%3D2%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0' alt='{r=2}' title='{r=2}' class='latex' /> for <img src='http://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7Br%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0' alt='{r}' title='{r}' class='latex' />), which is inferior for <img src='http://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7By+%3C+q%5E%7B1%2F8%7D%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0' alt='{y &lt; q^{1/8}}' title='{y &lt; q^{1/8}}' class='latex' />. </p> <p> The hypothesis that <img src='http://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7Bq%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0' alt='{q}' title='{q}' class='latex' /> be squarefree may be relaxed, but for applications to the Polymath8 project, it is only the squarefree moduli that are relevant. </p> <p> <em>Proof:</em> If <img src='http://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7BN+%5Cll+q_1%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0' alt='{N &#92;ll q_1}' title='{N &#92;ll q_1}' class='latex' /> then the claim follows from the trivial bound <a href="#chin">(1)</a>, while for <img src='http://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7BN+%5Cgg+q_2%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0' alt='{N &#92;gg q_2}' title='{N &#92;gg q_2}' class='latex' /> the claim follows from <a href="#polya">(2)</a>. Hence we may assume that </p> <p align="center"><img src='http://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%5Cdisplaystyle++q_1+%3C+N+%3C+q_2.&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0' alt='&#92;displaystyle q_1 &lt; N &lt; q_2.' title='&#92;displaystyle q_1 &lt; N &lt; q_2.' class='latex' /></p> <p> We use the method of Weyl differencing, the key point being to difference in multiples of <img src='http://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7Bq_1%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0' alt='{q_1}' title='{q_1}' class='latex' />. </p> <p> Let <img src='http://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7BK+%3A%3D+%5Clfloor+N%2Fq_1+%5Crfloor%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0' alt='{K := &#92;lfloor N/q_1 &#92;rfloor}' title='{K := &#92;lfloor N/q_1 &#92;rfloor}' class='latex' />, thus <img src='http://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7BK+%5Cgeq+1%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0' alt='{K &#92;geq 1}' title='{K &#92;geq 1}' class='latex' />. For any <img src='http://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7B1+%5Cleq+k+%5Cleq+K%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0' alt='{1 &#92;leq k &#92;leq K}' title='{1 &#92;leq k &#92;leq K}' class='latex' />, we have </p> <p align="center"><img src='http://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%5Cdisplaystyle++%5Csum_%7BM%2B1+%5Cleq+n+%5Cleq+M%2BN%7D+%5Cchi%28n%29+%3D+%5Csum_n+1_%7B%5BM%2B1%2CM%2BN%5D%7D%28n%2Bkq_1%29+%5Cchi%28n%2Bkq_1%29&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0' alt='&#92;displaystyle &#92;sum_{M+1 &#92;leq n &#92;leq M+N} &#92;chi(n) = &#92;sum_n 1_{[M+1,M+N]}(n+kq_1) &#92;chi(n+kq_1)' title='&#92;displaystyle &#92;sum_{M+1 &#92;leq n &#92;leq M+N} &#92;chi(n) = &#92;sum_n 1_{[M+1,M+N]}(n+kq_1) &#92;chi(n+kq_1)' class='latex' /></p> <p> and thus on averaging <a name="chim"> <p align="center"><img src='http://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%5Cdisplaystyle++%5Csum_%7BM%2B1+%5Cleq+n+%5Cleq+M%2BN%7D+%5Cchi%28n%29+%3D+%5Cfrac%7B1%7D%7BK%7D+%5Csum_n+%5Csum_%7Bk%3D1%7D%5EK+1_%7B%5BM%2B1%2CM%2BN%5D%7D%28n%2Bkq_1%29+%5Cchi%28n%2Bkq_1%29.+%5C+%5C+%5C+%5C+%5C+%284%29&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0' alt='&#92;displaystyle &#92;sum_{M+1 &#92;leq n &#92;leq M+N} &#92;chi(n) = &#92;frac{1}{K} &#92;sum_n &#92;sum_{k=1}^K 1_{[M+1,M+N]}(n+kq_1) &#92;chi(n+kq_1). &#92; &#92; &#92; &#92; &#92; (4)' title='&#92;displaystyle &#92;sum_{M+1 &#92;leq n &#92;leq M+N} &#92;chi(n) = &#92;frac{1}{K} &#92;sum_n &#92;sum_{k=1}^K 1_{[M+1,M+N]}(n+kq_1) &#92;chi(n+kq_1). &#92; &#92; &#92; &#92; &#92; (4)' class='latex' /></p> <p></a> By the Chinese remainder theorem, we may factor <p align="center"><img src='http://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%5Cdisplaystyle++%5Cchi%28n%29+%3D+%5Cchi_1%28n%29+%5Cchi_2%28n%29&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0' alt='&#92;displaystyle &#92;chi(n) = &#92;chi_1(n) &#92;chi_2(n)' title='&#92;displaystyle &#92;chi(n) = &#92;chi_1(n) &#92;chi_2(n)' class='latex' /></p> <p> where <img src='http://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7B%5Cchi_1%2C%5Cchi_2%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0' alt='{&#92;chi_1,&#92;chi_2}' title='{&#92;chi_1,&#92;chi_2}' class='latex' /> are primitive characters of conductor <img src='http://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7Bq_1%2Cq_2%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0' alt='{q_1,q_2}' title='{q_1,q_2}' class='latex' /> respectively. As <img src='http://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7B%5Cchi_1%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0' alt='{&#92;chi_1}' title='{&#92;chi_1}' class='latex' /> is periodic of period <img src='http://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7Bq_1%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0' alt='{q_1}' title='{q_1}' class='latex' />, we thus have <p align="center"><img src='http://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%5Cdisplaystyle++%5Cchi%28n%2Bkq_1%29+%3D+%5Cchi_1%28n%29+%5Cchi_2%28n%2Bkq_2%29&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0' alt='&#92;displaystyle &#92;chi(n+kq_1) = &#92;chi_1(n) &#92;chi_2(n+kq_2)' title='&#92;displaystyle &#92;chi(n+kq_1) = &#92;chi_1(n) &#92;chi_2(n+kq_2)' class='latex' /></p> <p> and so we can take <img src='http://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7B%5Cchi_1%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0' alt='{&#92;chi_1}' title='{&#92;chi_1}' class='latex' /> out of the inner summation of the right-hand side of <a href="#chim">(4)</a> to obtain <p align="center"><img src='http://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%5Cdisplaystyle++%5Csum_%7BM%2B1+%5Cleq+n+%5Cleq+M%2BN%7D+%5Cchi%28n%29+%3D+%5Cfrac%7B1%7D%7BK%7D+%5Csum_n+%5Cchi_1%28n%29+%5Csum_%7Bk%3D1%7D%5EK+1_%7B%5BM%2B1%2CM%2BN%5D%7D%28n%2Bkq_1%29+%5Cchi_2%28n%2Bkq_1%29+&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0' alt='&#92;displaystyle &#92;sum_{M+1 &#92;leq n &#92;leq M+N} &#92;chi(n) = &#92;frac{1}{K} &#92;sum_n &#92;chi_1(n) &#92;sum_{k=1}^K 1_{[M+1,M+N]}(n+kq_1) &#92;chi_2(n+kq_1) ' title='&#92;displaystyle &#92;sum_{M+1 &#92;leq n &#92;leq M+N} &#92;chi(n) = &#92;frac{1}{K} &#92;sum_n &#92;chi_1(n) &#92;sum_{k=1}^K 1_{[M+1,M+N]}(n+kq_1) &#92;chi_2(n+kq_1) ' class='latex' /></p> <p> and hence by the triangle inequality <p align="center"><img src='http://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%5Cdisplaystyle++%7C%5Csum_%7BM%2B1+%5Cleq+n+%5Cleq+M%2BN%7D+%5Cchi%28n%29%7C+%5Cleq+%5Cfrac%7B1%7D%7BK%7D+%5Csum_n+%7C%5Csum_%7Bk%3D1%7D%5EK+1_%7B%5BM%2B1%2CM%2BN%5D%7D%28n%2Bkq_1%29+%5Cchi_2%28n%2Bkq_1%29%7C.+&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0' alt='&#92;displaystyle |&#92;sum_{M+1 &#92;leq n &#92;leq M+N} &#92;chi(n)| &#92;leq &#92;frac{1}{K} &#92;sum_n |&#92;sum_{k=1}^K 1_{[M+1,M+N]}(n+kq_1) &#92;chi_2(n+kq_1)|. ' title='&#92;displaystyle |&#92;sum_{M+1 &#92;leq n &#92;leq M+N} &#92;chi(n)| &#92;leq &#92;frac{1}{K} &#92;sum_n |&#92;sum_{k=1}^K 1_{[M+1,M+N]}(n+kq_1) &#92;chi_2(n+kq_1)|. ' class='latex' /></p> <p> Note how the characters on the right-hand side only have period <img src='http://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7Bq_2%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0' alt='{q_2}' title='{q_2}' class='latex' /> rather than <img src='http://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7Bq%3Dq_1+q_2%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0' alt='{q=q_1 q_2}' title='{q=q_1 q_2}' class='latex' />. This reduction in the period is ultimately the source of the saving over the P&oacute;lya-Vinogradov inequality.</p> <p> Note that the inner sum vanishes unless <img src='http://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7Bn+%5Cin+%5BM%2B1-Kq_1%2CM%2BN%5D%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0' alt='{n &#92;in [M+1-Kq_1,M+N]}' title='{n &#92;in [M+1-Kq_1,M+N]}' class='latex' />, which is an interval of length <img src='http://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7BO%28N%29%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0' alt='{O(N)}' title='{O(N)}' class='latex' /> by choice of <img src='http://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7BK%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0' alt='{K}' title='{K}' class='latex' />. Thus by Cauchy-Schwarz one has </p> <p align="center"><img src='http://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%5Cdisplaystyle++%7C+%5Csum_%7BM%2B1+%5Cleq+n+%5Cleq+M%2BN%7D+%5Cchi%28n%29+%7C+%5Cll+&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0' alt='&#92;displaystyle | &#92;sum_{M+1 &#92;leq n &#92;leq M+N} &#92;chi(n) | &#92;ll ' title='&#92;displaystyle | &#92;sum_{M+1 &#92;leq n &#92;leq M+N} &#92;chi(n) | &#92;ll ' class='latex' /></p> <p align="center"><img src='http://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%5Cdisplaystyle++%5Cfrac%7BN%5E%7B1%2F2%7D%7D%7BK%7D+%28%5Csum_n+%7C%5Csum_%7Bk%3D1%7D%5EK+1_%7B%5BM%2B1%2CM%2BN%5D%7D%28n%2Bkq_1%29+%5Cchi_2%28n%2Bkq_1%29%7C%5E2%29%5E%7B1%2F2%7D.&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0' alt='&#92;displaystyle &#92;frac{N^{1/2}}{K} (&#92;sum_n |&#92;sum_{k=1}^K 1_{[M+1,M+N]}(n+kq_1) &#92;chi_2(n+kq_1)|^2)^{1/2}.' title='&#92;displaystyle &#92;frac{N^{1/2}}{K} (&#92;sum_n |&#92;sum_{k=1}^K 1_{[M+1,M+N]}(n+kq_1) &#92;chi_2(n+kq_1)|^2)^{1/2}.' class='latex' /></p> <p> We expand the right-hand side as <p align="center"><img src='http://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%5Cdisplaystyle++%5Cfrac%7BN%5E%7B1%2F2%7D%7D%7BK%7D+%7C%5Csum_%7B1+%5Cleq+k%2Ck%27+%5Cleq+K%7D+%5Csum_n+&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0' alt='&#92;displaystyle &#92;frac{N^{1/2}}{K} |&#92;sum_{1 &#92;leq k,k&#039; &#92;leq K} &#92;sum_n ' title='&#92;displaystyle &#92;frac{N^{1/2}}{K} |&#92;sum_{1 &#92;leq k,k&#039; &#92;leq K} &#92;sum_n ' class='latex' /></p> <p align="center"><img src='http://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%5Cdisplaystyle++1_%7B%5BM%2B1%2CM%2BN%5D%7D%28n%2Bkq_1%29+1_%7B%5BM%2B1%2CM%2BN%5D%7D%28n%2Bk%27q_1%29+%5Cchi_2%28n%2Bkq_1%29+%5Coverline%7B%5Cchi_2%28n%2Bk%27q_1%29%7D%7C%5E%7B1%2F2%7D.&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0' alt='&#92;displaystyle 1_{[M+1,M+N]}(n+kq_1) 1_{[M+1,M+N]}(n+k&#039;q_1) &#92;chi_2(n+kq_1) &#92;overline{&#92;chi_2(n+k&#039;q_1)}|^{1/2}.' title='&#92;displaystyle 1_{[M+1,M+N]}(n+kq_1) 1_{[M+1,M+N]}(n+k&#039;q_1) &#92;chi_2(n+kq_1) &#92;overline{&#92;chi_2(n+k&#039;q_1)}|^{1/2}.' class='latex' /></p> <p> We first consider the diagonal contribution <img src='http://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7Bk%3Dk%27%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0' alt='{k=k&#039;}' title='{k=k&#039;}' class='latex' />. In this case we use the trivial bound <img src='http://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7BO%28N%29%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0' alt='{O(N)}' title='{O(N)}' class='latex' /> for the inner summation, and we soon see that the total contribution here is <img src='http://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7BO%28+K%5E%7B-1%2F2%7D+N+%29+%3D+O%28+N%5E%7B1%2F2%7Dq_1%5E%7B1%2F2%7D+%29%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0' alt='{O( K^{-1/2} N ) = O( N^{1/2}q_1^{1/2} )}' title='{O( K^{-1/2} N ) = O( N^{1/2}q_1^{1/2} )}' class='latex' />. </p> <p> Now we consider the off-diagonal case; by symmetry we can take <img src='http://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7Bk+%3C+k%27%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0' alt='{k &lt; k&#039;}' title='{k &lt; k&#039;}' class='latex' />. Then the indicator functions <img src='http://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7B1_%7B%5BM%2B1%2CM%2BN%5D%7D%28n%2Bkq_1%29+1_%7B%5BM%2B1%2CM%2BN%5D%7D%28n%2Bk%27q_1%29%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0' alt='{1_{[M+1,M+N]}(n+kq_1) 1_{[M+1,M+N]}(n+k&#039;q_1)}' title='{1_{[M+1,M+N]}(n+kq_1) 1_{[M+1,M+N]}(n+k&#039;q_1)}' class='latex' /> restrict <img src='http://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7Bn%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0' alt='{n}' title='{n}' class='latex' /> to the interval <img src='http://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7B%5BM%2B1-kq_1%2C+M%2BN-k%27q_1%5D%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0' alt='{[M+1-kq_1, M+N-k&#039;q_1]}' title='{[M+1-kq_1, M+N-k&#039;q_1]}' class='latex' />. On the other hand, as a consequence of the <a href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Weil_conjectures">Weil conjectures</a> for curves one can show that </p> <p align="center"><img src='http://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%5Cdisplaystyle++%7C%5Csum_%7Bn+%5Cin+%7B%5Cbf+Z%7D%2Fq_2%7B%5Cbf+Z%7D%7D+%5Cchi_2%28n%2Bkq_1%29+%5Coverline%7B%5Cchi_2%28n%2Bk%27q_1%29%7D+e_%7Bq_2%7D%28an%29%7C+%5Clessapprox+q_2%5E%7B1%2F2%7D+%28k-k%27%2Cq_2%29%5E%7B1%2F2%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0' alt='&#92;displaystyle |&#92;sum_{n &#92;in {&#92;bf Z}/q_2{&#92;bf Z}} &#92;chi_2(n+kq_1) &#92;overline{&#92;chi_2(n+k&#039;q_1)} e_{q_2}(an)| &#92;lessapprox q_2^{1/2} (k-k&#039;,q_2)^{1/2}' title='&#92;displaystyle |&#92;sum_{n &#92;in {&#92;bf Z}/q_2{&#92;bf Z}} &#92;chi_2(n+kq_1) &#92;overline{&#92;chi_2(n+k&#039;q_1)} e_{q_2}(an)| &#92;lessapprox q_2^{1/2} (k-k&#039;,q_2)^{1/2}' class='latex' /></p> <p> for any <img src='http://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7Ba+%5Cin+%7B%5Cbf+Z%7D%2Fq_2%7B%5Cbf+Z%7D%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0' alt='{a &#92;in {&#92;bf Z}/q_2{&#92;bf Z}}' title='{a &#92;in {&#92;bf Z}/q_2{&#92;bf Z}}' class='latex' />; indeed one can use the Chinese remainder theorem and the square-free nature of <img src='http://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7Bq_2%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0' alt='{q_2}' title='{q_2}' class='latex' /> to reduce to the case when <img src='http://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7Bq_2%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0' alt='{q_2}' title='{q_2}' class='latex' /> is prime, in which case one can apply (for instance) the <a href="http://www.ams.org/mathscinet-getitem?mr=27006">original paper of Weil</a> to establish this bound, noting also that <img src='http://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7Bq_1%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0' alt='{q_1}' title='{q_1}' class='latex' /> and <img src='http://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7Bq_2%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0' alt='{q_2}' title='{q_2}' class='latex' /> are coprime since <img src='http://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7Bq%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0' alt='{q}' title='{q}' class='latex' /> is squarefree. Applying the method of completion of sums (or the Parseval formula), this shows that <p align="center"><img src='http://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%5Cdisplaystyle++%7C%5Csum_n+1_%7B%5BM%2B1%2CM%2BN%5D%7D%28n%2Bkq_1%29+1_%7B%5BM%2B1%2CM%2BN%5D%7D%28n%2Bk%27q_1%29+%5Cchi_2%28n%2Bkq_1%29+%5Coverline%7B%5Cchi_2%28n%2Bk%27q_1%29%7D%7C+&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0' alt='&#92;displaystyle |&#92;sum_n 1_{[M+1,M+N]}(n+kq_1) 1_{[M+1,M+N]}(n+k&#039;q_1) &#92;chi_2(n+kq_1) &#92;overline{&#92;chi_2(n+k&#039;q_1)}| ' title='&#92;displaystyle |&#92;sum_n 1_{[M+1,M+N]}(n+kq_1) 1_{[M+1,M+N]}(n+k&#039;q_1) &#92;chi_2(n+kq_1) &#92;overline{&#92;chi_2(n+k&#039;q_1)}| ' class='latex' /></p> <p align="center"><img src='http://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%5Cdisplaystyle++%5Clessapprox+q_2%5E%7B1%2F2%7D+%28k-k%27%2Cq_2%29%5E%7B1%2F2%7D.&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0' alt='&#92;displaystyle &#92;lessapprox q_2^{1/2} (k-k&#039;,q_2)^{1/2}.' title='&#92;displaystyle &#92;lessapprox q_2^{1/2} (k-k&#039;,q_2)^{1/2}.' class='latex' /></p> <p> Summing in <img src='http://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7Bk%2Ck%27%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0' alt='{k,k&#039;}' title='{k,k&#039;}' class='latex' /> (using Lemma 5 from <a href="http://terrytao.wordpress.com/2013/06/14/estimation-of-the-type-iii-sums/">this previous post</a>) we see that the total contribution to the off-diagonal case is <p align="center"><img src='http://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%5Cdisplaystyle++%5Clessapprox+%5Cfrac%7BN%5E%7B1%2F2%7D%7D%7BK%7D+%28+K%5E2+q_2%5E%7B1%2F2%7D+%29%5E%7B1%2F2%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0' alt='&#92;displaystyle &#92;lessapprox &#92;frac{N^{1/2}}{K} ( K^2 q_2^{1/2} )^{1/2}' title='&#92;displaystyle &#92;lessapprox &#92;frac{N^{1/2}}{K} ( K^2 q_2^{1/2} )^{1/2}' class='latex' /></p> <p> which simplifies to <img src='http://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7B%5Clessapprox+N%5E%7B1%2F2%7D+q_2%5E%7B1%2F4%7D%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0' alt='{&#92;lessapprox N^{1/2} q_2^{1/4}}' title='{&#92;lessapprox N^{1/2} q_2^{1/4}}' class='latex' />. The claim follows. <img src='http://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%5CBox&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0' alt='&#92;Box' title='&#92;Box' class='latex' /></p> <p> A modification of the above argument (using more complicated versions of the Weil conjectures) allows one to replace the summand <img src='http://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7B%5Cchi%28n%29%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0' alt='{&#92;chi(n)}' title='{&#92;chi(n)}' class='latex' /> by more complicated summands such as <img src='http://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7B%5Cchi%28f%28n%29%29+e_q%28g%28n%29%29%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0' alt='{&#92;chi(f(n)) e_q(g(n))}' title='{&#92;chi(f(n)) e_q(g(n))}' class='latex' /> for some polynomials or rational functions <img src='http://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7Bf%2Cg%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0' alt='{f,g}' title='{f,g}' class='latex' /> of bounded degree and obeying a suitable non-degeneracy condition (after restricting of course to those <img src='http://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7Bn%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0' alt='{n}' title='{n}' class='latex' /> for which the arguments <img src='http://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7Bf%28n%29%2Cg%28n%29%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0' alt='{f(n),g(n)}' title='{f(n),g(n)}' class='latex' /> are well-defined). We will not detail this here, but instead turn to the question of estimating slightly longer exponential sums, such as </p> <p align="center"><img src='http://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%5Cdisplaystyle++%5Csum_%7B1+%5Cleq+n+%5Cleq+N%7D+e_%7Bd_1%7D%28+%5Cfrac%7Bc_1%7D%7Bn%7D+%29+e_%7Bd_2%7D%28+%5Cfrac%7Bc_2%7D%7Bn%2Bl%7D+%29&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0' alt='&#92;displaystyle &#92;sum_{1 &#92;leq n &#92;leq N} e_{d_1}( &#92;frac{c_1}{n} ) e_{d_2}( &#92;frac{c_2}{n+l} )' title='&#92;displaystyle &#92;sum_{1 &#92;leq n &#92;leq N} e_{d_1}( &#92;frac{c_1}{n} ) e_{d_2}( &#92;frac{c_2}{n+l} )' class='latex' /></p> <p> where <img src='http://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7BN%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0' alt='{N}' title='{N}' class='latex' /> should be thought of as a little bit larger than <img src='http://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7B%28d_1d_2%29%5E%7B1%2F2%7D%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0' alt='{(d_1d_2)^{1/2}}' title='{(d_1d_2)^{1/2}}' class='latex' />.</p> <p> <span id="more-6867"></span> </p> <p> It will be convenient to introduce a little bit of formal algebraic notation. For the narrow task of establishing a new estimate on an incomplete Kloosterman-type sum of the type used in Zhang&#8217;s paper, one does not really need all this formalism, but it may be useful to have this formalism around for future generalisations and strengthenings of this estimate (e.g. when trying to set up a Burgess-style argument). </p> <p> Define an <em>integral rational function</em> to be a formal rational function <img src='http://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7Bf%28t%29+%3D+%5Cfrac%7BP%28t%29%7D%7BQ%28t%29%7D%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0' alt='{f(t) = &#92;frac{P(t)}{Q(t)}}' title='{f(t) = &#92;frac{P(t)}{Q(t)}}' class='latex' /> in a formal indeterminate <img src='http://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7Bt%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0' alt='{t}' title='{t}' class='latex' /> where <img src='http://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7BP%2CQ+%5Cin+%7B%5Cbf+Z%7D%5Bt%5D%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0' alt='{P,Q &#92;in {&#92;bf Z}[t]}' title='{P,Q &#92;in {&#92;bf Z}[t]}' class='latex' /> are polynomials with integer coefficients, and <img src='http://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7BQ%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0' alt='{Q}' title='{Q}' class='latex' /> is monic; in particular any polynomial <img src='http://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7BP%28t%29+%5Cin+%7B%5Cbf+Z%7D%5Bt%5D%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0' alt='{P(t) &#92;in {&#92;bf Z}[t]}' title='{P(t) &#92;in {&#92;bf Z}[t]}' class='latex' /> can be identified with the integral rational function <img src='http://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7BP%28t%29+%5Cequiv+%5Cfrac%7BP%28t%29%7D%7B1%7D%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0' alt='{P(t) &#92;equiv &#92;frac{P(t)}{1}}' title='{P(t) &#92;equiv &#92;frac{P(t)}{1}}' class='latex' />. For minor technical reasons we do <em>not</em> equate integral rational functions under cancelling, thus for instance we consider <img src='http://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7B%5Cfrac%7BP%28t%29R%28t%29%7D%7BQ%28t%29R%28t%29%7D%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0' alt='{&#92;frac{P(t)R(t)}{Q(t)R(t)}}' title='{&#92;frac{P(t)R(t)}{Q(t)R(t)}}' class='latex' /> to be distinct from <img src='http://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7B%5Cfrac%7BP%28t%29%7D%7BQ%28t%29%7D%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0' alt='{&#92;frac{P(t)}{Q(t)}}' title='{&#92;frac{P(t)}{Q(t)}}' class='latex' />; we need to do this because the domain of definition of these two functions is a little different (the former is not defined when <img src='http://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7BR%28t%29%3D0%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0' alt='{R(t)=0}' title='{R(t)=0}' class='latex' />, but the latter can still be defined here). Because we refuse to cancel, we have to be a little careful how we define algebraic operations: specifically, we define </p> <p align="center"><img src='http://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%5Cdisplaystyle++%5Cfrac%7BP_1%28t%29%7D%7BQ_1%28t%29%7D+%2B+%5Cfrac%7BP_2%28t%29%7D%7BQ_2%28t%29%7D+%3A%3D+%5Cfrac%7BP_1%28t%29+Q_2%28t%29+%2B+P_2%28t%29+Q_1%28t%29%7D%7BQ_1%28t%29+Q_2%28t%29%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0' alt='&#92;displaystyle &#92;frac{P_1(t)}{Q_1(t)} + &#92;frac{P_2(t)}{Q_2(t)} := &#92;frac{P_1(t) Q_2(t) + P_2(t) Q_1(t)}{Q_1(t) Q_2(t)}' title='&#92;displaystyle &#92;frac{P_1(t)}{Q_1(t)} + &#92;frac{P_2(t)}{Q_2(t)} := &#92;frac{P_1(t) Q_2(t) + P_2(t) Q_1(t)}{Q_1(t) Q_2(t)}' class='latex' /></p> <p align="center"><img src='http://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%5Cdisplaystyle++%5Cfrac%7BP_1%28t%29%7D%7BQ_1%28t%29%7D+-+%5Cfrac%7BP_2%28t%29%7D%7BQ_2%28t%29%7D+%3A%3D+%5Cfrac%7BP_1%28t%29+Q_2%28t%29+-+P_2%28t%29+Q_1%28t%29%7D%7BQ_1%28t%29+Q_2%28t%29%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0' alt='&#92;displaystyle &#92;frac{P_1(t)}{Q_1(t)} - &#92;frac{P_2(t)}{Q_2(t)} := &#92;frac{P_1(t) Q_2(t) - P_2(t) Q_1(t)}{Q_1(t) Q_2(t)}' title='&#92;displaystyle &#92;frac{P_1(t)}{Q_1(t)} - &#92;frac{P_2(t)}{Q_2(t)} := &#92;frac{P_1(t) Q_2(t) - P_2(t) Q_1(t)}{Q_1(t) Q_2(t)}' class='latex' /></p> <p align="center"><img src='http://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%5Cdisplaystyle++%5Cfrac%7BP_1%28t%29%7D%7BQ_1%28t%29%7D+%5Ccdot+%5Cfrac%7BP_2%28t%29%7D%7BQ_2%28t%29%7D+%3A%3D+%5Cfrac%7BP_1%28t%29+P_2%28t%29%7D%7BQ_1%28t%29+Q_2%28t%29%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0' alt='&#92;displaystyle &#92;frac{P_1(t)}{Q_1(t)} &#92;cdot &#92;frac{P_2(t)}{Q_2(t)} := &#92;frac{P_1(t) P_2(t)}{Q_1(t) Q_2(t)}' title='&#92;displaystyle &#92;frac{P_1(t)}{Q_1(t)} &#92;cdot &#92;frac{P_2(t)}{Q_2(t)} := &#92;frac{P_1(t) P_2(t)}{Q_1(t) Q_2(t)}' class='latex' /></p> <p align="center"><img src='http://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%5Cdisplaystyle++%28%5Cfrac%7BP%28t%29%7D%7BQ%28t%29%7D%29%27+%3A%3D+%5Cfrac%7BP%27%28t%29+Q%28t%29+-+P%28t%29+Q%27%28t%29%7D%7BQ%28t%29%5E2%7D.&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0' alt='&#92;displaystyle (&#92;frac{P(t)}{Q(t)})&#039; := &#92;frac{P&#039;(t) Q(t) - P(t) Q&#039;(t)}{Q(t)^2}.' title='&#92;displaystyle (&#92;frac{P(t)}{Q(t)})&#039; := &#92;frac{P&#039;(t) Q(t) - P(t) Q&#039;(t)}{Q(t)^2}.' class='latex' /></p> <p> Note that the denominator always remains monic with respect to these operations. This is not quite a ring with a derivation (the subtraction operation does not quite cancel the addition operation due to the inability to cancel) but this will not bother us in practice. (On the other hand, addition and multiplication remain associative, and the latter continues to distribute over the former, and differentiation obeys the usual sum and product rules.)</p> <p> In applications to bounded gaps between primes, we will deal with integral rational functions of the explicit form </p> <p align="center"><img src='http://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%5Cdisplaystyle++f%28t%29+%3A%3D+%5Cfrac%7Ba%7D%7Bt%7D+%2B+%5Cfrac%7Bb%7D%7Bt%2Bl%7D+%2B+ct&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0' alt='&#92;displaystyle f(t) := &#92;frac{a}{t} + &#92;frac{b}{t+l} + ct' title='&#92;displaystyle f(t) := &#92;frac{a}{t} + &#92;frac{b}{t+l} + ct' class='latex' /></p> <p> for various integers <img src='http://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7Ba%2Cb%2Cc%2Cl%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0' alt='{a,b,c,l}' title='{a,b,c,l}' class='latex' />, but much of the theory below extends without much difficulty to more general integral rational functions, so we shall state it in that level of generality.</p> <p> Note that if <img src='http://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7Bf%28t%29+%3D+%5Cfrac%7BP%28t%29%7D%7BQ%28t%29%7D%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0' alt='{f(t) = &#92;frac{P(t)}{Q(t)}}' title='{f(t) = &#92;frac{P(t)}{Q(t)}}' class='latex' /> is an integral rational function, we can localise it modulo <img src='http://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7Bq%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0' alt='{q}' title='{q}' class='latex' /> for any modulus <img src='http://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7Bq%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0' alt='{q}' title='{q}' class='latex' /> to obtain a rational function <img src='http://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7Bf%28t%29%5C+%28q%29+%3A%3D+%5Cfrac%7BP%28t%29%5C+%28q%29%7D%7BQ%28t%29%5C+%28q%29%7D%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0' alt='{f(t)&#92; (q) := &#92;frac{P(t)&#92; (q)}{Q(t)&#92; (q)}}' title='{f(t)&#92; (q) := &#92;frac{P(t)&#92; (q)}{Q(t)&#92; (q)}}' class='latex' /> that is the ratio of two polynomials <img src='http://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7BP%5C+%28q%29%2C+Q%5C+%28q%29%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0' alt='{P&#92; (q), Q&#92; (q)}' title='{P&#92; (q), Q&#92; (q)}' class='latex' /> in <img src='http://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7B%28%7B%5Cbf+Z%7D%2Fq%7B%5Cbf+Z%7D%29%5Bt%5D%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0' alt='{({&#92;bf Z}/q{&#92;bf Z})[t]}' title='{({&#92;bf Z}/q{&#92;bf Z})[t]}' class='latex' />, with the denominator monic and hence non-vanishing. We can define the algebraic operations of addition, subtraction, multiplication, and differentiation on integral rational functions modulo <img src='http://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7Bq%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0' alt='{q}' title='{q}' class='latex' /> by the same formulae as above, and we observe that these operations are completely compatible with their counterparts over <img src='http://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7B%7B%5Cbf+Z%7D%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0' alt='{{&#92;bf Z}}' title='{{&#92;bf Z}}' class='latex' /> (even without the ability to cancel), thus for instance <img src='http://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7B%28f%2Bg%29%5C+%28q%29+%3D+%28f%5C+%28q%29%29+%2B+%28g%5C+%28q%29%29%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0' alt='{(f+g)&#92; (q) = (f&#92; (q)) + (g&#92; (q))}' title='{(f+g)&#92; (q) = (f&#92; (q)) + (g&#92; (q))}' class='latex' />. We say that <img src='http://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7Bf%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0' alt='{f}' title='{f}' class='latex' /> is <em>divisible</em> by <img src='http://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7Bq%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0' alt='{q}' title='{q}' class='latex' />, and write <img src='http://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7Bq%7Cf%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0' alt='{q|f}' title='{q|f}' class='latex' />, if the numerator <img src='http://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7BP%28t%29%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0' alt='{P(t)}' title='{P(t)}' class='latex' /> of <img src='http://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7Bf%28t%29%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0' alt='{f(t)}' title='{f(t)}' class='latex' /> has all coefficients divisible by <img src='http://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7Bq%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0' alt='{q}' title='{q}' class='latex' />. </p> <p> If <img src='http://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7Bf%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0' alt='{f}' title='{f}' class='latex' /> is an integral rational function and <img src='http://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7Bn+%5Cin+%7B%5Cbf+Z%7D%2Fq%7B%5Cbf+Z%7D%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0' alt='{n &#92;in {&#92;bf Z}/q{&#92;bf Z}}' title='{n &#92;in {&#92;bf Z}/q{&#92;bf Z}}' class='latex' />, then <img src='http://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7Bf%28n%29%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0' alt='{f(n)}' title='{f(n)}' class='latex' /> is well defined as an element of <img src='http://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7B%7B%5Cbf+Z%7D%2Fq%7B%5Cbf+Z%7D%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0' alt='{{&#92;bf Z}/q{&#92;bf Z}}' title='{{&#92;bf Z}/q{&#92;bf Z}}' class='latex' /> except when <img src='http://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7BQ%28n%29%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0' alt='{Q(n)}' title='{Q(n)}' class='latex' /> is a zero divisor in <img src='http://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7B%7B%5Cbf+Z%7D%2Fq%7B%5Cbf+Z%7D%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0' alt='{{&#92;bf Z}/q{&#92;bf Z}}' title='{{&#92;bf Z}/q{&#92;bf Z}}' class='latex' />. We adopt the convention that <img src='http://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7Be_q%28f%28n%29%29+%3D+0%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0' alt='{e_q(f(n)) = 0}' title='{e_q(f(n)) = 0}' class='latex' /> when <img src='http://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7BQ%28n%29%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0' alt='{Q(n)}' title='{Q(n)}' class='latex' /> is a zero divisor in <img src='http://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7B%7B%5Cbf+Z%7D%2Fq%7B%5Cbf+Z%7D%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0' alt='{{&#92;bf Z}/q{&#92;bf Z}}' title='{{&#92;bf Z}/q{&#92;bf Z}}' class='latex' />, thus <img src='http://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7Be_q%28f%28n%29%29%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0' alt='{e_q(f(n))}' title='{e_q(f(n))}' class='latex' /> is really shorthand for <img src='http://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7B1_%7B%28Q%28n%29%2Cq%29%3D1%7D+e_q%28f%28n%29%29%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0' alt='{1_{(Q(n),q)=1} e_q(f(n))}' title='{1_{(Q(n),q)=1} e_q(f(n))}' class='latex' />; by abuse of notation we view <img src='http://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7Bn+%5Cmapsto+e_q%28f%28n%29%29%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0' alt='{n &#92;mapsto e_q(f(n))}' title='{n &#92;mapsto e_q(f(n))}' class='latex' /> both as a function on <img src='http://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7B%7B%5Cbf+Z%7D%2Fq%7B%5Cbf+Z%7D%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0' alt='{{&#92;bf Z}/q{&#92;bf Z}}' title='{{&#92;bf Z}/q{&#92;bf Z}}' class='latex' /> and as a <img src='http://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7Bq%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0' alt='{q}' title='{q}' class='latex' />-periodic function on <img src='http://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7B%7B%5Cbf+Z%7D%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0' alt='{{&#92;bf Z}}' title='{{&#92;bf Z}}' class='latex' />. Thus for instance </p> <p align="center"><img src='http://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%5Cdisplaystyle++e_q%28+%5Cfrac%7B0%7D%7Bn%7D+%29+%3D+1_%7B%28n%2Cq%29%3D1%7D.&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0' alt='&#92;displaystyle e_q( &#92;frac{0}{n} ) = 1_{(n,q)=1}.' title='&#92;displaystyle e_q( &#92;frac{0}{n} ) = 1_{(n,q)=1}.' class='latex' /></p> <p> Note that if <img src='http://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7Bq%7Cf%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0' alt='{q|f}' title='{q|f}' class='latex' />, then <img src='http://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7Bf%28n%29%3D0%5C+%28q%29%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0' alt='{f(n)=0&#92; (q)}' title='{f(n)=0&#92; (q)}' class='latex' /> for all <img src='http://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7Bn+%5Cin+%7B%5Cbf+Z%7D%2Fq%7B%5Cbf+Z%7D%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0' alt='{n &#92;in {&#92;bf Z}/q{&#92;bf Z}}' title='{n &#92;in {&#92;bf Z}/q{&#92;bf Z}}' class='latex' /> for which <img src='http://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7Bf%28n%29%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0' alt='{f(n)}' title='{f(n)}' class='latex' /> is well defined. We define <img src='http://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7B%28f%2Cq%29%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0' alt='{(f,q)}' title='{(f,q)}' class='latex' /> to be the largest factor <img src='http://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7Bq%27%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0' alt='{q&#039;}' title='{q&#039;}' class='latex' /> of <img src='http://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7Bq%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0' alt='{q}' title='{q}' class='latex' /> for which <img src='http://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7Bq%27%7Cf%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0' alt='{q&#039;|f}' title='{q&#039;|f}' class='latex' />; in particular, if <img src='http://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7Bq%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0' alt='{q}' title='{q}' class='latex' /> is square-free, we have <p align="center"><img src='http://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%5Cdisplaystyle++%28f%2Cq%29+%3D+%5Cprod_%7Bp%7Cq%3A+p%7Cf%7D+p.&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0' alt='&#92;displaystyle (f,q) = &#92;prod_{p|q: p|f} p.' title='&#92;displaystyle (f,q) = &#92;prod_{p|q: p|f} p.' class='latex' /></p> <p> We recall the following Chinese remainder theorem: </p> <blockquote><p><b>Lemma 2 (Chinese remainder theorem)</b> <a name="crt"></a> Let <img src='http://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7Bq+%3D+q_1+q_2%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0' alt='{q = q_1 q_2}' title='{q = q_1 q_2}' class='latex' /> with <img src='http://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7Bq_1%2Cq_2%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0' alt='{q_1,q_2}' title='{q_1,q_2}' class='latex' /> coprime positive integers. If <img src='http://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7Bf%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0' alt='{f}' title='{f}' class='latex' /> is a rational function, then <p align="center"><img src='http://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%5Cdisplaystyle++e_q%28+f%28n%29+%29+%3D+e_%7Bq_1%7D%28+%5Cbar%7Bq_2%7D+f%28n%29+%29+e_%7Bq_2%7D+%28+%5Cbar%7Bq_1%7D+f%28n%29+%29&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0' alt='&#92;displaystyle e_q( f(n) ) = e_{q_1}( &#92;bar{q_2} f(n) ) e_{q_2} ( &#92;bar{q_1} f(n) )' title='&#92;displaystyle e_q( f(n) ) = e_{q_1}( &#92;bar{q_2} f(n) ) e_{q_2} ( &#92;bar{q_1} f(n) )' class='latex' /></p> <p> for all integers <img src='http://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7Bn%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0' alt='{n}' title='{n}' class='latex' />, where <img src='http://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7B%5Cbar%7Bq_2%7D%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0' alt='{&#92;bar{q_2}}' title='{&#92;bar{q_2}}' class='latex' /> is the inverse of <img src='http://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7Bq_2%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0' alt='{q_2}' title='{q_2}' class='latex' /> in <img src='http://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7B%7B%5Cbf+Z%7D%2Fq_1%7B%5Cbf+Z%7D%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0' alt='{{&#92;bf Z}/q_1{&#92;bf Z}}' title='{{&#92;bf Z}/q_1{&#92;bf Z}}' class='latex' /> and similarly for <img src='http://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7B%5Cbar%7Bq_1%7D%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0' alt='{&#92;bar{q_1}}' title='{&#92;bar{q_1}}' class='latex' />. </p></blockquote> </p> <p> When there is no chance of confusion we will write <img src='http://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7Be_%7Bq_1%7D+%28+%5Cfrac%7B1%7D%7Bq_2%7D+f%28n%29+%29%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0' alt='{e_{q_1} ( &#92;frac{1}{q_2} f(n) )}' title='{e_{q_1} ( &#92;frac{1}{q_2} f(n) )}' class='latex' /> for <img src='http://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7Be_%7Bq_1%7D%28+%5Cbar%7Bq_2%7D+f%28n%29+%29%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0' alt='{e_{q_1}( &#92;bar{q_2} f(n) )}' title='{e_{q_1}( &#92;bar{q_2} f(n) )}' class='latex' /> (though note that <img src='http://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7B%5Cfrac%7B1%7D%7Bq_2%7D%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0' alt='{&#92;frac{1}{q_2}}' title='{&#92;frac{1}{q_2}}' class='latex' /> does not qualify as an integral rational function since the constant <img src='http://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7Bq_2%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0' alt='{q_2}' title='{q_2}' class='latex' /> is not monic). </p> <p> <em>Proof:</em> See Lemma 7 of <a href="http://terrytao.wordpress.com/2013/06/12/estimation-of-the-type-i-and-type-ii-sums/">this previous post</a>. <img src='http://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%5CBox&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0' alt='&#92;Box' title='&#92;Box' class='latex' /></p> <p> We need the following algebraic version of the fundamental theorem of calculus: </p> <blockquote><p><b>Lemma 3 (Fundamental theorem of calculus)</b> <a name="fund"></a> Let <img src='http://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7Bf%28t%29+%3D+%5Cfrac%7BP%28t%29%7D%7BQ%28t%29%7D%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0' alt='{f(t) = &#92;frac{P(t)}{Q(t)}}' title='{f(t) = &#92;frac{P(t)}{Q(t)}}' class='latex' /> be a rational function, and let <img src='http://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7Bq%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0' alt='{q}' title='{q}' class='latex' /> be a positive integer. If <img src='http://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7Bq%7Cf%27%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0' alt='{q|f&#039;}' title='{q|f&#039;}' class='latex' /> and all prime factors of <img src='http://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7Bq%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0' alt='{q}' title='{q}' class='latex' /> are sufficiently large depending on the degrees of <img src='http://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7BP%2CQ%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0' alt='{P,Q}' title='{P,Q}' class='latex' />, then there exists <img src='http://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7Bc+%5Cin+%7B%5Cbf+Z%7D%2Fq%7B%5Cbf+Z%7D%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0' alt='{c &#92;in {&#92;bf Z}/q{&#92;bf Z}}' title='{c &#92;in {&#92;bf Z}/q{&#92;bf Z}}' class='latex' /> such that <img src='http://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7Bq%7Cf-c%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0' alt='{q|f-c}' title='{q|f-c}' class='latex' />. </p></blockquote> </p> <p> <em>Proof:</em> By definition, the constraint <img src='http://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7Bq%7Cf%27%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0' alt='{q|f&#039;}' title='{q|f&#039;}' class='latex' /> may be rewritten as </p> <p align="center"><img src='http://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%5Cdisplaystyle++P%27%28t%29+Q%28t%29+-+P%28t%29+Q%27%28t%29+%3D+0%5C+%28q%29.&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0' alt='&#92;displaystyle P&#039;(t) Q(t) - P(t) Q&#039;(t) = 0&#92; (q).' title='&#92;displaystyle P&#039;(t) Q(t) - P(t) Q&#039;(t) = 0&#92; (q).' class='latex' /></p> <p> By abuse of notation, we view <img src='http://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7BP%2CQ%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0' alt='{P,Q}' title='{P,Q}' class='latex' /> as polynomials over <img src='http://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7B%7B%5Cbf+Z%7D%2Fq%7B%5Cbf+Z%7D%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0' alt='{{&#92;bf Z}/q{&#92;bf Z}}' title='{{&#92;bf Z}/q{&#92;bf Z}}' class='latex' /> (i.e. all occurrences of <img src='http://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7BP%2CQ%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0' alt='{P,Q}' title='{P,Q}' class='latex' /> in what follows should actually be <img src='http://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7BP%5C+%28q%29%2C+Q%5C+%28q%29%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0' alt='{P&#92; (q), Q&#92; (q)}' title='{P&#92; (q), Q&#92; (q)}' class='latex' /> if we did not abuse notation). If <img src='http://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7BP%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0' alt='{P}' title='{P}' class='latex' /> has degree larger than <img src='http://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7BQ%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0' alt='{Q}' title='{Q}' class='latex' />, then by inspecting the <img src='http://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7Bt%5E%7B%5Chbox%7Bdeg%7D%28P%29%2B%5Chbox%7Bdeg%7D%28Q%29-1%7D%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0' alt='{t^{&#92;hbox{deg}(P)+&#92;hbox{deg}(Q)-1}}' title='{t^{&#92;hbox{deg}(P)+&#92;hbox{deg}(Q)-1}}' class='latex' /> coefficient of this equation we obtain a contradiction if all prime factors of <img src='http://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7Bq%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0' alt='{q}' title='{q}' class='latex' /> are large enough. Thus we may assume that <img src='http://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7B%5Chbox%7Bdeg%7D%28P%29+%5Cleq+%5Chbox%7Bdeg%7D%28Q%29%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0' alt='{&#92;hbox{deg}(P) &#92;leq &#92;hbox{deg}(Q)}' title='{&#92;hbox{deg}(P) &#92;leq &#92;hbox{deg}(Q)}' class='latex' />; since <img src='http://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7BQ%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0' alt='{Q}' title='{Q}' class='latex' /> is monic, this implies that <img src='http://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7BP+%3D+cQ+%2B+R%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0' alt='{P = cQ + R}' title='{P = cQ + R}' class='latex' /> for some <img src='http://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7BR+%5Cin+%7B%5Cbf+Z%7D%2Fq%7B%5Cbf+Z%7D%5Bt%5D%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0' alt='{R &#92;in {&#92;bf Z}/q{&#92;bf Z}[t]}' title='{R &#92;in {&#92;bf Z}/q{&#92;bf Z}[t]}' class='latex' /> with <img src='http://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7B%5Chbox%7Bdeg%7D%28R%29+%3C+%5Chbox%7Bdeg%7D%28Q%29%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0' alt='{&#92;hbox{deg}(R) &lt; &#92;hbox{deg}(Q)}' title='{&#92;hbox{deg}(R) &lt; &#92;hbox{deg}(Q)}' class='latex' />. We can then rewrite the previous constraint as <p align="center"><img src='http://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%5Cdisplaystyle++R%27%28t%29+Q%28t%29+-+R%28t%29+Q%27%28t%29+%3D+0%5C+%28q%29.&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0' alt='&#92;displaystyle R&#039;(t) Q(t) - R(t) Q&#039;(t) = 0&#92; (q).' title='&#92;displaystyle R&#039;(t) Q(t) - R(t) Q&#039;(t) = 0&#92; (q).' class='latex' /></p> <p> If <img src='http://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7BR%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0' alt='{R}' title='{R}' class='latex' /> is non-zero, then inspecting the <img src='http://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7Bt%5E%7B%5Chbox%7Bdeg%7D%28R%29%2B%5Chbox%7Bdeg%7D%28Q%29-1%7D%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0' alt='{t^{&#92;hbox{deg}(R)+&#92;hbox{deg}(Q)-1}}' title='{t^{&#92;hbox{deg}(R)+&#92;hbox{deg}(Q)-1}}' class='latex' /> coefficient of this equation leads to a contradiction if all prime factors of <img src='http://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7Bq%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0' alt='{q}' title='{q}' class='latex' /> are large enough. Thus <img src='http://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7BR%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0' alt='{R}' title='{R}' class='latex' /> is zero, and so <img src='http://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7Bq%7Cf-c%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0' alt='{q|f-c}' title='{q|f-c}' class='latex' /> as required. <img src='http://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%5CBox&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0' alt='&#92;Box' title='&#92;Box' class='latex' /></p> <p> Now we give an estimate for complete exponential sums, which combines both Ramanujan sum bounds with Weil conjecture bounds. </p> <blockquote><p><b>Proposition 4 (Ramanujan-Weil bounds)</b> <a name="weil"></a> Let <img src='http://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7Bq%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0' alt='{q}' title='{q}' class='latex' /> be a positive square-free integer of polynomial size, and let <img src='http://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7Bf%28t%29+%3D+%5Cfrac%7BP%28t%29%7D%7BQ%28t%29%7D%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0' alt='{f(t) = &#92;frac{P(t)}{Q(t)}}' title='{f(t) = &#92;frac{P(t)}{Q(t)}}' class='latex' /> be an integral rational function with <img src='http://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7BP%2CQ%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0' alt='{P,Q}' title='{P,Q}' class='latex' /> of bounded degree. Then we have <p align="center"><img src='http://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%5Cdisplaystyle++%7C%5Csum_%7Bn+%5Cin+%7B%5Cbf+Z%7D%2Fq%7B%5Cbf+Z%7D%7D+e_q%28+f%28n%29+%29%7C+%5Clessapprox+q%5E%7B1%2F2%7D+%5Cfrac%7B%28f%27%2Cq%29%7D%7B%28f%27%27%2Cq%29%5E%7B1%2F2%7D%7D.&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0' alt='&#92;displaystyle |&#92;sum_{n &#92;in {&#92;bf Z}/q{&#92;bf Z}} e_q( f(n) )| &#92;lessapprox q^{1/2} &#92;frac{(f&#039;,q)}{(f&#039;&#039;,q)^{1/2}}.' title='&#92;displaystyle |&#92;sum_{n &#92;in {&#92;bf Z}/q{&#92;bf Z}} e_q( f(n) )| &#92;lessapprox q^{1/2} &#92;frac{(f&#039;,q)}{(f&#039;&#039;,q)^{1/2}}.' class='latex' /></p> </blockquote> </p> <p> For instance, if we set <img src='http://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7Bf%28t%29+%3A%3D+%5Cfrac%7B0%7D%7Bt%7D+%2B+bt%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0' alt='{f(t) := &#92;frac{0}{t} + bt}' title='{f(t) := &#92;frac{0}{t} + bt}' class='latex' /> for some integer <img src='http://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7Bb%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0' alt='{b}' title='{b}' class='latex' />, we obtain the familiar Ramanujan sum bound <a name="ram1"> <p align="center"><img src='http://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%5Cdisplaystyle++%7C%5Csum_%7Bn+%5Cin+%7B%5Cbf+Z%7D%2Fq%7B%5Cbf+Z%7D%7D+e_q%28+b+n%29+1_%7B%28n%2Cq%29%3D1%7D%7C+%5Clessapprox+%28b%2Cq%29.+%5C+%5C+%5C+%5C+%5C+%285%29&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0' alt='&#92;displaystyle |&#92;sum_{n &#92;in {&#92;bf Z}/q{&#92;bf Z}} e_q( b n) 1_{(n,q)=1}| &#92;lessapprox (b,q). &#92; &#92; &#92; &#92; &#92; (5)' title='&#92;displaystyle |&#92;sum_{n &#92;in {&#92;bf Z}/q{&#92;bf Z}} e_q( b n) 1_{(n,q)=1}| &#92;lessapprox (b,q). &#92; &#92; &#92; &#92; &#92; (5)' class='latex' /></p> <p></a> More generally, if we set <img src='http://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7Bf%28t%29+%3A%3D+%5Cfrac%7Ba%7D%7Bt%7D+%2B+bt%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0' alt='{f(t) := &#92;frac{a}{t} + bt}' title='{f(t) := &#92;frac{a}{t} + bt}' class='latex' /> for some integers <img src='http://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7Ba%2Cb%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0' alt='{a,b}' title='{a,b}' class='latex' />, we obtain Weil&#8217;s Kloosterman sum bound </p> <p align="center"><img src='http://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%5Cdisplaystyle++%7C%5Csum_%7Bn+%5Cin+%7B%5Cbf+Z%7D%2Fq%7B%5Cbf+Z%7D%7D+e_q%28+%5Cfrac%7Ba%7D%7Bn%7D+%2B+bn+%29+1_%7B%28n%2Cq%29%3D1%7D%7C+%5Clessapprox+q%5E%7B1%2F2%7D+%5Cfrac%7B%28a%2Cb%2Cq%29%7D%7B%28a%2Cq%29%5E%7B1%2F2%7D%7D%2C&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0' alt='&#92;displaystyle |&#92;sum_{n &#92;in {&#92;bf Z}/q{&#92;bf Z}} e_q( &#92;frac{a}{n} + bn ) 1_{(n,q)=1}| &#92;lessapprox q^{1/2} &#92;frac{(a,b,q)}{(a,q)^{1/2}},' title='&#92;displaystyle |&#92;sum_{n &#92;in {&#92;bf Z}/q{&#92;bf Z}} e_q( &#92;frac{a}{n} + bn ) 1_{(n,q)=1}| &#92;lessapprox q^{1/2} &#92;frac{(a,b,q)}{(a,q)^{1/2}},' class='latex' /></p> <p> and so forth. </p> <p> The bound in Proposition <a href="#weil">4</a> is quite sharp, with one exception of relevance to the polymath8 project, namely the estimation of the degenerate Kloosterman-type sum </p> <p align="center"><img src='http://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%5Cdisplaystyle++%5Csum_%7Bn+%5Cin+%7B%5Cbf+Z%7D%2Fq%7B%5Cbf+Z%7D%7D+e_q%28+%5Cfrac%7Ba%7D%7Bn%2Bl%7D+%29&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0' alt='&#92;displaystyle &#92;sum_{n &#92;in {&#92;bf Z}/q{&#92;bf Z}} e_q( &#92;frac{a}{n+l} )' title='&#92;displaystyle &#92;sum_{n &#92;in {&#92;bf Z}/q{&#92;bf Z}} e_q( &#92;frac{a}{n+l} )' class='latex' /></p> <p> with <img src='http://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7Ba%2C+l%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0' alt='{a, l}' title='{a, l}' class='latex' /> integers. Proposition <a href="#weil">4</a> gives a bound of <img src='http://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7B%5Cll+q%5E%7B1%2F2%7D+%28a%2Cq%29%5E%7B1%2F2%7D%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0' alt='{&#92;ll q^{1/2} (a,q)^{1/2}}' title='{&#92;ll q^{1/2} (a,q)^{1/2}}' class='latex' /> in this case, but one can do better by performing the change of variables <img src='http://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7Bm+%3D+%5Cfrac%7B1%7D%7Bn%2Bl%7D%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0' alt='{m = &#92;frac{1}{n+l}}' title='{m = &#92;frac{1}{n+l}}' class='latex' /> that transforms this sum into a Ramanujan sum, yielding the superior bound <a name="rama"> <p align="center"><img src='http://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%5Cdisplaystyle++%7C%5Csum_%7Bn+%5Cin+%7B%5Cbf+Z%7D%2Fq%7B%5Cbf+Z%7D%7D+e_q%28+%5Cfrac%7Ba%7D%7Bn%2Bl%7D+%29%7C+%5Cll+%28a%2Cq%29.+%5C+%5C+%5C+%5C+%5C+%286%29&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0' alt='&#92;displaystyle |&#92;sum_{n &#92;in {&#92;bf Z}/q{&#92;bf Z}} e_q( &#92;frac{a}{n+l} )| &#92;ll (a,q). &#92; &#92; &#92; &#92; &#92; (6)' title='&#92;displaystyle |&#92;sum_{n &#92;in {&#92;bf Z}/q{&#92;bf Z}} e_q( &#92;frac{a}{n+l} )| &#92;ll (a,q). &#92; &#92; &#92; &#92; &#92; (6)' class='latex' /></p> <p></a> One could try to modify the argument below to incorporate this improvement, but it leads to a significantly more complicated right-hand side for the estimate, so we will not do so here.</p> <p> <em>Proof:</em> By the Chinese remainder theorem and the divisor bound, it suffices to verify this when <img src='http://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7Bq%3Dp%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0' alt='{q=p}' title='{q=p}' class='latex' /> is a single prime and with <img src='http://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7B%5Clessapprox%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0' alt='{&#92;lessapprox}' title='{&#92;lessapprox}' class='latex' /> replaced by <img src='http://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7B%5Cll%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0' alt='{&#92;ll}' title='{&#92;ll}' class='latex' />, thus we wish to show that </p> <p align="center"><img src='http://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%5Cdisplaystyle++%7C%5Csum_%7Bn+%5Cin+%7B%5Cbf+Z%7D%2Fp%7B%5Cbf+Z%7D%7D+e_p%28f%28n%29%29%7C+%5Cll+p+&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0' alt='&#92;displaystyle |&#92;sum_{n &#92;in {&#92;bf Z}/p{&#92;bf Z}} e_p(f(n))| &#92;ll p ' title='&#92;displaystyle |&#92;sum_{n &#92;in {&#92;bf Z}/p{&#92;bf Z}} e_p(f(n))| &#92;ll p ' class='latex' /></p> <p> when <img src='http://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7Bp%7Cf%27%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0' alt='{p|f&#039;}' title='{p|f&#039;}' class='latex' /> (which implies <img src='http://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7Bp%7Cf%27%27%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0' alt='{p|f&#039;&#039;}' title='{p|f&#039;&#039;}' class='latex' />), <a name="ram"> <p align="center"><img src='http://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%5Cdisplaystyle++%7C%5Csum_%7Bn+%5Cin+%7B%5Cbf+Z%7D%2Fp%7B%5Cbf+Z%7D%7D+e_p%28f%28n%29%29%7C+%5Cll+1+%5C+%5C+%5C+%5C+%5C+%287%29&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0' alt='&#92;displaystyle |&#92;sum_{n &#92;in {&#92;bf Z}/p{&#92;bf Z}} e_p(f(n))| &#92;ll 1 &#92; &#92; &#92; &#92; &#92; (7)' title='&#92;displaystyle |&#92;sum_{n &#92;in {&#92;bf Z}/p{&#92;bf Z}} e_p(f(n))| &#92;ll 1 &#92; &#92; &#92; &#92; &#92; (7)' class='latex' /></p> <p></a> when <img src='http://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7Bp%7Cf%27%27%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0' alt='{p|f&#039;&#039;}' title='{p|f&#039;&#039;}' class='latex' /> but <img src='http://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7Bp+%5Cnot+%7C+f%27%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0' alt='{p &#92;not | f&#039;}' title='{p &#92;not | f&#039;}' class='latex' />, and <a name="epf"> <p align="center"><img src='http://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%5Cdisplaystyle++%7C%5Csum_%7Bn+%5Cin+%7B%5Cbf+Z%7D%2Fp%7B%5Cbf+Z%7D%7D+e_p%28f%28n%29%29%7C+%5Cll+%5Csqrt%7Bp%7D+%5C+%5C+%5C+%5C+%5C+%288%29&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0' alt='&#92;displaystyle |&#92;sum_{n &#92;in {&#92;bf Z}/p{&#92;bf Z}} e_p(f(n))| &#92;ll &#92;sqrt{p} &#92; &#92; &#92; &#92; &#92; (8)' title='&#92;displaystyle |&#92;sum_{n &#92;in {&#92;bf Z}/p{&#92;bf Z}} e_p(f(n))| &#92;ll &#92;sqrt{p} &#92; &#92; &#92; &#92; &#92; (8)' class='latex' /></p> <p></a> otherwise. We may assume that <img src='http://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7Bp%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0' alt='{p}' title='{p}' class='latex' /> is sufficiently large depending on the degrees of <img src='http://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7BP%2CQ%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0' alt='{P,Q}' title='{P,Q}' class='latex' /> as the claim is trivial otherwise.</p> <p> The first bound trivially follows from the triangle inequality, so we turn to the second bound. Since <img src='http://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7Bp%7Cf%27%27%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0' alt='{p|f&#039;&#039;}' title='{p|f&#039;&#039;}' class='latex' />, we conclude from Lemma <a href="#fund">3</a> that there is <img src='http://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7Bc+%5Cin+%7B%5Cbf+Z%7D%2Fp%7B%5Cbf+Z%7D%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0' alt='{c &#92;in {&#92;bf Z}/p{&#92;bf Z}}' title='{c &#92;in {&#92;bf Z}/p{&#92;bf Z}}' class='latex' /> such that <img src='http://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7Bp%7Cf%27-c%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0' alt='{p|f&#039;-c}' title='{p|f&#039;-c}' class='latex' />; since <img src='http://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7Bp+%5Cnot+%7C+f%27%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0' alt='{p &#92;not | f&#039;}' title='{p &#92;not | f&#039;}' class='latex' />, <img src='http://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7Bc%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0' alt='{c}' title='{c}' class='latex' /> must be non-zero. Since <img src='http://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7Bf%27-c+%3D+%28f-ct%29%27%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0' alt='{f&#039;-c = (f-ct)&#039;}' title='{f&#039;-c = (f-ct)&#039;}' class='latex' />, another application of Lemma <a href="#fund">3</a> shows that there is <img src='http://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7Bd+%5Cin+%7B%5Cbf+Z%7D%2Fp%7B%5Cbf+Z%7D%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0' alt='{d &#92;in {&#92;bf Z}/p{&#92;bf Z}}' title='{d &#92;in {&#92;bf Z}/p{&#92;bf Z}}' class='latex' /> such that <img src='http://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7Bp%7Cf-ct-d%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0' alt='{p|f-ct-d}' title='{p|f-ct-d}' class='latex' />. Thus <img src='http://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7Bf%28n%29+%3D+cn%2Bd%5C+%28p%29%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0' alt='{f(n) = cn+d&#92; (p)}' title='{f(n) = cn+d&#92; (p)}' class='latex' /> whenever <img src='http://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7Bf%28n%29%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0' alt='{f(n)}' title='{f(n)}' class='latex' /> is well-defined. Since the denominator <img src='http://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7BQ%28n%29%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0' alt='{Q(n)}' title='{Q(n)}' class='latex' /> of <img src='http://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7Bf%28n%29%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0' alt='{f(n)}' title='{f(n)}' class='latex' /> has only bounded number of zeroes, we conclude that <img src='http://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7Be_p%28f%28n%29%29+%3D+e_p%28cn%2Bd%29%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0' alt='{e_p(f(n)) = e_p(cn+d)}' title='{e_p(f(n)) = e_p(cn+d)}' class='latex' /> for all but a bounded number of <img src='http://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7Bn+%5Cin+%7B%5Cbf+Z%7D%2Fp%7B%5Cbf+Z%7D%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0' alt='{n &#92;in {&#92;bf Z}/p{&#92;bf Z}}' title='{n &#92;in {&#92;bf Z}/p{&#92;bf Z}}' class='latex' />. The claim then follows <a href="#ram">(7)</a> from the Fourier identity </p> <p align="center"><img src='http://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%5Cdisplaystyle++%5Csum_%7Bn+%5Cin%7B%5Cbf+Z%7D%2Fp%7B%5Cbf+Z%7D%7D+e_p%28+cn%2Bd%29+%3D+0.&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0' alt='&#92;displaystyle &#92;sum_{n &#92;in{&#92;bf Z}/p{&#92;bf Z}} e_p( cn+d) = 0.' title='&#92;displaystyle &#92;sum_{n &#92;in{&#92;bf Z}/p{&#92;bf Z}} e_p( cn+d) = 0.' class='latex' /></p> <p> Now we prove <a href="#epf">(8)</a>. By abuse of notation, we view <img src='http://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7BP%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0' alt='{P}' title='{P}' class='latex' /> and <img src='http://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7BQ%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0' alt='{Q}' title='{Q}' class='latex' /> as polynomials over the field <img src='http://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7B%7B%5Cbf+F%7D_p%5Bt%5D%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0' alt='{{&#92;bf F}_p[t]}' title='{{&#92;bf F}_p[t]}' class='latex' /> rather than over the integers. Let <img src='http://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7BR+%3A%3D+%28P%2CQ%29%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0' alt='{R := (P,Q)}' title='{R := (P,Q)}' class='latex' /> be the (monic) greatest common divisor, thus <img src='http://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7BP+%3D+R+%5Ctilde+P%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0' alt='{P = R &#92;tilde P}' title='{P = R &#92;tilde P}' class='latex' /> and <img src='http://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7BQ+%3D+R+%5Ctilde+Q%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0' alt='{Q = R &#92;tilde Q}' title='{Q = R &#92;tilde Q}' class='latex' /> with <img src='http://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7B%5Ctilde+P%2C+%5Ctilde+Q+%5Cin+%7B%5Cbf+F%7D_p%5Bt%5D%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0' alt='{&#92;tilde P, &#92;tilde Q &#92;in {&#92;bf F}_p[t]}' title='{&#92;tilde P, &#92;tilde Q &#92;in {&#92;bf F}_p[t]}' class='latex' /> coprime and of bounded degree with <img src='http://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7B%5Ctilde+Q%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0' alt='{&#92;tilde Q}' title='{&#92;tilde Q}' class='latex' /> monic. As in the previous paragraph, we have <img src='http://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7Be_p%28f%28n%29%29+%3D+e_p%28+%5Cfrac%7B%5Ctilde+P%28n%29%7D%7B%5Ctilde+Q%28n%29%7D+%29%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0' alt='{e_p(f(n)) = e_p( &#92;frac{&#92;tilde P(n)}{&#92;tilde Q(n)} )}' title='{e_p(f(n)) = e_p( &#92;frac{&#92;tilde P(n)}{&#92;tilde Q(n)} )}' class='latex' /> for all but a bounded number of <img src='http://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7Bn%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0' alt='{n}' title='{n}' class='latex' />. So it suffices to show that </p> <p align="center"><img src='http://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%5Cdisplaystyle++%7C%5Csum_%7Bn+%5Cin+%7B%5Cbf+Z%7D%2Fp%7B%5Cbf+Z%7D%7D+1_%7B%5Ctilde+Q%28n%29+%5Cneq+0%7D+e_p%28%5Cfrac%7B%5Ctilde+P%28n%29%7D%7B%5Ctilde+Q%28n%29%7D%29%7C+%5Cll+%5Csqrt%7Bp%7D.&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0' alt='&#92;displaystyle |&#92;sum_{n &#92;in {&#92;bf Z}/p{&#92;bf Z}} 1_{&#92;tilde Q(n) &#92;neq 0} e_p(&#92;frac{&#92;tilde P(n)}{&#92;tilde Q(n)})| &#92;ll &#92;sqrt{p}.' title='&#92;displaystyle |&#92;sum_{n &#92;in {&#92;bf Z}/p{&#92;bf Z}} 1_{&#92;tilde Q(n) &#92;neq 0} e_p(&#92;frac{&#92;tilde P(n)}{&#92;tilde Q(n)})| &#92;ll &#92;sqrt{p}.' class='latex' /></p> <p> We now use the Weil bound for exponentials of rational functions over a field of prime order, as stated for instance in <a href="http://www.ams.org/mathscinet-getitem?mr=241424">this paper of Perelmuter</a> or <a href="http://www.ams.org/mathscinet-getitem?mr=2195926">this paper of Cochrane and Pinner</a> (in the case when <img src='http://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7Bf%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0' alt='{f}' title='{f}' class='latex' /> is polynomial, one can also use the <a href="http://www.ams.org/mathscinet-getitem?mr=27006">original paper of Weil</a>, who also treats the important case of Kloosterman sums when <img src='http://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7Bf%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0' alt='{f}' title='{f}' class='latex' /> is a fractional linear transformation). We remark that the Cochrane-Pinner paper uses Stepanov&#8217;s method and is thus essentially elementary in nature, whereas the other papers use more sophisticated tools from arithmetic geometry (such as <img src='http://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7B%5Cell%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0' alt='{&#92;ell}' title='{&#92;ell}' class='latex' />-adic cohomology). In any event, the results in these papers give the required bound except when the rational function <img src='http://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7B%5Ctilde+P+%2F+%5Ctilde+Q%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0' alt='{&#92;tilde P / &#92;tilde Q}' title='{&#92;tilde P / &#92;tilde Q}' class='latex' /> has the form <a name="tptq"> <p align="center"><img src='http://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%5Cdisplaystyle++%5Cfrac%7B%5Ctilde+P%7D%7B%5Ctilde+Q%7D+%3D+g%5Ep+-+g+%2B+c+%5C+%5C+%5C+%5C+%5C+%289%29&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0' alt='&#92;displaystyle &#92;frac{&#92;tilde P}{&#92;tilde Q} = g^p - g + c &#92; &#92; &#92; &#92; &#92; (9)' title='&#92;displaystyle &#92;frac{&#92;tilde P}{&#92;tilde Q} = g^p - g + c &#92; &#92; &#92; &#92; &#92; (9)' class='latex' /></p> <p></a> in the field <img src='http://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7B%7B%5Cbf+F%7D_p%28t%29%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0' alt='{{&#92;bf F}_p(t)}' title='{{&#92;bf F}_p(t)}' class='latex' /> of rational functions over <img src='http://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7B%7B%5Cbf+F%7D_p%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0' alt='{{&#92;bf F}_p}' title='{{&#92;bf F}_p}' class='latex' /> for some <img src='http://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7Bg+%5Cin+%7B%5Cbf+F%7D_p%28t%29%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0' alt='{g &#92;in {&#92;bf F}_p(t)}' title='{g &#92;in {&#92;bf F}_p(t)}' class='latex' /> and <img src='http://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7Bc+%5Cin+%7B%5Cbf+F%7D_p%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0' alt='{c &#92;in {&#92;bf F}_p}' title='{c &#92;in {&#92;bf F}_p}' class='latex' />. (The presence of the <img src='http://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7Bg%5Ep-g%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0' alt='{g^p-g}' title='{g^p-g}' class='latex' /> factor arises because of elements of <img src='http://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7B%7B%5Cbf+F%7D_p%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0' alt='{{&#92;bf F}_p}' title='{{&#92;bf F}_p}' class='latex' /> are all roots of <img src='http://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7Bx%5Ep-x%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0' alt='{x^p-x}' title='{x^p-x}' class='latex' />.) </p> <p> Suppose that <a href="#tptq">(9)</a> holds. Writing <img src='http://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7Bg+%3D+R%2FS%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0' alt='{g = R/S}' title='{g = R/S}' class='latex' /> for some coprime polynomials <img src='http://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7BR%2CS+%5Cin+%7B%5Cbf+F%7D_p%5Bt%5D%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0' alt='{R,S &#92;in {&#92;bf F}_p[t]}' title='{R,S &#92;in {&#92;bf F}_p[t]}' class='latex' /> with <img src='http://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7BS%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0' alt='{S}' title='{S}' class='latex' /> monic, we conclude on multiplying everything out that </p> <p align="center"><img src='http://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%5Cdisplaystyle++%5Ctilde+P+S%5Ep+%3D+%5Ctilde+Q+R%5Ep+-+%5Ctilde+Q+R+S%5E%7Bp-1%7D+%2B+c+%5Ctilde+Q+S%5Ep&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0' alt='&#92;displaystyle &#92;tilde P S^p = &#92;tilde Q R^p - &#92;tilde Q R S^{p-1} + c &#92;tilde Q S^p' title='&#92;displaystyle &#92;tilde P S^p = &#92;tilde Q R^p - &#92;tilde Q R S^{p-1} + c &#92;tilde Q S^p' class='latex' /></p> <p> in the polynomial ring <img src='http://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7B%7B%5Cbf+F%7D_p%5Bt%5D%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0' alt='{{&#92;bf F}_p[t]}' title='{{&#92;bf F}_p[t]}' class='latex' />. By unique factorisation, this forces <img src='http://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7BS%5E%7Bp-1%7D%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0' alt='{S^{p-1}}' title='{S^{p-1}}' class='latex' /> to divide <img src='http://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7B%5Ctilde+Q%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0' alt='{&#92;tilde Q}' title='{&#92;tilde Q}' class='latex' />, which for <img src='http://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7Bp%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0' alt='{p}' title='{p}' class='latex' /> large enough forces <img src='http://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7BS%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0' alt='{S}' title='{S}' class='latex' /> to have degree zero, thus <img src='http://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7BS%3D1%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0' alt='{S=1}' title='{S=1}' class='latex' /> as <img src='http://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7BS%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0' alt='{S}' title='{S}' class='latex' /> is monic. We thus have <p align="center"><img src='http://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%5Cdisplaystyle++%5Ctilde+P+%3D+%5Ctilde+Q+R%5Ep+-+%5Ctilde+Q+R+%2B+c+%5Ctilde+Q.&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0' alt='&#92;displaystyle &#92;tilde P = &#92;tilde Q R^p - &#92;tilde Q R + c &#92;tilde Q.' title='&#92;displaystyle &#92;tilde P = &#92;tilde Q R^p - &#92;tilde Q R + c &#92;tilde Q.' class='latex' /></p> <p> Inspecting the <img src='http://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7B%5Chbox%7Bdeg%7D%28%5Ctilde+Q%29+%2B+p+%5Chbox%7Bdeg%7D%28R%29%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0' alt='{&#92;hbox{deg}(&#92;tilde Q) + p &#92;hbox{deg}(R)}' title='{&#92;hbox{deg}(&#92;tilde Q) + p &#92;hbox{deg}(R)}' class='latex' /> coefficient of this equation, we obtain (for <img src='http://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7Bp%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0' alt='{p}' title='{p}' class='latex' /> large enough) a contradiction unless <img src='http://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7BR%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0' alt='{R}' title='{R}' class='latex' /> has degree zero, thus <img src='http://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7BR%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0' alt='{R}' title='{R}' class='latex' /> is constant. In particular <img src='http://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7BR%5Ep+-+R+%3D+0%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0' alt='{R^p - R = 0}' title='{R^p - R = 0}' class='latex' /> and so <img src='http://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7B%5Ctilde+P%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0' alt='{&#92;tilde P}' title='{&#92;tilde P}' class='latex' /> is a scalar multiple of <img src='http://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7B%5Ctilde+Q%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0' alt='{&#92;tilde Q}' title='{&#92;tilde Q}' class='latex' />, hence <img src='http://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7BP%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0' alt='{P}' title='{P}' class='latex' /> is a scalar multiple of <img src='http://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7BQ%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0' alt='{Q}' title='{Q}' class='latex' /> and so <img src='http://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7Bp+%7C+f%27%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0' alt='{p | f&#039;}' title='{p | f&#039;}' class='latex' />, contradicting the hypothesis. This covers all cases and we are done. <img src='http://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%5CBox&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0' alt='&#92;Box' title='&#92;Box' class='latex' /></p> <p> Now we obtain a bound for incomplete exponential sums to smooth moduli. We will focus attention here on the specific sum we need to bound for the Polymath8 project, namely a sum of the form </p> </p> <p align="center"><img src='http://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%5Cdisplaystyle++S+%3A%3D+%5Csum_n+%5Cpsi_N%28n%29+e_%7Bd_1%7D%28+%5Cfrac%7Bc_1%7D%7Bn%7D+%29+e_%7Bd_2%7D%28+%5Cfrac%7Bc_2%7D%7Bn%2Bl%7D+%29&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0' alt='&#92;displaystyle S := &#92;sum_n &#92;psi_N(n) e_{d_1}( &#92;frac{c_1}{n} ) e_{d_2}( &#92;frac{c_2}{n+l} )' title='&#92;displaystyle S := &#92;sum_n &#92;psi_N(n) e_{d_1}( &#92;frac{c_1}{n} ) e_{d_2}( &#92;frac{c_2}{n+l} )' class='latex' /></p> <p> where <img src='http://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7Bd_1%2Cd_2%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0' alt='{d_1,d_2}' title='{d_1,d_2}' class='latex' /> are square-free numbers (not necessarily coprime), <img src='http://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7Bc_1%2Cc_2%2Cl%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0' alt='{c_1,c_2,l}' title='{c_1,c_2,l}' class='latex' /> are integers, <img src='http://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7BN+%5Cgg+1%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0' alt='{N &#92;gg 1}' title='{N &#92;gg 1}' class='latex' />, and <img src='http://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7B%5Cpsi_N%3A+%7B%5Cbf+R%7D+%5Crightarrow+%7B%5Cbf+C%7D%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0' alt='{&#92;psi_N: {&#92;bf R} &#92;rightarrow {&#92;bf C}}' title='{&#92;psi_N: {&#92;bf R} &#92;rightarrow {&#92;bf C}}' class='latex' /> is a function supported on an interval <img src='http://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7BI%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0' alt='{I}' title='{I}' class='latex' /> of length <img src='http://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7BO%28N%29%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0' alt='{O(N)}' title='{O(N)}' class='latex' /> that obeys the smoothness bounds <p align="center"><img src='http://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%5Cdisplaystyle++%7C%5Cpsi%5E%7B%28j%29%7D_N%28t%29%7C+%5Clessapprox+N%5E%7B-j%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0' alt='&#92;displaystyle |&#92;psi^{(j)}_N(t)| &#92;lessapprox N^{-j}' title='&#92;displaystyle |&#92;psi^{(j)}_N(t)| &#92;lessapprox N^{-j}' class='latex' /></p> <p> for any fixed <img src='http://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7Bj+%5Cgeq+0%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0' alt='{j &#92;geq 0}' title='{j &#92;geq 0}' class='latex' />. The arguments below also apply to more general exponential sums as these, but the specific sum <img src='http://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7BS%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0' alt='{S}' title='{S}' class='latex' /> benefits from the additional cancellation <a href="#rama">(6)</a> that is not available for more general sums.</p> <blockquote><p><b>Proposition 5</b> Let <img src='http://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7BS%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0' alt='{S}' title='{S}' class='latex' /> be as above. Write <img src='http://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7Bd%27_1+%3A%3D+d_1%2F%28d_1%2Cd_2%29%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0' alt='{d&#039;_1 := d_1/(d_1,d_2)}' title='{d&#039;_1 := d_1/(d_1,d_2)}' class='latex' /> and <img src='http://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7Bd%27_2+%3A%3D+d_2%2F%28d_1%2Cd_2%29%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0' alt='{d&#039;_2 := d_2/(d_1,d_2)}' title='{d&#039;_2 := d_2/(d_1,d_2)}' class='latex' />. </p> <ul> <li>(i) (Trivial bound) We have <a name="trivial"> <p align="center"><img src='http://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%5Cdisplaystyle++%7CS%7C+%5Clessapprox+N.+%5C+%5C+%5C+%5C+%5C+%2810%29&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0' alt='&#92;displaystyle |S| &#92;lessapprox N. &#92; &#92; &#92; &#92; &#92; (10)' title='&#92;displaystyle |S| &#92;lessapprox N. &#92; &#92; &#92; &#92; &#92; (10)' class='latex' /></p> <p></a> </li> <li>(ii) (Standard bound) We have <a name="loo"> <p align="center"><img src='http://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%5Cdisplaystyle++%7CS%7C+%5Clessapprox+%5Bd_1%2Cd_2%5D%5E%7B1%2F2%7D+%2B+%5Cfrac%7BN%7D%7Bd_1+d_2%7D+%28d_1%2Cd_2%29%5E2+%28c_1%2Cd%27_1%29+%28c_2%2Cd%27_2%29.+%5C+%5C+%5C+%5C+%5C+%2811%29&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0' alt='&#92;displaystyle |S| &#92;lessapprox [d_1,d_2]^{1/2} + &#92;frac{N}{d_1 d_2} (d_1,d_2)^2 (c_1,d&#039;_1) (c_2,d&#039;_2). &#92; &#92; &#92; &#92; &#92; (11)' title='&#92;displaystyle |S| &#92;lessapprox [d_1,d_2]^{1/2} + &#92;frac{N}{d_1 d_2} (d_1,d_2)^2 (c_1,d&#039;_1) (c_2,d&#039;_2). &#92; &#92; &#92; &#92; &#92; (11)' class='latex' /></p> <p></a> </li> <li>(iii) (Improved bound) We have <a name="goo"> <p align="center"><img src='http://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%5Cdisplaystyle++%7CS%7C+%5Clessapprox+N%5E%7B1%2F2%7D+%28d%27_1%29%5E%7B1%2F4%7D+%2B+N%5E%7B1%2F2%7D+d_2%5E%7B1%2F2%7D+%2B+%5Cfrac%7B%28c_1%2Cd%27_1%29%5E%7B1%2F4%7D%7D%7B%28d%27_1%29%5E%7B1%2F4%7D%7D+N.+%5C+%5C+%5C+%5C+%5C+%2812%29&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0' alt='&#92;displaystyle |S| &#92;lessapprox N^{1/2} (d&#039;_1)^{1/4} + N^{1/2} d_2^{1/2} + &#92;frac{(c_1,d&#039;_1)^{1/4}}{(d&#039;_1)^{1/4}} N. &#92; &#92; &#92; &#92; &#92; (12)' title='&#92;displaystyle |S| &#92;lessapprox N^{1/2} (d&#039;_1)^{1/4} + N^{1/2} d_2^{1/2} + &#92;frac{(c_1,d&#039;_1)^{1/4}}{(d&#039;_1)^{1/4}} N. &#92; &#92; &#92; &#92; &#92; (12)' class='latex' /></p> <p></a> </li> </ul> </blockquote> </p> <p> The estimate (ii) is a slightly improved version of Lemma 11 of <a href="http://annals.math.princeton.edu/wp-content/uploads/YitangZhang.pdf">Zhang&#8217;s paper</a> (which is a key estimate to treat the Type I/II sums); one can also write the second term <img src='http://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7B%5Cfrac%7BN%7D%7Bd_1+d_2%7D+%28d_1%2Cd_2%29%5E2+%28c_1%2Cd%27_1%29+%28c_2%2Cd%27_2%29%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0' alt='{&#92;frac{N}{d_1 d_2} (d_1,d_2)^2 (c_1,d&#039;_1) (c_2,d&#039;_2)}' title='{&#92;frac{N}{d_1 d_2} (d_1,d_2)^2 (c_1,d&#039;_1) (c_2,d&#039;_2)}' class='latex' /> on the right-hand side more suggestively as <img src='http://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7B%5Cfrac%7B%28c_1%2Cd%27_1%29%7D%7Bd%27_1%7D+%5Cfrac%7B%28c_2%2Cd%27_2%29%7D%7Bd%27_2%7D+N%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0' alt='{&#92;frac{(c_1,d&#039;_1)}{d&#039;_1} &#92;frac{(c_2,d&#039;_2)}{d&#039;_2} N}' title='{&#92;frac{(c_1,d&#039;_1)}{d&#039;_1} &#92;frac{(c_2,d&#039;_2)}{d&#039;_2} N}' class='latex' />. But it is the estimate (iii) which is a more substantial improvement, as for the medium-sized values of <img src='http://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7BN%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0' alt='{N}' title='{N}' class='latex' /> that come up in Zhang&#8217;s argument, the first two terms <img src='http://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7BN%5E%7B1%2F2%7D+%28d%27_1%29%5E%7B1%2F4%7D%2C+N%5E%7B1%2F2%7D+d_2%5E%7B1%2F2%7D%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0' alt='{N^{1/2} (d&#039;_1)^{1/4}, N^{1/2} d_2^{1/2}}' title='{N^{1/2} (d&#039;_1)^{1/4}, N^{1/2} d_2^{1/2}}' class='latex' /> that appear in <a href="#goo">(12)</a> are superior to the main term <img src='http://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7B%5Bd_1%2Cd_2%5D%5E%7B1%2F2%7D%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0' alt='{[d_1,d_2]^{1/2}}' title='{[d_1,d_2]^{1/2}}' class='latex' /> in <a href="#loo">(11)</a>. (Admittedly, the final term in <a href="#goo">(12)</a> is worse than the final term in <a href="#loo">(11)</a>, but in practice these terms are not dominant.) The improved bound <a href="#goo">(12)</a> leads to significantly better values of <img src='http://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7B%5Cvarpi%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0' alt='{&#92;varpi}' title='{&#92;varpi}' class='latex' /> and <img src='http://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7B%5Cdelta%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0' alt='{&#92;delta}' title='{&#92;delta}' class='latex' /> for the assertion <img src='http://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7BMPZ%27%5B%5Cvarpi%2C%5Cdelta%5D%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0' alt='{MPZ&#039;[&#92;varpi,&#92;delta]}' title='{MPZ&#039;[&#92;varpi,&#92;delta]}' class='latex' /> that we need for bounded gaps between primes; this is sketched in this previous comment and will be detailed in a subsequent post. </p> <p> <em>Proof:</em> The trivial bound <a href="#trivial">(10)</a> is immediate from the triangle inequality and the bounds and support of <img src='http://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7B%5Cpsi_N%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0' alt='{&#92;psi_N}' title='{&#92;psi_N}' class='latex' />, so we turn now to the standard bound <a href="#loo">(11)</a>. We can write </p> <p align="center"><img src='http://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%5Cdisplaystyle++e_%7Bd_1%7D%28+%5Cfrac%7Bc_1%7D%7Bn%7D+%29+e_%7Bd_2%7D%28+%5Cfrac%7Bc_2%7D%7Bn%2Bl%7D+%29+%3D+e_q%28+f%28n%29+%29&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0' alt='&#92;displaystyle e_{d_1}( &#92;frac{c_1}{n} ) e_{d_2}( &#92;frac{c_2}{n+l} ) = e_q( f(n) )' title='&#92;displaystyle e_{d_1}( &#92;frac{c_1}{n} ) e_{d_2}( &#92;frac{c_2}{n+l} ) = e_q( f(n) )' class='latex' /></p> <p> where <img src='http://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7Bq+%3A%3D+%5Bd_1%2Cd_2%5D+%3D+d_1+d%27_2+%3D+d%27_1+d_2%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0' alt='{q := [d_1,d_2] = d_1 d&#039;_2 = d&#039;_1 d_2}' title='{q := [d_1,d_2] = d_1 d&#039;_2 = d&#039;_1 d_2}' class='latex' /> and <img src='http://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7Bf%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0' alt='{f}' title='{f}' class='latex' /> is the integral rational function <a name="f-form"> <p align="center"><img src='http://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%5Cdisplaystyle++f%28t%29+%3A%3D+%5Cfrac%7Bc_1+d%27_2%7D%7Bt%7D+%2B+%5Cfrac%7Bc_2+d%27_1%7D%7Bt%2Bl%7D.+%5C+%5C+%5C+%5C+%5C+%2813%29&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0' alt='&#92;displaystyle f(t) := &#92;frac{c_1 d&#039;_2}{t} + &#92;frac{c_2 d&#039;_1}{t+l}. &#92; &#92; &#92; &#92; &#92; (13)' title='&#92;displaystyle f(t) := &#92;frac{c_1 d&#039;_2}{t} + &#92;frac{c_2 d&#039;_1}{t+l}. &#92; &#92; &#92; &#92; &#92; (13)' class='latex' /></p> <p></a></p> <p> By Fourier inversion and the <img src='http://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7Bq%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0' alt='{q}' title='{q}' class='latex' />-periodicity of <img src='http://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7Be_q%28f%29%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0' alt='{e_q(f)}' title='{e_q(f)}' class='latex' />, one can rewrite <img src='http://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7BS%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0' alt='{S}' title='{S}' class='latex' /> as <a name="hq"> <p align="center"><img src='http://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%5Cdisplaystyle++S+%3D+%5Cfrac%7B1%7D%7Bq%7D+%5Csum_%7Bh+%5Cin+%7B%5Cbf+Z%7D%2Fq%7B%5Cbf+Z%7D%7D+%5Chat+%5Cpsi_N%28%5Cfrac%7Bh%7D%7Bq%7D%29+%5Csum_%7Bn+%5Cin+%7B%5Cbf+Z%7D%2Fq%7B%5Cbf+Z%7D%7D+e_q%28f%28n%29+%2B+hn%29+%5C+%5C+%5C+%5C+%5C+%2814%29&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0' alt='&#92;displaystyle S = &#92;frac{1}{q} &#92;sum_{h &#92;in {&#92;bf Z}/q{&#92;bf Z}} &#92;hat &#92;psi_N(&#92;frac{h}{q}) &#92;sum_{n &#92;in {&#92;bf Z}/q{&#92;bf Z}} e_q(f(n) + hn) &#92; &#92; &#92; &#92; &#92; (14)' title='&#92;displaystyle S = &#92;frac{1}{q} &#92;sum_{h &#92;in {&#92;bf Z}/q{&#92;bf Z}} &#92;hat &#92;psi_N(&#92;frac{h}{q}) &#92;sum_{n &#92;in {&#92;bf Z}/q{&#92;bf Z}} e_q(f(n) + hn) &#92; &#92; &#92; &#92; &#92; (14)' class='latex' /></p> <p></a> where <img src='http://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7B%5Chat+%5Cpsi_N%3A+%7B%5Cbf+R%7D%2F%7B%5Cbf+Z%7D+%5Crightarrow+%7B%5Cbf+C%7D%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0' alt='{&#92;hat &#92;psi_N: {&#92;bf R}/{&#92;bf Z} &#92;rightarrow {&#92;bf C}}' title='{&#92;hat &#92;psi_N: {&#92;bf R}/{&#92;bf Z} &#92;rightarrow {&#92;bf C}}' class='latex' /> is the function </p> <p align="center"><img src='http://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%5Cdisplaystyle++%5Chat+%5Cpsi_N%28%5Ctheta%29+%3A%3D+%5Csum_%7Bn+%5Cin+%7B%5Cbf+Z%7D%7D+%5Cpsi_N%28n%29+e%5E%7B-2%5Cpi+i+n+%5Ctheta%7D.&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0' alt='&#92;displaystyle &#92;hat &#92;psi_N(&#92;theta) := &#92;sum_{n &#92;in {&#92;bf Z}} &#92;psi_N(n) e^{-2&#92;pi i n &#92;theta}.' title='&#92;displaystyle &#92;hat &#92;psi_N(&#92;theta) := &#92;sum_{n &#92;in {&#92;bf Z}} &#92;psi_N(n) e^{-2&#92;pi i n &#92;theta}.' class='latex' /></p> <p> From the Poisson summation formula and integration by parts, we have the standard bounds <a name="psint"> <p align="center"><img src='http://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%5Cdisplaystyle++%7C%5Chat+%5Cpsi_N%28%5Ctheta%29%7C+%5Clessapprox+N+%28N+%7C%5Ctheta%7C%29%5E%7B-j%7D+%5C+%5C+%5C+%5C+%5C+%2815%29&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0' alt='&#92;displaystyle |&#92;hat &#92;psi_N(&#92;theta)| &#92;lessapprox N (N |&#92;theta|)^{-j} &#92; &#92; &#92; &#92; &#92; (15)' title='&#92;displaystyle |&#92;hat &#92;psi_N(&#92;theta)| &#92;lessapprox N (N |&#92;theta|)^{-j} &#92; &#92; &#92; &#92; &#92; (15)' class='latex' /></p> <p></a> for all <img src='http://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7B%5Ctheta+%5Cin+%5B-1%2F2%2C1%2F2%29%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0' alt='{&#92;theta &#92;in [-1/2,1/2)}' title='{&#92;theta &#92;in [-1/2,1/2)}' class='latex' /> (which, by abuse of notation, we identify with <img src='http://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7B%7B%5Cbf+R%7D%2F%7B%5Cbf+Z%7D%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0' alt='{{&#92;bf R}/{&#92;bf Z}}' title='{{&#92;bf R}/{&#92;bf Z}}' class='latex' />) and any fixed <img src='http://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7Bj+%5Cgeq+0%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0' alt='{j &#92;geq 0}' title='{j &#92;geq 0}' class='latex' />. </p> <p> Consider first the <img src='http://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7Bh%3D0%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0' alt='{h=0}' title='{h=0}' class='latex' /> term in <a href="#hq">(14)</a>. By the Chinese remainder theorem, we may factor <img src='http://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7B%5Csum_%7Bn+%5Cin+%7B%5Cbf+Z%7D%2Fq%7B%5Cbf+Z%7D%7D+e_q%28f%28n%29%29%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0' alt='{&#92;sum_{n &#92;in {&#92;bf Z}/q{&#92;bf Z}} e_q(f(n))}' title='{&#92;sum_{n &#92;in {&#92;bf Z}/q{&#92;bf Z}} e_q(f(n))}' class='latex' /> as </p> <p align="center"><img src='http://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%5Cdisplaystyle++%28%5Csum_%7Bn+%5Cin+%7B%5Cbf+Z%7D%2Fd%27_1+%7B%5Cbf+Z%7D%7D+e_%7Bd%27_1%7D%28+%5Cfrac%7Bc_1%7D%7Bn+%28d_1%2Cd_2%29%7D+%29%29+%28%5Csum_%7Bn+%5Cin+%7B%5Cbf+Z%7D%2Fd%27_2+%7B%5Cbf+Z%7D%7D+e_%7Bd%27_2%7D%28+%5Cfrac%7Bc_2%7D%7Bn+%28d_1%2Cd_2%29%7D+%29%29&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0' alt='&#92;displaystyle (&#92;sum_{n &#92;in {&#92;bf Z}/d&#039;_1 {&#92;bf Z}} e_{d&#039;_1}( &#92;frac{c_1}{n (d_1,d_2)} )) (&#92;sum_{n &#92;in {&#92;bf Z}/d&#039;_2 {&#92;bf Z}} e_{d&#039;_2}( &#92;frac{c_2}{n (d_1,d_2)} ))' title='&#92;displaystyle (&#92;sum_{n &#92;in {&#92;bf Z}/d&#039;_1 {&#92;bf Z}} e_{d&#039;_1}( &#92;frac{c_1}{n (d_1,d_2)} )) (&#92;sum_{n &#92;in {&#92;bf Z}/d&#039;_2 {&#92;bf Z}} e_{d&#039;_2}( &#92;frac{c_2}{n (d_1,d_2)} ))' class='latex' /></p> <p align="center"><img src='http://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%5Cdisplaystyle++%28%5Csum_%7Bn+%5Cin+%7B%5Cbf+Z%7D%2F%28d_1%2Cd_2%29%7B%5Cbf+Z%7D%7D+e_%7B%28d_1%2Cd_2%29%7D%28+%5Cfrac%7Bc_1%7D%7Bnd%27_1%7D+%2B+%5Cfrac%7Bc_2%7D%7B%28n%2Bl%29d%27_2%7D+%29%29.&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0' alt='&#92;displaystyle (&#92;sum_{n &#92;in {&#92;bf Z}/(d_1,d_2){&#92;bf Z}} e_{(d_1,d_2)}( &#92;frac{c_1}{nd&#039;_1} + &#92;frac{c_2}{(n+l)d&#039;_2} )).' title='&#92;displaystyle (&#92;sum_{n &#92;in {&#92;bf Z}/(d_1,d_2){&#92;bf Z}} e_{(d_1,d_2)}( &#92;frac{c_1}{nd&#039;_1} + &#92;frac{c_2}{(n+l)d&#039;_2} )).' class='latex' /></p> <p> Applying <a href="#rama">(6)</a> to the first two factors and the trivial bound of <img src='http://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7B%28d_1%2Cd_2%29%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0' alt='{(d_1,d_2)}' title='{(d_1,d_2)}' class='latex' /> to the second factor, we conclude that <p align="center"><img src='http://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%5Cdisplaystyle++%7C%5Csum_%7Bn+%5Cin+%7B%5Cbf+Z%7D%2Fq%7B%5Cbf+Z%7D%7D+e_q%28f%28n%29%29%7C+%5Clessapprox+%28c_1%2Cd%27_1%29+%28c_2%2Cd%27_2%29+%28d_1%2Cd_2%29&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0' alt='&#92;displaystyle |&#92;sum_{n &#92;in {&#92;bf Z}/q{&#92;bf Z}} e_q(f(n))| &#92;lessapprox (c_1,d&#039;_1) (c_2,d&#039;_2) (d_1,d_2)' title='&#92;displaystyle |&#92;sum_{n &#92;in {&#92;bf Z}/q{&#92;bf Z}} e_q(f(n))| &#92;lessapprox (c_1,d&#039;_1) (c_2,d&#039;_2) (d_1,d_2)' class='latex' /></p> <p> and so the contribution of the <img src='http://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7Bh%3D0%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0' alt='{h=0}' title='{h=0}' class='latex' /> term is acceptable. It remains to establish that <p align="center"><img src='http://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%5Cdisplaystyle++%5Cfrac%7B1%7D%7Bq%7D%5Csum_%7Bh+%5Cin+%7B%5Cbf+Z%7D%2Fq%7B%5Cbf+Z%7D+%5Cbackslash+%5C%7B0%5C%7D%7D+%7C%5Chat+%5Cpsi_N%28%5Cfrac%7Bh%7D%7Bq%7D%29%7C+%7C%5Csum_%7Bn+%5Cin+%7B%5Cbf+Z%7D%2Fq%7B%5Cbf+Z%7D%7D+e_q%28f%28n%29+%2B+hn%29%7C+%5Clessapprox+q%5E%7B1%2F2%7D.&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0' alt='&#92;displaystyle &#92;frac{1}{q}&#92;sum_{h &#92;in {&#92;bf Z}/q{&#92;bf Z} &#92;backslash &#92;{0&#92;}} |&#92;hat &#92;psi_N(&#92;frac{h}{q})| |&#92;sum_{n &#92;in {&#92;bf Z}/q{&#92;bf Z}} e_q(f(n) + hn)| &#92;lessapprox q^{1/2}.' title='&#92;displaystyle &#92;frac{1}{q}&#92;sum_{h &#92;in {&#92;bf Z}/q{&#92;bf Z} &#92;backslash &#92;{0&#92;}} |&#92;hat &#92;psi_N(&#92;frac{h}{q})| |&#92;sum_{n &#92;in {&#92;bf Z}/q{&#92;bf Z}} e_q(f(n) + hn)| &#92;lessapprox q^{1/2}.' class='latex' /></p> <p> Let <img src='http://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7B%5Cepsilon+%3E+0%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0' alt='{&#92;epsilon &gt; 0}' title='{&#92;epsilon &gt; 0}' class='latex' /> be fixed. For <img src='http://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7B%7Ch%7C+%5Cgeq+x%5E%5Cepsilon+q+%2F+N%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0' alt='{|h| &#92;geq x^&#92;epsilon q / N}' title='{|h| &#92;geq x^&#92;epsilon q / N}' class='latex' /> the bound is trivial from <a href="#psint">(15)</a> (for <img src='http://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7Bj%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0' alt='{j}' title='{j}' class='latex' /> large enough), so by overspill it will suffice to show that <p align="center"><img src='http://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%5Cdisplaystyle++%5Cfrac%7B1%7D%7Bq%7D+%5Csum_%7B1+%5Cleq+%7Ch%7C+%5Cleq+x%5E%5Cepsilon+q%2FN%7D+%7C%5Chat+%5Cpsi_N%28%5Cfrac%7Bh%7D%7Bq%7D%29%7C+%7C%5Csum_%7Bn+%5Cin+%7B%5Cbf+Z%7D%2Fq%7B%5Cbf+Z%7D%7D+e_q%28f%28n%29+%2B+hn%29%7C+%5Clessapprox+x%5E%7B%5Cepsilon%7D+q%5E%7B1%2F2%7D.&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0' alt='&#92;displaystyle &#92;frac{1}{q} &#92;sum_{1 &#92;leq |h| &#92;leq x^&#92;epsilon q/N} |&#92;hat &#92;psi_N(&#92;frac{h}{q})| |&#92;sum_{n &#92;in {&#92;bf Z}/q{&#92;bf Z}} e_q(f(n) + hn)| &#92;lessapprox x^{&#92;epsilon} q^{1/2}.' title='&#92;displaystyle &#92;frac{1}{q} &#92;sum_{1 &#92;leq |h| &#92;leq x^&#92;epsilon q/N} |&#92;hat &#92;psi_N(&#92;frac{h}{q})| |&#92;sum_{n &#92;in {&#92;bf Z}/q{&#92;bf Z}} e_q(f(n) + hn)| &#92;lessapprox x^{&#92;epsilon} q^{1/2}.' class='latex' /></p> <p> By Proposition <a href="#weil">4</a> and <a href="#psint">(15)</a>, the left-hand side is </p> <p align="center"><img src='http://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%5Cdisplaystyle++%5Clessapprox+%5Cfrac%7B1%7D%7Bq%7D+%5Csum_%7B1+%5Cleq+%7Ch%7C+%5Cleq+x%5E%5Cepsilon+q%2FN%7D+N+q%5E%7B1%2F2%7D+%5Cfrac%7B%28f%27%2Bh%2Cq%29%7D%7B%28f%27%27%2Cq%29%5E%7B1%2F2%7D%7D.&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0' alt='&#92;displaystyle &#92;lessapprox &#92;frac{1}{q} &#92;sum_{1 &#92;leq |h| &#92;leq x^&#92;epsilon q/N} N q^{1/2} &#92;frac{(f&#039;+h,q)}{(f&#039;&#039;,q)^{1/2}}.' title='&#92;displaystyle &#92;lessapprox &#92;frac{1}{q} &#92;sum_{1 &#92;leq |h| &#92;leq x^&#92;epsilon q/N} N q^{1/2} &#92;frac{(f&#039;+h,q)}{(f&#039;&#039;,q)^{1/2}}.' class='latex' /></p> <p> Writing <img src='http://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7B%28f%27%2Bh%2Cq%29+%5Cleq+%5Csum_%7Bd%7Cq%7D+d+1_%7Bd%7Cf%27%2Bh%7D%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0' alt='{(f&#039;+h,q) &#92;leq &#92;sum_{d|q} d 1_{d|f&#039;+h}}' title='{(f&#039;+h,q) &#92;leq &#92;sum_{d|q} d 1_{d|f&#039;+h}}' class='latex' />, we may bound the previous expression by <p align="center"><img src='http://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%5Cdisplaystyle++%5Clessapprox+%5Cfrac%7BN%7D%7Bq%5E%7B1%2F2%7D+%28f%27%27%2Cq%29%5E%7B1%2F2%7D%7D+%5Csum_%7Bd%7Cq%7D+d+%5Csum_%7B1+%5Cleq+%7Ch%7C+%5Cleq+x%5E%5Cepsilon+q%2FN%3A+d%7Cf%27%2Bh%7D+1.&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0' alt='&#92;displaystyle &#92;lessapprox &#92;frac{N}{q^{1/2} (f&#039;&#039;,q)^{1/2}} &#92;sum_{d|q} d &#92;sum_{1 &#92;leq |h| &#92;leq x^&#92;epsilon q/N: d|f&#039;+h} 1.' title='&#92;displaystyle &#92;lessapprox &#92;frac{N}{q^{1/2} (f&#039;&#039;,q)^{1/2}} &#92;sum_{d|q} d &#92;sum_{1 &#92;leq |h| &#92;leq x^&#92;epsilon q/N: d|f&#039;+h} 1.' class='latex' /></p> <p> Since <p align="center"><img src='http://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%5Cdisplaystyle++f%27%28t%29+%3D+-+%5Cfrac%7Bc_1+d%27_2%7D%7Bt%5E2%7D+-+%5Cfrac%7Bc_2+d%27_1%7D%7B%28t%2Bl%29%5E2%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0' alt='&#92;displaystyle f&#039;(t) = - &#92;frac{c_1 d&#039;_2}{t^2} - &#92;frac{c_2 d&#039;_1}{(t+l)^2}' title='&#92;displaystyle f&#039;(t) = - &#92;frac{c_1 d&#039;_2}{t^2} - &#92;frac{c_2 d&#039;_1}{(t+l)^2}' class='latex' /></p> <p> vanishes at infinity, we see that <img src='http://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7Bd%7Cf%27%2Bh%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0' alt='{d|f&#039;+h}' title='{d|f&#039;+h}' class='latex' /> implies <img src='http://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7Bd%7Ch%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0' alt='{d|h}' title='{d|h}' class='latex' />. Thus <p align="center"><img src='http://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%5Cdisplaystyle++%5Csum_%7B1+%5Cleq+%7Ch%7C+%5Cleq+x%5E%5Cepsilon+q%2FN%3A+d%7Cf%27%2Bh%7D+1+%5Cll+%5Cfrac%7Bx%5E%5Cepsilon+q%2FN%7D%7Bd%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0' alt='&#92;displaystyle &#92;sum_{1 &#92;leq |h| &#92;leq x^&#92;epsilon q/N: d|f&#039;+h} 1 &#92;ll &#92;frac{x^&#92;epsilon q/N}{d}' title='&#92;displaystyle &#92;sum_{1 &#92;leq |h| &#92;leq x^&#92;epsilon q/N: d|f&#039;+h} 1 &#92;ll &#92;frac{x^&#92;epsilon q/N}{d}' class='latex' /></p> <p> and hence by the divisor bound <p align="center"><img src='http://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%5Cdisplaystyle++%5Csum_%7Bd%7Cq%7D+d+%5Csum_%7B1+%5Cleq+%7Ch%7C+%5Cleq+x%5E%5Cepsilon+q%2FN%3A+d%7Cf%27%2Bh%7D+1+%5Clessapprox+x%5E%5Cepsilon+q%2FN&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0' alt='&#92;displaystyle &#92;sum_{d|q} d &#92;sum_{1 &#92;leq |h| &#92;leq x^&#92;epsilon q/N: d|f&#039;+h} 1 &#92;lessapprox x^&#92;epsilon q/N' title='&#92;displaystyle &#92;sum_{d|q} d &#92;sum_{1 &#92;leq |h| &#92;leq x^&#92;epsilon q/N: d|f&#039;+h} 1 &#92;lessapprox x^&#92;epsilon q/N' class='latex' /></p> <p> and the claim follows.</p> <p> Now we prove <a href="#goo">(12)</a>. We first observe that if <img src='http://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7BN+%3C+d_2%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0' alt='{N &lt; d_2}' title='{N &lt; d_2}' class='latex' />, then <img src='http://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7BN+%3C+N%5E%7B1%2F2%7D+d_2%5E%7B1%2F2%7D%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0' alt='{N &lt; N^{1/2} d_2^{1/2}}' title='{N &lt; N^{1/2} d_2^{1/2}}' class='latex' /> and the claim <a href="#goo">(12)</a> follows already from the trivial bound <a href="#trivial">(10)</a>. Similarly, if <img src='http://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7BN+%3E+d%27_1%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0' alt='{N &gt; d&#039;_1}' title='{N &gt; d&#039;_1}' class='latex' />, then <img src='http://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7BN%5E%7B1%2F2%7D+d_2%5E%7B1%2F2%7D+%3E+%5Bd_1%2Cd_2%5D%5E%7B1%2F2%7D%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0' alt='{N^{1/2} d_2^{1/2} &gt; [d_1,d_2]^{1/2}}' title='{N^{1/2} d_2^{1/2} &gt; [d_1,d_2]^{1/2}}' class='latex' /> and also </p> <p align="center"><img src='http://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%5Cdisplaystyle++%5Cfrac%7B%28c_1%2Cd%27_1%29%5E%7B1%2F4%7D%7D%7B%28d%27_1%29%5E%7B1%2F4%7D%7D+N+%5Cgeq+N+%5Cfrac%7B%28c_1%2Cd%27_1%29%7D%7Bd%27_1%7D+%5Cgeq+%5Cfrac%7BN%7D%7Bd_1+d_2%7D+%28d_1%2Cd_2%29%5E2+%28c_1%2Cd%27_1%29+%28c_2%2Cd%27_2%29&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0' alt='&#92;displaystyle &#92;frac{(c_1,d&#039;_1)^{1/4}}{(d&#039;_1)^{1/4}} N &#92;geq N &#92;frac{(c_1,d&#039;_1)}{d&#039;_1} &#92;geq &#92;frac{N}{d_1 d_2} (d_1,d_2)^2 (c_1,d&#039;_1) (c_2,d&#039;_2)' title='&#92;displaystyle &#92;frac{(c_1,d&#039;_1)^{1/4}}{(d&#039;_1)^{1/4}} N &#92;geq N &#92;frac{(c_1,d&#039;_1)}{d&#039;_1} &#92;geq &#92;frac{N}{d_1 d_2} (d_1,d_2)^2 (c_1,d&#039;_1) (c_2,d&#039;_2)' class='latex' /></p> <p> so <a href="#goo">(12)</a> follows from <a href="#loo">(11)</a> in this case. Thus we may restrict attention to the regime <p align="center"><img src='http://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%5Cdisplaystyle++d_2+%5Cleq+N+%5Cleq+d%27_1.&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0' alt='&#92;displaystyle d_2 &#92;leq N &#92;leq d&#039;_1.' title='&#92;displaystyle d_2 &#92;leq N &#92;leq d&#039;_1.' class='latex' /></p> <p> As before, we can rewrite <img src='http://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7B%5Csum_n+%5Cpsi_N%28n%29+e_q%28f%28n%29%29%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0' alt='{&#92;sum_n &#92;psi_N(n) e_q(f(n))}' title='{&#92;sum_n &#92;psi_N(n) e_q(f(n))}' class='latex' /> as <a href="#hq">(14)</a>. Now set <a name="K-def"> <p align="center"><img src='http://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%5Cdisplaystyle++K+%3A%3D+%5Clfloor+%5Cfrac%7Bd%27_1%7D%7BN%7D+%5Crfloor%2C+%5C+%5C+%5C+%5C+%5C+%2816%29&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0' alt='&#92;displaystyle K := &#92;lfloor &#92;frac{d&#039;_1}{N} &#92;rfloor, &#92; &#92; &#92; &#92; &#92; (16)' title='&#92;displaystyle K := &#92;lfloor &#92;frac{d&#039;_1}{N} &#92;rfloor, &#92; &#92; &#92; &#92; &#92; (16)' class='latex' /></p> <p></a> so <img src='http://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7BK+%5Cgeq+1%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0' alt='{K &#92;geq 1}' title='{K &#92;geq 1}' class='latex' />. Shifting <img src='http://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7Bh%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0' alt='{h}' title='{h}' class='latex' /> by <img src='http://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7Bd_2k%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0' alt='{d_2k}' title='{d_2k}' class='latex' /> for <img src='http://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7Bk%3D1%2C%5Cldots%2CK%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0' alt='{k=1,&#92;ldots,K}' title='{k=1,&#92;ldots,K}' class='latex' /> and averaging, we may then rewrite <a href="#hq">(14)</a> as <p align="center"><img src='http://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%5Cdisplaystyle++%5Cfrac%7B1%7D%7BqK%7D+%5Csum_%7Bh+%5Cin+%7B%5Cbf+Z%7D%2Fq%7B%5Cbf+Z%7D%7D+%5Csum_%7Bk%3D1%7D%5EK+%5Chat+%5Cpsi_N%28%5Cfrac%7Bh%2Bd_2k%7D%7Bq%7D%29+%5Csum_%7Bn+%5Cin+%7B%5Cbf+Z%7D%2Fq%7B%5Cbf+Z%7D%7D+e_q%28f%28n%29+%2B+hn+%2B+knd_2%29.&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0' alt='&#92;displaystyle &#92;frac{1}{qK} &#92;sum_{h &#92;in {&#92;bf Z}/q{&#92;bf Z}} &#92;sum_{k=1}^K &#92;hat &#92;psi_N(&#92;frac{h+d_2k}{q}) &#92;sum_{n &#92;in {&#92;bf Z}/q{&#92;bf Z}} e_q(f(n) + hn + knd_2).' title='&#92;displaystyle &#92;frac{1}{qK} &#92;sum_{h &#92;in {&#92;bf Z}/q{&#92;bf Z}} &#92;sum_{k=1}^K &#92;hat &#92;psi_N(&#92;frac{h+d_2k}{q}) &#92;sum_{n &#92;in {&#92;bf Z}/q{&#92;bf Z}} e_q(f(n) + hn + knd_2).' class='latex' /></p> <p> From Lemma <a href="#crt">2</a>, we have <p align="center"><img src='http://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%5Cdisplaystyle++%5Csum_%7Bn+%5Cin+%7B%5Cbf+Z%7D%2Fq%7B%5Cbf+Z%7D%7D+e_q%28f%28n%29+%2B+hn+%2B+knd_2%29+%3D+%28%5Csum_%7Bn_1+%5Cin+%7B%5Cbf+Z%7D%2Fd_2%7B%5Cbf+Z%7D%7D+e_%7Bd_2%7D%28f%28n_1%29%2Fd%27_1+%2B+hn_1%2Fd%27_1%29%29&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0' alt='&#92;displaystyle &#92;sum_{n &#92;in {&#92;bf Z}/q{&#92;bf Z}} e_q(f(n) + hn + knd_2) = (&#92;sum_{n_1 &#92;in {&#92;bf Z}/d_2{&#92;bf Z}} e_{d_2}(f(n_1)/d&#039;_1 + hn_1/d&#039;_1))' title='&#92;displaystyle &#92;sum_{n &#92;in {&#92;bf Z}/q{&#92;bf Z}} e_q(f(n) + hn + knd_2) = (&#92;sum_{n_1 &#92;in {&#92;bf Z}/d_2{&#92;bf Z}} e_{d_2}(f(n_1)/d&#039;_1 + hn_1/d&#039;_1))' class='latex' /></p> <p align="center"><img src='http://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%5Cdisplaystyle++%28%5Csum_%7Bn_2+%5Cin+%7B%5Cbf+Z%7D%2Fd%27_1%7B%5Cbf+Z%7D%7D+e_%7Bd%27_1%7D%28f%28n_2%29%2Fd_2+%2B+hn_2%2Fd_2+%2B+kn_2%29%29&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0' alt='&#92;displaystyle (&#92;sum_{n_2 &#92;in {&#92;bf Z}/d&#039;_1{&#92;bf Z}} e_{d&#039;_1}(f(n_2)/d_2 + hn_2/d_2 + kn_2))' title='&#92;displaystyle (&#92;sum_{n_2 &#92;in {&#92;bf Z}/d&#039;_1{&#92;bf Z}} e_{d&#039;_1}(f(n_2)/d_2 + hn_2/d_2 + kn_2))' class='latex' /></p> <p> and so we may bound <img src='http://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7B%7C%5Csum_n+%5Cpsi_N%28n%29+e_q%28f%28n%29%29%7C%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0' alt='{|&#92;sum_n &#92;psi_N(n) e_q(f(n))|}' title='{|&#92;sum_n &#92;psi_N(n) e_q(f(n))|}' class='latex' /> by <p align="center"><img src='http://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%5Cdisplaystyle++%5Cfrac%7B1%7D%7BqK%7D+%5Csum_%7Bh+%5Cin+%7B%5Cbf+Z%7D%2Fq%7B%5Cbf+Z%7D%7D+%7C%5Csum_%7Bn_1+%5Cin+%7B%5Cbf+Z%7D%2Fd_2%7B%5Cbf+Z%7D%7D+e_%7Bd_2%7D%28f%28n_1%29%2Fd%27_1+%2B+hn_1%2Fd%27_1%29%7C+&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0' alt='&#92;displaystyle &#92;frac{1}{qK} &#92;sum_{h &#92;in {&#92;bf Z}/q{&#92;bf Z}} |&#92;sum_{n_1 &#92;in {&#92;bf Z}/d_2{&#92;bf Z}} e_{d_2}(f(n_1)/d&#039;_1 + hn_1/d&#039;_1)| ' title='&#92;displaystyle &#92;frac{1}{qK} &#92;sum_{h &#92;in {&#92;bf Z}/q{&#92;bf Z}} |&#92;sum_{n_1 &#92;in {&#92;bf Z}/d_2{&#92;bf Z}} e_{d_2}(f(n_1)/d&#039;_1 + hn_1/d&#039;_1)| ' class='latex' /></p> <p align="center"><img src='http://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%5Cdisplaystyle++%7C%5Csum_%7Bk%3D1%7D%5EK+%5Chat+%5Cpsi_N%28%5Cfrac%7Bh%2Bd_2k%7D%7Bq%7D%29+%5Csum_%7Bn_2+%5Cin+%7B%5Cbf+Z%7D%2Fd%27_1%7B%5Cbf+Z%7D%7D+e_%7Bd%27_1%7D%28f%28n_2%29%2Fd_2+%2B+hn_2%2Fd_2+%2B+kn_2%29%7C.&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0' alt='&#92;displaystyle |&#92;sum_{k=1}^K &#92;hat &#92;psi_N(&#92;frac{h+d_2k}{q}) &#92;sum_{n_2 &#92;in {&#92;bf Z}/d&#039;_1{&#92;bf Z}} e_{d&#039;_1}(f(n_2)/d_2 + hn_2/d_2 + kn_2)|.' title='&#92;displaystyle |&#92;sum_{k=1}^K &#92;hat &#92;psi_N(&#92;frac{h+d_2k}{q}) &#92;sum_{n_2 &#92;in {&#92;bf Z}/d&#039;_1{&#92;bf Z}} e_{d&#039;_1}(f(n_2)/d_2 + hn_2/d_2 + kn_2)|.' class='latex' /></p> <p> By Proposition <a href="#weil">4</a> (and the coprimality of <img src='http://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7Bd_2%2Cd%27_1%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0' alt='{d_2,d&#039;_1}' title='{d_2,d&#039;_1}' class='latex' />), we have </p> <p align="center"><img src='http://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%5Cdisplaystyle++%7C%5Csum_%7Bn_1+%5Cin+%7B%5Cbf+Z%7D%2Fd_2%7B%5Cbf+Z%7D%7D+e_%7Bd_2%7D%28f%28n_1%29%2Fd%27_1+%2B+hn_1%2Fd%27_1%29%7C+%5Clessapprox+d_2%5E%7B1%2F2%7D+%28f%27%2Bh%2Cd_2%29+%28f%27%27%2Cd_2%29%5E%7B-1%2F2%7D.&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0' alt='&#92;displaystyle |&#92;sum_{n_1 &#92;in {&#92;bf Z}/d_2{&#92;bf Z}} e_{d_2}(f(n_1)/d&#039;_1 + hn_1/d&#039;_1)| &#92;lessapprox d_2^{1/2} (f&#039;+h,d_2) (f&#039;&#039;,d_2)^{-1/2}.' title='&#92;displaystyle |&#92;sum_{n_1 &#92;in {&#92;bf Z}/d_2{&#92;bf Z}} e_{d_2}(f(n_1)/d&#039;_1 + hn_1/d&#039;_1)| &#92;lessapprox d_2^{1/2} (f&#039;+h,d_2) (f&#039;&#039;,d_2)^{-1/2}.' class='latex' /></p> <p> Thus we may bound the previous expression by <p align="center"><img src='http://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%5Cdisplaystyle++%5Clessapprox+%5Cfrac%7B1%7D%7Bd_2%5E%7B1%2F2%7D+%28f%27%27%2Cd_2%29%5E%7B1%2F2%7D+d%27_1+K%7D+%5Csum_%7Bh+%5Cin%7B%5Cbf+Z%7D%2Fq%7B%5Cbf+Z%7D%7D+%28f%27%2Bh%2Cd_2%29&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0' alt='&#92;displaystyle &#92;lessapprox &#92;frac{1}{d_2^{1/2} (f&#039;&#039;,d_2)^{1/2} d&#039;_1 K} &#92;sum_{h &#92;in{&#92;bf Z}/q{&#92;bf Z}} (f&#039;+h,d_2)' title='&#92;displaystyle &#92;lessapprox &#92;frac{1}{d_2^{1/2} (f&#039;&#039;,d_2)^{1/2} d&#039;_1 K} &#92;sum_{h &#92;in{&#92;bf Z}/q{&#92;bf Z}} (f&#039;+h,d_2)' class='latex' /></p> <p align="center"><img src='http://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%5Cdisplaystyle++%7C%5Csum_%7Bk%3D1%7D%5EK+%5Chat+%5Cpsi_N%28%5Cfrac%7Bh%2Bd_2k%7D%7Bq%7D%29+%5Csum_%7Bn_2+%5Cin+%7B%5Cbf+Z%7D%2Fd%27_1%7B%5Cbf+Z%7D%7D+e_%7Bd%27_1%7D%28f%28n_2%29%2Fd_2+%2B+hn_2%2Fd_2+%2B+kn_2%29%7C.&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0' alt='&#92;displaystyle |&#92;sum_{k=1}^K &#92;hat &#92;psi_N(&#92;frac{h+d_2k}{q}) &#92;sum_{n_2 &#92;in {&#92;bf Z}/d&#039;_1{&#92;bf Z}} e_{d&#039;_1}(f(n_2)/d_2 + hn_2/d_2 + kn_2)|.' title='&#92;displaystyle |&#92;sum_{k=1}^K &#92;hat &#92;psi_N(&#92;frac{h+d_2k}{q}) &#92;sum_{n_2 &#92;in {&#92;bf Z}/d&#039;_1{&#92;bf Z}} e_{d&#039;_1}(f(n_2)/d_2 + hn_2/d_2 + kn_2)|.' class='latex' /></p> <p> Next, let <img src='http://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7B%5Cepsilon%3E0%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0' alt='{&#92;epsilon&gt;0}' title='{&#92;epsilon&gt;0}' class='latex' /> be a small fixed quantity. By <a href="#psint">(15)</a> as before, the contribution of those <img src='http://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7Bh%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0' alt='{h}' title='{h}' class='latex' /> outside of the interval <img src='http://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7B%5B-x%5E%5Cepsilon+q%2FN%2C+x%5E%5Cepsilon+q%2FN%5D%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0' alt='{[-x^&#92;epsilon q/N, x^&#92;epsilon q/N]}' title='{[-x^&#92;epsilon q/N, x^&#92;epsilon q/N]}' class='latex' /> is negligible, so it will suffice to show that <a name="major"> <p align="center"><img src='http://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%5Cdisplaystyle++%5Cfrac%7B1%7D%7Bd_2%5E%7B1%2F2%7D+%28f%27%27%2Cd_2%29%5E%7B1%2F2%7D+d%27_1+K%7D+%5Csum_%7B%7Ch%7C+%5Cleq+x%5E%5Cepsilon+q%2FN%7D+%28f%27%2Bh%2Cd_2%29+%5C+%5C+%5C+%5C+%5C+%2817%29&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0' alt='&#92;displaystyle &#92;frac{1}{d_2^{1/2} (f&#039;&#039;,d_2)^{1/2} d&#039;_1 K} &#92;sum_{|h| &#92;leq x^&#92;epsilon q/N} (f&#039;+h,d_2) &#92; &#92; &#92; &#92; &#92; (17)' title='&#92;displaystyle &#92;frac{1}{d_2^{1/2} (f&#039;&#039;,d_2)^{1/2} d&#039;_1 K} &#92;sum_{|h| &#92;leq x^&#92;epsilon q/N} (f&#039;+h,d_2) &#92; &#92; &#92; &#92; &#92; (17)' class='latex' /></p> <p></a> <p align="center"><img src='http://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%5Cdisplaystyle++%7C%5Csum_%7Bk%3D1%7D%5EK+%5Chat+%5Cpsi_N%28%5Cfrac%7Bh%2Bd_2k%7D%7Bq%7D%29+%5Csum_%7Bn_2+%5Cin+%7B%5Cbf+Z%7D%2Fd%27_1%7B%5Cbf+Z%7D%7D+e_%7Bd%27_1%7D%28f%28n_2%29%2Fd_2+%2B+hn_2%2Fd_2+%2B+kn_2%29%7C+%5Clessapprox&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0' alt='&#92;displaystyle |&#92;sum_{k=1}^K &#92;hat &#92;psi_N(&#92;frac{h+d_2k}{q}) &#92;sum_{n_2 &#92;in {&#92;bf Z}/d&#039;_1{&#92;bf Z}} e_{d&#039;_1}(f(n_2)/d_2 + hn_2/d_2 + kn_2)| &#92;lessapprox' title='&#92;displaystyle |&#92;sum_{k=1}^K &#92;hat &#92;psi_N(&#92;frac{h+d_2k}{q}) &#92;sum_{n_2 &#92;in {&#92;bf Z}/d&#039;_1{&#92;bf Z}} e_{d&#039;_1}(f(n_2)/d_2 + hn_2/d_2 + kn_2)| &#92;lessapprox' class='latex' /></p> <p align="center"><img src='http://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%5Cdisplaystyle++x%5E%7B%5Cepsilon%7D+%28N%5E%7B1%2F2%7D+%28d%27_1%29%5E%7B1%2F4%7D+%2B+N%5E%7B1%2F2%7D+d_2%5E%7B1%2F2%7D+%2B+%5Cfrac%7B%28c_1%2Cd%27_1%29%5E%7B1%2F4%7D%7D%7B%28d%27_1%29%5E%7B1%2F4%7D%7D+N%29.&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0' alt='&#92;displaystyle x^{&#92;epsilon} (N^{1/2} (d&#039;_1)^{1/4} + N^{1/2} d_2^{1/2} + &#92;frac{(c_1,d&#039;_1)^{1/4}}{(d&#039;_1)^{1/4}} N).' title='&#92;displaystyle x^{&#92;epsilon} (N^{1/2} (d&#039;_1)^{1/4} + N^{1/2} d_2^{1/2} + &#92;frac{(c_1,d&#039;_1)^{1/4}}{(d&#039;_1)^{1/4}} N).' class='latex' /></p> <p> Now let us consider the sum <a name="shoo"> <p align="center"><img src='http://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%5Cdisplaystyle++%5Csum_%7B%7Ch%7C+%5Cleq+x%5E%5Cepsilon+q%2FN%7D+%28f%27%2Bh%2Cd_2%29%5E2.+%5C+%5C+%5C+%5C+%5C+%2818%29&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0' alt='&#92;displaystyle &#92;sum_{|h| &#92;leq x^&#92;epsilon q/N} (f&#039;+h,d_2)^2. &#92; &#92; &#92; &#92; &#92; (18)' title='&#92;displaystyle &#92;sum_{|h| &#92;leq x^&#92;epsilon q/N} (f&#039;+h,d_2)^2. &#92; &#92; &#92; &#92; &#92; (18)' class='latex' /></p> <p></a> Bounding <img src='http://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7B%28f%27%2Bh%2Cd_2%29%5E2+%5Cleq+%5Csum_%7Bd%7Cd_2%7D+d%5E2+1_%7Bd%7Cf%27%2Bh%7D%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0' alt='{(f&#039;+h,d_2)^2 &#92;leq &#92;sum_{d|d_2} d^2 1_{d|f&#039;+h}}' title='{(f&#039;+h,d_2)^2 &#92;leq &#92;sum_{d|d_2} d^2 1_{d|f&#039;+h}}' class='latex' />, we may bound this sum by </p> <p align="center"><img src='http://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%5Cdisplaystyle++%5Cll+%5Csum_%7Bd%7Cd_2%7D+d%5E2+%5Csum_%7B%7Ch%7C+%5Cleq+x%5E%5Cepsilon+q%2FN%3A+d%7Cf%27%2Bh%7D+1.&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0' alt='&#92;displaystyle &#92;ll &#92;sum_{d|d_2} d^2 &#92;sum_{|h| &#92;leq x^&#92;epsilon q/N: d|f&#039;+h} 1.' title='&#92;displaystyle &#92;ll &#92;sum_{d|d_2} d^2 &#92;sum_{|h| &#92;leq x^&#92;epsilon q/N: d|f&#039;+h} 1.' class='latex' /></p> <p> The inner sum is only non-vanishing when <img src='http://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7Bd+%7C+%28f%27%27%2Cd_2%29%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0' alt='{d | (f&#039;&#039;,d_2)}' title='{d | (f&#039;&#039;,d_2)}' class='latex' />, and in that case we have a bound of <img src='http://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7BO%28+%5Cfrac%7Bx%5E%5Cepsilon+q%2FN%7D%7Bd%7D+%2B+1+%29%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0' alt='{O( &#92;frac{x^&#92;epsilon q/N}{d} + 1 )}' title='{O( &#92;frac{x^&#92;epsilon q/N}{d} + 1 )}' class='latex' /> as in the proof of <a href="#loo">(11)</a>; note that <p align="center"><img src='http://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%5Cdisplaystyle+%5Cfrac%7Bx%5E%5Cepsilon+q%2FN%7D%7Bd%7D+%5Cgeq+%5Cfrac%7Bq%7D%7BN+d_2%7D+%5Cgeq+%5Cfrac%7B%5Bd_1%2Cd_2%5D%7D%7Bd%27_1+d_2%7D+%3D+1%2C&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0' alt='&#92;displaystyle &#92;frac{x^&#92;epsilon q/N}{d} &#92;geq &#92;frac{q}{N d_2} &#92;geq &#92;frac{[d_1,d_2]}{d&#039;_1 d_2} = 1,' title='&#92;displaystyle &#92;frac{x^&#92;epsilon q/N}{d} &#92;geq &#92;frac{q}{N d_2} &#92;geq &#92;frac{[d_1,d_2]}{d&#039;_1 d_2} = 1,' class='latex' /></p> <p> so we may replace <img src='http://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7BO%28+%5Cfrac%7Bx%5E%5Cepsilon+q%2FN%7D%7Bd%7D+%2B+1+%29%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0' alt='{O( &#92;frac{x^&#92;epsilon q/N}{d} + 1 )}' title='{O( &#92;frac{x^&#92;epsilon q/N}{d} + 1 )}' class='latex' /> by <img src='http://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7BO%28+%5Cfrac%7Bx%5E%5Cepsilon+q%2FN%7D%7Bd%7D+%29%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0' alt='{O( &#92;frac{x^&#92;epsilon q/N}{d} )}' title='{O( &#92;frac{x^&#92;epsilon q/N}{d} )}' class='latex' />. By the divisor bound we may thus bound <a href="#shoo">(18)</a> by <p align="center"><img src='http://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%5Cdisplaystyle++%5Clessapprox+x%5E%5Cepsilon+%28f%27%27%2Cd_2%29+%5Cfrac%7Bq%7D%7BN%7D.&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0' alt='&#92;displaystyle &#92;lessapprox x^&#92;epsilon (f&#039;&#039;,d_2) &#92;frac{q}{N}.' title='&#92;displaystyle &#92;lessapprox x^&#92;epsilon (f&#039;&#039;,d_2) &#92;frac{q}{N}.' class='latex' /></p> <p> By Cauchy-Schwarz, we may thus bound the left-hand side of <a href="#major">(17)</a> by <a name="minor"> <p align="center"><img src='http://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%5Cdisplaystyle++%5Clessapprox+x%5E%5Cepsilon+%5Cfrac%7B1%7D%7B%28d%27_1%29%5E%7B1%2F2%7D+N%5E%7B1%2F2%7D+K%7D+%7CX%7C%5E%7B1%2F2%7D+%5C+%5C+%5C+%5C+%5C+%2819%29&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0' alt='&#92;displaystyle &#92;lessapprox x^&#92;epsilon &#92;frac{1}{(d&#039;_1)^{1/2} N^{1/2} K} |X|^{1/2} &#92; &#92; &#92; &#92; &#92; (19)' title='&#92;displaystyle &#92;lessapprox x^&#92;epsilon &#92;frac{1}{(d&#039;_1)^{1/2} N^{1/2} K} |X|^{1/2} &#92; &#92; &#92; &#92; &#92; (19)' class='latex' /></p> <p></a> where <img src='http://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7BX%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0' alt='{X}' title='{X}' class='latex' /> is the quantity <p align="center"><img src='http://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%5Cdisplaystyle++X+%3A%3D+%5Csum_%7Bh+%5Cin+%7B%5Cbf+Z%7D%2Fq%7B%5Cbf+Z%7D%7D+%7C%5Csum_%7Bk%3D1%7D%5EK+%5Chat+%5Cpsi_N%28%5Cfrac%7Bh%2Bd_2k%7D%7Bq%7D%29+%5Csum_%7Bn_2+%5Cin+%7B%5Cbf+Z%7D%2Fd%27_1%7B%5Cbf+Z%7D%7D+e_%7Bd%27_1%7D%28f%28n_2%29%2Fd_2+%2B+hn_2%2Fd_2+%2B+kn_2%29%7C%5E2.&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0' alt='&#92;displaystyle X := &#92;sum_{h &#92;in {&#92;bf Z}/q{&#92;bf Z}} |&#92;sum_{k=1}^K &#92;hat &#92;psi_N(&#92;frac{h+d_2k}{q}) &#92;sum_{n_2 &#92;in {&#92;bf Z}/d&#039;_1{&#92;bf Z}} e_{d&#039;_1}(f(n_2)/d_2 + hn_2/d_2 + kn_2)|^2.' title='&#92;displaystyle X := &#92;sum_{h &#92;in {&#92;bf Z}/q{&#92;bf Z}} |&#92;sum_{k=1}^K &#92;hat &#92;psi_N(&#92;frac{h+d_2k}{q}) &#92;sum_{n_2 &#92;in {&#92;bf Z}/d&#039;_1{&#92;bf Z}} e_{d&#039;_1}(f(n_2)/d_2 + hn_2/d_2 + kn_2)|^2.' class='latex' /></p> <p> We may square <img src='http://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7BX%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0' alt='{X}' title='{X}' class='latex' /> out as <p align="center"><img src='http://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%5Cdisplaystyle++X+%3D+%5Csum_%7B1+%5Cleq+k%2C+k%27+%5Cleq+K%7D+%5Csum_%7Bn%2Cn%27%7D+%5Cpsi_N%28n%29+%5Coverline%7B%5Cpsi_N%28n%27%29%7D+%5Csum_%7Bn_2%2Cn%27_2+%5Cin+%7B%5Cbf+Z%7D%2Fd%27_1%7B%5Cbf+Z%7D%7D+%5Csum_%7Bh+%5Cin%7B%5Cbf+Z%7D%2Fq%7B%5Cbf+Z%7D%7D+&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0' alt='&#92;displaystyle X = &#92;sum_{1 &#92;leq k, k&#039; &#92;leq K} &#92;sum_{n,n&#039;} &#92;psi_N(n) &#92;overline{&#92;psi_N(n&#039;)} &#92;sum_{n_2,n&#039;_2 &#92;in {&#92;bf Z}/d&#039;_1{&#92;bf Z}} &#92;sum_{h &#92;in{&#92;bf Z}/q{&#92;bf Z}} ' title='&#92;displaystyle X = &#92;sum_{1 &#92;leq k, k&#039; &#92;leq K} &#92;sum_{n,n&#039;} &#92;psi_N(n) &#92;overline{&#92;psi_N(n&#039;)} &#92;sum_{n_2,n&#039;_2 &#92;in {&#92;bf Z}/d&#039;_1{&#92;bf Z}} &#92;sum_{h &#92;in{&#92;bf Z}/q{&#92;bf Z}} ' class='latex' /></p> <p align="center"><img src='http://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%5Cdisplaystyle++e_%7Bd%27_1%7D%28f%28n_2%29%2Fd_2+%2B+hn_2%2Fd_2+%2B+kn_2+-+f%28n%27_2%29%2Fd_2+-+hn%27_2%2Fd_2+-+k%27n%27_2%29&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0' alt='&#92;displaystyle e_{d&#039;_1}(f(n_2)/d_2 + hn_2/d_2 + kn_2 - f(n&#039;_2)/d_2 - hn&#039;_2/d_2 - k&#039;n&#039;_2)' title='&#92;displaystyle e_{d&#039;_1}(f(n_2)/d_2 + hn_2/d_2 + kn_2 - f(n&#039;_2)/d_2 - hn&#039;_2/d_2 - k&#039;n&#039;_2)' class='latex' /></p> <p align="center"><img src='http://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%5Cdisplaystyle++e_q%28+h+n%27+-+h+n+%29+e_%7Bd%27_1%7D%28k%27n%27+-+kn%29.&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0' alt='&#92;displaystyle e_q( h n&#039; - h n ) e_{d&#039;_1}(k&#039;n&#039; - kn).' title='&#92;displaystyle e_q( h n&#039; - h n ) e_{d&#039;_1}(k&#039;n&#039; - kn).' class='latex' /></p> <p> Now observe from Fourier analysis that the sum <p align="center"><img src='http://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%5Cdisplaystyle++%5Csum_%7Bh+%5Cin+%7B%5Cbf+Z%7D%2Fq%7B%5Cbf+Z%7D%7D+e_%7Bd%27_1%7D%28+hn_2%2Fd_2+-+hn%27_2%2Fd_2+%29+e_q%28hn%27+-+hn%29&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0' alt='&#92;displaystyle &#92;sum_{h &#92;in {&#92;bf Z}/q{&#92;bf Z}} e_{d&#039;_1}( hn_2/d_2 - hn&#039;_2/d_2 ) e_q(hn&#039; - hn)' title='&#92;displaystyle &#92;sum_{h &#92;in {&#92;bf Z}/q{&#92;bf Z}} e_{d&#039;_1}( hn_2/d_2 - hn&#039;_2/d_2 ) e_q(hn&#039; - hn)' class='latex' /></p> <p> equals <img src='http://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7Bq%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0' alt='{q}' title='{q}' class='latex' /> when <img src='http://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7Bn%3Dn%27%5C+%28d_2%29%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0' alt='{n=n&#039;&#92; (d_2)}' title='{n=n&#039;&#92; (d_2)}' class='latex' /> and <img src='http://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7Bn-n%27+%3D+n_2-n%27_2%5C+%28d%27_1%29%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0' alt='{n-n&#039; = n_2-n&#039;_2&#92; (d&#039;_1)}' title='{n-n&#039; = n_2-n&#039;_2&#92; (d&#039;_1)}' class='latex' />, and vanishes otherwise. Thus we may simplify the above expression as <p align="center"><img src='http://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%5Cdisplaystyle++X+%3D+q%5Csum_%7B1+%5Cleq+k.+k%27+%5Cleq+K%7D+%5Csum_%7Bn%2Cn%27%3A+n%3Dn%27%5C+%28d_2%29%7D+%5Cpsi_N%28n%29+%5Coverline%7B%5Cpsi_N%28n%27%29%7D+e_%7Bd%27_1%7D%28k%27n%27+-+kn%29&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0' alt='&#92;displaystyle X = q&#92;sum_{1 &#92;leq k. k&#039; &#92;leq K} &#92;sum_{n,n&#039;: n=n&#039;&#92; (d_2)} &#92;psi_N(n) &#92;overline{&#92;psi_N(n&#039;)} e_{d&#039;_1}(k&#039;n&#039; - kn)' title='&#92;displaystyle X = q&#92;sum_{1 &#92;leq k. k&#039; &#92;leq K} &#92;sum_{n,n&#039;: n=n&#039;&#92; (d_2)} &#92;psi_N(n) &#92;overline{&#92;psi_N(n&#039;)} e_{d&#039;_1}(k&#039;n&#039; - kn)' class='latex' /></p> <p align="center"><img src='http://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%5Cdisplaystyle++%5Csum_%7Bn_2%2Cn%27_2+%5Cin+%7B%5Cbf+Z%7D%2Fd%27_1%7B%5Cbf+Z%7D%3A+n%27_2-n_2+%3D+n%27-n%5C+%28d%27_1%29%7D+e_%7Bd%27_1%7D%28f%28n_2%29%2Fd_2+%2B+kn_2+-+f%28n%27_2%29%2Fd_2+-+k%27n%27_2%29.&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0' alt='&#92;displaystyle &#92;sum_{n_2,n&#039;_2 &#92;in {&#92;bf Z}/d&#039;_1{&#92;bf Z}: n&#039;_2-n_2 = n&#039;-n&#92; (d&#039;_1)} e_{d&#039;_1}(f(n_2)/d_2 + kn_2 - f(n&#039;_2)/d_2 - k&#039;n&#039;_2).' title='&#92;displaystyle &#92;sum_{n_2,n&#039;_2 &#92;in {&#92;bf Z}/d&#039;_1{&#92;bf Z}: n&#039;_2-n_2 = n&#039;-n&#92; (d&#039;_1)} e_{d&#039;_1}(f(n_2)/d_2 + kn_2 - f(n&#039;_2)/d_2 - k&#039;n&#039;_2).' class='latex' /></p> <p> Substituting <img src='http://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7Bn%27_2+%3D+n_2+%2B+n%27-n%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0' alt='{n&#039;_2 = n_2 + n&#039;-n}' title='{n&#039;_2 = n_2 + n&#039;-n}' class='latex' />, this becomes <p align="center"><img src='http://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%5Cdisplaystyle+X+%3D+q%5Csum_%7B1+%5Cleq+k%2C+k%27+%5Cleq+K%7D+%5Csum_%7Bn%2Cn%27%3A+n%3Dn%27%5C+%28d_2%29%7D+%5Cpsi_N%28n%29+%5Coverline%7B%5Cpsi_N%28n%27%29%7D+e_%7Bd%27_1%7D%28%28k%27-k%29n%29&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0' alt='&#92;displaystyle X = q&#92;sum_{1 &#92;leq k, k&#039; &#92;leq K} &#92;sum_{n,n&#039;: n=n&#039;&#92; (d_2)} &#92;psi_N(n) &#92;overline{&#92;psi_N(n&#039;)} e_{d&#039;_1}((k&#039;-k)n)' title='&#92;displaystyle X = q&#92;sum_{1 &#92;leq k, k&#039; &#92;leq K} &#92;sum_{n,n&#039;: n=n&#039;&#92; (d_2)} &#92;psi_N(n) &#92;overline{&#92;psi_N(n&#039;)} e_{d&#039;_1}((k&#039;-k)n)' class='latex' /></p> <p align="center"><img src='http://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%5Cdisplaystyle+%5Csum_%7Bn_2+%5Cin+%7B%5Cbf+Z%7D%2Fd%27_1%7B%5Cbf+Z%7D%7D+e_%7Bd%27_1%7D%28f%28n_2%29%2Fd_2+%2B+%28k-k%27%29n_2+-+f%28n_2%2Bn%27-n%29%2Fd_2+%29.&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0' alt='&#92;displaystyle &#92;sum_{n_2 &#92;in {&#92;bf Z}/d&#039;_1{&#92;bf Z}} e_{d&#039;_1}(f(n_2)/d_2 + (k-k&#039;)n_2 - f(n_2+n&#039;-n)/d_2 ).' title='&#92;displaystyle &#92;sum_{n_2 &#92;in {&#92;bf Z}/d&#039;_1{&#92;bf Z}} e_{d&#039;_1}(f(n_2)/d_2 + (k-k&#039;)n_2 - f(n_2+n&#039;-n)/d_2 ).' class='latex' /></p> <p> As <img src='http://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7B%5Cpsi_N%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0' alt='{&#92;psi_N}' title='{&#92;psi_N}' class='latex' /> is supported in an interval <img src='http://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7BI%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0' alt='{I}' title='{I}' class='latex' /> of length <img src='http://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7BO%28N%29%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0' alt='{O(N)}' title='{O(N)}' class='latex' />, we obtain the bound <p align="center"><img src='http://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%5Cdisplaystyle++X+%5Clessapprox+q%5Csum_%7B1+%5Cleq+k%2C+k%27+%5Cleq+K%7D+%5Csum_%7Bn%2Cn%27+%5Cin+I%3A+n%3Dn%27%5C+%28d_2%29%7D+%7C%5Csum_%7Bn_2+%5Cin+%7B%5Cbf+Z%7D%2Fd%27_1%7B%5Cbf+Z%7D%7D+e_%7Bd%27_1%7D%28f%28n_2%29%2Fd_2+%2B+%28k-k%27%29n_2+-+f%28n_2%2Bn%27-n%29%2Fd_2%29%7C.&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0' alt='&#92;displaystyle X &#92;lessapprox q&#92;sum_{1 &#92;leq k, k&#039; &#92;leq K} &#92;sum_{n,n&#039; &#92;in I: n=n&#039;&#92; (d_2)} |&#92;sum_{n_2 &#92;in {&#92;bf Z}/d&#039;_1{&#92;bf Z}} e_{d&#039;_1}(f(n_2)/d_2 + (k-k&#039;)n_2 - f(n_2+n&#039;-n)/d_2)|.' title='&#92;displaystyle X &#92;lessapprox q&#92;sum_{1 &#92;leq k, k&#039; &#92;leq K} &#92;sum_{n,n&#039; &#92;in I: n=n&#039;&#92; (d_2)} |&#92;sum_{n_2 &#92;in {&#92;bf Z}/d&#039;_1{&#92;bf Z}} e_{d&#039;_1}(f(n_2)/d_2 + (k-k&#039;)n_2 - f(n_2+n&#039;-n)/d_2)|.' class='latex' /></p> <p> We first isolate the diagonal terms <img src='http://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7Bn%27%3Dn%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0' alt='{n&#039;=n}' title='{n&#039;=n}' class='latex' />. In this case the inner sum is a Ramanujan sum, so by <a href="#ram1">(5)</a> the diagonal contribution is bounded by <p align="center"><img src='http://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%5Cdisplaystyle++%5Clessapprox+q+%5Csum_%7B1+%5Cleq+k%2Ck%27+%5Cleq+K%7D+N+%28k-k%27%2Cd%27_1%29.&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0' alt='&#92;displaystyle &#92;lessapprox q &#92;sum_{1 &#92;leq k,k&#039; &#92;leq K} N (k-k&#039;,d&#039;_1).' title='&#92;displaystyle &#92;lessapprox q &#92;sum_{1 &#92;leq k,k&#039; &#92;leq K} N (k-k&#039;,d&#039;_1).' class='latex' /></p> <p> Summing in <img src='http://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7Bk%2Ck%27%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0' alt='{k,k&#039;}' title='{k,k&#039;}' class='latex' /> using Lemma 5 from <a href="http://terrytao.wordpress.com/2013/06/14/estimation-of-the-type-iii-sums/">this previous post</a>, this is bounded by <p align="center"><img src='http://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%5Cdisplaystyle++%5Clessapprox+q+N+%28K%5E2+%2B+K+d%27_1%29+%5Clessapprox+qN+K+d%27_1.&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0' alt='&#92;displaystyle &#92;lessapprox q N (K^2 + K d&#039;_1) &#92;lessapprox qN K d&#039;_1.' title='&#92;displaystyle &#92;lessapprox q N (K^2 + K d&#039;_1) &#92;lessapprox qN K d&#039;_1.' class='latex' /></p> <p> Now we handle the non-diagonal terms <img src='http://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7Bn+%5Cneq+n%27%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0' alt='{n &#92;neq n&#039;}' title='{n &#92;neq n&#039;}' class='latex' />. By Proposition <a href="#weil">4</a>, this contribution to <img src='http://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7BX%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0' alt='{X}' title='{X}' class='latex' /> is </p> <p align="center"><img src='http://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%5Cdisplaystyle++%5Clessapprox+q%5Csum_%7B1+%5Cleq+k%2C+k%27+%5Cleq+K%7D+%5Csum_%7Bn%2Cn%27+%5Cin+I%3A+n%3Dn%27%5C+%28d_2%29%3B+n+%5Cneq+n%27%7D+%28d%27_1%29%5E%7B1%2F2%7D+%28f%27+-+f%27%28%5Ccdot%2Bn%27-n%29+%2B+%28k-k%27%29d_2%2C+d%27_1%29+%28f%27%27+-+f%27%27%28%5Ccdot%2Bn%27-n%29%2Cd%27_1%29%5E%7B-1%2F2%7D.&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0' alt='&#92;displaystyle &#92;lessapprox q&#92;sum_{1 &#92;leq k, k&#039; &#92;leq K} &#92;sum_{n,n&#039; &#92;in I: n=n&#039;&#92; (d_2); n &#92;neq n&#039;} (d&#039;_1)^{1/2} (f&#039; - f&#039;(&#92;cdot+n&#039;-n) + (k-k&#039;)d_2, d&#039;_1) (f&#039;&#039; - f&#039;&#039;(&#92;cdot+n&#039;-n),d&#039;_1)^{-1/2}.' title='&#92;displaystyle &#92;lessapprox q&#92;sum_{1 &#92;leq k, k&#039; &#92;leq K} &#92;sum_{n,n&#039; &#92;in I: n=n&#039;&#92; (d_2); n &#92;neq n&#039;} (d&#039;_1)^{1/2} (f&#039; - f&#039;(&#92;cdot+n&#039;-n) + (k-k&#039;)d_2, d&#039;_1) (f&#039;&#039; - f&#039;&#039;(&#92;cdot+n&#039;-n),d&#039;_1)^{-1/2}.' class='latex' /></p> <p> Bounding <p align="center"><img src='http://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%5Cdisplaystyle++%28f%27+-+f%27%28%5Ccdot%2Bn%27-n%29+%2B+%28k-k%27%29d_2%2C+d%27_1%29+%5Cleq+%5Csum_%7Bd%7Cd%27_1%7D+d+1_%7Bd%7C+f%27+-+f%27%28%5Ccdot%2Bn%27-n%29+%2B+%28k-k%27%29d_2%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0' alt='&#92;displaystyle (f&#039; - f&#039;(&#92;cdot+n&#039;-n) + (k-k&#039;)d_2, d&#039;_1) &#92;leq &#92;sum_{d|d&#039;_1} d 1_{d| f&#039; - f&#039;(&#92;cdot+n&#039;-n) + (k-k&#039;)d_2}' title='&#92;displaystyle (f&#039; - f&#039;(&#92;cdot+n&#039;-n) + (k-k&#039;)d_2, d&#039;_1) &#92;leq &#92;sum_{d|d&#039;_1} d 1_{d| f&#039; - f&#039;(&#92;cdot+n&#039;-n) + (k-k&#039;)d_2}' class='latex' /></p> <p> we can bound the preceding expression by <p align="center"><img src='http://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%5Cdisplaystyle++%5Clessapprox+q%28d%27_1%29%5E%7B1%2F2%7D+%5Csum_%7Bn%2Cn%27+%5Cin+I%3A+n%3Dn%27%5C+%28d_2%29%3B+n+%5Cneq+n%27%7D+%28f%27%27+-+f%27%27%28%5Ccdot%2Bn%27-n%29%2Cd%27_1%29%5E%7B-1%2F2%7D+%5Csum_%7Bd%7Cd%27_1%7D+d+%5Csum_%7B1+%5Cleq+k%2Ck%27+%5Cleq+K%7D+1_%7Bd%7Cf%27-f%27%28%5Ccdot%2Bn%27-n%29%2B%28k-k%27%29d_2%7D.&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0' alt='&#92;displaystyle &#92;lessapprox q(d&#039;_1)^{1/2} &#92;sum_{n,n&#039; &#92;in I: n=n&#039;&#92; (d_2); n &#92;neq n&#039;} (f&#039;&#039; - f&#039;&#039;(&#92;cdot+n&#039;-n),d&#039;_1)^{-1/2} &#92;sum_{d|d&#039;_1} d &#92;sum_{1 &#92;leq k,k&#039; &#92;leq K} 1_{d|f&#039;-f&#039;(&#92;cdot+n&#039;-n)+(k-k&#039;)d_2}.' title='&#92;displaystyle &#92;lessapprox q(d&#039;_1)^{1/2} &#92;sum_{n,n&#039; &#92;in I: n=n&#039;&#92; (d_2); n &#92;neq n&#039;} (f&#039;&#039; - f&#039;&#039;(&#92;cdot+n&#039;-n),d&#039;_1)^{-1/2} &#92;sum_{d|d&#039;_1} d &#92;sum_{1 &#92;leq k,k&#039; &#92;leq K} 1_{d|f&#039;-f&#039;(&#92;cdot+n&#039;-n)+(k-k&#039;)d_2}.' class='latex' /></p> <p> The inner sum vanishes unless <img src='http://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7Bd+%7C+%28f%27%27+-+f%27%27%28%5Ccdot%2Bn%27-n%29%2Cd%27_1%29%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0' alt='{d | (f&#039;&#039; - f&#039;&#039;(&#92;cdot+n&#039;-n),d&#039;_1)}' title='{d | (f&#039;&#039; - f&#039;&#039;(&#92;cdot+n&#039;-n),d&#039;_1)}' class='latex' />. In that case, <img src='http://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7Bk-k%27%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0' alt='{k-k&#039;}' title='{k-k&#039;}' class='latex' /> is restricted to a single residue class modulo <img src='http://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7Bd%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0' alt='{d}' title='{d}' class='latex' />, and so the inner sum is <img src='http://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7BO%28+K%5E2%2Fd+%2B+K+%29%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0' alt='{O( K^2/d + K )}' title='{O( K^2/d + K )}' class='latex' />. From the divisor bound we conclude that <p align="center"><img src='http://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%5Cdisplaystyle++%5Csum_%7Bd%7Cd%27_1%7D+d+%5Csum_%7B1+%5Cleq+k%2Ck%27+%5Cleq+K%7D+1_%7Bd%7Cf%27-f%27%28%5Ccdot%2Bn%27-n%29%2B%28k-k%27%29d_2%7D+%5Clessapprox+K%5E2+%2B+K+%28f%27%27+-+f%27%27%28%5Ccdot%2Bn%27-n%29%2Cd%27_1%29&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0' alt='&#92;displaystyle &#92;sum_{d|d&#039;_1} d &#92;sum_{1 &#92;leq k,k&#039; &#92;leq K} 1_{d|f&#039;-f&#039;(&#92;cdot+n&#039;-n)+(k-k&#039;)d_2} &#92;lessapprox K^2 + K (f&#039;&#039; - f&#039;&#039;(&#92;cdot+n&#039;-n),d&#039;_1)' title='&#92;displaystyle &#92;sum_{d|d&#039;_1} d &#92;sum_{1 &#92;leq k,k&#039; &#92;leq K} 1_{d|f&#039;-f&#039;(&#92;cdot+n&#039;-n)+(k-k&#039;)d_2} &#92;lessapprox K^2 + K (f&#039;&#039; - f&#039;&#039;(&#92;cdot+n&#039;-n),d&#039;_1)' class='latex' /></p> <p> and thus this contribution to <img src='http://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7BX%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0' alt='{X}' title='{X}' class='latex' /> is bounded by <p align="center"><img src='http://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%5Cdisplaystyle+%5Clessapprox+q%28d%27_1%29%5E%7B1%2F2%7D+%5Csum_%7Bn%2Cn%27+%5Cin+I%3A+n%3Dn%27%5C+%28d_2%29%3B+n+%5Cneq+n%27%7D+%28K%5E2+%28f%27%27+-+f%27%27%28%5Ccdot%2Bn%27-n%29%2Cd%27_1%29%5E%7B-1%2F2%7D+&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0' alt='&#92;displaystyle &#92;lessapprox q(d&#039;_1)^{1/2} &#92;sum_{n,n&#039; &#92;in I: n=n&#039;&#92; (d_2); n &#92;neq n&#039;} (K^2 (f&#039;&#039; - f&#039;&#039;(&#92;cdot+n&#039;-n),d&#039;_1)^{-1/2} ' title='&#92;displaystyle &#92;lessapprox q(d&#039;_1)^{1/2} &#92;sum_{n,n&#039; &#92;in I: n=n&#039;&#92; (d_2); n &#92;neq n&#039;} (K^2 (f&#039;&#039; - f&#039;&#039;(&#92;cdot+n&#039;-n),d&#039;_1)^{-1/2} ' class='latex' /></p> <p align="center"><img src='http://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%5Cdisplaystyle++%2B+K+%28f%27%27+-+f%27%27%28%5Ccdot%2Bn%27-n%29%2Cd%27_1%29%5E%7B1%2F2%7D+%29.&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0' alt='&#92;displaystyle + K (f&#039;&#039; - f&#039;&#039;(&#92;cdot+n&#039;-n),d&#039;_1)^{1/2} ).' title='&#92;displaystyle + K (f&#039;&#039; - f&#039;&#039;(&#92;cdot+n&#039;-n),d&#039;_1)^{1/2} ).' class='latex' /></p> <p> From the explicit formula <a href="#f-form">(13)</a> we see that if <img src='http://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7Bp+%7C+d%27_1%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0' alt='{p | d&#039;_1}' title='{p | d&#039;_1}' class='latex' />, then <img src='http://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7Bp+%7C+f%27%27+-+f%27%27%28%5Ccdot+%2B+n%27-n%29%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0' alt='{p | f&#039;&#039; - f&#039;&#039;(&#92;cdot + n&#039;-n)}' title='{p | f&#039;&#039; - f&#039;&#039;(&#92;cdot + n&#039;-n)}' class='latex' /> if and only if <p align="center"><img src='http://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%5Cdisplaystyle++p+%7C+%5Cfrac%7B2c_1%7D%7Bt%5E3%7D+-+%5Cfrac%7B2c_1%7D%7B%28t%2Bn%27-n%29%5E3%7D.&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0' alt='&#92;displaystyle p | &#92;frac{2c_1}{t^3} - &#92;frac{2c_1}{(t+n&#039;-n)^3}.' title='&#92;displaystyle p | &#92;frac{2c_1}{t^3} - &#92;frac{2c_1}{(t+n&#039;-n)^3}.' class='latex' /></p> <p> For <img src='http://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7Bp%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0' alt='{p}' title='{p}' class='latex' /> large enough, this only happens if <img src='http://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7Bp+%7C+c_1%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0' alt='{p | c_1}' title='{p | c_1}' class='latex' /> or <img src='http://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7Bp+%7C+n%27-n%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0' alt='{p | n&#039;-n}' title='{p | n&#039;-n}' class='latex' />. We conclude that <p align="center"><img src='http://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%5Cdisplaystyle++%28f%27%27+-+f%27%27%28%5Ccdot%2Bn%27-n%29%2Cd%27_1%29+%5Cll+%28c_1%2Cd%27_1%29+%28n%27-n%2C+d%27_1%29&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0' alt='&#92;displaystyle (f&#039;&#039; - f&#039;&#039;(&#92;cdot+n&#039;-n),d&#039;_1) &#92;ll (c_1,d&#039;_1) (n&#039;-n, d&#039;_1)' title='&#92;displaystyle (f&#039;&#039; - f&#039;&#039;(&#92;cdot+n&#039;-n),d&#039;_1) &#92;ll (c_1,d&#039;_1) (n&#039;-n, d&#039;_1)' class='latex' /></p> <p> and thus this contribution to <img src='http://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7BX%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0' alt='{X}' title='{X}' class='latex' /> is <p align="center"><img src='http://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%5Cdisplaystyle++%5Clessapprox+q%28d%27_1%29%5E%7B1%2F2%7D+%28K%5E2+N%5E2+%2F+d_2+%2B+K+%28c_1%2Cd%27_1%29%5E%7B1%2F2%7D+%5Csum_%7Bn%2Cn%27+%5Cin+I%3A+n%3Dn%27%5C+%28d_2%29%3B+n+%5Cneq+n%27%7D+%28n%27-n%2C+d%27_1%29%5E%7B1%2F2%7D+%29.&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0' alt='&#92;displaystyle &#92;lessapprox q(d&#039;_1)^{1/2} (K^2 N^2 / d_2 + K (c_1,d&#039;_1)^{1/2} &#92;sum_{n,n&#039; &#92;in I: n=n&#039;&#92; (d_2); n &#92;neq n&#039;} (n&#039;-n, d&#039;_1)^{1/2} ).' title='&#92;displaystyle &#92;lessapprox q(d&#039;_1)^{1/2} (K^2 N^2 / d_2 + K (c_1,d&#039;_1)^{1/2} &#92;sum_{n,n&#039; &#92;in I: n=n&#039;&#92; (d_2); n &#92;neq n&#039;} (n&#039;-n, d&#039;_1)^{1/2} ).' class='latex' /></p> <p> If we estimate <p align="center"><img src='http://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%5Cdisplaystyle++%28n%27-n%2C+d%27_1%29%5E%7B1%2F2%7D+%5Cleq+%5Csum_%7Bd%7Cd%27_1%7D+d%5E%7B1%2F2%7D+1_%7Bd%7Cn%27-n%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0' alt='&#92;displaystyle (n&#039;-n, d&#039;_1)^{1/2} &#92;leq &#92;sum_{d|d&#039;_1} d^{1/2} 1_{d|n&#039;-n}' title='&#92;displaystyle (n&#039;-n, d&#039;_1)^{1/2} &#92;leq &#92;sum_{d|d&#039;_1} d^{1/2} 1_{d|n&#039;-n}' class='latex' /></p> <p> we have <p align="center"><img src='http://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%5Cdisplaystyle++%5Csum_%7Bn%2Cn%27+%5Cin+I%3A+n%3Dn%27%5C+%28d_2%29%7D+%28n%27-n%2C+d%27_1%29%5E%7B1%2F2%7D+%5Cleq+%5Csum_%7Bd%7Cd%27_1%7D+d%5E%7B1%2F2%7D+%5Csum_%7Bn%2Cn%27+%5Cin+I%3A+n-n%27%5C+%28dd_2%29%3B+n+%5Cneq+n%27%7D+1&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0' alt='&#92;displaystyle &#92;sum_{n,n&#039; &#92;in I: n=n&#039;&#92; (d_2)} (n&#039;-n, d&#039;_1)^{1/2} &#92;leq &#92;sum_{d|d&#039;_1} d^{1/2} &#92;sum_{n,n&#039; &#92;in I: n-n&#039;&#92; (dd_2); n &#92;neq n&#039;} 1' title='&#92;displaystyle &#92;sum_{n,n&#039; &#92;in I: n=n&#039;&#92; (d_2)} (n&#039;-n, d&#039;_1)^{1/2} &#92;leq &#92;sum_{d|d&#039;_1} d^{1/2} &#92;sum_{n,n&#039; &#92;in I: n-n&#039;&#92; (dd_2); n &#92;neq n&#039;} 1' class='latex' /></p> <p align="center"><img src='http://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%5Cdisplaystyle++%5Cll+%5Csum_%7Bd%7Cd%27_1%7D+d%5E%7B1%2F2%7D+%5Cfrac%7BN%5E2%7D%7Bdd_2%7D%5C+&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0' alt='&#92;displaystyle &#92;ll &#92;sum_{d|d&#039;_1} d^{1/2} &#92;frac{N^2}{dd_2}&#92; ' title='&#92;displaystyle &#92;ll &#92;sum_{d|d&#039;_1} d^{1/2} &#92;frac{N^2}{dd_2}&#92; ' class='latex' /></p> <p align="center"><img src='http://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%5Cdisplaystyle++%5Clessapprox+N%5E2+d_2%5E%7B-1%7D.&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0' alt='&#92;displaystyle &#92;lessapprox N^2 d_2^{-1}.' title='&#92;displaystyle &#92;lessapprox N^2 d_2^{-1}.' class='latex' /></p> <p> This contribution to <img src='http://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%7BX%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0' alt='{X}' title='{X}' class='latex' /> is thus <p align="center"><img src='http://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%5Cdisplaystyle++%5Clessapprox+q%28d%27_1%29%5E%7B1%2F2%7D+K%5E2+N%5E2+d_2%5E%7B-1%7D+%2B+qK+%28d%27_1%29%5E%7B1%2F2%7D+%28c_1%2Cd%27_1%29%5E%7B1%2F2%7D+N%5E2+d_2%5E%7B-1%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0' alt='&#92;displaystyle &#92;lessapprox q(d&#039;_1)^{1/2} K^2 N^2 d_2^{-1} + qK (d&#039;_1)^{1/2} (c_1,d&#039;_1)^{1/2} N^2 d_2^{-1}' title='&#92;displaystyle &#92;lessapprox q(d&#039;_1)^{1/2} K^2 N^2 d_2^{-1} + qK (d&#039;_1)^{1/2} (c_1,d&#039;_1)^{1/2} N^2 d_2^{-1}' class='latex' /></p> <p> and thus <p align="center"><img src='http://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%5Cdisplaystyle++X+%5Clessapprox+qNKd%27_1+%2B+q%28d%27_1%29%5E%7B1%2F2%7D+K%5E2+N%5E2+d_2%5E%7B-1%7D+%2B+qK+%28d%27_1%29%5E%7B1%2F2%7D+%28c_1%2Cd%27_1%29%5E%7B1%2F2%7D+N%5E2+d_2%5E%7B-1%7D.&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0' alt='&#92;displaystyle X &#92;lessapprox qNKd&#039;_1 + q(d&#039;_1)^{1/2} K^2 N^2 d_2^{-1} + qK (d&#039;_1)^{1/2} (c_1,d&#039;_1)^{1/2} N^2 d_2^{-1}.' title='&#92;displaystyle X &#92;lessapprox qNKd&#039;_1 + q(d&#039;_1)^{1/2} K^2 N^2 d_2^{-1} + qK (d&#039;_1)^{1/2} (c_1,d&#039;_1)^{1/2} N^2 d_2^{-1}.' class='latex' /></p> <p> Inserting this back into <a href="#minor">(19)</a> gives the desired bound <a href="#major">(17)</a>. This completes the proof of <a href="#goo">(12)</a>. <img src='http://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%5CBox&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0' alt='&#92;Box' title='&#92;Box' class='latex' /></p></p> <br />Filed under: <a href='http://terrytao.wordpress.com/category/mathematics/mathnt/'>math.NT</a>, <a href='http://terrytao.wordpress.com/category/question/polymath/'>polymath</a> Tagged: <a href='http://terrytao.wordpress.com/tag/burgess-inequality/'>Burgess inequality</a>, <a href='http://terrytao.wordpress.com/tag/characters/'>characters</a>, <a href='http://terrytao.wordpress.com/tag/exponential-sums/'>exponential sums</a>, <a href='http://terrytao.wordpress.com/tag/kloosterman-sums/'>Kloosterman sums</a>, <a href='http://terrytao.wordpress.com/tag/polymath8/'>polymath8</a>, <a href='http://terrytao.wordpress.com/tag/weil-conjectures/'>Weil conjectures</a>, <a href='http://terrytao.wordpress.com/tag/weyl-differencing/'>Weyl differencing</a>, <a href='http://terrytao.wordpress.com/tag/yitang-zhang/'>Yitang Zhang</a> <a rel="nofollow" href="http://feeds.wordpress.com/1.0/gocomments/terrytao.wordpress.com/6867/"><img alt="" border="0" src="http://feeds.wordpress.com/1.0/comments/terrytao.wordpress.com/6867/" /></a> <img alt="" border="0" src="http://stats.wordpress.com/b.gif?host=terrytao.wordpress.com&#038;blog=817149&#038;post=6867&#038;subd=terrytao&#038;ref=&#038;feed=1" width="1" height="1" />
